String: ...Find the computer lab, hack into a terminal and search for the box's location.
Seems like Wang is making a run for it. He's heading for the roof. Hunt him down and take him out. It's time to put an end to this.
OK. Give me a minute or so.
That's the Army's wagon. The plates must be inside that train car.
The code is on the screen.
Aw shit!
...it's a toss-up, really.
This startled the whole town! The cops are locking everything down!
Hey, how did you do that so quickly, friends? Old Locke almost feels unnecessary...
Prepare for a rough landing, guys!
We're doing this nice and quiet. The computer we're looking for should be located on the second floor.
I was afraid of this. The containers are shut and locked. Gonna have to drill them.
Oh fuck, I heard about that shootout! Y'all got hit by the Payday Gang!
Find anything useful nearby to use on the crate?
They are taking the bags!
Oh ok. But we're sending a team over to have a look.
Leave it with me. I can certainly help you with that.
I'm sure Vlad wanted some more blood but this was clean and mean. The Russians will know they got hit by pros. See you back at the safe house.
First, you gotta break into the warehouse. It'd be great if you can keep the noise down.
Keep looking for that cell block!
Either direction will get you where you need to be, so go on. No turning back now.
Stay lively, friends. Assault wave incoming.
Search those bags of coke, guys.
They're my guns, asshole! Mine!
They're going to keep sending harder kerels, friends.
When we get outta here, we're gonna open the shit outta that present! Don't you die on me!
Oh! I almost forgot! I need one more... special ingredient. Yeah, that's right. The mechanic needs a coke from the vending machine. Chop chop, pretty please.
Thank you for your call. We look forward to hearing from you again.
My Daddy's a powerful man! He knows the President!
We gotta get past that gate. Look around and see if you can find something useful.
... Take these sons of bitches out!
Ghaa! What the blerrie!? Vlad, you dronkie chop, what...!? Get out of here!
Have you lost your mind? Stop shooting the cameras!
Next up, let's head to the Research Center. We need to round up any documents that mention the Neo-2.
God damn it! They locked the containers! Must've been the alarms. Alright, we break through.
Grab the C4, gang!
Commissioner Garrett Speaking. What? Is this a joke? GOODBYE.
Guys, look for a way to shut off the gas!
Anti-air defenses?! Are you shitting me?! Turn the plane around, Bile! Do it now! Guys, take the parachutes and jump out!
I'm moving out.
An inventor named Rossy - residing somewhere in DC - may have found a cheap way to produce energy from water.
Kerels got to the IT guy, get in there and stop them!
Well done guys.
I got us someone to make sure the stuff doesn't get stolen from the trunk.
Remember - the explosion may have scattered the loot across the floor.
Alright, fry that bastard, see how long he lasts.
Keep looking for the USB stick, friends.
Are you having second thoughts or what!?
Hola?
What? Who is this?
Drop them, crew!
Now, find the transfer hose and lower it down.
This is fine, we'll take it.
You made a mighty big mistake coming here!
Half the Washington PD is behind us!
They are coming from the railway bridge! Watch out!
Who the hell do you think you are!?
Guys! Every time the mercenaries mess with the EMP, the charging process decreases! Don't let them touch it!
You want fancy guns? I want to hurt the bastard who's got 'em.
You get to make a lot of money if you do as I say. Now, proceed inside and get that door open.
I'm gonna fuck you up!

How entertaining, you truly won't give up, and you're destroying quite a bit of my property in your wake. No matter, I can rebuild, but you won't be able to come back from the dead.
I think I will relax, enjoy you stumbling about on your way to me. My men will make sure that you're good and tender before you march to your death.
Keep and eye on that control tower guys, I thought I saw some movement up there.
The hell do you think you're doing?
All's quiet still. Good work. Stay hidden while the Moretta docks.
There's that... Aargh, he's as much use as tits on teapot. Get up. Get up, suka blyad! On your feet!
One minute...almost there.
Boris will get you, you'll never get away never, you hear me?!
What I'm hearing here is envy, man. Envy.
This friend of McKendrick's sure has the bling, by the looks of it.
Put the product in the car!
Still waiting for you to access that camera feed.
The coke is shipped out. Well done sailors! Go get you payday!
You need to find the right storage unit!
Ok now, which transport is he in? Saw them all open and find out!
This is a ten thousand dollar carpet man! Fix it!
Look for the evidence storage!
Let's just fix this bank and burn the Mendoza money ASAP. We can find you new identities after.
We got what we came for, so you can get out whenever you are ready.
That's enough corporate espionage for one day! Time to head out.
Be careful! They have snipers incoming!
Rey's Pizza, what can I get you?
Blow the vault free with C4!
Great.
Time to find a keycard for that reader. See any lying around?
You need to patch me in so I can open those doors.
I hope they weren't giving this marching powder to our boys.
Oh, shit!
It will come in handy, I'm sure of it.
Nice job! The Payday Piggy thanks you for your service.
Alright, finally!
Blerrie chop Murky soldiers... hope they don't follow.
Think you can assemble those weapons?
No more cameras! Thank god for that.
I got a contact on the ranch, tells me Esteban always keeps his laptop in the main house, usually in his office. Gate to the right will take you straight there.
These motherfuckers... I heard the car battery asshole is on the boat.
Well that's done it. No sense in being quiet now. Break out the hardware, yeah?
Trying to find some good recipies here... some of Bain's files are a blerrie mess, so I hope I get it sorted!
Helicopter is waiting.
That's it for the fans. Temperature is spiking fast. What the hell is in there?
Get the elves working on the product. Just holler at them.
Damn! They have anti-air defenses set up around the whole factory. Turn the plane around, Bile! Gang, you need to use the parachutes and get out! Right now!
You could say Ernesto Sosa is lucky to have this beautiful house in Miami Beach. But his luck is about to change...
Get the hell out!
OK gang, time to find that keycard. Birthday Boy is probably still around, so go find him!
The vault code seems to change according to the current time. Find a way to suss the right one, yeah?
The timer stopped! Restart it!
Damn, did the Commissar bring this piece of crap from the Motherland?
Nice job! The Payday Piggy thanks you for your service.
Our contacts tell me a new invention have seen the light of day. Cold fusion energy, the end of fossil fuels and death of oil conglomerates. We are all about risk management here.
Keep those kerels occupied until the escape vehicle arrives, yeah?
Alright.
He dropped his keycard. That should open the other gold stash.

The Benevolent Bank has history. Oldest US bank, sacked by the British in 1812, held Civil War gold, issued FDR's first bonds. Hell, you'll even find it on the back of your ten-spots. And guess what - in all that time, it has never been successfully knocked over. Successfully". Well
column3: today it is your turn to try and change that. You're going in through the front door. Scope the place to figure your best way through the lobby to the vaults beyond. I've got some ideas of how we're going to boost all that loot. Trust me. Make history

String: ... put the product in the car!
Vlad is very weak, you need to help him outside.
Put holes in 'em!
The alarm sounded but it's too late for the vault. Get it empty, as fast as you can.
It's getting there!
Maybe something to do with his wife... an anniversary or something?
Well, fuck me, that was a waste of time. The vault is empty. Find the good ones, you hear?!
A worker probably has the server room keycard. See if you can find it. And if you can't...You know the drill.
Ok get the shoes!
You don't want us to leave, do you?
30 seconds till pick-up!
Not much time. F35s deployed to patrol D.C. airspace. We're goners for sure if you don't hurry!
All right now, careful with this. You press the wrong buttons and there's no telling what you might turn into.
OK friends, not much time until the coppers get there. Go have a look inside the bank.
You must have shit for brain, coming here!
Guys, remember! The sooner you get up there, the more cocaine we can grab.
Set the magnet on the vault.
Yeah, I'm getting the new car on Wednesday. New wheels man, it's good.
Get to the vault.
He passed out!
You are lucky I'm a kind man...
C4 in the armory. Go get it!
Crack that safe, probably something good in it.
I think we can make more cuts, yeah. We don't need all these tellers. Who gives a rats ass if people queue for an hour!
.. or take a little more.
C'mon, you gotta get in there. Use that torch.
I was born in Colombia but have become quite successful building a small import/export business here in Washington DC. I feel my calling is to help others secure things of value at cost.
Amazing! Just climb up onto BFD and we call it a job done. Or stay behind and really pick the place clean.
... just chill!
Our buyers only want cars in great condition. That means you can't alert the cops. They won't care what they shoot up. So keep this a quiet one.
Find that whiteboard, guys.
Do not lay that on me, woman child!
Guys, the pilot is circling! Drop the flare!
I bet there's something valuable in there. Hope you live long enough to open it!
Gadgets. You can try out whatever you brought over here.
I'll be the bigger man and admit you were right, Bain. It was actually good to do this before going after more challenging heists.
The police are here. They'll storm the building if they get the chance, so maybe stop them before they can.
Right guys, great job but you gotta ---. There's movement ---.
50 grand worth of stuff down the drain!
I'll be there in 2 minutes!
The tiara has to be in there somewhere...
Hey, was that the vault? Can't argue with your sense of style.
On my way. I see the fire. Hold on for a while, right?
Here it is - the GenSec arena. This Alesso gig is the biggest show it's seen. Let's make sure it goes down in history.
So what do you really know about these Payday guys? Can't imagine this shit is our fault.
Hey, call that elevator down to the garage. Get going.
Drill that safe, chop chop!
Looks like the goat managed to nibble through the power. Ladder's electrocuted. Disable the power!
You need to deal with those fires. Use the sprinklers.
Put the delivery in the car!
The code begins with a two, according to my source.
Ah, there we go. One box of strangeness. Pick it up and get onto the next one.
The plane is full, you can take off the hose.
Great. Get it moving!
This is like candy for Duke, yeah? But we just need what's inside. Those symbols are probably the key to opening it. Look around for clues.
Not my fucking car! Motherfuckers!!
Gather the winch and assemble it!
Let our friend lead, and keep moving. Carefully.
Go on now, chops! Find that server room.
Dallas. That console panel could actually be very useful. Try it out and see if you can find the computer. That would save us some time.
Great! That's the server, now set up the connection.
Come on, show me you can be hackers!
Nine down.
That's about halfway done.

OK gang, we have received a communique from the Elephant. He claims to want to help us. Seems that in the early 1900s, a Kataru member stole what he calls a family heirloom". This person then bought his way onto the famous Shacklethorne expedition bound for Antarctica. His presence
column4: doomed the voyage from the start. The familiarity of this is not a coincidence
column5: despite the Elephant's caginess. The ship and crew were lost
column7: when the wreckage was found crushed in the ice
column8: far from the original planned route. A couple of miles from the wreckage
column9: they also found a mummified corpse who looks to have died rather horrifically
column10: and a sled along with a collection of artifacts. The items recovered are going to be auctioned in secret to a bunch of decadent society types
column11: and the Elephant says that one of those items will help us with the device in the kitchen. I have a strange feeling about this one. It hits rather close to home."

String: You guys forget how an elevator works? Push the button!
You got the package, now stash it in the tree.
This device should be found and delivered to my client for... Evaluation". Also
column3: the know-how should be erased so it does not end up in the wrong hands."

String: No standing around. Find the plane, quickly.
Time to start looking for that stash of Murky loot. We're looking for cash, and lots of it.
Diamonds are just bad luck man.
Great! That's what we came for. Once the driver drops 'em off, he'll return for the ammo.
Can't unlock the doors until you patch in properly.
Hold on for dear life!
There he is!
Check the RFID for which wires to cut, then find the right ones.
My contacts can ensure that medical supplies are left for your use.
If we succeed with this, we'll have the whole criminal underworld talking about it forever. Ladies and gentlemen, this is how you make history.
All right, I'm gonna need my special tools to put the bike together. They should be in their usual place in the workshop inside one of the toolboxes.
You gotta restart the override on that box.
Right, now let me just get this sorted. Won't be a jiffy.
Go put that door breaker to good use!
Nice job, friends. I've just about had enough of Vlad's dwankie relatives, but it gives us a good marker to call in if we need a favor in the future, yeah?
The manifest is probably kept on a computer.
God dammit! Another guy, and this one's watching the server room. I guess you have to take him out as well.
Get inside the vault, gang. See what's inside!
That's the armor of Oda Nabunaga. Bag the pieces. If that's genuine...
Start cracking those boxes. We need one bag, but let's try and take them for everything!
Quick now! Send the drive down the dumbwaiter.
Let's keep this one under the radar.
50 percent full.
Damn you cut the wrong wire. Next time, maybe you want to wait for me.
Guys, there's a goat stuck in the streetlight! Saw it down.
How's it going, Alex? Get a grip!
I've had it with these guys!
They say having family is beautiful but sometimes I don't know. Now find that stupid fuck and free him - hopefully he's not too drunk to remember in which boxes he hid the cocaine.
Good! Now steal one of the police cars and get out of there.
Great, hihi. He had it coming!
Wow, this boat is expensive. This Powell guy's got money.
You just headbutted the motherfucking hornets' nest!
Please free my brother-in-law. He's an idiot, but he's family.
Nice guys. Sneaky and still sent a message. They lost the dough and Vlad will be sure to point out to them you are on his team.
We need hydrogen chloride!
Signal the chopper on the roof whenever you're ready.
Hurry up! Move to the next building.
I see one!
Murkywater like their technology, so they should have some kind of mobile command center nearby. See what you can find.
Now, let's see what kind of damage we can do.
Who are these guys?!
Put the bugs where we can pick up Esteban's voice. There has to be a way to make him talk.
I'll meet you at the docks.
Nothing. Damn! Are there more around?
Now that the network's unlocked, we can add our last-minute oil transfer to the shipping schedule. The admin computers need a USB key to work. Find the cabinet where they're storing it.
And..open the sesame! Bravo, my friends! Now, please, get in the fucking airlock.
Fill his glass. Once he downs that, well... he's going to lose interest in the slots. Follow him, and get his keycard.
Alright people, this is a pretty sweet opportunity, All sorts of mid-ranged diamonds and the like in the display cases. Do your worst, make your bones, get on out. A classic knockover.
Keep going til you see the prison transports.
They've got everything. Every heist, every job. References to you guys too. But no names - guess the traitor is holding onto those.
They're using gas! You can wait it out or find a way to turn it off.
Have you found the power yet?
OK, thermite's through. A chopper is bringing the water. Connect it when it arrives.
Good work! Let's move out.
I'm 100% it is some caustic soda needed here. Drop some in.
Find the server room. From there we should be able to open the lab door.
Who the hell are you!
Kill everyone!
Fall back!
Return to the mainframe and search, yeah?
Ey! Hurry up, will ya!?
Masterful, friends. Now make your escape.
Woah! Be careful with that stuff. That's military grade explosives you're throwing around.
Jesus... how the fuck did I get involved in this bullshit...
Take that sample to the laboratory. There's a machine that can detect the oil's purity.
There you go. If there's nothing else you want to take, get out of there.
Assault is on the way.
The reception area. Remember the location. Might come in handy.
You may have gotten the better of us this time creeps, but we will apprehend you eventually!
If Esteban's as paranoid as they say, he's got more than a Do Not Disturb" sign on the door."
Ok, steal the Tin Boy!
Welcome to Russia, gang! Nice welcoming party, right?
Hustle it, guys. You need to get on the ground near the money.
The guy with the server room keycard is in the admin office.
Got that lighting fluid yet?
We lost a little coke on this job but it could've been worse. Hector will still be pleased with us saving what we could.
And... got it! Storage room is open. Get the keys.
The code begins with a six, according to my source.
We're in a bit of a hurry, friends. Find something to cut open that container.
Hook me up again.
I'm at the pick-up!

Hector's death left a vacuum in the powder trade. Nature abhors a vacuum. Fucking abhors it! There's muck-fuckers crawling in from everywhere. Bunch of Hondurans are trying to spread. Let's hit them before they can take root. Break up their smuggling ring. Steal their product. What can go wrong?
There are three security boxes. Find them and plug in the hacking device so I can brute force the system. Stay close and make sure no one messes with the hack.
You cleaned the place out. Good job. Time to get the hell out of there.
Blerrie! This should be interesting!
...I think so, at least.
I'm off in one minute.
Who the hell can do what we just did? No one! This will go down in history, just like I said.
Casino manager has the first briefcase. The Pit Boss has the second. And then the head of security. Need all three for the code.
What's that? A blueprint?
You guys got lucky. The vault's already open!
Ah, kak. He's in his office again. We've got to get him out of there.
Let's get right to it, shall we?
Nah, don't throw 'em into the blades, man!
Uh-huh.
Great! Cutter's done! Here comes the sweet loot!
Come on guys, find the whiteboard already, yeah?
... then, we'll trade.
Hey you know what? I'm afraid the cops are going to find me here!
There you go, now you need to get into the actual mansion.
You have reaped the rewards of a well considered and deliberately executed plan - most impressive. I will contact you when I have further need of you.
We got ice cream too. You like ice cream?
Huh.... that door is code locked.
Just follow our friendly kerel. And don't let the real ones see you.
The rat was Hector!? He used to say that there were a lot of stupid criminals in the world. Apparently he was one of them for thinking he could screw us over.
See that light grid? It should correspond directly with the keycode. Get back to the console and punch it in.
The prisoner is your prize my friends. Keep him locked up and safe. He probably has information that someone doesn't want you to have, see if you can extract some of it...
The Neo-2's in that display case, right out in the blerrie open. See if you can drop the curtains, give us a little privacy.
Looks like his drink is getting low. Let's serve him another, with a little something added. Find the same bottle at one of the bars.
Okay, the seal is down. Protect the drill!
Drills incoming!
15 bags!
Come on now, 1 more.
Find the computer with the mask order invoice.
This will be a lesson to all: Don't fuck with The Butcher. Thank you for your help, my friends.
Bring that beast down, gang.
Burning 100 million dollars is a hell of a thing. It makes me feel like a real banker. All in a day's work. See you at the safe house.
This is the boat. You guys aren't exactly subtle. I'm coming in.
Almost open!
All right, snatch up those winch parts.
Keep the coppers away from the servers, yeah?
Sweet! The bridge is fixed! Now into the car, people! Time to leave this behind!
Great! Now get them up to the station on the roof and connect them.
OK, get to the controls. I've got something planned.
I see one of 'em!
Time to put that drill together. Get those bags.
No bullets with Garrett's name on them tonight, OK friends?
OK, let's move to the next part of the plan.
The cops have sent in a chopper carrying heavy SWATs. You better be ready when it arrives.
Damage? Who needs it?!
Hold it, hold it - wait til everyone's in the car.
Thanks, here's the cash!
Go to the roof and wait for the choppa"!"
Who's flying that chopper. Not the cops.
Use the saw on that door.
Must be that drivers first day. The dumbass stopped for the ambulance! Now it's your turn, gang. Get out there and do your job!
Hoxton's rottin' in a cell, and you're scratching your ass in there. Out of the crate!
The tunnel entrance should be outside somewhere.
Fuck me, man... I don't wanna die over this shit... I'll keep my promise and assemble the bike for ya, but I'm staying right here. Find the parts and bring them back here.
Keep going, friends.
Cops running up - 40 seconds to confrontation.
This didn't go as planned, guys!
OK, I'm coming back soon!
Kill 'em!
Vaults take just a moment to open. A security measure. Security is important, you know.
Imagine, the cruelty of children.
These fuckers are trying to rip us off!
Have you planted the bug yet?
No standing around. Get into the sanctum.
Stay focused! Keep moving up! They're wasting coke like they were trained for this!
Right, now just let it fill up.
The cops are on our tail!
Ok. But we said no drugs on the job. Better be careful or the boss will kick your ass.
You still got your old reflexes, old friend. Quickly, get these bodies out of sight.
What's that crane doing? Opening a new route for Kerels?
All the Neo-2 data is saved in here. Clear it out.
Are you alive?!
No time to dally, find Vlad some meds. Quickly, friends!
Get that cage built before you deal with the money.
The copy machine over there has a stash of equipment *if* this caper goes loud.
Now get inside the Oval Office and find the keycard.
Don't forget the goat in the scaffold.
We have half of needed fuel.
It's open! Bag the gold!
We're gonna need two vials. If one of them fails the test, you gotta get more blood and start again.
Wow! Guys? Are you OK? I told you to be careful!
Seven bags. You guys are fucking Olympic champions.
One more time
Alright, we're working again. Just hold on.
That's the last mistake you're ever going to make...
The cops have disconnected the hose. Reconnect it!
Check the humvees for explosives.
These machines are for nickel-and-dime suckers. Don't waste your time.
Half of them loaded.
Woo-wee! That's gonna cost 'em.
Okay, that must be one of the test subjects. Get the body to the scanner so we can get the information we need.
Great. Now, blow the doors!
So long my little smiling friends!
Come on, compute with the computer!
SWATs are incoming from the forest next to the road, be careful!
Yeah, tell him his ass is on the line if he isn't available for the regular time-lock check in.
OK, guys, here they come. Get that crane moving!
Our All You Can Eat buffet is now open, and I wanted to make sure that you knew.
Nope, can't do it. I'll return once you clear the roof.
Almost there. Fire up the pump generator.
Fucking Homeric, man.
Get down that elevator shaft so you can meet up with Charon!
Ouch! I hope that's not a sign of the luck you'll enjoy tonight.
Keep searching the motel, guys. There has to be some clue to where the Commissar is.
Remember. Go in, get the tiara, hit the store for more jewels if you feel lucky - the place is loaded. But watch out for guards, cameras, metal detectors.
...I'm 72% sure.
Man... This place... Find that gold and we can buy one of our own.
Get those chains off!
Right now you are succeeding.
Dammit! That bastard went up to the roof. Follow him! Take him out!
The employee only areas.
Now use the card to get inside the server room. Second floor.
Hey, you got your base covered, right?
The chopper will be leaving! Move!
Gonna give you a faceful of lead!
There could be something behind the books, like in one of those old spy movies, yeah?
Listen! That vault contains the prototype. It's in one of the crates. The others are decoys...
We've got your money right here. The info is in the safe. I'll open it. No funny shit or you die.
We need to get into Buluc's office. The way in can be found in his secret meeting room. See if you can find it.
Old Locke knows what to do with those suits.
I can't believe you're chasing this guy AGAIN!
Ok, now find Wilson's code lock.
OK folks: you go in, breach the vault with the thermal lance, burn the money and remember to film it.
The associate will be standing by.
You know what to do. Signal the chopper, and we'll drop off more ingredients. Or bail. Your choice.
Watch out, Sniper!
Can't stand around all day. Get to it.
We're good and going, I'm hacking the system through the computer
It took you long enough.
The bank is up. Get in, get the loot and stay frosty.
Collect the cage bags. You need to assemble it in the street.
Cops are trying to stop us. Defend those routers while I work!
Get inside the bank now, friends!
Good job, friends!
We have to make sure SERA can't build another prototype! Get over to the laboratory, and let's do some damage!
They're choppering in snipers!
What the hell? Elephant's sources didn't mention an additional security door...
Fucking phones are fucked. Ah, my friends!
Uhh.. Must be my police scanner. I'll shut it down. The police are miles away.
Hey! Put the groupie down, and get on the Intercom!.
OK, now you can take all of Vlad's special loot, but don't make too much noise.
I'm ready!
He's getting something from the trunk.
That terminal isn't linking. Murky always had crap IT people, except for me of course. Find another one.
Now you just need to start moving loot to Mr Blonde's car.
You will die for this!
Getting a massage, where he can't cause any trouble.
That's the head of security. He seems to be at the dock.
Get over to the gates. Let's get this done.
Coppers incoming everyone, they found you faster that I thought. Take care of them!
OK people, my contact thoughtfully stashed the thermal drill you're going to need to crack the bank vault somewhere in the parking lot. Get it, then hit the bank vault.
Two minutes till escape guys!
Alright team, this jewelry store has a number of display cases flaunting some medium range gems and gold.
Excellent! Well done. DC will party tonight!
Moment of truth. Use the crane to move our locomotive. Pretend it's one of those claw games! Just bigger! And with much higher stakes!
I can last a year in here, you pig-fucks!
You did the job, but with none of the finesse I hoped for. Roll home, gang.
Ach, that's one of the Mark II safe models. We can't simply blast through it without destroying the contents.
The active code seems connected to the time of day, so you'll need to find it.
Good. Hose is OK. Let's get that pressure back. Start the pump.
Cops just pulled up!
Clear the blast zone, friends!
Cops shut of the power, go to the box in the street .
Now get onboard!
What are you doing, you chop?
Moretta's comm frequency will be on one of the computers. Check them out.
On second thought - we'll take everything you have!
You can't let that bastard get away!
OK, the mall's up ahead. Get in, hit it with everything you got, and get out. Try to keep people to a minimum. This is strictly material, not personnel damage. This means you, Wolf.
One more!
There goes your driver. He's left a drill behind. Get it, and keep working!
Old Chinese proverb.
Great, let's take a peek under the hood. Hmmm, nice. Good security, but nothing I can't handle.
Am I glad to see this stuff again. Good recovery boys.
Crap, that's the alarm. Alright, gang - time to go loud.
Keep going you chops. Empty out more cash. We want to ruin these dwankies, yeah?
I don't think there is cause to worry. Anyone would have to be din gau to try something out here.
That's a nice keycard. Must go somewhere important.
Protect the drill from the kerels.
You have to wait for the time lock to end before you can get in. Shouldn't take too long.
Set up a hack so we can get those documents, yeah?
Hit me with another one of those phrases you think you know.
Fuck! The cops got roadblocks everywhere! It's like they knew! I'll pick you guys up a bit further ahead!
Did you check the wine cellar for fertilizer?

Now flip the power switch and it will trigger an overload spike.
You will board the meat truck and accompany our shipment to the harbor. My people will offload the coke. A speedboat will be on standby to expedite the transport of the goods.
You guys got me covered, right?
We got pretty far, but I gotta scram. You guys give me my cut later, right?
Hit the display cases.
Got connection. Keep working.
Fuck the other toys - get Tin Boy!
Hector is going to kill you!
Here's the deal:
C'mon, get in the vault.
Those Federales are going to want to stop the Beast. Don't let them!
Bile can't pick you up while those guns are active. Find the control boxes and shut them down, yeah?
Ready for the greatest heist of all?
You tripped something! Reset the alarm before it goes off!
Let me remind you - you need to be wiping out the mobsters. Search the motel.
Ey.
This job is important. The safes in those trucks, you need to get them out...uh, safely. You hear?
Looks like this store is pretty packed with jewels. Everyone getting ready for the holidays I guess. Anyway, I'm looking for at least four bags of jewels. That ought to cover us nicely.
Now things get interesting...
Well they're coming now. No two ways about it. Ready up!
Get the bags to the van!
OK. Nice tech! It appears the panic room door is controlled with a code and a retinal scanner.
That's the last one. Now you can get far away, or return to the warehouse for more loot.
OK, you got it. Now open the door.
Keep it together! Get him!
Jen over at GenSec here. So we detected an unscheduled activation of the time lock there. Everything OK?
Fuck 'em up!
Deposit boxes! Start breaking them, gang. One bag is minimum, but take as much as you can.

Okay, here's the tricky part. The turntable's locked, but there's a crane on-site for lifting heavy cargo. Fingers crossed it's strong enough to move our locomotive to an open track. Work the controls to get it into position.
Keep it steady. I'm connected.

I'm pretty sure that you will find what you need if you go ahead and look in the bookshelves. Like, 90 percent. Or maybe 20. But never mind. Go on, look in a bookshelf, chop chop. Hurry up you laanie dwankies, we don't have all night, yeah?
Alright. I need you to do one more errand before you bug out. Get to the security room and grab the footage from the cameras. Just in case they got anything incriminating.
You need to disable the lasers around that gate. Have a look at the wires in the RFID panel, then find the matching wire box, and cut them.
Are you having problems with that gate?
Great. Now find something else to steal. We need to make it look like a simple robbery.
Get the power to the server back on!
Here it comes. Room...
The server with the results should be around here somewhere. Find it and make those votes unusable.
Chop kerels have shut down power to the lab. Find the wall box and get it up again.
What the fuck is this!?
I mean you could try a trip mine if you have one... But it'll be loud... So I don't recommend it.
Take a look in the Jade Room for one of the PCs.
Cops are on our tail!
First thing to do is get inside. Front door is the most obvious way, but maybe you can figure out something less conspicuous.
Time to slip out of there! No reason to go loud now.
Good afternoon. Benevolent Bank. Martin speaking.
What's taking so long? Just activate that switch.
Hurry and get one of those gates open, chop chop.
I would really appreciate some help with those snipers!
Not going home this early...
Timer has finished. Get the keycard.
It's going to get real heavy if you stay around too long. Get moving!
I'm on my way!
Just one more to go.
We've had just about enough of Vlad's brother-in-law, yeah? It was a nice breakout. Always fun to burn down things kerels own! Nicely done, friends.
Ok gang, let's give Mr Blonde some help with a distraction. Lure away the cops by getting out through the bazaar by the Jack Rabbit Slim's.
I was able to glean that the sequence to this door can be found in Buluc's inner sanctum"
column3: somewhere in the house. Get to it

String: Ouch... let's hope the airbags did their job....
Not to worry friends, I've gotten in touch with Twitch. He's not too far out and will come get you.
All right. Head to reception, find a terminal and download the guest list.
You're breaking up... Can you hear me ok?
Sure I saw this place in a movie. Hope the walls don't spit poison darts.
Use that paper shredder - it's the easy way.
Just one more now.
You gotta get that dinges out of there.
... It's fine, we'll settle for this.
Look at the crowd. Insane. Right, focus on the job, and let's give them a show.
This is harshing my buzz!
Once you get that card from Ralph, his dad's probably gonna disown him.
No dossing about, yeah? Get inside the mansion.
Remember to check inside the buildings for the remaining keycard.
Damn it! They locked you in. Main entrance is the only option now!
Looks like we're out of luck. This one's no good. Go get me another. I'm sending the chopper back to pick it up.
Almost there.
Hurry friends. Left or right, make a choice and get going.
Ok, you're there. Now, see the RFID reader by the gate? Open it.
Ah, they hit him good.
There he is. Locke.
Where is he?!
Good work getting the meth out. That was not exactly an easy gig. I'm sure whoever ratted out the lab is going to get Hector's full attention.
Got one supermodel on my D, second supermodel mixing me a mighty fine G & T. King looks over and winks.
Find and deal with the manager, crew. Gotta get that keycard!
Almost there. One more bag.
Wasn't personal, Gabriel. Use his keycard to access the control room, then disable the blowout preventer.
No bags!? The trade will not be good to us. Hope you guys has some tricks up your sleeve for the trade.
Those snipers will get me soon if you don't take them out!
Guys, make sure Charon gets to the van!
I think you're going to find the vault on the other side of those doors.
I got real bad news!
Yes... gamble away, like little parrots.
Good. Now keep the cops off of it.
Good, now combine all the components and arm that firecracker.
Halfway there.
Strap in fellas!
There you go gang, get in there and start hauling the loot to Mr. Blonde's car.
Yeeeeehaaw!
We're almost finished. Get to the escape, come on!
Get out of that damn lobby!
This is your pilot...
Hell yeah! That was crazy, gang! Now get in there.
Alright, I'm in, hold on...
Use your guns! Put him in the ocean to drown!
You need to get in there.
I'm going with hydrogen chloride.
We can only proceed once you have acquired those items, my friends.
It's a big bank, but still a bank. You know the drill. Check the place out, and decide whether to keep things quiet or bring the noise.
One more.
Perhaps there was interference on the radio, so let me repeat. Plant the fucking charges on the locks. Please.
That's it. Open it up and let's see what we got.
Go on! Kill that bastard!
Secure the wire between the door and the elevator. Then shoot the cable.
Well Vernon, when you see how much money we make off the stuff, it's gonna smell like roses.
We're looking for the Lao Che Shipping warehouse. Get over there.
Grab the USB flash drive and get outta there. And, Dallas, don't get sloppy here.
GenSec on the scene. You've bloodied their noses before, prepare to do it again.
Okay. So. Let me see if I understand you, you aren't interested in funding my idea for a tv show - Pig Brother?
It's not going to be like on TV where you drive through the doors. Use the button!
Okay, that's one keycard. Hunt down the other.
Great. Now, please, keep the cops away from the time lock.
They put the fire out with sprinklers!
Is this on? Hello...where are those fucking clow - oh, there you are!
Keep moving the bags to the van, guys.
The data scrambler just crashed. Get to the server and get it running again.
Go inside and drop the bag on the table so you can count it. I hope everything is there.
Keep looking for Kang's cabin.
Looks like we found our man!
That's it, on the table. Pick it up, get out of there and keep it away from the kerels, yeah?
A plan is essential for a successful conclusion to any heist.
Damn it. Cops alerted. They are loading up.
And... yes, that is a satisfactory piece of business! All of the bags! Now, please, attach yourselves to the cables, join me up here and let us meet in person!
You bloody wankers, took your time didn't you!
Get through the front gate however you can.
OK, we're inspecting it... So far so good... He's running tests now...
What a friendly welcome to the west coast. Jiu Feng said the tea shop is only a front for the triad.
The drill is no longer working. See if you can get it running.
OK, the door is locked. We're gonna need a key. I think finding Chavez will mean finding the key. So search the building for Chavez.
Should be clear soon.
13 to go.
FYI: the metal on these trains is weakest at the roof. Blowtorch should burn right through.
Well, you know how it is, you smile, nod. But they sign on the line...and you have their soul!
That's the elevator. Let's go, people! You got military units gathering in the parking lot!
Hope that cable holds. Wait, did I add the weight of the safes...?
The Mendoza cartel runs a lot of guns through DC. We need you to hit one of their weapons caches here, weaken their soldiers.
If you want to grab something extra, I've got a guy standing by. You can use a zipline.
That entrance looks tough. Can you get around it?
Blerrie, the Kataru have really messed him up.
This is the hangar, bag those weapons and get ready bring them back up to Vlad's boys.
Well we didn't have the decoy because we didn't invest in the cargo scam. But at least we reprogrammed the ballot machines and no one saw... I hope it holds.
Why do laanie dwankies always host secret parties in old mansions, when it's raining outside?
Guys, we needed the boss alive to open the panic room quietly! Alright. We're gonna have to do this the loud way now.
Awesome! Let's go!
I've found a terminal. Get to it, hack in and we lower that magnetic seal.
Nice! I'll detonate these when the time comes. Get back to that storage room. I got it open!
The trains belonging to Murkywater should be easy to spot. Find them.
Great, now you just gotta hold out 'till it gets there.
Alright, restart the computer and we'll be back online again.
You can't leave by road 'cause of the army checkpoints. So you're gonna take the plates off this train...And escape on a different train? Can't wait to see this.
Twitch is arriving with the van to pick you up. He'll wait by the upper bridge side.
Remember to grab those loot bags!
On second thought - we'll take everything you have...
C'mon, take all the pardons. You need to leave.
Do the thing. This isn't your first rodeo, people. Be smart in there.
Don't let the cops shoot him up!
Everyone get ready to make a little withdrawal now.
Your ride is coming, should be there soon!
You're a dick for ever doubting us, but just get us a heist with good cash, and we'll forget about this.
Move faster!
We need to get inside the lumber mill. Why not see if you could use the anti-air gun we hacked earlier and redirect its position? Might be worth a shot.
OK, good. Let's find that server room.
Five to go!
Shit, the alarm went off! This heist is over. Try and escape before the big guns arrive. Hurry!
*grunts, wheezes*
Be there in 2 minutes.
A white MESA box, just as planned. Get the code breakers going on the locks.
Time to start looking for that stash of Murky loot. It's drugs we're after.
You can play it safe and call this a day...
Thanks guys. Hope you've got a good extraction plan.
It stopped! You gotta start it up again!
Boom! That couldn't have gone better. All four trucks are stopped and ready for your attention. At 'em, gang!
You benefited from a thoughtful plan. Your discipline impresses. Enjoy your payday. I will contact you when I require your expertise once again.
... be back in a moment!
We're using the roof as our pick-up spot. Over.
So..that's it? You got what you came for? Come on, follow me.
The alarm disabled the time lock. It's a setback but not a fail. There's a maintenance room on the roof. Get there. We should be able to reboot it.
Admit it. You tossers missed my beautiful English accent. Didn't you? Did you? Wankers.
Keep it quite. Don't get spotted.
Stay focused friends, you've set off the alarm!
These guys can drive!
Where did these guys come from anyway?!
BFD did a great job. Down into the vault. gang.
If there's one thing you don't want to find yourself in shortage of, it's medical supplies.
Go find the bank manager. We'll need that keycard off him.
Phew, the alarm is disabled. No need to worry about opening doors or windows now!
OK, that's all we need.
Place the goat on the floor and your hands in the air.
Nice. That's definitely worth a pretty penny. Now you need to sneak it out of there without making the triad guys go bossies.
Come one friends, that's not Bain. Open the right one.
Good, now get out to the main hub and use the crane to pull the box out of storage, yeah.
Wait a second...
Jiu Feng should be on the way by now, but Vlad isn't looking to well. Just hold on for a bit until the boat arrives.
These guys are fucking jokes!
The helicopter is on its way. But don't relax just yet. Keep focused.
OK, this is business as usual for Vlad. We get the tiara, we get the jewels if you want them. You can do this job any way you want as long as you get the tiara. Back to the van when you are done.
Let's get inside that house!
Get going friends, no time to waste. Open those doors.
One of the civilians is making a run for it, better keep em' in check!
Careful with the head!
Nice job, Dallas. Now, get the cocaine and head back to the van. Our work here is done.
What are you blaming me for? This wasn't my idea!
No time to stop for coffee.
This is fine, we'll take it.
Wrong key!
How are you coming along with that winch, friends?
Los atacantes estn fuera! Vmonos!
If he's going to hide away, we'll have to draw him out. You could start destroying his treasured possessions and see if that does it.
The Mendoza money in the US is gone. You have done well. We will not stop here of course. I will call upon you again.
Hey, stop fucking around over there. What you doing?
Several defense turrets just came online!
Bronson here, I'm there in four!
Loud or quiet - your call. But if we can stealth this, we'll be able to blend in and escape with the crowd. Nice and easy.
Goddamn it! We want that cage on the roof. It's the most defensible spot around.
I left a case of thermal paste for you down there. Make sure you grab it.
I needed those earlier!
Yeah, I brought it, so what now?
OK. you're headed to the docks now - this isn't over!
I have to leave!
Clear the area from cops so Bile can come in and pick you up!
Come on, clowns, get the trucks open!
Ack, that makes things complicated. Go back to the laptop. Maybe I can bypass the voice reader.
And done, nice.
You need to prepare the next ingredient.
The feds'll do everything they can to stop you from leaving. Get out of there - hurry!
Alright, clear out! You don't want to be around when those windows break!
Keep moving!
That's one security box taken care of.
Just pull the fire alarm so we can get this bastard.
Ah, kak. The place has gone into lockdown.
See if there's a door around there.
The vault needs a code and a keycard to open. Start looking.
Is this the right place? Mooooove!
Put the stuff in the car...
Damn! They have anti-air defenses set up around the whole factory. I need to turn the plane around! Comrads, you need to use the parachutes and get out! Right now!
Ah shit, this one broke on impact. We got bundles of cash scattered about. You're going to have to find them, bag them and get them back here.
...grab some of that gold if you can friends, but remember that money is secondary, yeah?
This didn't go as planned, guys!
That disabled the metal detectors. Good job.
You still need to bring the drill inside, yeah?
I'm leaving in half a minute!
Look, do I need to tell you everything. Use the thermal paste to burn through the grate.
We're not going in by the main entrance. You see that fence? That's our way in. Put on your mask and cut it open.
You're still golden.
...you need to move all parts of the winch into the bank.
Why does this bloody feel like the end of the world?
There must be some way to shut off the gas!
Paydirt! That's what we came for, gang.
I'll be there in two!
Move your asses!
Pump generators down! Fix it, and keep those kerels back!
Yes, that is the epicenter - right there. I wonder what kind of treasure that house can hold. OK, on with our heist here.
Zap him!
Your talent for planning is as impressive as your talent for execution. Enjoy your well deserved payday. I will be in touch.
Just go over to the switch and pick the difficulty.
The Golden Grin never closes. You want to waste time nickel-and-diming the slots...?
LIKE A GLOVE!
Alright, I'm goin!
Shayu! Watch your tongue.
WHOAA!
Guys, it feels like something's in the air... Money!
The C4 did its job. Get that vault floor cut open. Impenetrable my ass!
Blow up the gate, friends!
Get that dinges out to the van, yeah?
Start the hack so we can find the shipping manifests.
Hey, if you don't find the lead scientist, you're not getting through that door.
I think that is the armor of Oda Nabunaga. This is serious loot, gang. Load up!
Get that jigger out of the way!
If you kill his guards, you will get to him.
You deal with that, I'll take care of our little boy here...
The silent way to open those doors would be to use the keys. If you can find them.
The police have been alerted and are closing in. They'll be there any second.
Make shure no SWATs get in to the lab. Keep them away at all costs!
Guys... Can you see any hints on what the correct one should look like?
Come on, guys. You have to get the cutters onto the vault floor.
Guys, take him to the retinal scanner and force him to use it!
Aight, four!
Still gotta get your hands on the card.
Time to find the vault.
Security barrier activated.
Get that fire going again!
There's your chopper. Get the bags in it. Then you can bug out, or stay and find more loot. It's up to you.
Make sure no one else is there.
The cops have this place surrounded. We're going to have to gracefully improvise"."
Find that key tag yet?

This is a big job. I'll talk you through it as we go, but the skinny is this: the Golden Grin has a big vault. Big. I mean Benevolent Bank big. Whether you sneak in, or go full assault, you're in for a tough time.
It's open, take our stuff back.
Get me hooked up and I'll get that door unlocked in just a few moments.
The admin office is on the lower deck, near the catwalks. Get down there.
You people have no respect for art! No respect!
Okay. I see the flare. Starting descent.
Come on, take those bollards down.
They're on my ass like a fucking tail!
The cannon can't fire until you get fresh batteries.
First thing I did when that bail-out came through was buy a Longfellow. Hey, I'm supporting the auto-industry!
Another 30 seconds. Over.
Ready or not, here I come!
Break into the Police storage compound and get your hands on some access codes we will need later.
Get the power back up!
You know, nothing makes a statement like ripping a vault from its foundation, in a ship no less!
What are you waiting for?
He's heading for the canteen, you gotta follow him!
Get to the van!
Great, you're in. One more door between us and the server.
You have sent message and it was good message! I think it was - fuck you
column3: haha! Loud and clear to everyone! Money was good. Hey! Have vodka and weekend.

String: He was a boring poe. Thank you.
We need to get the master keycard from the foreman's office.
Welcome, Director Stevens.
I think you just wiped out everything. All of it. The farm. Well done.
Great. That's keycard one. We need to find one more.
There has to be a door leading into the mansion.
Display case alarms are off now. Get your Dr. Jones on, fellas, and grab some antiquities. I know a guy who can fence this stuff. Trust me.
That's great. Now just hold on and wait for Bile.
Now enter the password.
Birthday boy Ralph is probably hiding somewhere pathetic.
Return fire! I'm getting you a driver, you need to keep them off the coke!
It's behind that security door.
The hack stalled! Can you reboot it?
What? Oh, come on! I'm out of here!
Let's just get it over with and hopefully without bloodshed. We have enough of that ahead of us.
Check through windows. See if you can find the alarm box. Once you go in, it's gonna go off pretty quick, so be ready.
Oh fuck me sideways!
Sup ese.
Hey hey hey guys, Guys! you better tell my brother-in-law to step on it!
OK, I'm back! Get on board the chopper!
The streets are crawling with cops! Not getting out that way. Light a flare and I'll bring in a chopper.
Guys, find the Murkywater trains.
There he is!
Ok chiefs, let's get your guy out of here. Get onboard!
Goats are great conductors of electricity. Turn off the power.
Ok, let's see... hmm... we need a plan for this...
Make sure he follows you!
Goddammit, you just missed the getaway.
Keep in mind that there might be cleaning personnel and other non-kerels moving about.
Everyone has gotta get on the chopper!
OK, Vlad seems happy. You can leave at your discretion, friends.
Those stacked crates are due to be shipped out to the Commissar. Check the labels. Get the right one to the code reader, and that should lead us straight to the Commissar.
The forest is dark and spooky tonight, gang. Let's cook a little meth.
Good friends, now get to the cell block so we can find and release Bain.
Alright, minds back on the job. The house is littered with evidence that could still screw us. Deal with it.
They probably keep the car keys nearby.
This war need guns to keep going, and now FBI have what is mine. Money is gone but hardware still at airport. Go and get the (fucking) weapon crates back.
Next, old Locke needs to put a nice little computer virus into the system.
Then you can go for their bank and burn all their money. Leaving them nothing.
You know I prefer to be involved in jobs where preparation is taken seriously. Don't disappoint me.
Get your head down, they called in snipers!
Ugh.
Nice! Time to blow this joint!
Found that evidence storage room yet?
When I get that bonus, it's gonna be time to party. Cabo San fucking Lucas, baby!
These cars are tough stuff, but the thermite will melt through easy.
Stay alive, I'm sending for Hector's people to pick-up the coke.
That container needs to be cut open with a blowtorch. Those places always have tools for metal repair, so see if you can find one.
Those are the right servers, but if you find the IT guy, we can get in faster.
Big ones and Benjamins. Beautiful!
Get ready. Bile's almost back. Connect the hose!
Two minutes. Learn to drive, asshole.
Oh shiiiiiit!
We need to get to the transfer room on the ground floor, but we need the Taxman and the server with us.
Make sure your gang are safely gathered in the airlock. The outer door cannot close until this is so.
I want what's in the safe!
You gotta listen to the diagnosis of each patient so you can find out target.
We're in. Alright, keep the cops off it. Might take some time.
We gotta get the ship moving! Lemme think... Alright, just hack the ship control terminal and make sure it stays on.
Good thinking! Use that fire to destroy the weapons.
Let's get that water flowing again!
Enemy helicopter inbound!
Time to go guys!
There's the way out, gang. Fresh air awaits.
Stick around. wankers! You'll get more bonuses!
OK, the data is scrambled! It will appear as an ordinary hard drive crash.
'Once more unto the breach...'
We got a Stage 3 Piggy Bank over here!
There's a blocker on the system. Get to another terminal and help me break it.
Bliksem, the place is rigged! Get out of there if you can't disarm it!
Have you forgotten what Bain looks like? Try again.
See you later muchachos.
Did he say Red Valley Red? Go find it in the wine store!
Dear friends! Enjoying the flight so far, yes? You're almost at the location I have selected as a drop point. So...
Two of them, there's two guys.
You need to hack the auctioneer's computer for the code, yeah?
I've had it with these guys!
No patience to look around, eh? With any luck, you'll stay under the radar.
I don't get what you're doing. You need to get rid of that camera. Just do as I say and deploy the ECM Jammer
I'll never tell you!
Get ready for the vault. I'll have the code for you soon.
Technical issues? Sounds like a load of crap.
They've rigged the place with C4!
That's the last one! Perfect!
Five to go.
Both drills done. Excellent.
They took out the wall with C4!
What, you looking for a fucking close encounter?
Get the hack restarted.
Come on, you can afford it I am sure.
Great, it is done. Get the keycard.
In this case it can be wise to spot" your target to keep track of its movements."
Go by the panel and pull that goddamn switch.
Make sure those domkop police don't get near the drill!
There she is! Shake the presents outta the tree!
Okay, here we are. It's show time.
It will be there. I assure you.
Use your ECM Jammer and disable it. That will give you the time needed to lockpick the door.
Thanks! My wrists hurt like hell!
We're helping an old friend of mine in L.A. He's got a diamond problem.
Stick some explosives on the gate and we're good to go.
The blueprint you found was for a new Type of Turret. It looks like the government is transporting it soon. If we act fast, we can catch them off guard and steal it without anyone noticing.
Who's that ugly kakspul?... What the blerrie... is that...!? Ach! No time to deal with that now! Get out of there! Hurry!
I'm going to make you bleed!
There's a light shining outside the Glitter Room, looks like a monitor.
There's an access ladder over the garage. Should be able to get to the roof there.
Gang, lead him to the scanner. Make him use it!
My line of work has allowed me to lay the groundwork for an impressive network of contacts.
Hang on folks, I've got a contact who's going to help you out.
Find the counting room right above the vault and pour out the thermite.
Blerrie odd, isn't it? I think they're from Chicago, of all places.
Let me handle this, yeah?
Moretta's at the berth. Time for a hostile boarding. The zip-line could speed things up.
Ach, piece of kek dinges!
Ach, that's not good. No way to break that open silently, friends.
Get to the chopper to escape!
Careful!
Not just ANY things...
To get to the Commissar, we have to find the Commissar. This motel is one of his operations. Cause as much damage as you can. If he calls, I can track him.
You'll need to remove those barrels, and you need to do it fast. Just release the straps or something.
We hit that vault and hit it hard. Ready?
He's almost finished!
Matt seems to have crashed his car! Go on forward!
Time for a bank job guys. I got a perfect one for you.
Thats your way out of here! To the right and down the stairs, guys!
Lots of interference at the moment. I can't reach Jiu Feng for pickup so you'll have to signal him. Find something to make a fire with.
Great that's it. Let's silently get out of here and find out if that's the right truck.
Job's half done. Find the second keycard and you can walk into the vault.
Damn you, Bain, but I think you were right. I needed something easy" to get back in the game."
You don't think our time's important!?
These fuckers chained me up! Get this shit off me!
We got the guns! I can trigger the C4 now. Clear the area!
Hurry! Answer his pager before they raise the alarm. Try and improvise or something.
They're onto us. Pick up the phone so I can put them at ease.
Gabriel's toast! Now, enter the control room and disable the blowout preventer. It's our turn to fuck up a drill!
Shit, you got crawlers outside. Watch those windows!
Ah shite. These interview files are locked. Can only be unlocked with approval from the Director himself. Fuck me, this goes to the top. Any of you guys fancy being king for a day?
You're breaking up... Can you hear me ok?
That's... A lot of money. I guess we're in the meth trade now. We really needed that information, though. Remember? Saddle up and let's get those pricks - with or without the information.

Well done, friends. Well done! We got our man back. Bain... is home. But the Murkies have done something to him. I've got some professionals looking at him right now and they say it's some kind of virus, maybe manufactured. If he dies... oh, blerrie Locke is going to be mad and make those Kataru pay...
That should do it. Now start the time lock again. I hope that it worked.
Cage is right where I put it. Like fucking 633 Squadron!

OK, looks like that helped. He looks stable enough to move, so help him out of there. Jiu Feng's man is waiting for you with a skid loader outside. I'll have a doctor waiting for him once you're all out of there.
