Shit, I guess I had it coming!
This vault's got an Achilles Heel. It's temperature controlled. Jam the vent fans at the back with crowbars. The temperature rises and the failsafe opens the door. Easy.
This is weird guys. The boards are lighting up like crazy. Something's wrong... I think we have major trouble coming. Damn it, I knew this was shady.
Get the lance working on the door. Burn through to that snitch!
A fighting retreat back to the van, guys. Let's get out of here.
I'm there, one minute!

I'm sure you guys have tangled with GenSec before. They're the East Coast's premier provider of security solutions, if you believe their brochure. But, PR aside, these guys are serious. Today, we hit them.
Lot's of shit happening in Washington right now.
Guys, don't let the cops take the coke!
All right, we're gonna need an engine to get this baby going. I'm almost positive I saw them store some inside the clubhouse.
Ok, now you need to aim the weapon at the second lock.
Get outside, friends! Twitch is incoming with the van!
I know this vault type... we can't just crack it.
I punch, you die!
Those cameras won't be a problem anymore!
Find that computer.
OK, friends. Time to put some fuel in that plane.
Watch out friends!
Admire the decor later. Get inside the Oval Office and find that keycard.
This is the correct hangar, bag those guns and get ready bring them back up to van.
Console on the right! And the left!
Think we're about to be outgunned!
You need to get that hose reconnected, guys. Come on!

Nice work, friends. Those brandy-snifting poshies got what they deserved, yeah? Now let's see what we can do with that artifact. Duke will get to looking at it as soon as you get back to the safe house. It's probably going to answer a lot of questions.
The switch there will open the cargo doors!
Easy as pie! Now where is he?
Go get the lance, badasses!
Get him in the back!
See that nice big hole? Drive through it, and hit the gas!
We've been expecting you fuckers!
Cut open that door with the saw.
Get away from the explosives now.
Dammit! Gas! Gas!
You should think very carefully about what you do next. Kill me, and you will live to regret it.
C'mon, move it get into the house.
OK we got the address - he lives in a high security villa, up in the mountains, real secluded, luxurious area. We will be going in blind with no intel. Arm yourself and let's go.
Wait for it...
This is a tricky job fellas, how you'll approach it is up to you.
...that gold would make a nice bonus. Bring some with you if you can friends, but remember why we're here.
You need to shut down those guns for Bile to get you out. Find the control boxes and shut them down.
Yes, it would be most agreeable to get some fuel in this chopper.
Get the control room door open and look for a shipping manifest. We can match up the company's container with which warehouse it's stored in.
Uhhh...no, that didn't work. Try another one.
First thing, get inside.
Look around the wine cellar for the fertilizer.
I need to get into the garage and you need to protect me. Let's go, come on.
Fires' out. You did well, gang.
I got one!
Maybe there's some C4 in the wine cellar. It needs a controlled environment.
I gotta bust out of here in one minute!
It takes special skills to ninja through a secure warehouse in broad daylight. Great work. Now, let's see if it was worth it.
Now wait for the cell to open.
You have to restart the drill!
Be sure no one sees you hacking the server.
Oh, shit!
We gotta clear the bollards. I mean you. And by you I mean hey assholes.
Police chopper is over you. We can't let them see which container we use.
You're one of the biggest smugglers in Texas. If you don't mind me asking, why shift to the oil industry now?
The cocaine is in the hands of the distributors now, and all is well. Enjoy the fruits of your labor.
Let's get that platform moving! Use the light by the window to signal our contact.
You better enjoy your life while you got any left!
Good. I can get on with the work now.
Don't let them burn the intel. Jesus!
That's the external hard drive. Nice.

I'm having trouble maintaining contact with Jiu Feng. Lots of radio interference, could be that Wang fellow still messing about. You'll have to signal for a pickup. The triad smuggles a lot of fireworks through here, maybe you can find some.
Maybe there's a faster way... there was some C4 in there.. maybe use it to blow an extra exit?
We need more, I already told you.
Plenty for Vlad - is it enough for us? Your call.
That's six!
This will provide an effective distraction for any guards.
That's the first.
Go find something to cut those chains!
I'll take Vlad's word, this guy is a dwankie kak, but it looks like he has good taste in wine, yeah?
Money and Mendozas up in flames. You made a statement and Hector's going to like it. Payday coming up.
He's sweating bullets by now.
No time for standing around.
Everyone OK?
The helicopter will see where we load our containers. Gotta deal with that.
When you're finished, bring back some tortillas and we'll have a barbecue or something. Vlad will make the Sputniks!
The key is likely held by someone like an FBI boss. Find him. Get it.
OK, three!
The event room's on the bottom floor of the office building. Go check it out.
You're so dead!
Time to deliver the bags!
What the hell! Come back here!
Hit the cargo door switch, friends!
You responded to a changing situation with admirable proficiency - and impressive firepower. Enjoy your payday. You will hear from me again.
Keep moving - get down to the garage.
The office of the manager. Maybe find keycards here. His terminal might have value as well.
I missed! Crapola! All right, I can do this. Just need Dutch courage.
What are you doing here!?
Damn, I almost had his location. Definitely near the centre. Keep at it.
Look, that must be that dwankie Kang! He's in the conference room!
You have to get the garage doors open.
Go get the teddy bear from the reception, then take out the saw and set it up on the doors.
No time to rest, empty that vault!

We want to wish a happy birthday to...Keith! You all know Keith! In his honor, we're serving cake on the patio! Get out there before it's gone! Keith will eat the whole thing if we let him! Got a bit of a problem, that Keith.
There's our guy. He's shit faced! Get him away from there. There's a deserted lumber yard near your position.
You actually think I would have failed?
Hmmm... He can't be in here... Neither there...
Find the cell block yet?
I'll be there in one minute!
OK, that's it! Now back away, this place's about to blow!
It's going to blow any second! Duck and cover, friends!
Since you have failed to surrender, we are forced to take you in by any means necessary.
People, I'm turning back now.
Tools for the trade, left whever you desire.
Excellent work, gang! Absolutely amazing. But now you need to get out of there before the place collapses.
Great! That's one of the closets!
OK. Any... Second...
No getting through that donnerse here. There's a scaffolding outside. See if you can find weak spot on the second floor, yeah?
That's bag one. Keep bagging, gang.
The van is coming back. Get ready!
Party might be over. Lots of people leaving.
... then, we'll trade.
Get inside the mansion, move!
We just did something people would have said was impossible. There's nothing we can't do, gang. Best of the best.
OK, time to get in that vault, chop chop.
Barriers are up! Crack the power box. That should drop 'em.
All right, drop it!
Let me remind you - drill the safe!
We're going to use the bank roof as the pick-up for the cage. Over.
Nicely done! The gate should be open.
I'll spoil the ending for you- the dragon is crushed by a mountain, and the little girl then breaks the mountain with her spirit.
There you go, one more should do it.
Yes sir, we'll help you with that right away.
Work faster!
I've always wondered why I seem to have such bad luck near wildlife. There's always something trying to bite old Locke... And I do nothing but nice things for the little bastards.
No... no...there will be no leg-cutting here right now, got that?
That's two!
Found that lever yet? Should be pretty big.
OK, friends. Hurry out and rescue Mr Pink, right?
Dammit. Go to plan B.
Oh man, the vault is already open. Thank you, Mr Manager, for being so accommodating.
Kill them all!
Is that a TV news crew? Try to stay away from them.
Gonna feed you to the pigs!
Lowering the winch now.
Great, now see about getting into the building proper.
You're gonna get that Croatian ship out of the dock and berth. Gonna try and keep the volume low.
Crew, you need to deal with the metal detectors. They use a lot of electricity so find and shut down the circuit boxes.
Every single one of them! Great!
They're throwing everything into this. Hold them off, my friends. They'll kill you, but they'll fuck me proper. For sure.
The escape driver had to go, I'll get you an alternative escape.
OK! We're gold. I think I got everything we need. You should be able to access his desktop computer now.
That's the fire dealt with. You guys are civil heroes!
Prepare to get fucked up!
Ok, I gotta sound the alarm now!
Today is the day. The day the Benevolent Bank goes down.
What? It stopped on the question marks. That could mean anything.
Thermite's done. We can use water pump nearby to fill the wagons. Connect that hose to the vault.
They've got every road out of there blocked. Time to go Vietcong on them. You'll see what I mean.
Looks like the vault in the blueprint you found.
They just activated several gun turrets. Stay frosty!
And....ta-da!
Think that shield will save your ass?
Looks like we have an opportunity to crack some deposit boxes.
Great. Now get that gas on those tires.
The cops know the snipers won't be able to finhs this. They're preparing to send in the troops!
You need to link the pipes from the generator to the right oil stock. Pull the lever on the tank when you're set.
I bet those wagons have loot. Check 'em out. Keep an eye open for C4 too.
They're going to stop the acid before it's finished! Look for the C4 Gemma's contact statshed nearby. That should take the workshop out for good!
I guess that you..? Wait, tell me nothing. I'm just an innocent bystander. This way.
Use thermite on the garage door! We're wasting time!
Did you hear that loud noise? Friends?
Great, the timer is done! Grab the keycard!
A luta continua!
Stick a blocker on the keypad to stop the code cycle.
It's SWAT choppers, they're on us!
OK, you're inside. Find the paintings with the red stickers on them, we want at least four.
Something's not right, something's not right here.
That keycard must open the gold stash.
Anti-air defenses?! Are you shitting me?! I can't fly any further! Take the parachutes and jump out!
Three.
As soon as you get out there, our 'delivery boy' will be coming with that drill.
Search the offices for dirt on Alice Rainey.
Shooters on the roof. Watch out!
Well the cops are all over the pick-up. I told Alex to set you down further away so you could claim the coke from a safer position. Once you have it, signal the boat and hustle the coke onboard.
That was it. Niiice.
I sure hope they never get rid of banks, but the way you guys work you might make 'em extinct. I love it.
Gang, ignite the tires. Give that chopper a nice thick smokescreen to worry about!
Event room's downstairs, friends.
I'm sending a chopper in for you guys to unload the loot. It's close by, shouldn't take too long. Stay tight.
Here we go!
Try splitting up. One of you might find me.
Go into the mall and rough up whatever you see. Keep civilians out if you can - we don't need unnecessary heat.
You've come to the wrong neighbourhood, motherfuckers!
Rust's bike isn't going to roll without an engine, and the mechanic said to check inside the clubhouse. Get a move on.
Great, that's him! Get him out of there and to the top of the tower!
Set up a flare!
A three digit code will open the armory. Find it.
No need to stay for a braai, get out of there.
See if you can find anything of interest while waiting for the drill to finish.
We've arrived. Use our thermite to open the ranch gate.
Ice that rat bastard!
All this waiting is fucking killing me!
The wheel stopped on smoke!
Son of a monkey smoker!
Security here is tight. We might be able to do this heist silently. But if things go loud, don't worry. I've always got a Plan B.
When you're ready, get to the window cleaning platform.
Time to go home!
Watch out, more snipers!
There's one of 'em!
Hook up the wire between the elevator and the door. Then shoot the cable.
Ok, get to searching for the answer to that code.
Don't let the SWATs interrupt that timer!
Come on, get those winches hooked up!
Gonna cut you into pieces!
Jiu Feng says you can take either path. Both will get you to the end of the docks.
There goes one of the bags!
It should be safe to approach the wagons now. Look for the ones branded with the shipping company from the manifest.
The alarm has activated a second feature on the gate - a magnetic seal. Drill can't touch that, so you need to access a terminal to release it.
You fucked up big time.

This is a simple job, but that doesn't mean it will be easy. We're going to head out to the forest. You remember the place. We did some work for Hector out there. Anyway, I scoped the place out and it is still intact. So, we're headed there to cook up as much meth as we can. You can stay as long as you want. If you run out of supplies, I'll get more flown in. Should be easy money.
I can't believe you maxed out the Piggy Bank! Did you see its eyes?! They were literally on fire!
The shaggy goat is unhappy with the knives.
There's a control terminal for the ship around there. Hack it!
Shit oh shit!
Hurry! They're flushing down bag after bag of coke and it looks like they're enjoying it!
How's it going with finding that uniform?
The chopper is en-route. Hold on, guys.
This won't take long. Don't let anyone borrow the keys to the truck.
Keep a look out for six cameras.
Great job, crew. Locke's already wired our cut. Still not sure about this guy, but maybe we can trust him.
Out of there, come on!
That's them. Now scan them in, and fax me a copy. I'll figure out the right vent.
OK, well I guess now you adapt!
Don't go down while carrying blood samples guys, they're likely to break.
Aaand here we go: The code is... 1138.
The comm frequency ain't here. Check the computer's in the control room across the dockyard.
You're dead!
Good work, crew. Now if Hector knew we just hit the FBI for the info he might worry a bit. But what Hector doesn't know won't hurt him. Let's go banking, shall we?
I knew we could trust that sniper! He delivers. Don't waste time - get to work on that transport!
You just fucked with the wrong people, my friend...
Next, the vault door. It's accessed by two keycard terminals. Swipe them both ASAP. Got it? Now find two keycards.
Good afternoon. Roberts Bank. This is Randolph speaking.
The coke's shipped out. Well done, sailors. Go get your payday.
You gotta get to Mexico. Hurry.
Okay... they have more guards patrolling the building. That's a no-brainer.
Why're you still searching containers? You got the bomb!
How's the search going? Remember to check Rainey's Executive Office.
I'm coming in four!
Everything ok over there?
Nothing yet.
I'll be following you through the head cameras as usual. Watch your step.
With you in a minute.
Some fortune cookie wisdom for you: Success depends upon previous preparation, and without such preparation there is sure to be failure.
Get over here!
Uh, this is very bad!
The next wave won't be as easy.
Shouldn't be too hard to get inside that ranch house.
Woop!
Guys, we're in the middle of the city - try to do this stealthy.
Chestnuts roasting on an open fire, Jack Frost snorting up his nose...
Go through with the trade, as we agreed on!
Aw, fuck me. The air in this place...
What's this? There's mention of a classified informant" here
Pressure's on, you chops! Turn those valves!
The system is running an auto-update. Go to the mainframe and stop it!
We've got this under control and you're just going to make the entire job go to kak if you mess with my guys.
Jiu Feng said you can go either left or right here, so pick a lane and stick to it.
Two minutes. Hey, fuckface!
You'll be needing that torch later for sure.
We're just getting started!
Don't stall. Just take him out.
That sounds like fun. I think I'll pay off my parents mortgage.
Get inside, lads! Got work to do.
Three gents eh? Come right in!
Great. Hector just informed me" he thinks they may have wired up the cash with C4 in case something like this happened."
Let's get this poisonous gas to its new home. Connect the canister to one of Gabriel's ventilation ducts.
... I'm back in a little while!
That C4? Pretend it is poor lost baby. Love it, nurture it....then put it on wall and blow it up! Yes.
Nicely done, friends.
Another C4 - defuse it!
Your getaway is ready. Get as much ammo as you can, and then get yourselves out.
Try and get by him unnoticed. Take your time.
No standing around, yeah? Kerels are on the way.
Oh, right. Yeah, sure. OK, have him check in when he can.
Hurry, friends! Get into that plane.
Okay, we're gonna need a fancy seat for Rust's fancy ass, don't we? There's an old bunker in the backyard. Get in there and you'll find what we need.
Watch out gang! BFD overheats if you don't give her enough water. Get it from the bathroom.
You took everything they have! Time to ride off into the sunset, guys!
OK, there's a boat on the way to pick up the bags, people. Go secure them first for the transport.
You made a sacrifice to Santa! Now the whole crew gets a bonus!
Your mall visit paid off. Fire and glass - like music for Vlad! I now protect again, and money... Money will be good. You have done favor. Spasiba.
Get to the ship control terminal and hack it!
Let the Inside Man know when you're ready to de-mask. He'll move the loot, so be sure you secured what you want inside the vent.
Shit! Bikers are on your case.
There are more of them down in the street! Take 'em out!
Alright he's here! Get the loot over there!
Guys, they're throwing everything they have at you. Better make it out, fast!
The damn scrambler just went down again. Get it fixed!
What are you doing here?!
Hurry friends, send it out of there.
Friends, it's probably best to go in through the back door with a saw, yeah?
The power has been disabled. Get it up!
Do you know I work for the Continental?
Those lights are part of the locking mechanism.
Deng usually hangs around the spa. The dwankie is known for harassing the ladies...
You've defeated the second wave of cops!
OK, I'm in. Give me a little time.
Get the prisoner up that tower!
Now collect those bags, and get to assembling the Beast!
We should have more security. The ship is vulnerable.
Double-crossing bastards! I'll fuck you up!
See if you can find a way into that area.
That's used bank notes from our 'allies' overseas.

That was a good run, friends. This Jiu Feng fellow seems like a reliable source to do business with. I just hope we haven't woken up the monster-in-the-mountain with this one, if you take my meaning. But needs must when the gin is gone, yeah?
Great!
Careful, looks like the bags are gonna explode!
OK. The panic room door is controlled with two keycards and a retinal scanner. No problem.
Why was he there? He's the cook!
Ach! Did you make it, friends?
Ok, drop the C4 into the safe and blow it open, the water will do the trick.
Yeah! Yeah! All right, hey, up in the booth, get on the Intercom.
That's a LOT of beautiful gold. Outstanding work, gang!
Some sergeant's here for a security inspection. Let him in.
Gentlemen - lobbyists inclined to stay on the current path of energy policy want your help. It is lucrative indeed - I say we answer their call.
The van had to leave. He'll be back, keep your eyes out for the new location.
Getting a nice clear signal. Time to leave, guys. I hope you tagged the right truck.
Stop! You didn't put it in yet, did you?
They interrupted the hacking device. You need to reboot it!
We need to work fast.
You gotta hack into the gate controls.
Oh fuck!
Fingers crossed this is the one
What the fuck do you think you are doing?
Get another key!
There's not much left now... If you just hurry up you might make a few extra grand.
What are you doing over there!
I need access to the server room. Some chop in the testing lab has the keycard.
There'll likely be workers here. Don't let them blow this.

We managed to bribe Buluc's old girlfriend for some info, and she mentioned this door. You will find how to open it deeper in the mansion, inside something Buluc calls his inner sanctum". Find that place."
Stand by. Hold your ground. The pilot will drop those bags any second.
Ah, it's empty! Find another one.
Left? Right? Where to go? I don't know! Hahahah!
Wait!
This is like a blerrie war movie! Come on you maggots! You wanna live forever? Go! Go! Go!""
Gently does it. Very gently.
Standby gang, the customer should be there in two minutes.
This will keep you in the fight longer.
You got the sequence wrong, friends. Either the symbols or the order.
I'm losing control!
It worked. All the records have been deleted.
Are you ready for the next step?
You're gonna cause a lot of headaches with this one!
I'm gonna kill you!

The Harvest & Trustee is a medium-size branch bank, vault in the back, a few different entries. Case the place first... You're going to want to get into the vault, drill it, get whatever's inside out of there and back to the escape car.
Hurry now, get that dinges some power.
Keep quiet while you bug out of there, and this is a perfect piece of shadow work.
I gotta leave in two minutes!
Get in. We should coast home in this!
Here comes your package. Have a nice party now!
Let's not waste any time, friends! Prep the locomotive for our escape!
Check every cranny, there is supposed to be a lot of ingredients there.
Keep those civvies stable, yeah?
I'm there in a minute.
There's a security office on the upper floor, in case you want to get rid of the camera surveillance.
Get this shit open!
Now clean these kaks out. Throw the bags into the ocean and I'll have them picked up.
This chop wants a fight? We'll give him a fight!
A contact of mine stashed a few body bags nearby just in case.
I've had enough. (to someone off phone) Send security up there. I want fingers pulled.
They've got an external firewall. Maybe you can shut it down with Xun Kang's computer in the meeting room.
Those chops took apart some of the best guns. If we reassemble them, we can pawn them off for a lot more money. Ever used a weapons workshop before?
The smoke looks thick enough from here. All right, choppers are bugging out.
A detenerlos! Vivos o muertos!
Quickly, get the power back before the guests get suspicious.
There goes all the good prints... That's a shame.
Get inside that ranch house. The laptop will be around there somewhere.
Look out for gas! Find somewhere to turn it off or wait it out.
The piece of shit just crashed again. Reboot the scrambler!
That's the exit! Just a few more steps to clean clothes and hot baths.
You're inside, but the alarm is counting down. Override the lockdown so we can get back on track!
We can't go through with the trade without the meth. You'll have to scout the nearby apartments and take the information yourselves.
I'm jealous you're going to get to drive this beast.
The boat is coming in at dock 7.
She's gonna blow! To the boat, friends!
30 seconds more and I leave.
Keep the cops busy and the drill will be through in no time.
Hell, this coke couldn't get ruined faster if a bomb exploded up in that room! Get! Up! There!
Office building, first floor. Come on, that's where you'll find the event room.
First Piggy Bucks are in! Let's get some more!
Nicely done! Now we have access to the shipping schedule. We can alter it from the admin office.
You're done? Good. Now keep going.
OK we're good to go. I'll get you guys cleared to the safe house. Their arsenal is gone. Their soldiers toothless.
Yeeaaaaah!
Taking fire! Taking heavy fire!
OK guys I want this to be a homerun. First get the drill from the parking lot. Then head in to hit the vault. Watch for guards and cameras.
URGH.
Remember to watch out for the guards.
Oh, you are over-delivering! Very nice!
Cops ahead!
Maybe there's a utility closet or something nearby with a toolbox you can use. Go have a look.
Now!
It's a Christmas miracle! Well done, my friends. May there be peace on Earth...until next year.
That should get the process going.
No standing around, yeah?
Columbian. Bolivian. Mexican. Wherever it's from, it's ours now.
We don't need another tea shop situation.
Remember, we are doing this silent. If the alarm goes off we're screwed.
Get that storage room door open.
You've been made! Damn, this is gonna get messy. Just keep hacking, I'll think of something.
GenSec in sight. Get those rigs moving. Go! Go! Go!
There's a good amount of tasty loot down here. Hustle out as much as you can.
You cut off his hand? That's some dark stuff, but a job is a job. Place it on the scanner and get the door opened.
They've almost on us, friends!
Hey, we're not done yet.
Fill me up, I'll come back for seconds if you stay around!
The inner complex is nothing to be scared of.
Ah, the elevator is broken! How inconvenient! Listen - since I can't get up, I need you to search for something important that they took from me. It's a metal briefcase. I must have it back!
Take the box and get out of there.
Hurry, friends. Get into the chopper!
Shiiit!
You know, on second thought - we'll take everything you have!
The gunship is back. Keep your heads down, gang.
This will thin out the security staff at the time of your arrival.
Let me check my records. Yes, I mentioned that the charges must be dropped near the door.
I'm at the pick-up!
You're breaking up... Can you hear me ok?
Guys, they're trying to jam the comms. Bile is on the way but he's gotta be careful.
Alrighty. Hook that canister to a ventilation filter, open it up, and gas the chop.
Yeah, we're gonna need a crowbar. See if you can find one.
Hook me up to that phone, yeah?
The keygen panel should give us a code for the motion sensors.
Gear up, we got a bad ass police force coming in!
Hook me up to a phone somewhere and I'll see about getting the dear Commissioner out of his office.
That's the keycard! Now, grab it and let's head back!
OK people, the pick-up drive is here! He's on the street behind you!
I got one!
The safe is open. See what was inside!
All connected? Good. Only need to get that pick-up working.
We need to shut off the motion sensors. Look around for that control console.
We need muriatic acid!
It's starting to smell like fried pig now.
Good. Let's see... it says here they have physical evidence on our friend as well.
Well done. Get into the chopper and let's go get our payday.
Now go find that business card with Kang's number.
Great, that's the guy. Start getting blood samples. We gotta validate them before you leave.
The crane here can be positioned over the main hall skylight.
You gotta help Charon! Clear the street!
Go inside.
I'm rolling so I should be with you in a little while.
Get back to armory and see what you can find!
Hello? Don't go without me!
One of the workers probably left their walkie lying out.
Woah, didn't take long for the SWAT's to show up. Must've been en route.
Put the bag on the table. I'm waiting.
Break the glass and bag those jewels. Remember all the extra stuff around the store.
Uhuh... uhuh... OK, sure. We'll have a look.
That's the vault, for sure.
These mercenaries must have some C4 or something around here that we could use.
One down!
Just picked up a call to a cop patrol. They've been asked to make sure everything's okay. They're on their way.
I don't want to die. I don't want to... Uuuurrrggh.
I'm coming in three minutes!
I'll feed you to my rottweilers. Dog food, is what you are.
The info we need is inside the admin office.
... I'm coming back soon!
Epic days.
That's the stuff. Get it to the van.
How... eh... gotta think of something... how to get inside...
Oh god, please don't shoot me!
That's more than four, Hector will be pleased!
That's the alarm - time for plan B. Do the countdown.
You'll need to figure out which key is the right one.
Consider these wise words: He who doesn't know where he's going should not start his journey.
Crew...
Benevolent Bank. A Neoclassical beauty. But business calls. We're going to need some codes, so get to their servers.
Nice, you took that sucker out. But hide the mess. The guards will react if they find out you destroyed one of their drones.
The fuck you think you're doing!?

Good, now hurry up and turn the lights back on or people will get suspicious and sound the alarm.
Look out! That Snowman's not fucking around!
Guys, the turret - take it apart.
You can grab oil samples from the pipes in the Extraction Room.
The first drill's finished.
Look out, wall breach!
Textbook execution people.
Vlad's got a little deal for us, wants us to hit this nightclub.
Be quick, gang. The guards will notice an open vault door.
The escape will be there in seven minutes.
This car doesn't have a door, so you'll have to use a blowtorch to make one.
Another goat secured.
Now, an eyeball with a pulse is needed for the scanner. Look out for the FBI boss. Make sure he keeps his pulse.
No deal, assholes!
OK, missing some files. Witness testimonies, kept in the Archives. Get me those files!
OK, now wait for the pilot.
The foreman keeps a master keycard in his office. Find it and get the card.
The code begins with a nine, according to my source.
Eight
Yeah, how much money do I got in there? How much?
The code should be on the screen. Get it and go open the vault.
Haha! You make destruction look like a blerrie artform. And something tells me your best work is ahead of you. Let's head home.
Police must have followed us...
You don't think our time's important?
Who's up for a lil hell-raising?
Don't forget, dear friends - you need to open the cargo bay doors.
Your ride out is on the way, but keep those blerrie Federales at bay until it gets there!
Hey! Get ready I'm... I'm close!
Hey, hold the door!
We really need that escape car now! How long do you think it will be?
One less prize for Murky to keep. Pick it up and move on, friends.
Nice! 20!
Adios amigo!
Okay, take a look around and see if you can find one.
Second. Keep going.
Cool, that's half of it!
It's not every day you get to burn a pile of cash that big in good conscience, yeah?
Ok, that's enough for now.
This place is locked down tight, but you can use keycards to gain access to different areas. Choose wisely - you probably won't find a lot of 'em.
...Start the winch and let it work. Keep the kerels away, yeah?
You won't make it anyway!
Ready to party like the old days, Dallas?
Time to go! Get on board before Murky attack craft reach us!
All right. There's one of the marked closets.
Wake up, old man. Fucking disgrace. I saw pilots do the Donetsk Run with four times as much booze!
Using your brain to control a drone? Jesus, I'm getting old. Anyway, this technology is worth a lot of cash, so we need to steal it from these bikers.
There we go! Now go grab that artifact and move!
The entrance to the warehouse with the vault is behind that rolling shutter. Find a way to get it open.
We're done, now get in there and find those pardons!

Alright, now, this is your safe house, this is where you spend your time off duty. It's not much at the moment, but give it some time. I'm working on it. I'll let you do some decorating yourself soon.
Come on guys, set off those fireworks.
Ach, friends. Maybe we'll get it right next time, yeah?
Jesus fucking Mugabe. Look at this. Fucking pallet broke! You're going to have to bag all the spilled loot, get it back to the pallet.
Gonna give you a faceful of lead, faceful of lead in you're head!
Time to get out of here. If you have enough gold, you can leave. But feel free to clean them out completely.
I'm betting the keys are locked away somewhere. Find the storage.
You have demonstrated that the Sosa Cartel does not own the Caribbean. With sufficient emphasis, I believe.
Keep an eye on the sprinklers, we don't want the kerels to set them off!
Oh, sorry man, must have called the wrong number.
Thanks! Fucking cops!
This is the deal:
When it comes to sourcing things like thumbs I operate a don't ask
column3: don't tell" policy. Now get to the security consoles."

String: Nice! Camera won't be a problem anymore.
No luck! No DNA match found on the evidence. Keep looking and scanning!
I just saw someone escape. Get ready for trouble.
Damn it! More frickin' laser beams. All right, no time to figure out where the system is controlled. Just watch the pattern and hurry through.

Dear friends. Commissioner Garrett has arrested the Elephant on trumped-up charges in order to get an item he has, that the owners of Murkywater- these Kataru people, want. He's making a deal to give it to them in exchange for what we can only guess is the body of Bain, now that they're done with him. The item obviously very important for them to risk exposing themselves and I wouldn't bet against the whole thing being about Bain's Grail-Dinges. We don't know yet what the Elephant's doing in all of this, if he's still solid with us, and we couldn't help him right now even if we wanted to, but Garrett will be in his FBI headquarters tonight preparing for the exchange, so we're going to ruin his plans.
We gotta find the bank manager.
You need to disable the metal detectors. Cutting their power will do the job. Look for electricity boxes.
Guys, wait... is that... Hector!? What the... fuck? Why the hell... I don't get this. Wait... the Watchdogs job, so that's why the cops were waiting for us. It was an ambush. That son of a bitch.
Okay. Get to the control room and disable the drill's blowout preventer. Heh, disable the drill...Shoe's on the other foot now, eh?
Damn, look at this place. This guy rides in style. You can do this quietly or with a bang, it's your choice.
Alright, get to the house and find the address, be careful.
So what do you think I should do?
And I thought maybe we could just do this quiet-like, but I guess not. You'll soon have lots of kerels on top of you, for sure!
Standard bank job, if there is such a thing. This one looks cash-rich.
Yeah, those are snipers!
Chopper's retreating! Wonder if Gage can get us SAM's.
We don't have time to load and unload the safes. The chopper's just going to carry the truck. It can do it. You just need to get in!
Who are these fuckers!?
You need caustic soda, yeah?
Only little more diesel.
What's a GenSec truck doing way out there?
Go, men - and get me what I want. The night out has just begun!
The shark went fishing for filthy Coyopa!
Console on the left!
The saw is finished, get through that door!
Remember that everything in those trucks is yours... So if you don't take it back, you'll be losing money.
What the hell, Dallas? I told you not to use the ECM until I said so!
Ok, so we now know which mask belongs to each guard, but that still doesn't tell us who currently has the card.
There's the chopper! Bile, lower the hose. Gang, get ready.
Get inside the office building!
Damn it! They saw you!
I think we need to distract those guards somehow.
Damn kerels interrupted the test!
Guess I'm bottom bunk, then.
Good. We're done with the fourth floor.
Maybe get rid of that tarp, yeah?
Sending a small plane to pick you up. Pilot can't land with those trees though. You gotta find a saw, clear a few and then mark the strip for him.
This is the reception desk.
Now what? Looks like a firewall backup is running. Find a computer to terminate it with.
... when it's done, we'll give you what you want.
Bain, you're not gonna dies, yeah? You gotta set us straight on this Kataru business!
That's five.
Right in the kisser!
Put the delivery in the car...
The wheel stopped on flames, I don't think that is a good thing.
Ah, there he goes. Hahaha, Good.
Good time for ziplines, maybe.
Daddy's rich, he can buy all of you!
Those things need to be put onboard the plane.
Aweh! That's it! Oh, sorry friends... got a bit carried away.
This is the emergency ladder. Only way up to the roof.
Running low on ingredients? If you want to stay and cook a little more, there's a supply drop waiting in the wings for you... Just signal the helicopter. Or you can bail now. Your choice.
We got 16!
Get to the prison transports.
Take down the alarm, friends.
Yeesh. Didn't they teach you colors in school?
Get him!

If we alter the rig's transfer schedule, we can take all the oil we want without raising suspicion. The network's unlocked, but we need a USB drive to access the computers. Should be locked up in a cabinet somewhere.
The van should arrive on a street near the park.
Cops are on us like white on rice!
Find those trucks! And don't shoot Vlad's guys if any of them are still around.
Two bags.
Find some way past the gates without raising any suspicions.
My friends! My pleasure!
Zup, homes?
Alright he's gone again, so get back in his office, yeah?
Still no alarm. Outstanding. Now open the gate.
Come on friends, get cracking with those cameras.
Put the flare close to the winch!
It's gonna blow! Get out!
Right you are old chum, but we do donuts too.
Nice. Now get it back to the loot drop.
What kind of bullets did you get? Only one way to find out!
I think the security room's somewhere nearby. Could take it down if you want. We've got time to kill.
...I'm seeing a lot of talk on Murkywater comms, so don't stay long. They might be wanting to join us, and we don't want that, yeah?
Ach, you're making me go bossies! We couldn't afford to lose anyone! Abort and return to the safe house.
Hey! Make sure you're ready!
Those look like sniper teams, folks. Careful now.
Don't forget to check the roofs of the buildings. Look for a ladder.
Getting pretty unpleasant out there. You guys sure you wanna stick around?
These guys, they remind me of some game I played, man.
There aren't any monsters behind those doors. I promise, yeah?
We're not going to get in there without the code. You'll have to find one.
Four.
I had a contact hide a cooler in the elevator for us. Drop the vials in there!
The armory, friends. Try following the smell of gun oil?
Put the wares in the car...
All you need to do is hit the bank, open the vault. In the chaos destroy the ballot machines.
So the safes can be drilled, even picked - if you have the skill.
Good. Now get a breaker on the second code lock.
Ok, one firewall down. Get to the next.
They're inside, take them out quietly
Too much flak. I'll move to a safer spot, follow me.
Vanguard is on the way. Everyone keep your eyes peeled.
Great. We're connected.
Open the door. Let's unmask this dirty traitor.
Kill 'em!
Ok, you know which wine we're looking for! Find it!
What pilot? I'm just giving some advice. Hey, aren't you going a little too fast?
You thought you were just going to stroll in through the main entrance? Look around for another way in.
All right! Streetlight is history. Grab the goat!
Nice and easy. Keep your heads down.
What are you guys doing over there?
We can't let them interrupt the hack again. Protect the laptop at all costs!
So, now start pump to transfer fuel.
Grab it, grab it now!
Great, set off the flare so the chopper can land!
Blerrie domkops have interrupted your hack.
That was crazy guys!
We're stuck without that keycard. Find Ralph Garnet!
Take them out!
Who is this? Who the fuck are you?
Throw it if you have to, just move it fast!
I am not worried.
Find the guns? They should be in cages. Maybe some crates.
There's still thugs in the building. You need to deal with them.
These motherfuckers... I heard the car battery asshole is on the boat.
Try shooting your way in.
Aw, there's a metal detector, wasn't in the plan.
Get on top of the train and secure those hooks!
Nine to five... helluva way to make a living.
You need to get the elevator going again. Restore the power.
Watch out! They are bringing in a sniper team by chopper!
Next up, head over to the ranch house and find that laptop for Gemma. You could use C4 to blow the gate.
Now dip that charge in and stand back!
I'll be damned. According to this email, Rainey paid some Overkill MC boys to hit one of my trucks. Paid 'em with SERA's money. Wait 'til the press sees this.
Find the transfer hose and lower it down!
Four
Who believes in fate? People with shit luck.
No time to waste - get through that door!
Kepe piling 'em up. Make a nice bonfire.
Not me, not me, not meeeeeeeee!
Very nice, bringing more than we expected!
Hey, Vlad! I'm on my way. Lots of cops around here!
Great! Now find a scanner in IT. Fax me a copy of the blueprints. I'll find that vent.
That must be the keycard that opens the gold stash.
OK that's the ticket. Get the scrambler on there. The Elephant claims this is going to win the election.
At the back you can throw any bodies over the railing into the sea.
They must be around here somewhere. One minute...
Ah, forget it, friends. Just hack into the server room instead.
Sorry, is the floor wet? You piss in your panties, little baby?
The armory shouldn't be too hard to find.
They shut off the transfer! Check the lever on the oil tank!
Yeah! Treat it like it's Keith Moon's birthday.
Sorry guys, he says this ain't the one. I'll be back in a few so you can give me the working one.
This place looks like it hasn't been decorated since the 60's.
... You made us come for nothing?
In! Right, need a few moments to get the lock. While you're waiting, head back out and fetch some C4. Let's get our escape ready.
Hook it up guys.
Time to use the keycard you picked up. Have your gun ready and take out anyone on the other side of that door.
OK that was severe OVERKILL. Vlad will eat this up. This will really work for him.
Snipers are almost moved in.
Acquring this asset is, in my opinion, a wise decision.
You let the dwankie kerels stop the IT guy! Clear them out!
What are you waiting for?
Gotta do it faster!
Right friends, you should get over to the weapons lab. I think they're keeping one of the boxes in the adjacent room.
Pick a direction guys. Rock, paper, lizard... whatever... any will do.
Don't stop too long, friends. This is bat country!
My recommendation is you hustle those bags to the van.
Well, this dump is the perfect place for a rat like the Commissar to hide out.
Great. Answer the pager first, then get rid of the body. That dumpster should do the job.
When you're ready hop into the van and we can roll.
That doesn't sound good! Be ready to fight!
This is the deal:
Stop throwing the coke into the fucking water!
It ain't gonna open itself. Use the keycard and code.
It's the police! They're tailing us!
Don't put on your mask and case the area first.
Gonna cut you into pieces!
Good job on not raising the alarm. Keep it up.
The power is down. You need to restore it.
Paging Dr McCoy... Dr McCoy?
Four.
Alternate entrance. Electronics, wire box, and a good place to hide bodies.
Told you it would work, didn't I?
Put your mask on.
Get to the office in the Research Center. We can't leave any documents on the Neo-2 behind.
Time to get out of here. Leave the tower and move further along the bridge.
OK, you're in! I've sent a security clearance request. You need to approve it.
That should'a been muriatic acid!
Good job. You reacted fast. Time to dispose of the bodies.
That's the wall gone. Looks like a few voting machines ate it too. Now move!
Some fuel will light that up right and proper, yeah?
We gotta open this dock gate to get the Moretta to Dock 3B.
...the object in the floor is our main priority, but it's a shame to leave all that pretty gold here. Bring some with you if you can, yeah?
Cop chatter on the radio just went off the charts gang!
Well, I'll be damned! Real talk, I did not think that was going to work.
Maybe we'll find out what happened to Jimmy Hoffa.
That's two!
Someone just bought the toy and walked off with Vlad's stuff. You need to get it back!
Time to go!
Place the missiles next to the radar and activate them. Easy peasy.
See any of that lying around?
I can not fucking believe this shit!
Get to L4!
This is gonna be easy as long as you steer clear of the security systems and guards. Well maybe not so easy. Take the paintings with red sold stickers and clear out. We need four at least.
Son, I'm giving you three minutes to get them to this phone, or I'm booking you for wasting police time.
Come on guys! I can't stay here forever!
Another security buffer kicked in. Need to be disconnected manually.
It took you long enough.
You should always trust Locke, except when you shouldn't.
Truck's open, go get what's ours out of there.
Outstanding work! All four trucks are stopped and ready. Make it rain, guys!
That's the head of security. He seems to be at the back of the house.
Not going to miss that prison food, I can tell ya. Shit on a fuckin' shingle.
The chopper is ready to leave!
You've got tear gas incoming! Stay away from it!
I see one!
The cops are taking our goats! Get them back!
The Lao Che Shipping company warehouse is Vlad's location. No time to waste.
Hector's worried... We're too far away from the coke in this chopper. Once you're on the ground get to the coke, signal his courier, and load it on to the pick-up boat.
Escape car is there. You need to be finished soon fellas. Hurry!
C'mon friends, the drill has been stopped!
Oh, shit, shit, I forgot something. Listen, If you find any tapes, take them too please... I don't know maybe burn them somewhere later, OK?
You should probably stash that extra loot somewhere safe, so you can take it with you when you leave, yeah?
You need a crowbar for this, guys.
Woah-woah-woah-woah!
Get some sentries up.
Hey! They're trying to fuck with us!
The elephant specifically told me not to forget the briefcase! Find it!
Yes, that is a giant piggy bank. No, I haven't lost my mind.
Search for the evidence! You'll know it when you see it!
Wrong wire! Maybe we lucked out...Maybe not.
You'll need a lighting fluid for the fire!
Don't shoot the Taxman now, shoot close and get him to jump into the limo.
Ballots: wiped. Asses: covered. Looks like a little heist accident. We didn't get the loot but we'll do better next time.
There's no way back now.
Gonna buy you a one-way ticket to Deadville!
Time for plan B. Start the countdown.
Alright, we're here. Grab some thermite and use it to get onto the ranch.
OK, bustin' outta here!
Portable computers. Times three.
Maybe have a look in some computers around there. See if anyone has been careless with their security clearance.
Deal's on, people. You made enough crystal to make royalty blush. Hector's going to be singing your praises if he isn't high as a kite. Well done.
No question about who was blerrie here, for sure!
Great, now we can open the crates laying around much faster. I bet you they contain some good stuff.
These guys can drive!
The plane needs juice to fly.
Pay attention! Valve H1 !
Gather together by the gate. Security here prevents more than one at a time to open.
The mercenaries are gonna come at you hard! Protect the EMP, gang!
Gentlemen? The crates with the strobes? Please?
Crack them open one at a time, and watch out for cops.
Get up to the second floor using the scaffolding. See if there's a weak area in the floor or something.
Crack open that container, chop-chop!
Getting all the pieces in place wasn't hard.
The auction hasn't started yet. Maybe the office is behind the stage. Distract the guests so you can get a look.
No, that's the wrong blend... now you gotta wait until the reaction dies down and start again, yeah?
Would have thought all those weapons would have got you there faster, yeah?
Building schematics show a high-voltage box on the upper floor. If you can shut it down, the vault will be safe.
I know this is old history - just get those civilians on their faces and get that thermal lance burning. Go for it.
Fuck!
Ok guys, you're in.
I spent some time away on business... I need to collect money from businesses.
You should see me coming any second!
Well done, we have the hard drive! Time to get Wang. The bastard is hiding in the meeting room. Rotate the show car platform, and we'll use it to break down the door.
I'm going to meet you just outside town. Best way for you to shake these kerel is the sewers. Get down there. I've arranged a little something.
The charge process needs to be started again.
I felt the tremor of that starting from here.
There's your ride out. Once you've got all the loot secured, you gotta get it refueled.
Hang tight, I'm looking for another escape point.
Gonna cut you into pieces!
How tough is he?
God dammit! Down, guys!
You can secure the loot bags in the boat you came in on.
There's your bonus. Get it to the van. You guys deserve it.
Watch out - there's more of them down there!
Go to the armory and find something that opens doors!
We're going.
... We'll settle for this right here.
There's an assault on the way.
Connect that cable to both the hatch and the truck.
I'm sure this will come in handy.
Someone remind me to send some fags back to the slags in Hazelton. And a cake of shit for the guards. Wankers.
We need that vault open. Quiet with keycards, or bust it open with a drill.
Don't forget to grab C4 from the armory.
Loot van is here.
Good job! Finding extra loot always makes me happy.
No worries, friends. I'll get Bain. Just keep those Murkies away from us, yeah?
Could never go wrong with that, I guess. Might be somewhere it can be useful later.
You could get a zipline up to move the bags.
Nice, homey place isn't it?
Keep going!
You're all dead men!
Thermite's burned out. You're all clear. Drop in and start bagging.
Ha, it worked! For once, TV is good for something, yeah? Now, use it to get past security.
Second truck can't be too far from the first. Find it.

Ok, so we're going to Salem and steal the artifact from the fancy rich dwankie party, right before the auction starts, yeah? You're going in after dusk, and it's foggy and raining, so maybe try to do the whole thing quietly if you can. It's an old mansion, but the security systems are pretty solid, with many upgrades. Under the circumstances, the less attention we draw from the kerels, the better. But if you gotta go loud, then get it done chop chop.
Hello, who is this?
Get to the warehouse and free our Ukrainian friend.
Can't go back now, the triad goons will probably see Vlad is missing any time now. Find a way to move that container so we can get the skid loader past it.
Gang. You gotta scan and fax over the blueprints. Sure that can be done in IT.
Kill the guards. Then you can kill Ernesto Sosa.
We want to get away cleanly so these must be destroyed. I can leave that to you, yes?
Keep those Murkies away from us!
We'll go with muriatic acid.
The hack has been interrupted!
Gang, GenSec truck. Hey, it might be carrying a keycard. You know what to do. Get at them.
Get two more!
Half the fucking police force is on our ass!
OK folks, we're going in and looking for the vault. Cartel or not - it's still a bank, right?
They turned the power off! The lights are down.
Wrong movie, Hox.
There he is!
Relight the fire! Come on!
The kerels unplugged the saw! It can't cut those shutters without power!
The drill won't break that door. You should try the armory and see if there's anything you can use.
Time to go! Hop on the train!
Cops and SWATs are arriving at the scene, be careful.
Hope you got your seat belts on!
Get the fuck outta here!
Time's running out! Reboot the alarm!
The car keys should be around there.
Come on! I need you to hook me up to the reception computer.
Guys, Fedor is waiting over at the lake. It's time to leave.
Ah kak - those poes are bringing in more SWAT turrets, with the express purpose of bringing me down. All right, I can't pick you up in town, but I am prepared for this.
Payday Gang, we have received the hostage and have authorized release of the payment.
You got made.
Is everything alright over there?
And that's it for the safes. Now I want that truck in the yard. We're closing this one!
There's a lot of stuff in here! I guess you'll know what you're looking for when you see it.
Alright on this webpage. What did you just add? Alright. OK, OK.
Look for something to do with history.
Make sure you keep the power up.
Great, it appears the Feds aren't as stupid as we thought, the alarm triggers a server security barrier. Now we gotta get that open too.
We need to get him out of that prisoner outfit. Find him a spare police uniform!
You need to clear the area outside the bank.

Murkywater's been moving stuff through DC by convoy for months. I've resisted hitting these til we got a shot at a big prize. Here it is. Gold bullion. Got a diversion" on the Woodrow set up to get it where we want it
column3: then we're gonna seperate an armored truck from an armed convoy. Once it's isolated
column4: hit it and boost that sweet bling. Au yeah."

String: Bring the flash drive with you and get out of there.
The pressure valves should be scattered around the Processing Area.
There are only a few ingredients left. You want more, just use a flare to signal the helicopter. He's got what you need for cooking more. Or you can bug out now. Up to you.
You'll have to go across the deck of that ship. We'll need to get the skid loader onboard somehow.
Bring the present to me! I stole a sled for just this occasion!
Blerrie courier threw the winch parts all around. Sorry, friends but you'll have to round them up.
Ey yo waddup.
Distracting those tonghua civvies will have given you some breathing room to move around.
Use the crane to bring back the crate.
Time to find Kang's phone number.
Blerrie, we're not cracking that in time. Going to need a code.
Those chops are using an RFID tag. No problem. Crack open that box, and let's see what we need to cut.
Go grab a blowtorch from the warehouse. We'll need it to get inside the wagons.
Come on, get that hose down to the safe, clowns!
Just put the stuff in a pile on the floor for now.
Alex will be seen by that helicopter!
Shit! Po po is here!
Your escape van just left...
Nice, nice. Now spark a flare close by. Show me where I'm flying.
Ok friends, you're almost home. Just a little further...
We know which oil supply to pull from now. Find the transfer hose and lower it down for our tanker ship.
H4! On the double!
Good job, gang. The server has been secured and Jimmy will be happy.
I'm patching in the driver!
Driver's here! Load the guns into the truck.
How's that door coming along?
Put them down!
This will reduce the effectiveness of their surveillance.
Keep looking for those router boxes, I'm working on a plan B.
That's not it! Where does the RFID get its power?
Hey friend
column3: it's Han Chan's birthday and we saved you some cake in the kitchen. Better hurry up and take it before Wu sees it - you know how he is!""

String: I've seen that equipment pull a two-ton Roadwarrior out of a bog in ten seconds, but that hatch is holding tight.
That's the alarm. Alright, weapons hot! Don't worry about the Moretta. She's moving and is gonna keep moving.
Looks like keys to an airplane or something.
Get that power running again, yeah?
Ohhhh shhhheeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeiiiiiiiiit. Out-fuckin'-standin'!
This code will unlock the display case!
No need to hang around, just decide what you want to do.
Damnit, that's the alarm. Stay frosty and get ready!
Looks like what we need... right over there.
Over-delivering! The boss likes that kinda shit!
Look for something that can breach a heavy door!
Nice to see you still have a keen observation. Take him out and do it quick.
You need to find those code fragments.
This algorithm will wreak havoc on their servers.
Watch for anything odd.
If the container holding Vlad is locked as tight as all those others, it will need cutting. You can probably find a blowtorch or something around there. Dockyards always have lots of tools, yeah?
Those sprinklers put the fire out!
Hmm... Ah, okay! I need some exhaust pipes and a gas tank. There's a ceiling lift in the workshop. They store them up there. Get me both and I'm all happy.
Ah, kak. Some of the guns are in pieces. If we leave any parts behind by mistake, they won't be worth much. I'm thinking we use the weapons workshop to cover ourselves.
You got the frequency already. Stay focused!
You need to tell them that shit? What are they, you treat them like babies?
They cut the power! Get it back up or we can't continue the download.
30 seconds, guys...
Now plant that C4 on the gas pumps. We'll light a fire they'll see in Moscow...
Guys, check out the printing press. Whaddya say we make a little extra cash while we're here...literally make it!
Might want to check out the cafeteria. I can see a PC monitor there.
You gotta get inside, quickly.
Ah kak, looks like he slipped off to the roof instead of the emergency exit. Get up there and take him out.
I fear the main entrance is not an option. They are all over it.
The driver should be there any moment.
Come on, you need to get inside.
It must be where they keep the pardons we are after.
Ey, I said we need more!
Can't believe we are breaking into the FBI. You guys get inside - quietly. Please.
Not the blades!
Seems the paintings are not enough. We must hit him harder.
Set out a smoke signal for the pilot to zero in on!
You guys are lucky, I'm feeling generous.
Make your way outside and go down into the sewers. You'll need a bit of thermite to cut through the grating, yeah?
Twitch is on his way with the van. One minute.
Attach the car so you can fly out of here!

That was a real pleasure, makes me think of the old days. Starting out small, the simple things, right? Good work.
Ok guys, if all goes to plan, we should be able to leave unnoticed. Just slip away with the crowd.
The chopper is headed for the antenna. Stand by!
At least seven more!
Still in whisper mode. Good, good. Now find the computer.
The prisoner knows the way out. Just keep an eye out for guards.
Find Wang's laptop and decrypt the drive.
My special tools. Yes, I definitely need my special tools, and you'll find those in the workshop. Look out for toolboxes.
Get back to the control box and shut it down.
Aw, that's a civilian casualty! Be careful!
Better get moving boys, the longer it takes the more cops are going to show up!
More snipers are coming in!
Alright, restart the computer and we'll be back online again.
Get those masks on, gang.
Man, this thing turns slower than your mom.
Ha, they still suspect nothing. Just stay careful while the ship is moving.
Hurry up and find Buluc's office.
Blerrie, there's no way to get to him without causing a ruckus. Let's gather some more info. Plant a bug near the office so we can hear what he's saying.
You like bread. We got bread. Uh... yeah. Assloads of bread... Sir.
I'm a self-made millionaire. When I run dry, well, I just make another million.
Good, now do your little magic on that baby. Get the pick-up running!
Heh. I suppose you learn something new every day.
You've got to relight the fire!
... I'm coming back real quick!
Death... by meth... sorry, friends. Not funny.
Maybe I should start importing wine too! Vlad's Wines! I like the sound of it.
Find those prison transports. They should be just up ahead.

You're going to New York tonight. The Continental called - one of their key staff has been ambushed and is being held by unknown assailants at an address in Brooklyn. We have the location from a call he made just as they took him. The target's name is Charon. We need to get there fast, take out whoever's got him and send him back to the Continental safe and sound.
All right. More C4. Almost got all we need now. Keep looking.
What are you doing to my paintings?!
Your cover's blown... Either get out or try to get a tracker on fast... Heat's coming either way.
Great. Now get to the zip-line and you're job is done.
Armory needs a three digit code. You can find the digits throughout the Grin. Get to it!
You're doing good, my friends. But that's just the first. Find the second pallet.
30 seconds, guys!
What the FUCK!?
Alright. Scanning equipment is in position on the rooftop. Sneak in, take his mobile phone, laptop, hard drives, and tablet pc. Anything technical. Then bring it to the roof.
It's trying to auto-update! Stop it, friends!
All his sins burned to ashes! Now let's find our friend, he should be in the cell block.
Come on, what are you waiting for?
Now, lay a fire trap in container 12. Dump some gas in there.
Chopper's not leaving without you.
There's a zip-line set up there. It's for getting loot out, nice and quiet and unseen. Lot of valuable stuff in there that you can tie on it.
You're not wrong.
We picked up a tail of SWAT choppers!
That's a start.
New plan, people, 'cause the old one is dead.
...This is how it looks right now.
Train is almost there. 30 seconds.
Rainey would've jacked the price of this thing through the roof. The world's better off buying it from me instead.
That's one less thing to worry about.
Grab that paste and burn through the gate. Fucking hell.
You gotta use the thermite on the barrier.
Gage sorted a dumpster to stash a bit of loot in. His people will collect it in the morning.
The Payday Gang is an anomaly. Each heist is a one-in-a-million scenario, you have to make the clients see that.
What's the problem? Get the gear, fuel the car, and hoist the back wheels!
The Piggy Bank just hit Stage 4!
Looks like you're going to have to go in through the back door. Use a saw to crack it open, yeah?
Get back to the mainframe.
You have to search the mainframe again to locate the second box. Quickly, now.
It's not working. Take another look at the pipes.
The street is where we need to assemble the cage. Move it!
Don't forget the coke in the van, or all of this would be for nothing!
Any room in the sanctum might have what we need. Look around!
Listen you fucking poes. You're only getting on the roof from the store room ladder, and you're only getting in that with the keycard. Look for it!
Those snipers couldn't stop you, so the cops are prapairing to move in with force. Get ready!
Alright man, you know what you're doing. Just don't want this shit biting our asses later.
Let's give Mr Blonde a diversion. Make a break for it over by the Big John's Burger Joint so the cops will follow you and not Mr. Blonde and the loot.
I got to dash out in two minutes!
People I think this job is a gold mine. Almost literally.
Where's the stuff, man!?
One minute.
Okay guys, keep it together. Get him.
Hey! You shop like Russian mistress, woo! Swish, swish, swish! With speed, and you do damage, ha!? Good money, good drink to you my friends. I, Vlad now own protection business again! Hehehe!
Something there. Right outside the Glitter Room.
Raise the balloon! It needs to be higher!
The fuck is going on? Some motherfucker sold us out.
Get those bags over here, now!
Time to end this caper! Get to the escape. Follow the blue containers!
Alright, the files are all uploaded, it should do the trick.
The cops are realizing those snipers won't be enough to take you down. They're prepairing to send in SWATs. Get ready!
You still got a long way to go!
You hear me? We need more fuel for ship to make international waters.
My clients are ready to enter the vault. You're not needed here right now. Go for a walk or something.
Get to the warehouse and free our Ukrainian friend.
Aha! That's it! Cold fusion, right here. You've got the keys to his airplane, remember? Get the hell out of there!
Bain - can you make the call?
Hey guys, what would you say to a diamond heist?
OK, gallery's just ahead. Watch out for motion detectors, cameras and guards. Get in there and bring me four of the paintings marked with a red sold sticker. Time is ticking guys.
Key to cold fusion is self-sustaining process... More energy out than goes in... Outputs will tell us if this is it or not...
Don't get too far away from that saw in case it breaks down.
It's gotta be worth a lot.
The bastards called in the SWAT-team! Okay, Dallas, show me you're no god damn rookie and take them down!
One more bag, then you get leave.
You must have shit for brains, comin' here!
Now get him to the server room!
Remember - there's a goat stuck in the scaffolds.
We should've switched fucking cars!
There's a dumpster down there. Gage says you can use it to stash some loot.
No, something is wrong... now you gotta wait until the reaction dies down and start again, yeah?
Aw no, you're not trying to fool ME, are ya?
The symbols in that codex. That's how we get the Mayan dinges to open. There must be more clues around there.
Kill Garrett's lights, quickly now.
Use that blowtorch you got a while back, yeah?
You'll get more loot if you stick around awhile!
Depend on it being there.
You guys are really something. No one knows a thing.
This isn't a request. Get your ass into position for a roof pick-up, or I'll see whole squadrons of F-16's scrambled in your direction!
You gotta find it! The uh, the...fuck, the tree! Christmas tree! It's got all the little presents and shit!
OK, Hector wants us to record this, so first: set up the camera.
I see one of 'em!
Get after him, and wait for your chance.
Few plans survive first contact with the enemy. You adapted well, and showcased an impressive capacity for violence. Enjoy your payday. I will contact you again once things cool down.
You need to find a way to shut off the gas.
Oh blerrie hell. Find the keys to his car then! Let's just hope that pile of junk even starts!
Keegan's got his oil! Now, head for the Drilling Tower. We've got a rig to destroy!
On second thought - we'll take everything you have!
Start collecting extra loot if you want to friends, it's time to get you out of there, yeah?
The escape train is now boarding! Hop on!
Keep the heat away from the circuit breakers.
Good! Get back to the lot, and start some fires!
That's the door, but don't open it yet. We need to disable the alarm, hold on a second...
Ah, that's what we came for. Nice and shiny. Take it and and keep it safe!
The Grin's vault can only be opened with a three digit code. This is one of the numbers we'll need to open it. Make a note.
What!? The Mendoza cartel is still there! Take care of them!
Protect the hacking device!
I have taken care of it.
Don't forget to take a look at the security checkpoint, yeah?
The next gate looks tough. Hmm...You know, if you find a worker's walkie talkie lying around here, maybe I can trick security into letting us in.
Just a few more steps, gang. The ladder is right ahead.
Ey, what's up homes?
The Murkywater trains will have a security panel on the side, so we'll have to hack them open.
Get the hell out! NOW!
Have a look in one of the other areas to see if you can distract the guests.

Hang in there guys, you're almost there!

Got to move!

Get to the basement and call the elevator.

The Taxman thought he was clever making a deal with a big corporation, but the information leaked, and now bigger sharks want in - all in. We have a complete, run-down building to ourselves, overlooking the deal. We've got a set-up installed. Alex will help with the crane. Scare the Taxman into his limo, shake him up, and he'll be sure to give us the server and the codes. When it's about $25,000,000, anything goes.
This should deal with their firewalls.

Keep them off the coke!

Running smoothly. Should be a good take this evening.

Hector's the rat! That's why the FBI knew all about Mendoza's secret bank, because this damn hardliner was feeding them information!

Hurry!
I'll eavesdrop, relaying...
Hmm...Alright, I see it. Back to work.
There's something at the Murkywater warehouse, down by the river. Something I would like.
Oh, looks like they've got a nice weapons lab! They've got one of the cases in an adjacent storage room, so get over there, yeah?
An old fashioned break in. Stay out of sight.
... make sure you're ready!
... then you get what you came here for, aight?
We're looking for the agreed amount of jewels from the store... If you want more, go back and get 'em.
Here's my idea: I take your shit. Then, you die...
The drill has stopped. Get it running again.
Just one more bag.
Wow. This would make a great tv movie. For someone who isn't you. Anyway now we know where the Mendoza bank is located.
Keep 'em comin'!
This is a warning. We are authorised to kill and your time is up. Your move, creeps.
OK folks, everyone into the train.
I see one!
A nice rubber dinghy. All aboard!
You need a couple of keycards. Look around.
Bueno we're gone man.
Go for it.

Get some fake sentry guns up and running. It'll buy us some time and keep people in place.

So far so good. Don't screw it up!
Sure there must be loot all over this place. Search the rooms if you fancy a few extra Benjamins.
Get that cargo somewhere safe for now.
Cop switchboard just lit up. Expect company, gang.
Welcome to Crime.net. This is your crime community. I will hook you up with crime contacts all over DC looking for guys like you. This net is built on mutual trust and money.

Employing this will reduce the security on duty.

Reactivate the computer, gang.
Get to the Tower, pronto! Don't want to keep Gabriel waiting.
Vlad's wife will be thrilled - now get that thing outta there.
Yeah, just heading there!
Kill everyone!
Pilot is coming in hot, guys. don't let the cops grab any goats.
Good, it's burning, now if you haven't, then take what you want from the other trucks, and let's leave.

Check inside those barns. That's where all the weapon prototypes should be.
This is the same type of vault as the one you did in that LA job last year. But we'll have to hack our way into this one.
Don't lose the asset, yeah?
Go for those security boxes. Remember, green light means active, yeah?

You need to find Taylor's computer.

Remember to sneak under the cameras so they won't spot you.

Monitoring their comms - no-one suspects a thing. Now get to the computer.
Over there!

I'm doing this. I'm committed. Limo's going bye bye.
Fourth floor is done. Good.
Ok! Get the briefcase!
A drill should make quick work of this door. See if you can find one.

They're upping the ante with snipers!
First job is getting inside. The front door is right there. But there's maybe other ways in.

Whoa! That's a gnarly bullet scar, man. Where'd you get tagged?

The vault is buried deep in the back of the bank. Getting through to it will be tough, but we have some help. An Inside Man is prepped and waiting for you. They're going to help us out once you're in there. You can do this loud, or you can take it softly. Up to you.
Time to leave the PEOC.
What about fucking their shit up a little?

No reason to stay quiet now. Chopper's on it's way!
Get the vault open with the thermal drill, then get the safe deposit boxes open - you might want a saw - and then carry your loot to the escape van.
Don't burn to death goddammit, save yourselves!
Guess this will be a bit of fun, yeah? Messing about with the Commissioner...
Well, OK then....
Don't let them take out the chopper, folks... We don't want to spend more time here.
Stage 4 for the win!
OK, we need the minimum cash amount - once you have that, I'll send the car for you. Now if you wanna stick around and get more be my guest.
The Golden Grin Casino: High stakes. High security. Large payday.
Abraham Lincoln once said: Give me six hours to chop down a tree and I will spend the first four sharpening the axe. He knew the importance of preparation.

Cops are taking your money, guys!
There! Fuel is now filling in boat.
Get to the roof and I'll send the chopper to pick you up!
Now you gotta blow a hole into the floor, yeah? What we're after is in the foundation of the building.
Hack's all done. Now get down to the garage and call the elevator. We need the shaft free and clear so you can get up to the penthouse.
I got another idea: Finders keepers, assholes!
Get the hell out!
Haul ass back to the chopper, clowns.
Ok, I'm coming back again for the next one. We could just drop it right on the house.
Pier 39. Find the truck that has the voting machines. It will be bound for Washington. Figure out which one it is, slap on the tracker and get the hell out. Keep it quiet.
Keep your heads down! They've got snipers in the area!
Go to the skylight with the box.
You can turn off the blowout preventer in the control room.
Dammit! The plane snagged the cage but there was no goddamn cash. You guys need to pick it up and haul it out.
We need to crack the rig's security network. The server room keycard should be on a worker by the helipad.
Hey clowns, the safe - drill it!
The oil's coming through! Keep hidden while our ship does its thing.
More cops! Give 'em hell!
We ain't got all night boys, hurry up.
It's the cops! They've followed us!

Eh, I'll say it for you: you didn't come here only to save me, now did ya? No, you're here for the custom built bike, am I right or am I right? I'll help you. I owe you that much, but you'll have to get me the parts I need.
Hacking the circuit box will stop the fan.
Don't worry, Boris. The chief will just pay him more money. He will be back.
Blerrie, you triggered the metal detectors!

Reactivate the charging panel.

Don't comply with them, we will secure you.
That's it for the snipers, gang. Nothing will stop Bile from dropping the C4 now.
Looks like we've hit the jackpot! Bag it up!
Force the elevator doors open and attach the lines. Next, you'll be zipping up to the penthouse for a jol.
Find a container with fireworks and use them to signal Jiu Feng to come get you!
May the best man win.
A little bird told me the Mendozas are flying in more weapons in preparation for the war with Hector. We go to their airport, find the weapons and take them all or destroy them.
There... behind that gate. C4. You'll need to cut through, maybe with a blowtorch. Look around in case someone carelessly left one lying around.
You can finish this when you want, but grab as much as you can.

When these pipes are connected to our tank of choice, pull the lever and activate the pump generator.
Kiff, now you just gotta make that hole bigger to get into the vault room.
Careful guys. If you go down carrying one of those things, you might break it.

Fuckin' 'ell, lads. Think about goin' straight. You don't want to be around Hazelton on Thursdays. Two words: fuckin' kinky night.

That was close. Good work carrying those guns up the hill. Vlad will build his army now and we will have a very fine payday indeed.
Yeah, yeah, just prepare a good heist for us that will make us rich.
Groot, it worked!
Kill him!
Well, you got a decent amount. Just about covers the gas money. Maybe next time we can push it further.
Now, hack into a workstation terminal.
Ok, here comes the first wave!
You gotta find that safe, yeah?
The alarm timer will start as soon as you open a door or window. That'll give you a few seconds to disable the alarm.
Clearance approved.
The manager is our target. Middle-aged creep with a bald spot. Get his keycard.
Guys, we're after the counterfeit money plates. Supposed to be stashed in the basement. Get friendly with Mitchell and get them.
Unlock the controls to the turntable.
Not out of the woods yet! Set sail for the tanker!
First thing to do is open that hatch to get inside. Once you're in, expect trouble right away.

Come on friends, saw those units open!

You need something to cut those chains.
Look out guys!
Now keep those dwankie Federales away from the bomb until it goes off.

You need to get to the basement.

Blerrie coppers have cut the power, get it up again!
