That can't be... a goddamn nuke!? Vlad!
Fuck!
I'm hit. But it just grazed me, I'm fine.
Open sesame! Now go find that prisoner!
It's all quiet still. Fantastic. Now open the gate.
...I'm 93% sure.
Just try to keep it in your pants this once and do the trade quiet. OK? OK.
He's lying, I'll take care of him myself. Bring him to the chopper on the roof!
They've got blowtorches back in the warehouse. Go get them.
I've had just about enough of that guy. Still... a fine job, friends. And the kerels are none the wiser.
Listen here...
No one steals from me!
You'll pay for this!
If forcing the door open feels too risky, you can find the keycard on one of the workers. Up to you.
... anything more than this is just bonus!
Hot damn! You guys did great! Enjoy your payday - you deserve it.
Fusion reaction is confirmed - all good and green. You guys skip out of there!
Looks like Jiu Feng's man was right. Vlad's in a container. Can't see how bad he's off.
That silo looks like a good drop zone. Putting it there.
The pallet fell on the roof, huh? All right, so get on the roof. Look for a ladder.
My connection is broken, you gotta get it back up again!
One of the items we are here for is being kept in the warehouse archive. You can use the crane in the central hub to get it, once you find the right shelf.
That looks heavy, but it sure stands out.
OK, the lights in the circuit box corresponds to the tiles. Use them to guide you across. No one can step on a wrong tile or this get's a whole lot messier!
They can go fuck themselves...
Eh, screw it. It doesn't look like you'll be able to pass him undetected. Take him out.
Guys, keep out of that corridor.
OK, while we wait for the money to burn you can open up some of those deposit boxes, what ever we find in there is ours.
Watch out, they're bringing in a sniper team by chopper.
They might be onto us, so don't take too long.
Clowns! Vlad here. What the hell are you doing in that - nevermind. There's a pig marked with an X in there. The Fed's will notice it when forensics come in. Get it out of there for me.
Whoa guys, don't blow it open too soon.
Good, I needed those.
Jesus fucking Christ... That was too close.
Oh blerrie hell. We don't have time for this. Fine, take his crappy car then.
You gotta get moving!
You need to get the bags to the platform where you came in.
Your reputation for being punctilious is well deserved.
You found a second vault?
It stopped on drills. Move away!
Great job, I've got connection!
I told you guys to be ready!
Zero.
Drill is done. Time for the Commissar to be done, too.
You have been warned. Surrender or we will shoot to kill.
How are you coming along with that computer?
There you go. Wait... now I'm getting something about air support? What the hell...
Time to get our friend out. Find the door to the custody cell block, it should be near.
Why aren't you at the wine cellar yet, you chops?
Stealing a man's car after killing him is the ultimate insult. I like it!
Have you found that business card yet?
Luck is where opportunity meets preparation.
When you return next time I won't be here, but you can always press that button to play a pre-recorded message.
There she is. The Moretta. No access here, though. Get it to dock 3B.
Took you long enough!
Time to fly, friends. Get onboard that dinges, quickly!
Still searching for the USB? Check back in IT.
Time to leave the PEOC, hurry!
Evening, this is Agent Green. Today's code seems incorrect. Just need to confirm.
The drill is out - damn cops!
Grab the encrypted flash drive. It should be in a laptop somewhere.
Got a plane en route to pick you up, but it can't land with trees blocking it's path. Find a saw, clear the trees and mark the landing with flares. Don't worry, CIA been doing this for years.
Son of a fucking bitch!
Drill that gate, guys.
Ok guys. Let's go in. Quiet or loud, you can kill this guy any way you want.
Find a way into that office. We need to get our hands on that laptop.
A night at the museum, gang. It's just you, a crew of security guards and a priceless diamond.
This is one tail I can't lose!
Damn!
It will be done, dai-lo.
Guys, don't forget to drill the safe.
Welcome, gentlemen.
Guys, you need to get out of there so the cops will follow you.
Are you having trouble with the winch?
It's rock'n'roll-time!
Don't fuck up. Hit it!
Probably a good idea to throw that dinges on the conveyor belt in the main hub - let the machines carry it back to the entrance for you, yeah?
I don't want to keep someone who calls herself the Butcher waiting. Get onto the ship!
Gringo over here!
Ok gang, looks like we're going after some diamonds.
Almost done. All you gotta do now is get hold of the keycard from Ralph Garnet. Find him and get it.
Hey, the escape chopper is here. If you feel lucky you can go get the rest of the bags - otherwise get out!
No one'll see that there.
There he is!
Remember guys, we need ten bags to escape.
Serious haul. You guys did well!
Intel tells us the EMP bomb will be two parts, and that's what we're here for. But with that said; if you see an opportunity to grab other valuable loot you should do it.
I'm sorry, but we don't provide loans without capital, and your favorite socks aren't that. No matter how long you've owned them.
Pro tip: use your blowtorch on the wagon roof. Metal's weakest up there.
Who are these fuckers?
That's enough for Vlad, but get more if you feel brave.
Good. One down, one more left!
Put the winch together where I marked, crew.
So you reached the top? Have the prisoner buckle up and then release the balloon. The plane will be coming in soon.
Yo, the info is in the safe. I'll get it open for ya.
Chopper is inbound. Stand by!
Kerels have stopped the drill. You gotta restart it.
Commissar's gonna be antsy after the motel attack, but he won't be expecting this. Masks on and give the rat what he deserves. Good luck.
Yes. It's working. Just need more in there. Keep loading.
Damn kerels have cut the emergency power lever and stopped the charge. Find it and pull it back, yeah?
You can never have too many bullets!
That's it. That's it! You're almost here, come on!
Drill the vault when you are ready. I don't know what's here but I like our chances.
Keep breaking things, gang.
I said it's time to go!
... I'll be back in a minute!
Old blueprints indicated a hatch or something to the next level. See if you can get through it.
I have an idea how we can get the code. Head to the telephone pole connected to the house. Time to make a call.
What the hell is Commissar working in this room?
Having trouble finding the cellar?
Into the helicopter!
You found it! That's the wagon with the printing plates.
I'm starting the clock. Look for a safe. If it's not in the safe - don't panic - it's in the building.
One down, two more to go. Find the other numbers and we get easy access to the vault.
If you need more supplies, there should still be more outside.
Bravo! Now, second step - find the local security station, cut through and approve the opening sequence.
Enough destruction and this client will rethink his whole stance on protection money. Dirty job but you like getting dirty, right?
Light up those tires, gang. Get some gas on them.
First step is getting inside the station.
We cannot use the main entrance. Too much heat.
Still looks stable, friends. Time to add the last ingredient.
As you have requested.
That's enough bags to make this worthwhile. Great work.
Use that blowtorch you got a while back, yeah?
Hurry! Find out where the RFID's getting power!
You're through to First World Bank. Yes sir, that's right - a free shotgun when you open an account!
Alex made the drop, I knew I was right in giving him a third chance.
The GenSec trucks just turned into our guy's sight. Wait for it... Wait for it...
Shit! Po po is here!

Hello, my friends. I hope you can overlook the fact that we haven't had time to properly tidy up the place. It's rather hard to get a cleaning crew out here, you understand. And believe me when I say, that I don't take this visit personally in any way.
Crap, someone got to the alarm. Alright, time for plan B.
We've got the engine, I'll have my guy here inspect it.
Cops climbing the outside. Get to the windows!
Ammo secured, I'm sending your pick-up ASAP. Be ready!
Use the intercom to call the foreman's office extension.
Alright! The drill should open that door!
This is a new tactic. I'm seeing cops placing tripmines in the parking lot. Don't let them get that shit set up.
Keycard. Great. You need to use it on the vault, but that's only half of it. Swipe it, and then hunt down the second card.
Is that door still creating a problem? Blerrie open it!
Last one is there.
Ok, you got the code but we have to get Kang's hand print as well.
Wait.. those bars are electrified. Maybe you can cut through them.
Hold up, the pilot overshot the cage. Hang tight while he comes back around.
Sniper? It... landed on sniper.
Finders keepers, gang. Finders keepers.
When you find yourself in a tight spot, there are few things more important than ammunition.
Mr... Locke? I'm surprised you have my number.
Now!
There must be a switch or something that opens up the rest of the house. Try to find it.
Ten bags?! We'll be swimming in Piggy Bucks!
Hello, what's this? Server room? Find an IT person and make them override the lock for you.
Get to the roof with the gadgets and bang, we're gold - literally.
There's one!
This has to be the most persistent fucking cops I've ever seen!
It's just a flesh wound!
You've got to keep at least 7 bags!
Cameras are down. Should make our lives easier.
Find the rig's transfer hose. You need to lower it down so our tanker can siphon the oil.
No other way out. Get into that container, gang. And hope the cable holds.
You made a bad mistake!
Please remember your fucking jobs - the breaching charges need to be attached to all four locks.

GenSec's overland armored convoys employ a lot of ex-military types, providing firepower and muscle, and they move everything from little Jimmy's favorite baseball card to the Crown Jewels. We got a line on a convoy moving into D.C. Let's see what we can get.
We can get better acquainted later, but I feel now would be the opportune time to, how you say, GTFO, yes?
Now light it up and give it a big push, yeah?
Witness me!
Guys, we're gonna partner up on a diamond job in Angel City.
Illegal untraceable weapons. This is what Gage is all about.
You're in for a nice surprise- our Cloakers are now carrying cuffs!
You have reaped the rewards of a well considered and deliberately executed plan - most impressive. I will contact you when I have further need of you.
Ah, look. See what that button does, yeah? Maybe the whole place will self destruct? Probably not.
We got an Inside Man there. They'll be able to open the gates leading to the vault area. Patching them through now.
Ready to snag those guns? Head to the barns. The weapons workshop will be somewhere that way.
The hack is no longer running.
Someone got away.
...I... think.
Put holes in 'em!
Now get those bags in the containers down on the floor. We'll return and collect them.
You're fucking DEAD!
Ok, come in.
Don't touch that gate without turning off the electric charge. You can't steal the plates if you're burnt to a crisp!
You auditioning for a TV show or somethin'?
Damn damn damn!
Come on, melt that cable, chop chop!
OK, the winch is secured. Let's pull this package out of here!
Gentlemen - I need your steady hands to remove a competitor from the political scene. The reward is golden.
You can't proceed unless you get that power up.
You have to keep them back, defend this dump or lose it.
There it goes. The vault is open. It's all yours, gang.
Gas! Shit, get out of there! Now!
Let's move, chops. That building has plenty of entrances.
We are done, my good friends! Everyone into the helicopter!
Kill 'em all!
Hmmm, couple of timelocks. Alright, you're gonna need keycards to go through. These rent-a-cop security won't have them, but I am sure the civilian researchers will. Get them to give those cards up.
Where's the shit?
Ok, have a breather while I fix this.
You got it? The briefcase? Good! Now let's get out of there.
I think we might need to spin another wheel. Find it.
Ambush... Another ambush... Hang in there and eyes on the prize!
We're gonna make your rest of your life real short!
You'll need some kind of explosive accelerant. Mulching fertilizer, diesel fuel... maybe these people even have some C4 laying around. See what you can dig up.
SWATs on the scene... Here we go.
OK, keep that smoke to a minimum... Keep going.
With all of these crates, there has to be a crowbar around here somewhere.
With Buluc's paranoia, he probably makes his four personal guards share only one keycard to open this door. Maybe they keep a note of it somewhere.
You swept that bus clean of Mendozas. A true Viking funeral in flames with their possessions and all.
That shitty network will transfer the databases faster if you can keep the cops from pulling the plug on it.
Nice work! Those plates ain't leaving 'til we're good and ready.
Is the container being difficult? Give it a good kick while you're cutting.
Start hacking, friends.
An engine. That's what we need. I think I saw some inside the clubhouse before they started beating the livin' shit out of me.
Taking a bit of time, isn't it?
Nice.
Uh...I can't change your mind? What if you...look into my eyes!
Told a guy who wanted a loan we couldn't under FTS regulations. FTS? Fuck. That. Shit!
No time to waste, take the artifact. Hurry!
Here take it, just take it!
Two down.
There's only one left now, you might as well tag it...
You almost got that winch ready?
Vlad, you chop! You said the vault was going to be easy!
Aw, no! The metal detector is new!
Nononono! Shit! I'm going down!
Ka-boom! That was on the bullseye, yes. Fight your way in!
Watch your step down here.
The R&D center should be right across from the main office building.
Now use those keycards to open the gate. Doesn't matter which does which.
Nicely done, friends! A job well done. We probably even emptied the Mayor's personal bank account this time!
Keep it coming. This bird can handle it all.
Hey, over here!
Don't forget to get the cutter onto the vault, heisters. Slice it open from beneath.
Some more cops have been called in. Be prepared!
Sorry about that, I should have known the com problems were not normal. Probably all that EMF interference...
The keys are probably close by.
Can't get the code without the keycard.
Before we begin, I've arranged for a few small articles to be left for you. Find the crates with the red strobe.
Deng should be in the spa, and you'll probably find Kang around the casino.
Well, well, well, so who's the fourth musketeer? This wanker's your little brother, Dallas?
That's another vault open and ready.
Get to the escape car!
Ok, here comes the fifth wave!
Are you nuts, Vlad? These are live nukes!
They just pulled up out front!
It's open, go get our stuff.
Where is that idiot, Li Deng?
Excellent job! We know where he is. Now hustle back to the car. Grab any loot before the Feds get it. You know... Those crates gave me an idea...
The cocaine is in the manager's office, but keep your eyes open for hired muscle.
Nice! Get it to the van.
Kerels aren't going to stop coming, so get out of there, friends!
See if you can find the car keys. They should be near.
Now look for a vent, and get the gas pumping. Send the security to Neverland.
There's a lever on the oil tank. Pull it when the pipes are set.
Vlad, my old comrade in business. How are you? Still having trouble with your brother-in-law?
Russian chopper pulling out.
It's been ages since I was there last. They've changed a lot of things.

OK folks, my guy stashed the thermal drill for the bank vault in the parking lot, so get that first. Watch for guards, keep an eye out for cameras - where there's cameras there's usually a security room... Money time.
Ninja's in socks tiptoeing on thick carpet make more noise than you. Expertly done!
Fucking hell!

Friends! It's Locke. I know you got little incentive to trust me after Alaska, but sending you there was the only credible ruse we had time for, to get you out of DC. People Bain used to think could be trusted... were listening. And now he's gone... we knew something was going to happen but not when or what. Keeping you in the dark was my call, not Bain's. Never thought they would actually be able to go after him. Look I realise it's a kakspul to hear, but you got out with the guns I left, yeah? I'm sorry about Bain... we'll deal with it... but first we have to get you out of there. Please trust me guys, I'm not bekakin ya. I promise I'll prove it.
All right, with that taken care of it's time to find the server room.
That makes seven. Gettin' kinda full already.
And big fiery explosions?
Don't let me wait now!
You didn't take care of the dragon statue, and look what happened!
I loved this room as a kid, but now... Makes me uneasy.
Nice. Security chief's number. He won't be happy to lose this.
You need to signal the boat driver with the floodlight in the warehouse. It's the only way.
The hose is laid out, good job.
Can't do anything until you hook me up guys.
It would be beautiful if we could do this with you hiding in the airlock, but... alas...
Reboot the shutdown sequence.
You'll have to keep the coppers away while the hack is working.
Got it? OK. Vlad wants his money. Go get it.
Fix the short circuit on the turntable. Be careful out in the open!
Helicopter inbound. Aw no, they will see Alex! Hide!
You'll find the code inside the auctioneer's office but to get in, you gotta get the keycard. Find the auctioneer and get it from him.
Those crafty chops got the asset from you! We gotta bail on this one. No cake tonight, friends.
I give you these toys and all you want to do is stay in the box. Move it!
Maybe I should've studied this ancient stuff more. Could the curse be true? Ah, it's just old shit worth money to me.
Ey, let's skip the formalities!
The plates are in reach! Just need to burn your way into the train cars.
This guy is doing well. Let's loot the place. We're gonna go for his floor safe. You've got some winches stashed near the entrance to the property. Get them and hook 'em up.
They're deploying gas! Get out of the room and wait for it clear.
Who let them in? What the fuck?
OK crew, you have enough to get the hell out now. If you want more then I need access to the surveillance room. I'll do the rest once you get in.
Bah, that offer is for chops. We can make them do better fo' sho'. Stay frosty, friends.
You got to find Valve L4!
That's enough...
You still need to collect your gear.
Mr Sturr get out of the limo.
I'm shutting this down. Make sure you're with the driver when he bails, or it's a long walk home.
Ok, now just down the ramp and out.
I'll be there in four...
And that's the second keycard. Nice job!
Maybe they have the information stored in a computer.
Now wire up those breaching charges. One for each of the four locks, if you please.
Get the prisoner out first, then you can go for the cash.
They're making a last effort. Make sure to stay away from that helicopter!

Remember, we're here to make it look like a bank robbery. If some election equipment gets destroyed in the process, that's too bad. And it would be a real shame if the voting results became unusable somehow...
Just two minutes.
How are you coming along with that floor?
These fuckers are going down!
This will throw a monkey wrench in the security works.
They're prepping the trains for an escape! Get inside the railyard, quick!
Now, please, bring the loot bags to the helicopter.
Who wants to do a little banking?
Here's the deal:
The big man is very angry.
Don't be overeager gang, store's not going anywhere.
Crisp and neatly stacked. Don't be shy, gang. Go get it!
Down there!
Thanks, here's your cash.
Coast guard's probably on their way. Let's move out.
Just got a message from The Elephant. Your bonus for keeping things clandestine has been dropped off. It's near the escape van.
We should have brought some gasoline or something to light this up with. But never mind, I'm sure they have something around here!
...I'm 79% sure.
The display case with the Neo-2 is on lockdown. Good thing we had a saw planted just in case.
Drill stopped - the cops disabled it!
Find the goods. I'm sure you'll know it when you see it!
Get that guy into the chopper. Come on, go!
Time to go. No time for lock-picking, just shoot off the door handle.
You're locked out. The system is gonna take 30 seconds to reset.
Gonna feed you to the pigs!
By method of elimination it has to be hydrogen chloride.
No more waiting. Shoot the bastard!
OK. Second act in our little drama - get the vault open.
The bird is inbound with the skyhook pieces. Pick-up target is the street.
Right, time to get the master code. The CFO will have it.
Roberts Bank values every chance to communicate with our customers.
The vault has gotta be there, yeah?
Let's empty this bank out, starting with the safe deposit boxes... Lots of mysteries in there I bet...
Wait for BFD to crack through the vault. Even this monster will take time. Keep the cops away.
It was really just a matter of getting all my ducks in a row, you know?
There you go, now make your way further into the facility. And be careful, yeah?
I know you had things under control. Not like that other time. You handled it in style. Hector owes us big.
Fantastic work! Fire up the engine, and let's head out!
We're here. Time to get your sneak-on.
Hang tight, too many cops for a pick-up.
We're almost there. Time to patch through to my pilot.
Why Switzerland?
Give him some help with the door.
Find me his server room. I will scan his stuff for info on the arms deal.
Mobster down. That should get Commissar's attention.
Did you need something from the buffet? Time to go!
Look at the formula, then prepare the next component.
Ah! No! No!
I paid the DJ to play some crappy songs he found online, so you'll risk less civilians getting in the line of fire.
Sniper! Take cover!
Deploy C4 inside the vault! Then get ready.
You need to get Vlad to the skid loader.
Cops incoming. I suggest you head down and take them heads-on by the front entrance. That way you can stop them before they flood the building.
You got to unscrew all the screws, friends.
What're you waiting for?
Gather up... At least 15k and then I'll get the driver to pick you guys up.
Where's the shit?
The Armory! Safely locked up, but spend a keycard and it should open up.
Gonna skin you goat-stealing fuckers!
Gonna keep it slow so you guys with the guns can stay with me.
Fuck 'em!
Shit, man I'm dyin' out here. What'd ya do, stop for a hot dog?
Damn damn damn!
Throw him down there. No one will find him. I hope.
Gonna feed you to the pigs!
The truck isn't moving til you deal with that van.
Wow. Russians would call this tactic scorched earth. Very aggressive. I'm sure Vlad will pour you a shot of vodka in thanks.
Have you forgotten where the mainframe is or something?
Get to West Wing. We need to get you into the Oval Office.
You can use one of Buluc's cars to escape. Might even fetch a nice price if Rust doesn't take it apart!
Looks like one of the goats is up in that apartment. Get up there!
One more should do it.
You guys OK in there?
Now you gotta blow a nice little hole to get into the vault room, yeah?
Good, now smoke that dwankie out. I'll be sure to send the kerels some cash for that gas later. When pigs go sailing over the Rocky's, yeah?
Nah, we'll keep everything!
Then we just need to go in to get the gold.
No-no-no-no-no!
Nine
I'm going to install some security scramblers.
Hey! That's mine! Leave it alone!
Time to go to plan B!
Remember! At least four bags!
Guys, you gotta get into the dockyard.
What are you doing overe there!
That's what I was afraid of. No way our usual stuff will take this out. You'll have to get medieval on it.
Get the bags here, quick!
What we got is big enough.
Fight your way back to the van, clowns.
If you see anything interesting... Save it. I'll have a look at it later.
The oil transfer is frozen. Shut down that firewall.
I need access to the server room. Some chop in the admin office has the keycard.
OK! We got some real scandal stuff here. He sold government arms to a rogue state - got paid in gold. The Democrats aint gonna like this.
The data is being stored on the server in the other room. You can get it and get the hell outta here, or you can stay and scan more bodies. I'm positive Jimmy will make it worth your while.
Cops are so far up my ass they're seein' daylight!
Was hoping we'd do this without police for once.
I've seen that before... is that... Romanov? The Russian empire?
So close now. That looks like three-quarters of the safes out of the truck. Keep going! I believe in you!
Okay, there it is. Kick the door down!
Red Squares!
Have you found that water-closet yet?
You don't want us to leave, do you? We're having so much fun together.
Looks like thick metal on those train wagons. Our contact said something about blowtorches stored in the warehouse. Go grab them!
Dangerous to stick around there, friends.
Look in the office and see if the keycard is there.
Every Christmas I set up a little operation - gifts for the children, and gifts" for the parents
column4: supplies are low this year. But! I have found an alternative. A clutch of assholes have an operation near here. Consider it a little toyshop
column5: yes. I need you to get down there
column6: take out the muscle and get the "elves" back to work."

String: Those crates are headed out to the Commissar's other dirty dens. Get those labels and check them at that code reader.
Damn kerels have cut the power to the terminals. Find the power box and get it back up!
Damn it! That's the alarm!
There's no easy way out for the tree. We'll have to take the glass roof off the mall. Signal Bile with a flare and he'll drop a little present for you. Yeah, C4.
Expect me in 3 mikes.
Cops in the store!
Hey Duke, is this what you thought you'd be doing a year ago?
Use your blowtorch to get inside the train wagon.
Use your code - defuse the C4!
That truck has our gold. Get after it!
Might be good to see things from the roofs, huh? For sure. Look for a ladder to get up.
Haha, the Commissar outsmarts you again, assholes.
Come on guys! You can do it!
Okay, good. You got the power back. Return to the scanning process.
That's the head of security. The pools, he's by the pools.
You know, the thing you're looking for might be in a bookshelf.
We're going to bring the drill in with a blimp. For the pilot to see your signal, you need to set off a firework display. So look for them!
Just get these bollards out of my way!
Thermite is slower than C4, but it gets inside without the noise.
So, they're studying one of the boxes in the archaeology lab. Get over there and have a look. And watch out for loose mummies.
If guests get in the way, shoot them too.
Get the bags here, quick!
Listen here:
I'm sure the Commissar doesn't have fire and damage insurance on this dump. So go nuts. Trash the rooms, scorch the cars - anything you can do to rile that guy and get him on the line.
Run that oil sample through the purity...analyzer...o'tron. Whatever it's blerrie called.
We pulled Mendoza's teeth on that job - destroying those weapons is gonna leave him with a lot more bark than bite. I bet Hector bumps us up the food chain for sure.
Why haven't you opened the gate?
Our friends have stashed the tools in a van. Find them to access the elevator shaft.
Mr Blonde can't escape unless you create that diversion guys!
That's torn it. Good luck.
Open up that last door and get to the server.
I don't know the code, I swear.
What's happening?!
Call the right extension to the foreman's office over the intercom.
That was the wrong computer. Try another one. Maybe there's a way to figure out which terminal we need.
I've swapped the voice recognition for a fingerprint scan. Now there's got to be a way to copy Esteban's prints.
Good idea! If you set this up right, that truck should pull the gate right off.
Okay, the winch is in place. Now I need you to attach the magnet on top of the panic room.
It's supposed to be hydrogen chloride!
Uhh.. ok. But next time I'm sounding the alarm.
Still need more power cells.
... drop 'em!
The papers we need are in the Document Storage room, but those doors are much heavier than we expected. The Chief Scientific Officer probably has an access tag. Go find him.
Payday Gang's so tight. Four fucking guys! I heard they mopped the floor with y'all!
Get those things onto the plane, chop chop!
Find those numbers, gang! We need all three to get into the armory.
The manager asked me to tell you to do the rounds. I'll be here for a while. Go on now.
Nice. It's getting hotter. What the hell is in there?
Codelocked door. You'll have to find the combination somehow.
Open for business! The business of finding goats!
Another two minutes and I'm out!
If you start bashing gear now, these chops will sound the alarm. We've got to clear them out. See if there's a PA system somewhere topside.
Stop those bastards from shutting down the cannon!
How I make my money? Publishing. Yeah, publishing.
What are you trying to pull?
The key no longer works. Automatic security is in place. Break out a drill, friends.
Stop dossing, time to go.
All this waiting is fucking killing me!
Come on, we need more than that!
Answer the phone!
The bastard fled to the roof! Get up there and kill him!
The chopper's here! Watch out for snipers when you're moving the loot!
You're not getting out of there unless you use a drill!
Have you got both boxes onto the helicopter?
The Brooklyn Bank has got something we need, and for once it isn't just cash!
I can't believe you destroyed my car!
Hey, I said we need more!
That laser alarm system will be a problem. Take it down.
These sons of bitches get nothing!
The employee lounge has a network router. If you patch me in, I can unlock the door.
That should'a been caustic soda!
The getaway just left without you. Sorry guys, you're gonna be spending some time behind bars.
Time for a nice, old fashioned cookout, for sure!
Blow a hole in the wall and get ready to run!
The cops will go all out to stop us here. Show 'em what we do.
Look for bookshelves, see if you can move them and find something.
You bet on the right spot! There's the vault!
The next step is to zipline up the elevator shaft. Shayu's people left tools for us in one of the vans. Find them.
Helicopter will have to bug out for a little while. If you're ready to go now, be on it.
Move it guys. Follow that gold.
Hey, Locky... this is going to be fun. You want popcorn? I'll get the popcorn and Sputniks.
Damn! I can't shake these pricks!
Don't insult my wheels, man!
Who are these fuckers!?
That's the first stash. Three to go!
Ha! Taking it back. This is our old loot, isn't it?
Here's the deal:
Raiders of the fuckin' wankers.
Sending you the lance in the elevator. Get ready for it, guys.
Our guest loves Ocean's Ten vodka. Find another blue bottle and spike it.
Grab the keychain friends.
Stop wasting time, yeah? You're risking the job!
Move it, guys. Find the locker room, and we find the armory.
Our intel says the USB drive's locked up in a cabinet.
19 bags!
Ok gang, you need to hack the console.
It's a trap! Out!
The presents are in that tree! Slap it! Slap the goddamn tree!
Come on, check those containers.
You can quit searching those cases - you found the bomb!
Guys, switchboards just lit up. Guess that's the alarm.
Good, now the next hack.
Hey! The cops are gonna stop the train further down the tracks, so you need to get the BCI tech and get the hell out of there!
Guys, patch into the radio. Let me speak to the Moretta.
Gang. Get that cutter onto the vault floor. Let's slice that thing open.
Check the camera feed so that you can locate Vlad. It should be upstairs.
Try another key!
Hold your ground until the helicopter arrives!
We're after his codes and the server. Make sure we go gentle on him. We can't loose him!
Ah, damn it. Close but now we got to rush it.
If you walk out of here alive, you're gonna get something real nice from that present!
Ernesto Sosa never saw it coming. With him dead, the Sosa's Miami operations lie in ruins. My point has been made.
Almost... there....
Ok, protect them now.
Kak! Some sloppy bastard forgot to refuel the chopper. Hook up the fuel, would you?
30 more seconds, then I'm out!
My money would be on the buildings having the keycards. Search 'em.
Arriving in four!
That's it, they're onto you. Guns loud, yeah?
The message has been delivered. The job is done, I thank you.
Hurry up and take all you can!
Hey, too bad you couldn't come. Was fun while it lasted anyway...
They're blasting the train doors with demo charges. They really don't want you guys in there!
Put the C4 in the main hall, right above the vault. Two possible spots, so it's a bit of a lottery. If need be, we'll blow them both!
How the blerrie hell should I know, you dwankie!
They got more snipers incoming!
You need to get through that door, friends.
Hey you guys really are the PAYDAY gang! Jesus!
The wheel stopped on the dozer again. Watch out guys!
When I get my hands on that bailout money, I'm going to Vegas to hit the ass and the blow. Like a fucking legend!
Holy shit, it's like a god damn warzone out here! I'm gonna stay here while you go around and do whatever you do. Find the parts and bring them back here.
Look outside the Jade Room, looks like a laptop.
We still need to find a blowtorch, gang.
Rotate L3!
I'll negotiate a deal with the cops, so we can get our friend back. You just sit tight.
You clowns ready? Hose is coming down.
Please don't shoot, don't shoot me please.
Are they cops? Are those fucking cops!?
I'm there in four...
Ok, I'm flying this sucker out!
Take control of the turntable!
Not that one! Let's start again.
Screw the winch down!
Sneak in, check the cameras to see the Feds working those thankless hours. Get the Mendoza info on the FBI server and get out. Go easy.
Not long now friends. Train will be there in half a minute.
Put the delivery in the car...
18 more needed!
We need approval from the security station. I would do it myself, but alas...
He's fucking asleep? Wake him up!
Don't let him get away!
Those poes fucked the detonator, mans. Fix it!

Things got messy, but you got through in the end. The hacks worked. It looks like the good lady Mayor's people was behind this. The press are already sharpening the knives for Schwartz. Needless to say, The Elephant is ecstatic. You have served your city well tonight, my friends.
One minute. Keep your eyes on the skies.
A little acid should go a long way on that workshop.
Hmm, nothing. I suppose it would have been too easy for us to find our prize here. It's probably still locked in the Evidence Room.
One minute for me.
The pick-up truck is here, you can throw the bags out the window if you wanna make a easy escape.
Don't shoot me please!
Everything OK so far?
One minute and we're through!
Guys I am serious. It is time to make our escape!
Is it too much to ask that you keep the cops away from the power?
They're dumping that coke like the mean it! Get up there and stop them!
Gang, it's time to bug. Get in the car!
Ok, that ramp needs to be lowered.
Time to make our escape. All aboard, friends!
Sure, why not? We might find use for it later.

Hey, Locky! Tell the guys that if they see that motherfucking noodle-sucking piece of shit that tried to kill me with the fucking car battery, I want them to cut off his fucking nose and bring it back!
Another gate blocking you. Get it open.

Alesso has promised a legendary gig. I'm promising we'll deliver a legendary heist.
You need to figure out which key goes with his car. This would really be easier if we could just take any car.
SWATs have stormed the building - watch yourselves.
There's a sniper covering the large alley, watch out!
C'mon friends, get onboard!
See that boat? That's your way out right there. Yeah, for sure. Get in.
Looks like the coast guard are sending in helicopter support. Can't risk taking the vault until you've cleared the air.
I think you're near one now.
Now check the screen for the code, then go and open the vault.
The pick-up truck is gonna be here in a few seconds.
Disable the alarm! It's counting down and things are gonna get real messy once it reaches 0.
Get that keycard into the panel and pull that switch. Let's see what happens.
Keycards - is there any game that don't have them?
Fucks sake. Assholes! Fucked it. Shape up, or I'm pullin' you out. By the short and curlies.
We still need to get that ship to the berth. Ummm... OK, I got it. Hack the ship control terminal. Keep the cops off it.
I can't wait to see what these shady assholes were hiding on that server.
Don't let me wait now!
The garage, friends!
OK, that's the tiara!
Now, blast that wall open! The explosion will trash the voting machines.
Here we are. Time to get back in business. Feels good, doesn't it?
I've set up the meeting location. You meet in an abandoned trainyard. Good luck.
You return fire and keep them off your position! I'll get you a God damn driver! OK!?
You trying to pull a fast one on us, huh?
For any questions pertaining to the changes in next weeks duty roster, please refer to form 47B-5A.
Time to juice up that plane. Get the fuel hose connected.
To business! There are crates near the entrance. Got a little red strobe on. Find them. They have a few little presents within.
Did you hear about the sniper? Ilija?

You know the secret to good barbecue? It's the meat. Don't skip on the meat. You can have the best sauce, best smoker, best goddamn chef's hat in the world, but if the meat ain't prime, the barbecue ain't worth a damn. Remember that.
Where he can't cause any trouble.
I messed up. It should'a been acid.
What is taking so much time?
Look inside before going in. Find the alarm box. When you open a door or window, it'll start, so you need to disable it fast.
What's the hold up, get moving before they move all the guns!
You're not who you say you are. I'm sounding the alarm!
Guys... Guys... Guys. We were supposed to get info... Not just cash. Hector's going to skin me alive.
Forget about the alarm, just get us in there ASAP, the cops are going to hammer us.
60 seconds to target. Over.
Ok, it's time to loot Ernesto's place. He's got a floor safe in his office. Hook those winches up to the floor and let's lift it.
CFO to the roof, ASAP!
That's the second stash. Two to go!
That's the last one, well done. I'll leave it up to you boys if you want to get more bags or pull out.
At least seven more.
Thank you. I'll get out of this yet.
... help! HELP!
And...voila!
OK, our pardons are locked in the vault. Have a closer look.
Next, we find the room whose vent connects with the security center. We can use that to knock out the guards with sleeping gas. So, we need blueprints. Check the archives.
I managed to get one of the employees onto our side. They willing to open the gates leading to the vault. Let me put them through.
Time to get onto the boat.
I might be in the business of taking, but don't say Vlad never gives back! It's christmas for fuck sake!
Look at this, I'm rich!
The asset has been accepted and payment is underway. Nice going.
Now stow those bags in the container on the floor. I'm sure I can find someone to collect it.
Come on, bring the key!
Okay, gang. The train yard is right in front of you. There should be several ways you can infiltrate the place, so make your choices wisely.
Ten left.
Now, get in there and see what you can find.
Ok, find Mitchell. He's our guy.
Listen, each path you create will only last a limited time. You can re-create the path - just make sure you aren't standing on one of the tiles.
Look around for entry ways that seem to stand out.
... never flew for anyone who had their shit as squared as you do.
You do realize, thermite is more or less standard equipment for us.
Hey, we don't have much time! I've got a boat on the way we're going to use as a pick-up. Just hustle ahead of those cops and get the bags secured.
You should find a pass phrase there. You'll need it when you call him.
Look for the guys packing the coke. Make sure these elves" know they're making toys for Santa fucking Christmas! Me! Okay?"
Right button! The right!
Well that's just 14 left.
We have to make sure SERA can't rebuild the Neo-2. Time to wreck some lab equipment.
Sorry, gang. You need to get more cash before leaving. Hold your breath and head back.
... it's fine, we'll settle for this.
That was outstanding! Whooooooo! Outstanding.
I have more guns than the Army. You wait and see.
Alright, I'm in. Give me a little time.
You got all of 'em? Ha!
Ignite the can and push that thing out of there towards the SWAT van!
That's one of the external hard drives.
I will bury you!
You can't escape by road 'cause of the army checkpoints, and you blocked most of the tracks with that pipeline. How you gonna pull this off?
We're doin' this shit for a fucking book?
Good day, my friends.
Kerels got to the terminal. You've got to restart the hack.
Almost got it all!
I hear the boss is pissed.
Cover me! They're tearing me to pieces!
Make sure you don't leave Charon behind!
Hold up!
You'll find the vault down in The Grin's Security Center. Head there.
Search the room! The evidence will be here somewhere!
Hope they respond as poorly as they usually do...
Assemble the fulton cage! We need it to carry those guns off the ranch. Don't keep me waiting, you dwankies!
Gang, you see those plates? I don't want to be greedy; or yes I do, actually. Why not stick around just a bit and try that printer out?
I'm here! I'm here!
The cops are right on top of us!
Ahhh, and another vault is ready to be plundered!
Get the hack restarted.
The cops have been bad this year. Someone should take their presents! Santa said so!
Sounds good to me.
Groot job with the code.
Blerrie! The Murkies have AA weapons outside the White House. You gotta take them offline so I can land.
Cops killed the lights - get it back on.
Where is it!?
I can't fucking lose 'em!
The plane is close. Mark the landing strip with flares.
Look out - they're putting tactical units in position nearby.
The Federales are using shape charges to open up another wall!
C'mon, get in the vault.
You know, my old grandmother used to hide Krugerrand behind the light fixtures....
Those suits will come in handy, later.
I will send in the necessary ingredients for you. Hold tight.
Hurry boys.
Try another one. See if you get it right this time.
Look, that must be that dwankie Kang! He's in the conference room!
Okay... I see more guards.
It looks like it's about to get busy in there.
Look everywhere you need to.. the lounge... library. You get the idea.
Damn right.
Caustic soda. Yes, that's it.
There's a police chopper incoming. You need to deal with it.
Kill these guys and bury 'em! Do it now!
Great! Now head to the terrace and place the fireworks.
Now listen: The police will have the entire site surrounded any minute. The clock is ticking! Take the canal route, quick!
Christ, we got cops!
We got a fucking police caravan on our ass!
Look over there. Little cop shits are stealing the money. The fuck is the world coming to! Kill them!
That's the last one. Tip toe back to the van, and we can consider this a job well done.
Thy Lord Locke giveth one commandment... find the right combination, yeah?
Chopper coming in.
OK. Find the bank manager.
SWAT's incoming from the right staircase.
Nothing left to do but make like a bush, yeah?
More mobsters on the way! Watch out for the vans.
Good, now set up the connection again.
Over here!
Almost there guys!
I got it. I didn't fuck up! I didn't fuck up.
Here it is! Take the bomb parts to the drop-off point!
Before we fuel up the getaway train, hook me to the railyard's PA system. I'll make an announcement to keep our work from looking suspicious.
We got what we need to get through the gate. Now, meet with the Insider.
Ok, here comes the ninth wave!
Faster, guys!
That goat's a trouble maker. He somehow turned on the power. Disable it at the power box.
Ach! Those guys are getting very close!
This one is very important to me. I'm here to make sure you don't screw it up, yes?
That's ten!
Two
Ok, I've got intel that mentions a hidden entrance to the PEOC near the library. Get over there ASAP.
OK that's the minimum amount we agreed on. I'll get the driver.
That invoice should point you to the right guard, so you can get the keycard.
You got the third stash. One more now!
We'll take what you have.
Stick to the plan! Load the plates onto our getaway train.
I would prefer it if you just left before anything goes wrong, but I understand if you wanna go back to get more of the loot.
Got it! I got the goats!
You need to help me here!
One minute. So close.
Double-time it, come on!
Three left.
OK guys, the pick-up driver is here! He's on the street behind you!
Police chatter has confirmed the presence of snipers. Keep your eyes on those rooftops!
Ach, another security failsafe. You're going to need to drill yourselves out.
Get to the archaeology room.
Nah, friend it's in the batter, yeah?
No, I'll tell you nothing!
Splendid, absolutely splendid! I confirmed the transaction of 25 million.
Those chains will have to come off somehow.
Hose needs to connect with pump now.
Shoot these fuckers!
Garrett's not going to be gone forever, so get to finding those boxes.
Perfect! Now, to mask the explosions, we need to time the concerts pyros. Get up to the booth and patch me in.

Wait...What the blerrie hell?! A freelance security team is en route to the parking lot! Must be an extra precaution for the event. We can't let these chops find evidence of your work, or they'll pull the alarm!
No more! There's no more room!
Make sure you protect the pump while it's running!
Searching the cases is pointless. You got the bomb, remember?
They keep samples of the rig's natural gas emissions for testing. Our man snagged us a canister. Hook it up to Gabriel's vent system.
Have you checked the back walls?
Don't smash the glass or the alarm will go off. Use a glass-cutter.
Looks like more guards are on the way, so stick some toothpicks in your eyes, yeah?
Port of Washington radio. This is Moretta. Standing by to receive GPS data. Over.
You don't think our time's important?
Great job gentlemen!
Okay, you're in! My intel says they keep the evidence on the second floor. Go find it!
Add some more paintings. A few more.
They're shooting at me!
Get to the bio-lab.
No-no-no-no-no!
That safe path won't last forever, gang. Make sure you make the most of it. You can create it again, though.
Do I need to remind you? Cocaine, worth a fortune, is being destroyed as we speak!
The gate should be open for you now.
The leak willl be in the basement. See Mitchell about it.
We got a fucking police caravan on our ass!
OK you're in, good. Now you need at least four paintings, the good ones have red stickers - those are the ones our art lover intends to buy.
Ach! If the kerels are here too, Garrett must be stepping up his game in helping Murky, to go all the way out here. Or he's just very pissed with us.
I gotta rush out of here!
An old... friend of mine in the FBI owed me a favor, so I got her to set up a laptop for us. She was going to hide its location on a whiteboard somewhere around there.
Our man is in position, and the target just turned on to McCarty. Almost there. Almost there...
The code should have a one at the beginning.
Our Insider can show you the way out. Find her.
You got the code wrong guys! System is locked for 30 seconds.
Now return to the terminal and give it a kickstart.
The end is upon us. And it is a good ending! Please, into the helicopter!
We'll act as simple drug dealers entering Chavez' crib, but once we're there we'll screw them over and go for his hidden panic room filled with cash.

The Harvest & Trustee is a vulnerable bank so I see an opportunity for us. Case it so you can find out where. You're going to need to get into the vault using a thermal drill, get whatever's in there bagged up and moved back to the escape car. Use your judgment and don't be greedy... Good luck, folks.
The Piggy Bank's at Stage 2! Now we're talking!
This tree is going to fly, my friends!
Forget about the main entrance. Put on your mask and cut through that fence instead.
I'll tell you what. We were never gonna deal with you guys! We'll take it all!
Right... got it. Go ahead and take the hard drive.
They're trying to take your money!
Don't shoot! I'll do anything! Daddyyyy!
Hey, that's awesome! I'm investing in Indian steel.
Oh I'm going with muriatic acid.
That's the ordnance, but it's not the turret. Get it out if you can, but keep looking.
Just don't try to escape on any floating doors. What? I saw it in a movie! That shit didn't work!
That's Xun Kang! There, in the conference room.
Ack, the crane shorted out! Repair the circuit box, fast! Those hooks won't hold forever!
OK money secured. Vlad will be buying the vodka I'm pretty sure and the police are gonna need some...
Guys, the first batch is unloaded - I'm coming back for more!
There you go, now just wait for it to open.
There should be a server with the voting results nearby. Locate the server and make the data unusable.
Think we got the right truck. Now go get it open.
What the hell, guys! You weren't supposed to kill them now! Wick wanted them alive so he could teach them a lesson... Let's hope he will be content with the thought of them dead.
That's one heavy-duty turret!
The bastards brought in a sniper! He's in the building across the street. Find some cover then take him out!
Funds have now been released into your account and we have received the asset. You got the upper hand on this one.
If we wanna get Hoxton back, we gotta follow the Dentist's plan. Step one: bust up the motel.
It's fine, we'll settle for this.
...Maybe someone forgot a keycard or something.
That's it. Now get the hell out of there!
Use the winch chain. Hook it up to the gate!
Alright. Let the driver know you're ready to move.
... I'm going as fast as I can!
Couldn't hurt to pick up some more things we can sell.
Just missed it. Try again.
We need to catch up with the Mendozas before they jet out of this country.
It's simplicity itself, friends. Just press the button of the vault you want to open. Just be sure it actually contains something.
Tac units on location.
OK, so this is an easy job to get accustomed to DC.
Once we are outside you will see our escape helicopter, as well as a large array of advanced radar equipment. State of the art. It could track us anywhere west of the Rockies.
Now get that gasoline on a car and torch it!
Maaan, this guy just can't stop talking. I'll kill him first.
Ok, we got that done. That was a lucrative asset, yeah?
The white thing floating in the sky? Got it! Two minutes, tops!
I'm afraid you've lost me.
Cops on the street...
Hey, that's a Franz-Jaeger Safe. This is unexpected. Well, only one way to crack it with the time we got. Water pressure!
... I'm coming back soon!
Good going, team. Time to move out.
Nothing I like seeing more than cheap foreign cars going up in smoke.
Move that car so we can get the hell out of here.
Green light means you need to cut it.
Guys, you need to attach the magnet on top of the panic room.
There's still a goat in the scaffold.
First World Bank, can I help you? Yes sir, we offer a full range of financial services. No sir, not that kind of fine" and definitely not that kind of service! Good day!"
Defend the drill. Should be through in a couple of minutes.
Find some, and pour it in.
Only 30 seconds left and I'm there!
They got a tracker on us or something!
Okay, I think the worst is behind us. Vlad's driver got the goats to a farm outside the city, ready to perform the extraction of the packages. Stick around. Watch the perimeter. Easy work, right?
Take a look inside the RFID box. You'll be able to see which colored wire we need to find.

OK, the thermal drill you need for the vault is somewhere in the parking lot. Get it before you do your takedown. Then you can go hit that vault. Watch for cameras and bank employees. Do your homework before you go in and remember cash is king.
Better do what he says.
That's two.
Heads up, they're deploying tactical squads on a nearby roof top.
Hey, fuck you.. you piece of shit.
There's a job at Mercy Hostpital. Not our usual stuff. Could be interesting.
Well, not like it's going to make this van go any slower! It helps me concentrate, right?
There's no way you're hauling those out on your backs. Hold on, I'm going to find you a transport.
A smart decision.
Chopper'll be here soon... Hang in there.
Do as you're told, goddamn it! I can shut down every airport for a thousand miles and have you ditched in the ocean, you spineless turd. Over.
That console panel should control all the cameras. Give it a go and see if you can find the computer we're after.
There goes the block. FBI SWAT is going to be here in a minute. Get in!
Let's head out! Jump on the train!
Hurry up! Connect to the IT grid!
We've dealt with RFID boxes before. If you check inside, you'll see which colored wire we need to cut outside of the wagon. You know, blablabla.
There's no time to waste! Get that vault door open!
Alright! The boat should be coming in soon!
Pilot just touched down with the cash. Well done guys and nice work on the cage. See you at the safe house.
The symbols. There's a correct order to them.
Better get that drill running again!
We could've used that guy on the retinal scanner. Nevermind. It's Plan B time.
One in place.
Shit! Po-po's here!
Dragon's buffet, how can I help you?
Snipers! on the roof.
This is Bronson, your getaway driver! What do you need?
OK, we're off. Tiara goes to Vlad and he'll get the revenge he wanted. I'm glad we could accommodate him. See you at the safe house.
Like... a glove.
These slot machines are networked. Hacking them would work. Find the control room.
There! It's just after the underpass!
Throw it into the truck, we'll deal with it later!
It's easy. Just choose a vault, and press the button. That will start the timelock, and the vault will open. Abracadabra!
You got it. The Diamond. The goddamn Diamond.
What's up guys? Find those routers!
Great, now get into the vault.
Good job! Our driver's on his way to pick up the guns.
That's close enough! I'll get it!
Don't want to get stuck in there with Garrett, so make sure you don't lose him.
There's a garbage truck waiting in the basement garage. Get down there and stash the loot there, quick!
Remind those elves what Christmas is really about. The production of narcotics at the point of a gun!
OK, let's have a look...
Now if you want to keep breaking stuff, Vlad's handing out a bonus for additional damages.
That's it, gang!
I'm there in 2.
I am pleased with this outcome.
There's a shipping manifest in the admin office that'll tell us which train has the plates. Use your drill to get inside.
That would look lekker in Duke's corner, for sure! Maybe you should take it!
Consider it done.
Bad news, guys!
Commissar is throwing everything he has left! Even his damned gunship! Keep your distance!
There you go, that's it! Now go inside.
The Warthog's here! Take him out for some extra Piggy Bucks!
We almost tasted that cigar!
That's it! I'm off now!
Dmitri, motherless son of whore who framed me, is getting married. His bride preparing for wedding. Oh! Big perfectionist! Hoh!
Probably can cut through fences...
A beautiful sight, yeah? Never thought I'd be that pleased to see a bunch of papers!
Get rid of that gas, friends.

With the turntable locked down, the railyard's cargo crane is our best shot for moving the locomotive to an open track. Head for the controls, and let's hope this is a so crazy it just might work" situation.                                                                                                                 "
Man, I can't believe you are back for more! All that gold. Well Bain's inside, go on in.
What's wrong with you chops? Too much to drink last night? Get moving!
The traitor will be in the panic room, so you have to find it. Then we can work on getting it open.
Light another flare to bring the chopper back, gang.
Their case against us probably won't recover from the amount of evidence we've stolen, but you're free to steal more.
Shayu! Watch your tongue.
Remember, you in civvie mode. That means no guns or masks. You're invisibles. Micho, our Inside Man here, left a guitar case with your gear somewhere.
OK, Hector wants us to record this so first set up the camera.
We can't proceed until you have the keycard.
30 thousand guys, keep it up!
Just dodging a sparrow, almost there!
Come on, you need to hustle it!
Hearing police signals. Someone must've called 'em. Stay alert.
Well....I guess that makes sense. I may do that too.
OK, OK! Plan B - find the server room. Shit!
If you want more room to maneuver, move the van out of the way.
The old drunk is on the ground again. Get him to his feet.
And another one.
Alright, now let's get out of here. Leave the PEOC!
Go to the tech store and find the VR headset. There coke should be there.
What you got there? You know what, I really don't care. Just throw it in the truck and I'll take it with me as I drive off.
Get to the computer so we can code the tag for access.
We're keeping this. Sorry...
Nooo!
And pop goes the Piggy Bank!
Office parties all over the capitol will be duller affairs if Uncle Vlad can't supply the Christmas cheer". You can help."
Diesel is now filling in ship.
These sons of bitches get nothing!

So, might any individual in this here room at present, be able to present to me, a constitutional provision regarding treasonous acts against the United States? Anyone? Well, Section 3, article 3 of the Constitution provides Treason against the United States
column3: shall consist only in levying war against them
column4: or in adhering to their enemies
column5: giving them aid and comfort. No person shall be convicted of Treason unless on the Testimony of two Witnesses to the same overt Act
column6: or on...?....on...? Would anyone care to finish? Anyone?... Bueller?"

String: To set it up we'll need some diesel fuel, fertilizer, wire and a timer. Look around if there's anything like that around there.
Friends, get the chain from the truck and attach it to the teller window!
Start the winch and it will move BFD into position. Don't let the cops stop it!
Here's the deal:
Just follow it all the way along. The poop pipe deposits into the Gulf.
Keep your eyes on the roofs! Got a bad feeling creeping up.
I need all y'all assholes on point tonight! Especially you up in the booth.
OK the vault's open!
Halfway mark. Hurry up!
Go down to the basement door in the back alley!
That was an excellent piece of whisper-work. They didn't know you were there. Now let's see where that truck leads us.
That crash in the roof you just heard was your C4. Get it and blow that vault!
OK, there's a clear entrance behind the shrine but we'll need to blow it open.
I'll need to find someplace where I can hide it.
They're on us like fucking flies on a turd!
What's that goddamn tanker doing here? We're not logged on its itinerary.
Still need to get that safe open. Use the print.
They got to the power line. Reset the breaker switch!
They're on us like fucking flies on a turd!
Don't forget the cooler!
Shit, the timelock has paused. Must be your ECM jammer that's making it go ape! Better holster those jammers.
They got to the computer. Reboot the hacking routine.
Boom! That's how it's done. I hope the CIA were taking notes. Now book it.
The pilot has noticed the signal, and the helicopter is on its way. Stay sharp until it's here.
Over here!
Low profile... You're doing well.
There it is. The McKendrick museum. Somewhere in there is a priceless diamond. Let's get it.
Arriving in two...
Comm systems just went haywire. Cops incoming.
Okay, same as before: secure as many bags as you can or leave this place. Make up your mind!
You need to bring that thermal drill into the vault room, yeah?
We've learned that most of the time, you can find Buluc in his office brooding over something, so it's a good place to look for him. Find it, yeah?
Alright. First goal - get inside. Front door's right ahead, but maybe show a little guile and look for other ways in.
This is the one! Let's go!
I'm out of here, two minutes!
Gang, there's got to be something in the motelrooms that can pinpoint the Commissar's location. Keep looking.
Find the power box! It's gotta be around here somewhere!
Cos it was like that, from the moment we woke. All day, every day - hookers and blow.
Why does it feel like I shouldn't be here right now?
It might be a good idea to look around before you go loud. Find your best approach.
Get to the warehouse, friends. Chop-chop.
Security is so tight here, only one gate can be open. Bunch yourselves together so the next one can open and no one is left behind.
If you're feeling rough, maybe spend a keycard and crack the Infirmary open.
Great, you now need to empty the nitro into the vault door.
You gotta restart the hack!
That's enough coke, not all, but enough. Hector's people are at the harbor - you need to meet them and get this stuff onto their boat. Then call it a day... OK, a payday.
Okay. Banking for another drop. 30 seconds!
Ey man, the deal ain't here. Turn around, this place is ours.
I'm coming in.
We can't get in without a keycard. We need to find one.
You heard Vlad. Get those bags into the chimney.
That's the head of security. Hmm... looks like he's at the back of the house.
My brother-in-law is on his way. He will drop a skyhook cage for you.
Picked up a tail!
That's it, router boxes taken care of.
We can't have this place on fire - it's the pyro booth. Put it out!
There's one!
The cops got to the Saw. Restart it ASAP.
Body is in place so start scanning, gang.
You need to get all the winch parts, friends.
All research on the Neo-2 is stored in this room. Find what we need and clear it out.
More than we agreed on, huh? How nice of you!
When you have enough bags, let the balloon go, and stand back.
The safe, friends. Use the print.
There will likely be wiring boxes there somewhere.
You better hurry up and fix that leakage
They heard the drill! The alarm's been triggered!
Tank's dry. Going to refill.
What the fuck is this!?
Don't forget to check the interrogation rooms. He might be in there.
Second color and number? Great!
That's him! Get him to the top of the tower!
So that's the penthouse up there. The view must be astonishing! Snap some pictures when you get up there, will ya?
Those shells have an angry temper. And a dollar value. Be careful with them.
The target is spotted. Just need to get you into position and...
Kill 'em!
And done, nice.
... Ey you're wasting our time!
You need to free all the hostages.
There we go. It's ringing.
I told you guys to be ready!
What!? The Mendoza cartel is still there! Take care of them!
OK, the drill is on the ground. Get it and get those vaults open.
This stuff makes great bombs...
Alright we need at least seven more.
Still gotta get your hands on the card.
Hey, I'm here... outside... not far from the street! Piece of shit car!
That's how we do it! Good job, guys. Get inside the mill now.
I got some horrible news, people!
Oh shiiiiiit!
Find the truck leaving for the mall. Slap the GPS on it and slip away. We'll ambush the truck later, I promise.
Drill's done its work. Get in that basement!
Looks like a good place to check for clues.
Got it! I'll do a background check on this guy. Hang on.
Farewell dear friends, we'll not meet again I think!
I'm like God damn Mother Teresa here.
Aw, fuck me sideways!
Well you didn't get any of the money but the important part is done. The art was delivered and the senator can look at his paintings in peace... For a little while.
Put all the stuff in the car!
Looks like we've got an RFID box on the vault. Check inside for the colored wires we need to find, and when that's cut, you can deactivate the lock.
I saw a conveyor chute over there. Throw the loot in, and it'll shift it to the lobby.
You have ten seconds to get to the van.
We need to get into the storage room.
Damn fine job! Now, start the engine so we can make our escape!
Answer that phone, or a guard might come poking around!
I'm here. And so's your box. Where's the goddamn money.
I know an IT dwankie when I see one, even in Mexico. Take that man to the server room and make him open up the security bars.
