We're not getting any presents? What is this, my goddamn childhood?!
The krels cut the power to the IT room! Get the lights back on and restart the hack!
Hvala.
Piggy's at Stage 1. Let's go higher!
The medic bag is in the bathroom.
Oh my god! You guys are kicking ass and taking names, Jesus!

Hello. My name is Locke. I lead a cyber task force organized by Murkywater. Due to your many attacks on our interests, we've been mandated to infiltrate your Crime.net, and destroy you. As you can no doubt ascertain, the infiltration part has been achieved. However, rather than bringing you down, which I could do with the press of this button, I come with a proposal. How would you like to work with me? I can supply you with intelligence, opportunities and materiel regarding Murkywater. Further, I can keep you hidden from the attentions of my co-workers. So...what do you say?
One perp apprehended, over.
You could probably get some good covering fire going from one of those roof tops.
Or maybe don't do that, yeah?
A can of fuel would set that ablaze rather nicely!
OK, friends. It's time to rescue Bain.
No cop could have seen this one coming. Perfect. The Russians are going to be pissed and Vlad will OD on vodka. After we get paid.
They have me pinned down - I can't get the door open!
Let's drain this oil rig dry! Deploy the transfer hose.
The roadblock worked and two transports have stopped. Get to work, and get 'em open!
That'll keep nosy bastards from spying on our business. Good.
That's a good amount of bling. But if you want to grab some more, you can.
Recon the bank. My guy dropped a thermal lance somewhere on the premises... Around the back of the bank, find it.
Ingredients have arrived. Going to take more than one load though. Keep throwing them in.
What's taking so long?
Ahhhh, the meth is done, but we can't get it out as it is. Need to break it down. Get smashing, gang!
Wait. What? Really? Our schedule says... God damn it, y'know, someone screwed up this schedule. Anyway, yeah, everything is fine here. Thanks for being so diligent.
Make sure to floss.
Damn, looks like the cops had been staking the place. Move it!
We got roadblocks on the perimeter, and cops closing the net. No way out by the road. Time for a new plan.
Are you drunk? It's ok, I won't tell the boss.
Good. Now, drop the charges at the main door over there.
You need to get that Jewelry box!
Have you tried Robert's?
Yeah I know the way.
That has to be the way into the PEOC. Get into the airlock.
Mercy Hospital, what do you want?
You have to wonder what a man thinks about when his genitals are being swallowed by a fish.
Cops tailed you... Shit! When we get out of this I'm taking care of the wheelman myself. Get ready folks...
Hell yeah. This intel should lead me straight to Esteban's employer, and they'll get what's coming to 'em. Nice work. I owe you one.
Now, we need to set the trap. More gasoline in container 12.
Blerrie, there's probably rats in the walls...
Harvest & Trustee. My contacts says it's juicy as hell. In and out. You with me?
Perfect, that's all of them.
Remember: blood poisoning and abnormal heart rate. Listen to Schneider.
Hey guys.. uuh... it seems we can't get into Sosa's office this way. It's on a separate system.
So destroying his art collection didn't hurt enough. Let's try something else then.
Now light up those tires. Get the gas on them. That'll deal with the chopper.
Find Garrett's safe, friends.
Gang, the Commissar - that grudging bastard - is dumping a fortune in cocaine just in spite! Get up there and save it. The faster you move, the more you can save!
You've seen that model before. Hard to break.
Now grab the hose and pull it down to the safe.
That's it! I'm off now!
What the hell happened to this guy?! Whatever, we need this guys hand.
C'mon friends, get out of there.
Still need to find that phone number, yeah?
... Put the stuff in the car!
Find the prison transports.
Remember, you need to find a blank key tag.
Come on, guys. Get the plans scanned and faxed. Do it in IT.
Everyone in the bird!
Keep the elevator under watch, guys.
Your ride is ready friends, get onboard!
Ah, they've gone and messed up your cocktail. You gotta mix up a new one, friends.
You will die for this!
Fly you fools!
Deal's off!
Grab the oh-shit handles!
What the hell! That crazy chopper is back.
Goddammit - they locked you out! Find a way around!
Some cash, look at it as a welcome gift to get you started. I expect you will pull in much more.
Alright, time for me to dash!
Excellent. Time to put it to the test.
Chopper is back and waiting for more bags!
He's coming in at dock 8, in front of the warehouse.
Try caustic soda... Or hydrogen... No no, wait, soda... Go for that. Yeah.
Yeah, listen. We can't have any screwups. The boss is nervous about security.
Nice. Now get that evidence to the lab. Any DNA might help us finger this rat.
Garrett is back in his office. We need to keep him out of there!
Nicely done!
There's the main gate. Could be watched. Maybe find another way in?
So you go in and you will find his safe and other moneys. He will have lots. He does not trust banks and he trusts only Russians. Go in party - and go out and party!
Sail out of the blast zone!
Look around for the laptop. You'll probably find it in Esteban's office.
Come on lads, get all close and cozy.
Alright, go ahead Chief. HEY, watch it!!
It's like a never-ending number of screws, yeah? But you got to get them all off.
Not a fucking word.
Enter the room right above the vault and pour out the thermite.
Any second...
Come on, chops! Get blowtorching!
It's open! Let's see what we got!
Here! Here!
We ain't got all night boys, hurry up.
Good, you found the drive. Get to the admin office, and I'll add our ship to the transfer schedule.
No code? Maybe look a little more.
Closing in!
Blerrie, there is a firewall blocking me on the network. Check the other computers and see if you can disable it.
Get onboard friends. Bile has to leave.
The chopper's coming to the lumber yard - be ready!
OK, now look around. We need to tag the truck headed for Washington. Look around for clues. Containers, terminals, any records. Find the right one, and tag it.
Sanchez, where the fuck is Ral? Someone is shooting up the place.
Dammit. Now we go the painful way.
What the hell! Keep 'em off of me!
Don't believe Duke's superstitions... get to the archaeology lab.
Get that weapon charged, friends.
Those lights... gotta mean something.
Completely understandable. Maybe if the opportunity presents itself, the guys'll take care of it.
Units converging on your position from all directions. Cops, SWAT, Feds and - hell! Even the National Guard are on they way. We need to find another way out.
Chopper's headed for the lumber yard - be there!
Drinks on me, that was a classic hit.
Reception will have the guest list, guys. Just head there, download it.
That crane was made to lift cargo crates, not escape trains. You'll have to secure the hooks manually.
... well shit, that's a first I suppose.
Hey! Hurry up, will ya!?
Just let them go quietly.
OK, that's got to be Deng. What kind of laanie kek would do that to his teeth? Find the safe in his private massage chamber and get the code.
You come here to disrespect us!?
Hey, pendejos! I fucked your mothers! All of them!
There you go, that's the vault.
Go lay down the water hose, move it!
Saw that one gun down a village in Uganda. Good man.
That Piggy Bank is maxed out!
Been hearing rumors from my contacts in the Golden Dagger.
Hack the turntable controls!
Damnit, you just alerted everyone that you're here. Fantastic.
Head in the game, guys. Look for the closets marked with the X.
Alright, one more minute til the time lock opens the vault.
It'll take some time, lots of data to up and a small pipe.
Good afternoon, Director Stevens.
Cool, break through the gates. You need a crowbar!
Run that sample through the testing lab.
The van is right around the corner.
All right, system has been hacked.
Money secured, the police got a taste of what we can do and Vlad will definitely be spinning that to his advantage. Nice.
Hey, we don't have all day aight?
That looks like it might be the server room. Better save it for after you find the cash. Remember where it is.
That's a lot of stones.
Ready for a nice surprise, courtesy of old Locke?
You have more, no? This is not enough.
The intel I need is on Esteban's personal laptop. My contact says he keeps it in his office at the ranch house. Use the gate to the right.
Looks like that shape charge got the best of some of the loot. Get the rest!
Enjoy that XP. The Piggy provides!
Don't shoot down the big helicopter that's coming in for the money, okay? That's me. Yeah, for sure.
That kak woulda sold his mother for a dollar.
Last thing we need to do is wreck the laboratory. SERA can't be allowed to rebuild the prototype.
Don't let the coke burn!
That's one of the keycards for the vault, but you need another. Keep looking.
They're putting a sniper team in play, watch out.
There you go. Now take a look inside the vault room, yeah?
Make sure the artifacts are stowed aboard the helicopter, friends.
They're attacking me! I'm a sitting duck here!
Work your way up to street level, I have a van ready to get you guys out of there!
Be careful going in...
You'll PAY for this!
Don't worry, no one will hear you back here. But keep it down to be safe...
You're at 20 thousand! Keep on going!
Son of a bitch!
That's a Royal Flush, gang. Every God damn truck is ready for the picking. Get to work!
There are clearly things missing. You probably need to find them to open the door. Have a look around.
Ah, we should have sneaked this. Tons of gold in this deal.
It's searching now. Christ, wish they spent as much on their servers as they do on their doors. Don't let anyone see.
Having problems with the pallet jack?
Don't get stuck anywhere, keep moving up! It'll be worth it, but it's wasting away quickly!
Get to the garage and call that elevator.
Those old sewers are a maze. Keep looking for the light, guys. Ignore the stench.
...what's the worst that could happen, right?
Chopper is here. Stow any bags. You can ride out now, or you can stay and find more coke. Your decision.
Loot's ours. One thing I like about bank jobs is the instant gratification. Good work.
Hiding them behind those crates should be good enough. Don't forget a body bag for the other guy.
That's the list. Now get back to IT and upload it from an online terminal.
Got it! Now get back to the vault and enter the code.
Yeah. For sure.
Activate the transfer crane!
Get them off me!
Get out of the crates. Hit 'em with surprise.
Looks like Matt's vehicle has crashed. Go check if he's alive!
You better enjoy your life while you got any left!
I tell you, Vlad will never like this hacking shit. Seems cowardly. When you want information or to get inside somewhere, you just need a good baseball bat.
Is my dad there? Mr Hunt. First name (disconnects)
Police breaching their way down. Heads up!
Shit! These bastards have anti-air defenses set up! Bile, turn the plane around immediately! Guys, use the parachutes and get out! We'll figure something out!
It's not like we um, can't get more.... riiiight?
Here we go. We should be through in a couple of minutes.
Alright...
I promise you will pay for this!
Cops are on their way. Looks like they had a lot of guys in the neighborhood.
Oh, fuck me sideways!
C'mon guys, find that safe.
OK, we're loaded up!
Good shooting! Okay then. The coke should be in that safe so get drillin'.
If there's dirt to be found on Rainey, our best bet is to check the offices on the second floor. Voicemails, emails, there's got to be something.
What the FUCK!?
You just keep it up.
Locke sold the Butcher out too. The ship by the dock is one of hers. Go help 'em out and maybe we can hitch a boat-ride.
Alright, now find the control panel to charge the weapon.
Construction site - cops coming in.
If he's not going to stick his head out, we'll have to draw him out. Start destroying his things and see if that makes him mad enough to come out and fight.
Turns out today's the day where they stockpile cash for armored truck transport to casino runs out of town. Let's roll the dice.
Look outside the Tiffany Room. I can see a laptop display in the security feed.

Friends, let's get to this, chop-chop. Find the compounds server room and access the camera feed to find the container they've got Vlad in. If you can match it up to the right company with a shipping manifest in the control room, we'll know where to go.
Don't go letting the cops mess with the elves.
These guys can drive!
We need something to help light this up!
19... 20... 21... All that money and Garnet is too cheap to pay for a faster window washing rig! Ok that's it, 22nd floor and... go.
You need to draw some blood from the patient.
The incoming group has Minigun Dozers!
OK, friends. You just get to it and old Locke will have you cooking in no time, for sure!
Hmm, the entrance looks secured. I suggest you try to find another way in.
The hack has been cut off. Get it up and running again.
You will need to find the key to that gate. See if you can find it.
Step it up! The escape vehicle is leaving in four minutes.
That's both crates found, yeah? Good! Time to get the hell out of there. Make your way back to the entrance so I can arrange your extraction.
Ah, its stuck. Can't get to it. Shoot the wires!
That cannon's not going to fire without some juice.
Carry the box back to the skylight where you entered, yeah?
Grab the raw materials and get them in the house.
Stay on the lot, guys. We want to keep this quiet.
Remember, we need eight bags!
That hard drive is encrypted, but it can be bypassed if you find the encryption protocol. It should be on Wang's laptop. Otherwise, we'll have to spend months decrypting it.
Don't worry, it will be fine. Ah! Here he comes!
Police coming in hot. 30 seconds.
Pronto people.
Make space for the escape van - get those police cars out of the way!
Right, here goes... Wuh duh ma huh tah duh fong kwong duh wai shung!
Nice! Dock is opening. Next step: get the Moretta moving to her berth. I need to talk to her directly. Find me the comm frequency - most likely on a computer in the offices there. Find it.
Holy... that was close! These Russians really don't want anyone to crash their party.
Prepare to get fucked up!
The gang that stole the Diamond. Outstanding, gang!
Have you checked all the rooms in the maintenance tunnels?
Find Esteban's office. That's where the laptop should be.
Really great so far.
Hey, maybe I take this house when you guys are done, yes?
Come on, ya blerrie pyro! Quit staring at the fire and get on the ship!
It's a dirty job, but if it means we stay in a job...
Run! Run!
Management Office, they always have portable computers.
That's typical. You should have a look in the clubhouse in case these dwankies have left a way to access the code somewhere. Start with the briefing room.
Can't drop the equipment until you arrange the smoke!
Deploy the transfer hose by activating that crane.
You just headbutted the motherfucking hornets' nest!
There oughta be a cargo manifest on one of those computers in here...
Get the bags here, quick!
Get that briefcase, guys!
15 bags!
Let's skip the formalities.
Pilot's gone down. Don't let him pass out. Get him moving!
We're ready to nab those weapon prototypes. Look around the barns, take as many as you can find.
That will have to do. There's a skid loader nearby being driven by Jiu Feng's man. Help Vlad get into the bucket.
Ok, make sure the codebreaker doesn't stall, they got a pretty secure system here. Guess you just can't be too careful these days.
Load it in!
They're the keys for the doors inside the vault. Good find.
We should have used caustic soda!
We need that server out of commission!
It's go time! Fire up the drill!
Sweet, you guys got it down - now go for the loot inside the safe!
That's enough for the fifth floor. Good job.
Every bullet is special, but your bullets are the special-est!
Son of a bitch!
I'm here!
Here!
There's one of 'em!
Can I ask if you are having a good day, sir?
Great, the scanning is up and running again.
Make them think it's break time or something?
You sure you wanna be greedy now?
Four minutes left, guys.
Those warheads are damned heavy. Use the forklifts to shift them.
If you get the chance, maybe grab some loot that might be useful to sell. It's not every day you got free reign in the FBI's evidence lockup!
Have a look in the cellar yet?
When you feel ready, go ahead and make your way out.
The domkops are trying to get off cheapsies with that offer, yeah? We can get more if we just don't give up.
... you gotta take 'em out! They're killing me!
You need to hack the control room door.
I watch man eat human shit in Attica. He look just like you. Wait, can it be..?
They're shooting at our tires!
OK, let's do this again. Here's hoping.
You need to secure all the loot with the zipline.
You kept them away. Good stuff! They aren't backing though, so get ready for more of them.
Keep the police away from the drill.
I'll tell you what. We were never gonna deal with you guys! We'll take it all!
Hello my friends - I have small favor to ask of you...
Don't let up! Find them and kill them!
OK, shit just got real. Run for the server guys. Rip it out of there.
One of Buluc's old girlfriends volunteered" information after we threw some cash her way
column3: that you can find the way to open this door in a part of the house that Buluc calls the "inner sanctum". Go find the entrance to it

String: Gonna buy you a one-way ticket to Deadville!
Remember the plan. Get the keycards, keep the civilians in check and set off no alarms.
Open the safe and check inside!
... then you get what you came here for.
Garrett's office, yeah?
Look at that beauty. It's called The Beast. Now start it up.
This panel was marked on that blueprint you snagged from the SERA office. Very interesting.
Someone pressed the alarm button.
Search the arena for the supply closets marked with a red X. That's where the C4 is.
Now, everyone to the chopper! Come on!
Hay personas sin autorizacin en la armera!
Got a line on that road. That's where your cage will be!
The drill is on the way, just wait for it.
The cops are pissed that you just bagged their snipers. They're getting ready to send in the cavalry!
Remember guys, we need eight bags to escape.
OK, get him outta there.
Kwaai kwaai. Now secondly there should be a security station nearby. Head there and approve the opening.
Make sure that happens. If not, I have been told you are good at improvising.
I'll ask my main man Chavez to fetch you guys' shipment. You guys hang around.
You have thirty seconds to get this shit done.
The wheel stopped on flames. Things are about to burn!
Get the fuck outta here!
Shayu's guys are waiting for the drive. Send it down the dumbwaiter.
I've lowered the winch, but I need you to attach the magnet.
Don't look now, but...
They're on us like fucking flies on a turd!
Bain, old time river here has been talking so I didn't quite catch that, but let's go.
Oh, this is gonna be fan-fucking-tastic! Get me the next part!
You need to get into the security camera feed to find our kidnapped Ukrainian friend.
All right, that's the last of the C4. Get down to the garage. Our Inside Man has marked the spot you need to blow.
The way is blocked. You gotta find the controls to the walkway and extend it!
Keep a low profile near the workers to be safe.
Come on! Get the coke out of the truck!
Now get to cutting that gate.
Okay, you're good to go. Start the hack.
Or what?! Are you two gonna make an old man wait for the next one?
Two minutes until the customer is on the scene.
From what we know, Kang usually stays near the casino.
Anything could be on that server. Maybe the President's email address.
Almost... done...
I trust you have had a vacation worthy of real heisters. You worked hard, you needed it, but you are needed once again.
Second digit for the vault. Just the last to find.
I'd help but the car gets lonely without me.
That's all the C4 we need.
Pick your loadout already! I want to find that Piggy Bank!
The coast guard is sending in air support. You've got to take care of them before we can pull out the vault.
Here we go. Tax money put to good use.
Just keep hacking those machines. The more shit we fling at Schwartz, the more will stick.
Comm chatter is getting real busy, you gotta go. Now.
Get our investment back and switch the machines.
Friends, was that C4 I saw you pass before? Maybe use it to open a faster way out of there.
Hurry, go go go!
Hey guys, there's nothing left. Get out of there!
It's working! Shoot him while he's on fire!
I fuckin' hate hospitals, man. I ever turn into a vegetable, you guys end my ass.
How are those drills coming?
Hurry and open the gate!
Great, guys! Now you can grab some more loot or take the escape, the choice is yours.
You gotta get those police cars out of the way so the escape van can move in!
All right, I made the deal. Un-cuff the hostage so we can get our teammate back.
Take these sons of bitches out!
Automated security has locked out the key. You've got to drill it.
Well, turns out the FBI are escorting the Mendozas out of the country. Maybe they have a deal, maybe they don't. Frankly I don't give a crap whether they're renditioning them or whatever.
Get that bastard!
Nothing yet? Keep looking.
Just press the button. You can understand that, yeah?
No. Uh, just give me a second...
Good. Now search the coke bags.
...Kerels right around the corner, friends.
Haven't spotted you yet... Still good.
Ok, that should do it. Now start the computer again.
... over-delivering! Way to go! Hector likes that shit!
You need to get past that keypad. Check the main building for something that matches.
Get some cross fire going!
Meet our new Cuff Cloakers, I'm sure you'll love 'em...
I can't pull you out of there until you've got through that floor, friends.
There's a conference room in the casino where Xun Kang spends a lot of time.
Find the room that controls those bollards. Gotta be here somewhere. Check the doors.
Uh don't please!
Alright you chops, go and find his office!
We got a bollocks-load of clearance now. Get back here. Still work to do.
Follow Bile so he can pick you up in a safer spot! Don't forget Roscoe!
Good, Jiu Feng's insider put this equipment right where he was supposed to. Seems like a reliable chop.
Clock's ticking - just move it along, we don't have all day.
Not bad, wanker. Not bad.
What, he knows my brother-in-law?
Lucky for us, someone in the Mendoza cartel gave up info that they're being investigated by the FBI. So all we need to do is hit the local FBI office handling the cartel to get the data.
Hey, we're not done yet.
Gang, cops have set up a three block perimeter. The hard way through is the only way, so you're boots on the ground. Stay with the truck, and the truck will stay with you.
Get me the bags!
Have a look in the computer. See what turns up, yeah?
It's as if you think I've never been threatened.
Look around. There should be clues that will point you to the right truck. Perhaps matching their color to the containers.
Cops are en route. Move faster!
You guys can take a smoke break, or grab a coffee. I'll be here for a while.
Boris is on his way. Isn't that right, Boris?
Three.
Now! Hit these bastards!
Snipers deployed, keep your heads down!
You need to find the code that is currently being used, friends.
Fuck! No!
Golden Grin, or bust!
Imagine whatever you gotta imagine to hold these pricks off!
They're here!
Here's Johnny!
Vaya con Dios, dickhead.
Keep going forward!
Connecting...
Ah kak, they know we're trying to fuck off. They're going all in! Hold steady, friends!
Every second counts friends.
Damn it, Dallas! You've been spotted!

Well I've been through the intel and this is gonna be interesting. Check out the assets. Get to know them inside out, upside down. We need to sneak in to find the guy's lab, and in the lab, his fusion engine.
Uh, sorry, this is my first day, what do you need?
On the scene! Bring me the goats!
You're running out of time! Get off the platform!
Use the zipline to secure the bags.
The storage room is blocked off with sturdy metal doors, yeah? If you find and tap me into the security boxes, I can unlock them from here.
Well, you did lose some of the coke but you finished the job, so good on you! We'll get our payday yet, just put some ice in the back of your head in the meantime.
Aaaargh!
That's the right panel. Now search for the other keycard. Get the other panel activated.
Get to one of Wang's stashes and grab up the gold. Not to shabby of a payment.
I gotta keep moving!
Cold fusion energy may be the next big thing for my clients. Unfortunately, they do not own the most promising prototype - yet.
Had a whole standoff just to steal a bike! Fucking classic!
Ten seconds.
Come on, get the bags!
There. Our intel was right, he's inside a shipping container.
Nope... This isn't working either. Get me another one, I'll be there in a sec.
It will open in a second or two. And then...
Remember we need both the Taxman and the server, people. Scare him and make him go into the limo once we've confirmed that he has the server on him.
The police is on our back like a fucking pony tail!
Whoa! Look at this place! Imagine all the loot we can boost from here!
Nice, it's full!
Don't think about it. Treat it like any other job.
I see one!
Dig in somewhere good!
The White House IT dwankies aren't as dumb as I thought. There is a firewall blocking me. Touch.
Ach, Jiu Feng didn't mention the vault being that solid. You'll have to drill it. I've got someone ready to deliver one outside, will only take a jiffy!
This is Bronson, what do you need?
You need to find where the camera footage is kept. Move it, guys.
Good. Temperature is climbing faster. Must be something hot in there.
There's the ladder, guys. Get up there!
That's the alarm, hurry inside so we can get that server.
So, here's some good news and bad news. Bad news is my car died. Good news is that I had time to grab some diamonds from the trunk. They're in a storage unit nearby.
Ze plane
Here they come, get ready.
The wheel has stopped. It says drills. I got no clue.
Although we didn't bring the amount of meth that we promised, we can still go ahead with the deal. But be prepared in case things go south.
Time to lift those weapons out of there. Our plane will drop off parts for a fulton extraction cage. Hang tight.
Garrett is old school... sticks to what he knows. Things like history.
Four left now!
You got a blowtorch, don't you? Use it on that gate.
Blerrie! Didn't work. You must have gotten something wrong. Wait a bit and try again, yeah?
Now, release the fulton balloon, our plane can snag those guns right out of the sky.
Get the equipment bags!
Get those wires connected to the car ASAP!
OK, remember, this should stay peaceful. Trade the meth for the info, surplus meth for cash. Easy and clean, walk away without bloodshed.
This system is built to be simple. All you got to do is choose a vault and press a button. Easy, yeah? For sure.
That gate will get you into the more secure areas of the bank.
Right, now you got to get it open. See if you can find a tool around there somewhere to help do the job, yeah?
There they are, just like Wick said they would be. Get them to the van and tie them up for now. We'll bring them back with us when we leave. Wick wants to have a chat"
You can tell a lot about a man by how he takes care of his teeth. This makes me a formidable judge of character.
Keep them in check. No escapes!
I got word those wagons are weakest at the roof. Try cutting through there.
Good job, friends. One less secret occult mystery box for Murky. Take it and get cracking on the next, yeah?
They've deployed snipers. Stay low.
You heard that - two minutes, stay alive and protect the coke until he arrives!
Fuck me back and forth: We are done! Take this bike and get the hell outta here. I'm not staying a moment longer!
Well, that usually comes with the territory for my guys, yeah?
Should be a higher security type of door, look for a GenSec logo.
First thing we need to do is access the server room. We've got intel saying that a lab worker has the keycard.

That truck you assholes tagged wasn't the right one, so we can forget about intercepting those voting machines. We're going to try something else to keep the Elephant sweet. We can trigger a re-election by scrambling the server at the polling place. To avoid suspicion on our sponsor, we'll make it look like collateral damage by robbing the bank next door.
I need to be patched into the mainframe so I can hack the system.
Think it's almost there... Some kind of... It crashed.. Dammit start it up again.
Damn it to hell! What is wrong with a traditional security door that you can drill? Looks like you're gonna need the actual lead scientist for hand print authorization. Find him.
We can't record Esteban's voice now. Check the laptop again. Maybe we can find another way around the biometric lock.
Great. Now get the keys to Hox. Decrypting the servers will help pinpoint the traitor.
Just one to go.
We sailed out too far to bring our extraction team. You'll have to get those loot bags on the way out. Don't forget.
We got cops moving in from the west. Watch em!
Now, there will be time for longer hellos later, but we should really make our escape now, yes?
Now what? A bluescreen? Dwankie computers.
Get her down from there, guys.
Get ready for another bulldozer!
Heey! So, we're dropping cars in the sea, huh? This'll be fun - just attach the magnet and we're go!
Good job, that drone won't be here to witness the robot revolution. But make sure you hide the pile of junk. We can't have one of the guards finding it.
Okay, blimp is lowering her to you. BFD. Look at that beauty.
Tanks should almost be done. I've got Bile coming with a package for you.
Don't mess up or get seen now. Almost there...
You gotta blow the floor, friends!
The saw lost power!
Right, the fuel tank is full, the blades are spinning and the cargo is secure. Time to get out of here. Gentlemen, please join me aboard!
Good afternoon. My name is Randolph, and I'll be helping you today.
Remember, find those laptops.
Now. Overlooking this area you will find the control room. From there the vaults in this part of the facility are controlled. That would be useful, yes?
Something to open that door, remember!
OK people, my guy says this is a good time to hit the bank. Turns out the Harvest & Trustee bank manager should have kept his mouth shut. Anything could be in here.
Acessing now...
Didn't you hear the man, gang? He needs a gas tank and exhaust pipes from the workshop. Get over there and deliver.
Go to the corridor outside the server room!
There's a briefcase with updated intel waiting for you in a cabin bathroom. Better go find it, yeah?
Yes, good - now open the doors. The switch there!
Stick two drills on that vault door, ASAP.
Ok, the powers back on!
I've got your airborne friend Bile coming in to lift you out.
Put the C4 on the wall and stay back!
Ach! They've started searching the building!
Head upstairs to the office corridors!
I'm done, on to the next hack.
Almost there, gang. Just some more on the roof and we're good.
There we go, friends. Now get inside and see if you can find the dinges we can here for. It's probably in a safe.

GenSec have a brand new vault - the Investment Safe. Unbreakable, they say, and they're showcasing it at the arena. The door is made of their new compound - Vivinite. But everything has a soft spot. With a bit of C4 and a new circular cutter, we can steal their cash out right from beneath them.
Any problems?
Looks like this gate requires a keycard. Find one guys!
Are you having a difficult time choosing which way to go?
Hey, is everything ok? You better not be sleeping on the job, eh.
Ready whenever you are guys. Let's Miami-Vice-it out of here.
Hey Tin Boy! You got a drug problem!

The lunch-time crowd at Sherping Memorial Park usually don't see anything more exciting than a pigeon taking a crap, so put a good show on for them, gentlemen. You got GenSec trucks and the strongboxes inside to deal with.
Cut him loose!
Oh no, that's the alarm! Let's go to plan B.
Head to Washington D.C. and kidnap a scum bag taxman trying to strike a dirty deal.
Sit tight, gang. The helicopter will be back to pick you guys up.
It was a bad move to ambush me!
There's the drop. Snatch it and place it by the lab.
Cruel child, killing such a beautiful creature.
The Tin Boy box has got to be in one of those toy piles!
Chop-chop. To the chopper.
What are you waiting for? The vault is open.
Just get the server clear of its housing and take it to the van.
I'm sure someone betrayed me. It had to be an informer. But who?
Let's be quick now!
Don't know if I can bluff them again, so let's get this done.
I see SWAT vans rolling into the neighbourhood coming from the east. Dig in!
Aight, four!
Amazing! Bet you can see that beauty from the mainland. Let's clear out friends. We got places to be. Things to steal.
Saw some survivors from the motel. Looked like the army hit them.
Now head to the hatch and hook up the cable.
Ach, another bloody problem. Find the control box and hack into it so we can get through.
Now that we've packed up the getaway train, we need it fueled and ready to go. Hook me into the railyard's PA system. I'll make our work seem like business as usual.
It should be on the bottom floor.
That's the one, bring it back to the mechanic!
This is the wrong truck. Find the right one.
Almost home free! Hurry back to the tanker!
Nicely done. Leave it to those Overkill dwankies to go over the top with security.
Oh, a Jger Mark II... difficult things to get through without destroying the contents.
Doors are open, quickly now, get inside and find what we came for.
We have some excellent lobster tails for you to enjoy.
Kerels have transferred payment for the asset. Nicely done.

It looks like someone at Murkywater might be behind our current predicament. They have closed all communication channels with me. Still got a couple friends there, but it looks like I am officially... ousted. Mr. Lindenhurst was kind enough to decrypt some notes an ancestor had printed on the back of a painting: The View of Mount Vernon. Bain owned the real thing you know; you have to wonder how he pulled that one off, yeah? Watookal, the notes detail that inside the vault of the Brooklyn Bank, there's something buried in the foundation; something that Bain needed, put there when the concrete was poured. I've no idea what it is, and how all this fits together, but whoever got to him put in a lot of resources, so it's probably not any old dinges. We're going in to get it before anyone else finds out, yeah?
Good, now go ahead with the drills.
Like a glooove!
Can't do much from down here!
The pick-up is on its way. Not much margin for error here. Get to the roof.
Follow Bile and don't forget the prisoner!
Aha! Ship database, including comm frequencies. Great! That's what we need. Now get on the horn to the Captain.
Damn, get the saw going again.
That door looks like it's made of balsa, shoot the lock of that thing.
Charon gave us a password for a laptop that contains data on where the money is. Find it!
You need to hack the auctioneer's computer for the code, yeah?
That's a beautiful tree! Stop it, you barbarians!
You need to restart the device.
There you go. The vault with Vlad's merchandise is behind a security gate.
You will need a bit of torque to get through those massive security doors. Good thing we got a plan, ey? Let's start with powering the elevator back up. Head for the generator and start it up.
That's what we need. I'm making a call to the driver.
Maybe that equipment will come in handy later, so hold on to it.
You're going to need the code for it. Start searching.
Cops and SWATs have arrived, be careful!
Don't forget the terminals, friends!
That was a bit of bloody business, but sometimes it gets like that. Still, job done. Great work!
Great - that's the last of 'em!
No time to load the chopper. It's just going to grab the truck, so you need to be inside!
Jiu Feng told us that the triad keeps a lot of operational information in their harbor office. Might be worth a look.
OK, time for a jewelry hit. We need at least ten bags. That's kinda crazy - but you guys are good at crazy!
We'll go with hydrogen chloride.
Coming around again. Going to leave this on the road for you.
Great, now Mr Blonde brought some liquid nitrogen to help crack that door. Mr Blonde?
Get to the escape point, clowns! Follow the blue containers!
This Payday Gang Cabot brought in... we sure this isn't their mess?
Run! RUN!
Find me a telephone around there and I'll try to get Mr. Garrett to take a little walk or something.
Let's get out of here. After you, please...
I'm off in one minute.
I'm coming in one minute!
Have you found a way to get the gate open?
We're going to water crack this vault, guys. Fill it with water, and detonate it. It'll blow the door right off without damaging the contents.
The hell do you think you're doing!?
Vlad, we don't have time for this.
So you got nine of the paintings? That's awesome.
Use the RFID tag to find out which wires to cut.
Get those plates to our escape train! You're doing great!
What we need to do is go in, place a GPS transmitter on the truck carrying the containers and then get out unseen. Easy.
One thing Buluc had was good taste in cars. You can take one from his garage to leave in!
Hacking now. Need a minute or two.
I had a feeling that was the wrong stuff...
Those keys will open the doors in the vault. That should help.
The drive, friends... take it.
That's all the coke nice and secure. Even for you, this was a hell of a win. Let's get the stuff to the boat so we can get our payday on.
One down!
Wrong terminal. Try another.
Almost feel sorry for the chop. He'll be gone for a good while now, no need to worry.
The colored RFID wires are rigged to the wagon's exterior. Don't snip the wrong one by mistake.
Keep 'em off the drill!
Just the guys we've been waiting for!
Seriously though, if they got them ray guns, they're coming with me.
Xun Kang. Speak.
Move that pallet jack out of the way.
They've got some pretty heavy doors on the Document Storage room, so we'll need an access tag to get at those documents. See if the Chief Scientific Officer has one.
I fucking hate war movies.
Screws don't usually unscrew themselves. You gotta help.
Hang tight! Hang tight! I'm searching for an escape driver right God damn now!
Hey guys, what's your status?
... put all the stuff in the car!
See those colored tanks? We need to connect these pipes to the one matching our oil sample. Set it up, then pull the lever on the tank. I'll get our ship into position.
Pick it up, you chops! L1!
I heard rumours. Bunch of clowns hit the motel. My poor Yuri.
Get the shoes with my cocaine!

You telling me the cops got each other gifts, but they didn't buy us anything? Fuck that! Go smack the presents out of their damn Christmas tree! But remember: they're NOT gonna be happy when you steal their toys.
The evidence lockup should be on the second floor.
Good show! Time to break the man out! Find the cell block.
Use the keycard to enter the server room on the second floor.
It took two hundred years, but the Benevolent Bank has finally been robbed. Outstanding work!
You managed to unlock the outer panic room door, so the lance shouldn't take as long!
Thirty seconds, gang! You're pushing it!
You got it. Excellent. Time to bring it all to the helicopter. Bile's waiting, get going!
Hurry up and take the keycard, then make your way back.
You can always rely on the press to swarm on scandal in DC. The weapons deal is the talk of the town. The Elephant and his party are very pleased. Hell of a plan B, folks.
Come on, crew. Get the safes out. Put your back into it.
Hey, we should have a little fun while we take these fuckers down. What about putting an ink bomb in the rest of that money as a nice fuck you" bonus
Nicely done! It'll take SERA a long time to recover from this. Let's head out!
These sons of bitches get nothing...
Second, I want a proper bath. Third, a beer. Fourth, the cathouse. But first... Well, keep driving.
My contact will be on the scene with his vehicle. Be prepared.
Nicely done. Now get into that office, friends.
Hey, bring me a burger next time around.
There's one of the closets. Get picking that lock.
Ok, you'll have to open that safe now!
Ha! I bet he didn't expect that, for sure!
As before, gang. Get that cage prepared.
You guys are lucky, I'm feeling generous.
Yeah, I want a lift-off, people. Haul ass!
Haul the goats in the car. Just don't let 'em crap on the upholstery.
My associate is ready for you. Just go to the apartment to make the deal.
I've arranged a false pager for a first-year resident, but first you need to get hold of a patient file.
Uh, is this on? I can get you through the gates, but only after you find a 4-digit keycode. We can't use mine, or they'll know it was me.

OK, friends! We're going to be touching down near the South Portico. There are Murkies everywhere, so be ready. To get into the PEOC you're going to need a keycard and I think we should start looking for one in the West Wing.
You should be able to hack that computer, easy!
Come on, clowns. Get those bags up to the balcony and into the container. The chopper's waiting.
Snipers across the alley!
The escape vehicle will be there in ten minutes.
OK, I'll get right on fencing this. It won't be hard - this is the perfect kind of merchandise. Nice work!
She proved her.. skill and worth. I felt reciprocation was warranted. To leave her to those... assholes... after she helped me... would not have been proper, right?
Blerrie! I can hear that alarm from here on land! Break out the guns before the coast guard arrives!
There goes the time lock. You're doing great. Try and keep things quiet. Now, the vault has three steps to open it. First is in the bag - just go there and use the fingerprint scanner.
Drill, friends! Drill some more.
Thanks, it's good to have some firepower behind me.
I'd bet money that's the Marketing Lead's car. She'll probably come running if you make the alarm go off. Food for thought.
Master, this is dangerous. We need more security on that ship.
Look at all these nice things. Must have done a lot of public service in his career.
It's open! Bag the money!
Remember, you're looking for keycards. Check the buildings.
The Mendoza cartel just got knocked on its ass. Nothing hurts like taking a financial beating and they just took a big one. Hector will rise and that's good fortune for us down the line.
Smoke? The wheel stopped on smoke?

We need to find exactly which container Vlad is in. Use the camera system in the server room to find the right containter, then try to get hold of a shipping manifest in the control room so that you can match it to a company.
Almost here. Hurry! You beautiful bastards!
Jesus! Are you OK!
Don't think we can talk our way out of this one!
Well...There's going to be some bad news at the GenSec shareholders meeting tomorrow.
Grab those parts, heisters.
The readings on that sample are excellent! Pure as can be!
You got it! Siphoning the oil as we speak. Stay out of sight.
Good! Ah, not so complicated after all. You should be able to get through by accessing the wire boxes around there and cutting the right cables.
No way out the front. Quick! Get into the container. You're leaving with the loot. Don't think about the drop, okay?
That's so badass! I heard they came at you with just four guys!
Move the van out of the way!
That diner has a service ladder leading up to the roof, but you'll need a keycard to get to it. Look around for one.
I've always wondered what Murky's Top Men look like.
You lot ready to go?
OK, you guys totally emptied that hangar, time to get out of here.
It's time to rotate the dealers.
You don't destroy a man's car! You just don't do that, you hear?!
We'll settle for this right here.
There's a park nearby that should offer some cover...
Stop, I'll cooperate!
The head of security will have that USB stick.
You know what to do. Break into the wagons and get those plates.
That's the vault, fo' sho'.
Dinner time, little fishies.
Great, That's the pit boss' number.
Get over here!
The crane has been stopped. You need to restart it!
They shot the driver! You'll have to continue on foot!
You'll die for this!
Hurry now, go find the artifact in the bio-lab.
Attach the frame!
He dropped a keycard. Probably for his office. Maybe something there will help.
Fuel is always useful to have around.
It's the cops! They're following us!
Welcome to DC - I'll catch you vets later. Go inside and see Bain in the back.
I'm gonna drive a fucking spike through your eye!
BFD's without power. Reconnect the power sockets.
I'm getting nervous, guys!
Feelin' good there, donut boy?
There should be some nice, expensive cars in the garage. Use one of those to destroy the turret.
You guys there?!
Help! HELP!
God damn!
This is the only entrance to the bank. At least until the SWAT's start making their own ways in.
The Mayan dinges is probably opened with that codex. Just need to find the right symbols. Have a search nearby and see what you can find.
There it is! Now drill that door open!
Get two more!
Use those offices as your advantage!
I want a beautiful Christmas tree with presents in it!
You've got the keys to his airplane - head for it and fly out. You do know how to fly right?
Chloride. Hydrogen chloride.
I think she's ready to cooperate! Take her back to the display case, and don't alert anyone on the way.
The bridge looks good. Dropping the cage there.
How is it going with the key tag?
Well you heard Hector. No time to piss around. We go into the meth lab and secure the goods.
This is the room! Now put that drill to work!
OK, time for the hit. You might see some Garnet things in there too - I like seeing they're still in business after all we've done to them. I need at least two bags to make this worth our while.
I got one word for you: whooooooooooooooooooooo!
Tick-tock, said the detonator. Keep the kerels away.
Put holes in 'em!
The customer is about a minute away.
I got another idea: Finders keepers, assholes!
This is not all of we had agreed on.
Someone pick up the phone. I'll talk to them.
An off-shore methlab? Clever. A methlab in a metal box? Not so clever...
You need to add the muriatic acid to keep the process going!
Signal the driver when you're ready to go.
I'm sending a chopper in for you guys to unload the loot. It's close by, shouldn't take too long. Stay tight.
A little bird told me the Mendozas are flying in more weapons in preparation for the war with Hector.
We're gonna have a look and check if everything's ok.
Amazing job! Now, climb up on top of BFD and the blimp will take you to safety. Or grab more loot. Your choice.
Out into the sky, friends!
Find those electrical boxes yet?
Fear, as you surely know, is a powerful motivator. The District Attorney can now be considered properly... motivated. He will be ready to help your friend. I will contact you in due course.
I've got a driver standing by. Eddie, that's your cue, get in there!
Look out friends! They have an active weapons turret!
Friends! Beautiful friends! How is the flight? We are getting close to the drop location. So, please, open the hatch and...
We need all SERA's documentation on the prototype. Find the offices in the Research Center. They'll have what we need.
...caustic soda?
I'd look around before setting everything on fire as it were. Maybe there's a better way.
There's goes the alarm. And our stealth plan. Don't sweat it. The ship is moving.
Ok, we can still do this. Mr Blonde, you brought the special sauce, right?
You find it yet?
Now, you ready to call it? Find our Insider. She's going to show you a way to slip out.
We've accessed the schedule. Keep hidden while I work my magic.
Must be an error on their end. I see them right here on our schedule, Mr. Santiago.
I'm moving out.
There's a machine in the laboratory for analyzing oil samples. Just what we need.
Come on, gang. Patch me into the radio.
What the hell! A little help!?
Someone said the attackers look like the Payday Gang. Can anyone confirm? Is it true?
Turn on the water again!
There's someone in the elevator, keep a lookout.
A Stage 6 Piggy...I thought it was just a legend!
Huh... I bet they have cargo tracking in that warehouse... Probably on a PC or tablet...
Light the flare near the winch!
There's a worker in our way! We'll get caught if we wait around too long. Go tie him down, then finish prepping the locomotive.
All right. Now bunker down, gang. Hold them off until we burn through.
Wait... another vault?
This one's coming down at the bridge.
There must be some kind of instruction manual around there.
Slow vaults down there, yeah?
Nicely done, friends. Now you can go open that door.
Hmm, Bile is right. You should get to the top of the overpass so he can pick you up.
OK, time for a jewelry hit. We need at least three bags. That should be fairly easy.
Hurry now, reconnect me to the grid.
Put these suckers in the ground!
Not this stuff, this shit is nano-thermite! Was smuggled out of Sweden for me. Extra strong.
What's taking so long? Don't waste that thermite.
This has to be the most persistent fucking cops I've ever seen!
There are three security boxes. Disable them so I can access the system. Whichever has a green light is the current one you need to go for.
OK, that's enough. You can keep cooking or get out of there.
There are eight valves around the Drilling Tower. Only turn the ones I call out, or we'll need to start again.
Escape is on the scene. Whenever you're ready gentlemen!
I've got a helicopter coming in to pick you up. I believe you are acquainted with the pilot.
One of the workers here is on Keegan's payroll. He left a tool to help us jam the ventilation fan to Gabriel's room. Find it now.
...unless I've missed something...
Open a door or window and the alarm timer will kick in. You'll only have a few seconds to disable it, before it goes to hell.
... are you having second thoughts or what?
Have you tried answering the phone?
For me, Vlad, this is new start. I look forward to goal, like in football. I will rise.
You made too much of a ruckus, the vault is completely locked down.
Yeah-yeah-yeah... Run the plan!
Now the hard part.
Vegas Sky Express blimp here. Codename Heartbreaker" commanding. We got a package for your party."
Wang is held up in the meeting room with a bunch of lackeys. Let's get him out of there and cause a bit of confusion in the process. Pull the fire alarm. That should get things going.
Help me! The've got guns!
Moretta. This is Port Washington radio. Free to clear dock and berth at 3B. Stand by for GPS data. Over.
There might be janitors and other civvies in the building, so take extra care.
Alright, you got far without getting detected, but it's over now. The cops are reported missing and they're sending in a SWAT team. The party just got started.
OK, some dwankie has gone and locked himself in there. If you can find a tube of gas or something, we can choke him out.
Five.
Remember guys, this is for all the marbles. And the can, too.
Watch out! Bulldozer in the transport!
What the fuck do you think you are doing!?
Ok team, let's get a move on. The Butcher means business here... remember, you've got to kill Ernesto Sosa, and steal the loot.
We're going to need that code. Rummage 'round a bit and see of you can find any clues. Maybe try one of the workstations? But stay quiet, friends.
This is First World Bank. We have offices in Washington, London, Bogota and Karachi.
Like... a glooove...
Ah, just imagine putting a slug right in the middle of old Garrett's gob. But not tonight, friends. Long game and all that, yeah?
Good, thank you.
Hack the ship control terminal!
Lots of people and cars blocking access to the bank. Clear out the area so the escape van can get through.
Thank you. I'm impressed that you showed up so quickly. I'm in your debt.
Get that open, and get whatever is in there!
The Dentist just clued me in - the Commissar likes to keep his best loot in the basement. Look around the ground floor rooms for something that might be an entrance.
I'm connected.
Not much cover up here, but opportunities for spotting and getting inside.
There's the hose! Connect it to the vault.
How do their heads keep making that noise?
What are you doing? Follow Bain!
We really need that escape car now! How long do you think it will be?
... Going, I'm going.
Looks like we pushed the transfer pump too hard. Crank the pressure valves to fix it.
Some fucking cunt snitched! I need to find out who.
Good job, now get the bags to the van so we can get the hell out of here!
The Mendozas are going to be busy loading their guns in the warehouse. Go in and hit 'em fast before they go all Lord of War on you. Get those weapons or destroy 'em.
Now swipe the vault keypanel! Come on!
How long did that report take? An hour? Bill them for ten.
Get the power plugged in. Keep that running.
What are you waiting for?
Ok guys, get after that gold!
I'll be there in 2 minutes. Get ready!
What? You don't want to get away scot-free? Well, I do, so please hurry up and take all of those pardons!
Ok, so maybe blending in isn't our style. Sending the helicopter now!
Have a look around and and see if you can find a utility closet. Maybe there will be some useful tools.
Now put your sombreros on and get into that tunnel.
Our inside man ascertained a small vault on the top floor. It could serve Commissar well as a panic room if everything goes to hell.
You can zipline to the rig from here. There's a private security force topside, so stay alert.
We weren't fast enough here, the getaway just left.
Highway with guns drawn in broad daylight... OK, never said it was going to be easy. Find the marked truck.
Alright, you're in. You've got access to the PC of the bloody Director of the fuckin' FB bastard I! Approve the request.
Damn! They drove through Wilson's wall.
Your escape car is here, better hurry before the cops kill him.
It needs hydrogen chloride, for sure... OK wait, soda... Yeah, caustic soda!
Get at least four bags or we don't leave.
Oh, that voice is familiar. Just hope he doesn't crash.
Is the entire crew in agreement on the plan?
They're not letting us go!
I'm a bit worried our intel on the Murkies is bad.
What's in the box?!" Man
column4: but it's definitely valuable. Survive so you can find out!"

String: I'm there in 2 minutes.
Fuck man, I got Brown's brains all over me!
Right, the numbers for the code are...
What does this have to do with the heist?
Instead of twiddling your thumbs, why not take out the security room while the oil's draining? Should be nearby.
There's one!
I appreciate that times are difficult. First World Bank truly does. But, with regret, we cannot sanction the loan of $10,000 on a promise to pay it back when Fat Pat's" insurance comes through."
One down. One to go.
All right, gang, up ahead is Chavez' crib.
I don't want to bail you out! fight!
Time to get you out of there. Grab whatever loot you can on the way out.
Go through that door right there. Twitch is waiting!
Found the library yet?
Tap into the security boxes.
Another attack helicopter! Careful guys!
Now get out of there without triggering the alarm, and this is a perfect stealth job.
Not that one! From the top, alright?
Get the loot to the van.
The blueprints are in the archives. My guess would be the employee only areas.
Well done guys.
They're moving snipers into position folks.
Hang in there!
Alright, the next ingredient is...
Make sure to poke around the Executive Office. Look hard. When someone's as dirty as Rainey, there's always dirt to find.
Fantastic, friends. Now you need to get back to the entrance so that I can pull you out of there.
The doors aren't locked, friends. Get to the offices.
OK, hook up the server and let's go.
You gotta fuckin' keep 'em off me, goddamnit!
Hurry friends, get out of there.
You guys are professional ghosts. Now get to the computer.
Hmm, looks like all the best guns were disassembled. They'll be worth way more to a buyer in one piece. You should put that workshop to use before we mess it up.
Let's meet in the building next door. You can probably enter from the roof.
For fucks' sake! Lads! The power!
Should stay running for a bit, now.
Very strange, this. One of the boxes is in the bio-lab? That's where you go next then, friends.
OK, friends. Time to leave.
The office door needs a keycode. See it written down anywhere?
Crazy to think this stuff came from the time of the Caesar's.
Hurry friends! Stop it from running a firmware update or we'll be back at the start!
Merry christmas, my friends! I need you to help me with a little Christmas miracle.
Great, I'm in. Keep watching those hostages.
Drill through that vault, friends.
OK, time for a new plan!
Watch it, friends! Those laanie Mexican police are spreading gas in the vent system. It will clear soon, so stay away until it does!
Looks like they have cameras... Watch the alarms.
Great, you found some evidence! Analyze it in the lab. Let's see if there's any trace of the traitor's DNA on it.
Protect the timer, the SWATs will interrupt it if you don't!
Snip the right color? Good. Now rewire the RFID box, and the gate should open.
Oh, that piece of shit is going to wish he had not fucked with Vlad.
Vault security has been divided. You need to get the code from Deng, and take a casting of Kang's handprint.
You need to add the muriatic acid to keep the process going!
OK, now let's see if we can't find that phone number.
That dumpster should do the trick.
Release Vlad!
Woah, that must be full of valuables! I can understand why Vlad wants these business' money...
I got an Inside Man there. They'll help us get through to the gates leading to the vault. Patching them through now.
The data from the scanning is being collected on that server in the other room. You can stay and get more data, or you can leave. But I'm sure Jimmy would pay us for the trouble.
Great work. There's always a market for untraceable guns.
You're almost at the gallery. Slip in, avoid cameras, guards, and motion detectors. Security's high because of a bomb threat.
There's space between the trains too. It's worth a look.
It'd be easier for Bile to pick you up if you go to the top of the overpass.
Hey, you wouldn't be interested in a little mercenary work, eh? No?
The PC is showing where the trucks are headed. Keep an eye out for those bound for Washington.
Don't let the guy lag behind!
I'm gonna give you a faceful of lead!
Damn it! Someone just tripped the alarm!
Gang, we still need a way to get through that steel gate. You need to find something that we can use.
The server room should be above the catwalks!
Lining up on the target. Fuck me, it's hotter than Khe Sanh!
Those crates in the basement got me thinking. We can use them to get into the Commissar's place - undercover like. He won't be expecting this.
This is an FBI branch office so you really, really, really want to be quiet. We're in the lion's den. First step, get inside.
You will go there take all money you can find and leave them hurt! Show them Vlad pays back what is done to Vlad!
Can't find the Piggy Bank? Look in wide open spaces. Parking lots. Rooftops. That kind of stuff.
Remember to sort the fireworks. Light up the night sky.
No bags!? The trade will not be good to us. Hope you guys has some tricks up your sleeve for the trade.
When the cage is full, let the balloon up. And watch what happens next.
I knew you were pros and no one even heard you. Amazing!
Keegan doesn't want just any batch of oil. It's all about purity. You can snag a testing sample from the Extraction Room.
I'm not sure. I'm dispatching an officer just to be safe.
Go on, try another key!
We got company! The Mendozas' probably here.
I'm Julian.
...Goddamn goddamn goddam police must have followed us... I'm slipping... Sorry guys... Ride's gonna get rough!
Looks like the Army figured out your escape plan! They're getting ready to blow up the tracks. Get outta there!
There you go! Time to get that handprint off Xun Kang!
Store is open! Find that goat!
Stop throwing the coke into the fucking water!
Protect the winch from the coppers!
That's 17 bags!
The pardons we are looking for will be inside.
Hell no, don't try no games, sucker!
Don't drop that thing.
Get away from the gate! Fast!
Good, now get back in there.
Right, now you gotta find Garrett's office.
Uh, control, I shat the bed again. Repeat: shat the bed. Trying again.
If there's any extra loot you want to grab, you can drop them into the sewer and I'll have Garth pick them up for us!
Just start shooting, that gets people moving!
Hydrogen... chloride. Ach, nasty!
Connecting now. Better pray this is the right one.
The safes are way too heavy to carry, and those trucks are screwed. Gonna need another transport. I'll find something - hang tight.
Ahhh, the safes. My precious little. Bring them safely out. Find a transport.
Damn. Alright. Expect company, gang.
We need to get a look at that manifest!
Not much further now. Get him up the tower on the right!
Defend that drill, people!
Grab as much C4 as you can, gang.
Well, we're not getting the van down any time soon, so blast the doors.
Hack the computer and see if you can find the code.
We go to our backup plan. Have a look around and see if you match anything to those wire boxes.
Ok, you have to go to the Jewelry store.
Gotta be a power box that controls the barriers. Find it!
Ready to go? We can go at anytime now.
If you're up for some multitasking, now would be a good time to take out the security room.
I like the sound of that. I think I'll put mine in my 401k.
That's the time lock done. Try and keep the sneak going. Now, the vault has a three step clearance control. The first I've already taken care of. Just head there and use the fingerprint scanner.
OK, that's it, I got to bail!
Everything's going to plan.
Drop 'em!
We'll send you to the lake!
When you feel ready, make your escape!
You can't let them kill the power, it'll slow everything down!
I've got him. Let's get out of this bekakin' place.
There's a helicopter standing by to get you out. But as soon as you call it, things are going to get loud fast. So pick your moment.
We're headed back to cook in the meth lab in the forest. None of Hector's shit this time. This is just for profit.
We need more water! Chopper's going to fill her tank. Hold the vault!
See if you can find a cleaning chemical around there, then spike the cake.
Hurry up!
Need you to get to those routers.
You gotta crack that door open, friends.
The plane is full, you can take off the hose.
Go through the hole! Head to the neighboring building!
Crack that door.
Dropzone is directly below! Jump now!
Open that gate.
You still need to find the safe, friends.
OK... I'm checking. Seems OK... Hmm... Seems like the power grid here keeps fluctuating... Maybe his invention...
I'm not 100% but I think it is hydrogen chloride now. Yep, should be.
Come on, crew - focus! C4 the doors!
A couple years ago, some civvie chop got all they way past the Secret Service and stole a pair of knickers from the First Lady. It's true, friends!
Have you set the thermite on that cable yet?
You can see the number inside the office.
Dentistry is a job that requires a lot of precision and attention to detail - just like my alternative line of work.
See if you can find a crowbar.
You heard Fedor. Get your asses to the lake.
That's the right choice, guys. Keep scanning away. We didn't come all the way to Russia for a small payout, now did we?
Keep preparing the right chemicals.
It's getting dangerous here!
You made us come for nothing?
This man can drive like no one else. You'll appreciate it when the pressure is on.
Guys, the briefcases. Check the owners office. Then find the pit boss. And, lastly, check near the guards' locker room.
Flush it down the toilet! It will mix with the rest of the kak.
He should have stayed out of the kitchen!
Just the guys we've been waiting for!
Did I speak in Afrikaans? My apologies! I meant to say please" "plant" "the" "charges" "on the locks"... you kaks."
It's time to leave, get back to the street!
Network traffic indicates someone in the mansion placed an order to a custom mask shop. if you can find the right computer with the invoice, we'll know which mask is which.
Everything you've taken needs to go out on the zip.
You heard him. The trucks are around here somewhere.
That codex! Those symbols... that's how we get the Mayan door to open, yeah? Look around for more clues!
You can get through via the warehouse or by moving that truck.
Sure. Please hold.
He's getting away!

Kak! Hang on, friends. Some goons from an outside security firm are headed this way. Must be here for the event. If they find traces of your work, they'll sound the alarm! Meet them in the parking lot and take them out!
And if you could sign here, here, here... here, and here. And your initials here. And sign here.
Another day, another bank. We can liberate some cash, I'm sure.
You're messing with ME? Show me the money!
That keycard is one less thing we need to find.
Still no sign of an alarm. Great. Find the comm frequency.
Just throw the bags in here!
Yeah yeah, just put on your mask now.
I know what you guys are after but I won't give it to ya!
Maybe the shutter door could be opened with that terminal.
Kalashnikovs return now with my men. (Thank you) I will destroy those who have done this.
Holy shit! Help!
Intruders! Fire!
...Might be able to hack them with bank computers, yeah?
There's the soft underbelly of the Investment vault. Get the cutter to work.
Wang is on the run. Track him down and deal with him.
Right, now let me just get this sorted. Will be done in a jiffy.
Someone switched off the lights. Get them back on!
Ach, the dinges is trying to update the operating system. Stop it at the mainframe!
Damn! Someone saw the body! Take him out before he calls it in!
I've sent the helicopter for you, you'll be picked up soon.
Okay, hacking the system now...
Keep moving the crane. Can't drop it there.
Looks like an entry in the wall behind the shrine, but you'll have to blow open a hole. Time for a home-brew explosive!
Good job, Dallas. You still have it in you. Now, throw the loot in the van and let's leave.
From the crust of the Earth to our bank accounts. Gorgeous.
If you're feeling ready, go ahead and leave the facility.
That's how I would have done it too.
Fucking hell!
So what do you think I should do?
What a mompie. He's better dead.
We got a tail - and they're getting closer!
Die! DIE!
Each one will bring a King's ransom. That's literally true (laughs)!
That's the last camera in the vault area. Good job.
The IT guy has stopped opening the lock. Laanie Federales got to him!
Our inside guy should have left the wiring box for it open. Find it and cut the wiring.
Shit, Feds will be here shortly. Hit the server room door now.
Quickly now, get the crane moving.
Uh, if I read this correctly... uh...
The cops cut the power. We need to get it back on.
The plane should be on its way.
That's the head of security. He's by the pools.
Now turn on BFD. They'll display her for years to come.
You gotta find the laptop if you want to get the money.
Bile is on the way with the choppa, hang in there for a bit, yeah?
You guys did a great job up there. You wanna join the road crew?
Use the control panel in the yard to move that firetrap.
See this tattoo? Got this off the king himself. Fucking A, man.
There you go! Almost home free.
That was close! Security here's more complex than I expected. Let's restart the transfer on the laptop.
The cops shut you down. You gotta find the electricity box.
... I'm coming back soon!
Just leave the car in the container and mosey on out. We're nearly done.
I can't lose these sons of bitches!
Might be a good place to look.
Okay, good. Now, take the hostage to the room in the back.
Answer the Intercom!
Access the computer I have marked out for you. Use it to drop the magnetic seal.
Now let's rescue our friend. The cell block should be nearby.
What... hey! Did Vlad send you to get me out?
Locke never forgets anything!
Would you look at that!? We did it, gang. We did it.
Crap! It missed the cable. Alright, don't panic. He's swinging around for another pass.
If you feel like you're done looting, maybe we can make a little statement. Setting off an ink bomb on the rest of that cash would be a nice middle finger to the Golden Dagger, for sure!
Nice, that should do it for the roof.
They're on the roof!
With any luck, the Murkies will not follow you. This tunnel is said to be able to withstand a couple nukes.
The drill needs some attention, friends!
Blerrie! They're flooding the vault with toxic gas! Wait until it clears!
Remember that the EMP bomb is two parts and I don't have to remind you we need both.
Get the bags to the platform.
Gotta get that winch running again, gang.
Come on, we watched the show and you know how to do it. Set the C4!
You're close to the FBI boss. Keep your finger off the trigger, we may need him alive.
Need the power back, guys.
I... don't know where we are...
You found a blowtorch! That could prove useful.
Put the stuff in the car...
Your escape helicopter is here, try and secure the rest, but if you can't I suggest you get the hell out of there!
Keep moving along the bridge until you reach the prison transports.
Now, the keycard I left for you. That large door has two security stages, and an airlock beyond. The first is using the keycard. So...
Boom! There's a garbage truck positioned to pick up the bags. Dj vu, I know.
They ain't getting through this way!
Get ready for the ninth wave!
You better hurry up and fix that leakage.
Gang, get to the computer. Get those coordinates to the ship.
Well, by Odin's beard, the codes seems to have worked.
Loads of cash! Bag it up boys!
Looks like we got everything, gang, Your pick-up is on its way.
Crap, they're driving away! Sorry guys, looks like it's plan B. Let's get out of here and deal with it elsewhere.
Don't go to the neighbours.
Hey gang, you got trouble comin' by helicopter.
Keep those stinking chops off the cage!

Every last one of you leaves here in a body bag!

The charging has been interrupted! Get it started again!
You have 30 seconds!
Ralph just showed himself. Keep your eyes open!
That's the tea shop the triad is using as a front!
... put the stuff in the car...
All right, clowns - keep your eyes on the road.
Looks like there might be an underground vault somewhere.
The wheel stopped on sniper!
Hurry up, Hurry up, I want to see that my merchandise is OK.
Looks good...

OK, we're here. Time to go to work.
Don't be shy of the explosives, friends. C4 good. C4 is friend, yes?
Do pekla! Finally, Butcher send help. You untie me please!
Starting my approach. ETA four minutes. Over.
Get over here, guys.
Don't mess around...
There you go, now find that laptop and hack it.
That boss would have been useful alive. Always a back-up though. A *loud* back up.
Are you moving the loot?
Great, you're in. One more door between us and the server.
I haven't handled something this big and clumsy since... nevermind.
But I heard y'all went head-to-head on a train-
No time here gang, get to the vault.
Nice. Buluc's sanctum isn't going to provide much sanctuary now, yeah?
Finishing is the only thing.

Gonna give you a motherfucking faceful of lead!

Get up to the roof and light a flare to signal pickup.

... keep cool!
Make sure the skid loader is not interfered with.
Keep the people in check...

Alright, four!

No alarm on that door now. Get inside.
