Open those Murkywater containers. If anything has illegal loot, it will be them.
If I were a USB, where would I hide? Maybe in a cabinet? Sounds cozy.
Don't let anyone see you while you're fixing the turntable.
That asshole?
...I'm 93% sure.
You afraid of flying, eh? Get going with the elevator doors and zipline up!
Fuckin feds and their doors. OK, let's hit that like it is hot. Go!
We're here. Get inside and get your hands on the access codes.
Restart the bypass on those security boxes.
Kerels stopped the hacking routine. You gotta restart it.
I've got your escape vehicle coming, but those kerels will give you some hell in the meantime.

Not when it's right under our nose. GenSec completely saturated the D.C region. We're every camera, every truck, every access card. The clients that got hit are looking for someone to blame, and we're an easy target. Our security failed.
The crafty cops have closed off the bridge. Go to the control room to turn it back.
You've just etched your names into history, gang. Heisters will tell this story for generations.
You know how much that stone is worth?
Looks heavy, but you will find a way to get it out.
Scanner tells me 60 seconds until the police are there. Load up.
Ok, now for the server room... That laptop you found earlier should enable me to give you access. Go back there and hook me up.
Deal's off so FUCK YOU!
They're getting too close to the hacking device, people! Watch it.
OK..OK.. Just need to get the server out of its housing and walk it to the van.
Hi! Yes, what can I do for you?
The safe is in Deng's massage parlor!
Tracker placed. Signal coming through. Now haul ass, and let's hope we're chasing Elephant's machines.
Grab the thermite and use it to burn through the door.
Whoa. Did I win?
Never mind. Get into the server room and hack the system instead.
Why don't I hear the sound of sawing coming through my headphones?
I owned cash flow from four stores on Maple Street - my steady income! My bread. Now some cocksmoker takes my operation - steps on me. On Vlad! Huh!
Uhh, fuck no!
Alright, we're in for deposit boxes.
Cops in 20 - gear up.
The keys have to be close, yeah?
OK, looks like a proper cocktail, now get that stuff on the door and let it work, yeah?
Let's see, what else. You can test any of the objects out in here - just pick up the equipment and find something it fits on.
One of those oil tanks should match our sample. Line up the pipes, activate the pump, and our ship will take care of the rest.
That's it. The printing plates should be in those wagons.
Come on, you wankers. Get that power up again.
The control room is up there. You see?
Just get the chrome skull the mechanic is asking for. Go inside the clubhouse and use the blowtorch he gave you.
I wanted to remind you that our All You Can Eat buffet is now open.
That didn't do it. Try a different one.
I'm just a few blocks away - I can hear and see the sirens, I'm there in one minute!
Damn! Alright, I'm sending the drill. You'll have to open each vault til you find the turret.
Do we really have time for this?
Great. Sure we can find a use for a little C4 later.
A real bargain, yes?
What's going on down there? You staying alert?
You remember when we hauled the samurai armor out of here? Ahhh, good times!
You should have let Vlad mix up some special Sputniks for him. Would have taken him out much faster!
Hostage has been retrieved. The clowns will have to give this one up, and go home with their tails between their legs, over.
Move the ramp off the ship. Gotta get your hands dirty, friends.
Alright, looks like we have... 11... 12 prototypes. See if you can find something around the house that can indicate which is the working one. Then pick it up and get it to me.
We've got some company, folks!
Keep a lookout for guards. There's fairly good soundproofing in those walls, and the ships engine noise will mask some of the drill, but it's still risky.
Fuck me sideways!
Almost there now, just a few more bags and we should have enough.
I'm sorry, but I don't think there is much demand for confederate flag bedsheets.
They shot me, but it's only a minor one. Barely hurts.
Armored glass. Blerrie. Maybe we can smash it. Try burning through a cable holding that chandelier with some thermite and see what happens.
We're gonna make the rest of your life real short!
Keep it together!
Have a look around for a ladder, if you want to get up on that roof. And you want to get up on that roof, I assure you.
That's the code! Great. Now get it working on that time lock.
Nice, friends. Thank you.
Go on in, the ballot machines are near the bank. Hit the bank, open the vault, and raise hell. Shoot the joint up. Destroy the ballot machines as unfortunate collateral damage.
My old protection business must start up. It is taken, and customers need change of mind.
Wait for Bile to come back and pick you up along with the loot.
Ok! Now find a gas can and shoot it to set it all alight. Let's burn some art!

Ernesto Sosa is the local boss in Miami for the Sosa Cartel, and The Butcher wants him dead. You're gonna love this: he lives in Tony Montana's old mansion in Miami Beach. Yeah that's right - Scarface, the legendary 80's drug lord. Anyway, you've got to hit the mansion, find a way in and then kill Ernesto Sosa. It won't be easy, the place is like a fortress. But you can do it. Oh yeah, I almost forgot - there should be a lot of money and other loot in that house. Steal it. Wipe them clean. But above all - kill Ernesto Sosa.
I'll be there in three minutes!
...And yeah, there goes the alarm.
You still have 16 left!
Cloakers on the way, sneaky bastards!
Hey, look, everything is fine here. You don't need to do that.
...what's the worst that could happen, eh?
Look at us interupting a dirty deal between the IRS and some big corporation: we are like Robin Hood!
Set up the laptop to the anti-aircraft gun. Maybe I can work my magic.
Looks like some codes, that'll come in handy.
That house is going up in flames. Let's get the product to Hector and get paid. I wonder how much he pays for the blue.
Esteban's fingerprints will open the laptop now. Find a way to get them. You might need some kind of adhesive.
Ey, who the hell are you!?
This is how you succeed, just keep it going.
Every key's got a lock. See any clues where this one might be?
The Beast is at work.
So, joke over, right? This just big joke? Don't do this!
You need to repair the turntable. Quickly!
Alright, I'm at the spot!
Ah, bloody hell. Some interview files are locked. Need approval from... Fuck me, the Director himself. Whoever this rat is, he's connected. Get to the Director's office!
That's the server room door alright. Inside there is what we want.
Alright, looks like some witness testimonies were missing. Going to have to hit the hard copies. Get to the Archives and grab 'em.
That's it, that's it. Go. Go!
Wow, that was one hell of an explosion! Cops are on their way now, so drive fast!
There's an access hatch to the sewers over by the gas station. Go there, and get down.
Don't let the cops near the cage. Those sneaky bastards can walk off with your hard-earned cash.
Wait, I just had an idea. Let's have some fun.
We got a tail - and they're getting closer!
They've cut the power on you, friends. Find the circuit box and get it running again!
No need to stay there longer. Take the box and make for extraction.
Time to defend, gang! Bile's on his way!
No more!
Look out for the gas, friends! Wait until it dissipates!
Two more.
Are you looking for the IT dwankie?
Great. Now get it to the vault. We're doing this the old fashioned way.
Dear hearts! You see me? Yes, I am here. For sure. I hate to be a bother, but would you mind strapping that lovely money to my helicopter?
Throw more tablets in the mixer if you want to keep cooking, crew. Or light the flare and bail. Up to you!
My old acquaintance in the FBI that owed me a favor has doctored a laptop for you to use. She said she would mark which one on a whiteboard. See if you can find it, yeah?
Well, now I was wondering when you were going to call.
You see that movie where the guy has to spend a billion dollars in a day? Something like that. Well, that motherfucker was me.
You're going to have to find the keycard for that door.
You can use any laptop to extract the information.
My mother said the devil appears when you speak his name. Be careful!
That whiteboard you found... certainly looked like a code configuration. Did you see which one is being used right now?
It's the big office building! Hard to miss!
There we go.
The CFO has the master code guys. Find him!
Arriving in four!
Guys! Don't forget Charon!
Chopper is almost there.
There's a half-eaten candy bar here. Mmmmm nutty. Oh....wasn't a candy bar.
Oh crap, is that an attack helicopter?
Six left!
Get the fuck out'a here real fast is what I'm sayin'.
We're a keycode away from stealing the Neo-2. I'm told the SERA Marketing Lead should have it written down in her office.
That's good enough for the roof.
Have you found that code yet?
Hey! Where's my backup? I'm a sitting duck up here!
The database should be on the second floor of the building.
We got a fucking police caravan on our ass!
Now cut those beams to free the vault.
Get the mechanic to help you assemble Rust's bike. You're gonna have to follow his lead on this one.
It's open! Bag the gold!
Hurry up guys, you need to move to the other building.
Yes. That will work well.
Get out of there guys!
There you go, that's him. Start drawing some blood.
The server room. Get me hooked up, guys.
There's just no losing 'em!
And another...
Connect the garden hose to the safe.
Diesel tank and hose somewhere around dock.
Get that limo!
Hey, I'm not gonna be able to break out of here without some help.
Wasn't this one. Keep going. Vault is here somewhere.
What a blerrie mess! There's flooding everywhere, and those are live wires dipping into the water. If you touch the floor, you're toast!
Ok, I'm inside - but it seems the elevator isn't working. Listen - I need to get something important that they took from me. It's in a metal briefcase. Can you get it for me?
And how much will it cost you? Shall we say... 18 bucks?
Unless you want to stay there, get that door open.
And that is how you put on a great show. Great work!
Jumpin' fuckin' Jesus guys, I'm gonna get creamed.
The oil's not coming through!
I guess they know we're not selling Girl Scout cookies. Grab the C4 and blast your way in.
Almost... Done. Just a moment now, guys.
This one is a hit on the Teuer dealership. High class joint.
It's not that hard, chops! Again...
Puta madre!
Ah, I know a lot of faces here, back again for more enjoyment!
If you're low on gear, go back and check the drop point outside, yeah?
Moretta is on the move. Going to take a while before she is berthed, so you can stay low and quiet, or use the time to hunt down any extra loot. Up to you.
Excellent! Now, let it run for a few seconds.
Nice. Now start her up.
Can't go down that way, they'll hear you.
Don't let them close, gang!
Someone cut the juice, you need to get it back up again.
Attach the magnet!
Your time is almost up, creeps. We're coming in to stop you by any means necessary.
We got twelve!
You people are wasting your time.
You guys can cook! Which one of you is Heisenberg, Hector wants to know.
I think we have time for a little detour before you go past those bollards, yeah?
Snipers! Too many civilians dead, can't stay there!
You need that keycard, friends.
Three minutes to go!
We got the armor from here when we did it quiet, you recall?
Take all the money you can and throw the bags overboard. I've got someone waiting to pick them up.
There goes the alarm. Let's go straight for the server room door.
The police are on our back like a fucking pony tail!
You can disable the blowout preventer from the control room.
Hey, what's the hold up?
Great job gang, but now --- get out of there. My systems --- lighting --- a Christmas tree here.--- Something is up.
Found that safe, yet friends?
... Fuck 'em up!
The rig's set to blow. Just gotta start the drill!
Case the place before lighting things up. Maybe there's a better way.
OK folks, I spoke to Hector. The Mendoza higher ups are fleeing the country but Hector isn't quite ready to let them leave. He wants to know where they're headed.
The center one!
The fucking Hondurans found us! How did they follow us?!
Make sure to check the top floor if you wanna leave this place. But there are so many bags...
Outstanding marksmanship. Three trucks got it. They're ready, gang - get out there.
Okay. Now hold them off til the thermite finishes.
...Shit we picked up a tail folks, no shaking 'em now!
Maybe you can find something to get in there. Have a look in the utility closet if you can find it.
Do L1!
Damn kerels have cut the power. Get it back up and reactivate the crane.
Stay under the cameras and they won't be able to spot you.
Try to get up to the next floor.
Coppers got to the drill!
Ok, well... maybe. IF, there's time.
Straightforward job, this one. A bunch of thugs are running a little operation. Got a bunch of elves" cutting coke that Vlad wants. Deal with the thugs
column3: and then get the elves producing. Shouting at them should do it. Get as much coke as Vlad needs

String: Maybe there's a saw in the garage.
He was a bakvissie anyway.
First World Bank, how can I help you today?
All right, the C4's on the ground. Grab it!
I just got some intel about another bunch of Sosa thugs arriving at the mansion to reinforce security. The area better be clean, or they'll be onto you when they arrive.
And... Alex made the requested drop. Somewhere.
This won't end well for you, suckers!
This will pay off later.
You guys sure take an awfully long time.
We're in. Now get after that goat!
Okay, the electricity is back, now just start the printer again
Off we go! Get in the car everyone!
Sweet money, guys! Now make this worth it by grabbing as much loot as you can!

That's 17 bags!
Hang on - too much heat for a pick-up.
Ah, that's it friends. A nice little Payday, though I think we could have gotten more!
The ballot machines arrive at the harbor today by truck. Now we don't know which truck but we know the destination is the Shield Mall.
Have you found a blowtorch yet?
Use the keycard you picked up and enter the room. Just be ready to silence anyone inside.
Thank you!
You guys really ARE the Payday Gang!
Can one of you please, when time permits, swipe the keycard in the lock?
Got memories of this place at 4am...
No need for tip-toeing now. I'm sending the drill.
OK, you heard the Captain. Find the computer. Enter the GPS coordinates. Let's get her moving.
My associate is ready for you. Just go to the apartment to make the deal.
See if you can find a way down to the basement and keep a lookout for the alarms.
Alright, now hook that hose to the vault.
Get me hooked up again.
It was a bit of a bumpy ride, but it turned out a-ok. We got the flash drive and the gold as a bonus. It should give you some nice cash to get started again.
He bought it. Fix his leaks.
Bring the laptop to the AA gun. See if you can hook it up.
Grab those bags, gang, come on!
Dammit, SWATs have hit the ground floor, coming from the left staircase.
Guys, you got guards coming. Take them out before they find anything.
God damn!
This will hit their computer network and increase your chances of success.
Alex, get a grip!
Who the fuck said you could come in here!?
Either get on the chopper or find some more loot!
Stick to the plan! Get inside the main building!
You can either look for more loot or get out of there now.
That reads correct. Thanks for your assistance.
All right. Good. But the door's got two locks - one for Mitchell, one for Wilson. You'll need a codebreaker on the second lock.
Quickly friends, grab the box.
OK OK, truck's about to leave... You better tag it if you think that's it.
Yes, sir, will do. Thank you!
You'll find it on the bottom floor.
Ok, coast is clear. Coming in.
What the hell! Don't run away from me!
Eleven bags!
Look around. The codes must be written somewhere. I can't stall them forever!
Once you start, you'll only have a few seconds to take out all the cameras.
I'll get that one! Go get another!
I'm gonna drive a spike through your eye!
Don't feel bad for the cops. They need to learn that Christmas isn't about getting gifts. Unless you're us, then it totally is!
Escape time, friends! We got what we came for!
Hurry up with the coke!
Now you gotta clear the runway by blowing the gates!
Get everyone into the chopper!
...have a look in the dumpers at the construction site outside, yeah?
They stopped the drill!
There's your ride. Once you've got all the loot secured, you gotta get it refueled.
Restart the shutdown, friends.
OK folks, we just need one more bag for Hector and we're good to go.
Better find that computer, friends.
Wheelman is moving. ETA: One minute.
Did you really think you could capture me?
Ugh! Wrong valve, chops. Let's start again.
SWATs incoming from the lumber mill. Keep them away!
Ah! There it is, but hold up a second. Those tiles are pressure sensitive - stay off of 'em. You can use that circuit box to make a safe path across.
Now, the drive is encrypted. It would take us months to crack. But we can bypass that. Wang should have the encryption protocol on his laptop. If you use that, we'll break open that baby in a flash.
There's an override switch in the security office. It closes the bank's shutters. That's gonna help you keep the feds out of the bank.
That's one bag!
Search around for the Tin Boy toy!
I got another idea: Finders keepers, assholes!
Ok, now mount the tanks onto the vault.
Almost enough.
What's happening with those drills?
Now make your way to the West Wing and find the Oval Office!
OK, guys, Vlad has arranged a way into the bank for you.
One down.
... then, we'll trade.
Now, if I understand. As it pertains to my business idea for free bar for my friends, your answer is no?
Look for the manager. Balding, black suit. Tie him down and see if he has more information.
I admit I thought it would go this well.
They're on our ass like we're pulling a fucking trailer!

As you know, intelligence and information is my business. And I recently came across something important that concerns you. the Payday Gang. Someone is out to destroy you, possibly kill all of you. This morning I intercepted a message indicating that an agent of these people is meeting someone at a certain location downtown. I don't know yet who these people are, but as you know, I find you a valued asset, and so I want to help you apprehend this agent so you can squeeze information out of him. I'll give you the location and then keep an eye on you while you conduct the operation.
Pilot just landed the passenger. You can go home!
It will be here! Keep up the search!
Put a call through to Fed Central. And let me do the talking.
Those Murkies will be rather angry when you return, but we'll deal with that later.
Just be alert with that server room door open... They'll know something up...
I know the only thing he loves more than barbeque is shooting trespassers. Don't let him spot you. He ain't the asking questions" type."
Alright, that's enough...
Perp is in custody, over.
Hang on... oh... they've got additional security blocks here. You gotta find a security switchboard and rewire it.
I got to leave in a minute!
Sometimes the direct route lacks finesse, yet is still remarkably effective.
They're on to us like a fucking sticker!
You got to find those shoes!
Let's put this boat in the water and find out if it leaks.
Fuckin' Locke, always gotta spoil the fun.
Blerrie police reached the IT guy and made him stop overriding the lock. Get in there and make him finish!
You've got to keep at least 2 bags!
Come on, get to that garage.
Sorry, friends.
Hurry up if you have more - I don't want the cops to find the car!
Hey! What are you doing to my stuff?!
Maybe there's a utility closet or something nearby with a toolbox you can use. Go have a look.
One bag in! You've done the bare minimum!
Great job, friends! That's both boxes. Head back to the entrance so that I can get you out of there.
I'm done with the first box.
Kerels have pulled the emergency power cutoff lever. Find and reset it, friends!
Don't wait too long with that door, friends.
Lekker! That's the spot. Cut through the top layer with a saw, yeah?

Welcome to the sunshine state! Where the women are gold diggers and the men are crooks. Meet Mr. Mitchell: on the surface, a golf coach for a respectable country club. Under the surface, a professional money launderer and counterfeiter - a master criminal. Mitchell and his partner in crime, Wilson, have managed to stay under the radar literally making millions. Until now.
Murky dwankies coming your way!
Vlad's reputation will rise. You guys will get a nice little payday from this.
Grab the box, friends.
Good, you are on track! Keep going.
You made a bad mistake!
Don't tell me you killed him...
... I'll be back in a little while!
We played here back when Harry's Wine Box stood here. That was '73.
Get to the chopper!
Whoever they are, it seems they chose poorly in ambushing me.
Run, heisters, run!
At private airport my men arrested by FBI. They were with weapons from old country, Kalashnikov and so on. My money is gone but weapons still there.
Well, not ideal, but we managed to steer the election a bit and make people uncertain of the legitimacy of the result. The Elephant will get what he wants, I think. Now it's time to get paid.
There's a machine in the lab for testing oil purity. Use it on the sample you just took.
Do you have the contents of the safe?
...Get those civvies under control, cop cars are about one minute out, friends.
Good job! Now you need to clear the elevator shaft. Go down to the garage and call the elevator.
Vault access has been disabled. You'll need to hack the control panel to get in. Should be nearby.
C'mon, let's get you out of here. Oh how is he even still alive?
Maybe if you dog-whistle, Ralph will come out.
The security system has shut down vault access. You need to override it. There should be a panel nearby with controls that you can hack to get inside.
Doing good... They haven't noticed anything...
Well forget the quiet route...
Wait a blerrie minute!
That's five bags!
Getting the skid loader onto the deck of the ship will be a problem.
Motherfuckers!
Locke wants us to blow that door. Better drop the charges off there.
Throw the BFD's switch! Let the show begin!
Okay, follow me, but stay out of sight.
Good money coming in today.
Okay, what's next...
Those crafty fuckers are dropping grenades into the sewers.
Start hauling those bags to the vault, gang. Time to crack this place.
Closing in!
Aw, NO!
Let's do this faster, guys!
Clock's ticking, you chops! Get through the first gate!
That was some damn good sneaking, Dallas. I am impressed.
Those charges must be hooked up to the four locks. I am sure you don't need walking through the procedure.
Fuck me sideways!
You guys are Godlike. Keep it coming.
Gentlemen - an opportunity to change the world awaits. Your effort will count!
This is the police. We are ready to trade for the asset and are prepared to raise our offer.
Fancy giving me a hand up north while I buy som hardware?
Get up on the roofs, friends. Maybe you will see things clearer up there, yeah? You'll probably need a ladder to get up.
Time to get those tonsils checked guys. We're going to Mercy Hospital.
Okay, the rowdy way it is!
Just wait and see guys, this is gonna be great.
The light must stay on, so the pilot knows you're ready to go.
I know you want to put a bullet in his face, but you got to stay focused, yeah?
Great! You can use this ladder to get up on the wagons.
Gang, there's a construction yard across the river! Got a truck parked up. Reckon it's our best way out. Sending you C4 now. Protect the safes!
You got some of that somewhere?
Clear the path. Clear the trees!
Damn kerel cut an RFID wire! You'll have to reboot the hack.
Umm... help me out with this door, guys.
Snipers are inbound!
No time to waste, chops! Lower the transfer hose!

Now we're getting into the bank vault. This job is about deposit boxes. You need to get in there and drill that vault. Case the bank first. They're wired out the ass with security cameras and trigger-happy guards.
Okay. Mask up when you're ready.
That's enough. Now put a gas can on it and shoot it to light it up!
Go hit up Crime.net when you are ready.
The drill is in the area. Get it, and get it to work on that vault.
I hear ya. Alright, no problem. Just try and keep us in the loop next time.
Try the locker room for uniforms!
Think you can figure out how to put those weapons together? I believe in you.
Two minutes and I am out of here!!
Mr. Sturr if you hear me, don't toss them. You are only hurting your chances.
I think it's time we leave, don't you?
Alright, fuck it...
Don't forget to wipe out any Russian mobsters you find.
You're all dead men!
Christ, look at this place!
Maybe if you cut the power nearby, he'll come investigate what's going on, yeah?
*grunts, wheezes*
Nice! Now, hurry over to the vault. Chop chop!
Keep the cops away from the terminal guys.
This is it, gang. They're throwing everything they have in to this. Get out of there!
I need partner to collect my money I left behind... While time in restricted house.
...They don't suspect anything yet.
They keep the USB stick somewhere secure. Look around.
Get him the tiara and take everything else in the place if you have time... Lot of incidental income you don't want to waste. Just once you decide to make your move, make it fast.
Now you're gonna take that present, bring it over to my sled! It's gonna be sick!
And... bam!
Nothing can now stop Vlad - nothing! I will be the king of this city and my men will be my army to use for good profit. Perhaps you see us on news. You will smile, and I will also, also smile...
We are going to party. Party all my former money from my (asshole) competitor. You will help?
For now, just enjoy the view. We'll put more in here, I promise.
I'll take your word for it.
Your getaway is all ready. There's a bridge just down the road, and Twitch is on the other side, with a truck. Just drive right up into the truck and we are done!
Blerrie! Murky bastards!
Get the briefcase! The thermite will burn right through that gate.
I'm gonna need the car key here, guys.
Ey, you sleeping?
You won't find a better New York steak anywhere, including New York.
Now get that winch put together in the main hall.
By the barbecue. That's our man.
I'm there in 3 minutes.
Just keep yer lid on. Let me find all the files you need to sign off on.
Gang? I'm not sure you can hear me, but you know what you're supposed to do: enter the laboratory via the hatchet.
Everything else is gravy.
Hot damn! Commissar, you dirty old Bertie.
Just put the ticket back in the gate and we're home free!
Hey, I was jamming to that! What happened to the damn radio?
There's a network of RFID wires on the wagon's exterior. Keep them safe.
Something wrong with that computer. It's not connecting. Damn MurkyDOS. Try another one.
Okay, think the bridge is looking good for a drop point.
You have to open up that ark-dinges.
Alright, that's it for the concert. Time to de-mask and blend in with the crowd. If all goes to plan, you'll be able to stroll right out the front door. Good luck.
Eye on the ball. Fire it!
Make sure the car is in the correct position by rotating the platform.
Get some eyes on that vault.
The bomb is now just sitting there. Restart it!
Keep an eye out for the chopper.
Looks safe now, go ahead.
Thank you. That was getting a little... uncomfortable.
Ah hell. Heat is on the way. Guess the cops were watching the place.
That thermite you picked up before should work.
Now get rid of that evidence. There must be a way to destroy it here in the station.
Okay, there's the ingredients. Going to need a little extra in there, though. More than one bag.
More loot than I expected. Good work!
Careful guys, time's running out! 10 seconds!
Get to the control room - the black heart of the facility. From there, you can open the vaults and grab all that, as you say, 'good shit'.
Woo! Now that was a show! Rainey's probably shaking in her damn boots right about now.
No more wall. Go on in.
... then, we'll trade.
Wrong wagon. Crap! Keep looking!
Next step - open the vault. Find some crowbars inside the warehouse and jam them into the cooling fans at the back. That'll raise the temperature within, and engage the failsafe.
That wasn't right. You need to try a different combination, yeah?
Hey Dentist, you around here somewhere?
Bile is en-route with the lance. Hold the line!
Can't reach that one, get me another one!
Alright alright, two!
Keep looking for the vault.
Let's access that shipping manifest, yeah?
Damn! This was the wrong pc! Cops are on their way. You don't have much time now.
...Hack into a mainframe computer terminal and try to find some clue where to begin searching, yeah?
Get the target to the tower!
Gang. Use the radio. Let me speak to our ship.
Nice, you should be able to go back and try the hack again.
Start a hack on the computer. We can set up an overload on the keypad so you can get into the warehouse.
Keep an extra eye out for Murkies.
They're sending in Minigun Dozers too!
I'm here, where the fuck are you?
Great, you found some thermite. Now we can melt our way through that steel gate.
Coming in now - just can't tell you what dock yet!
Good. We're in business again.
Now, we convert this preparation into success.
Oof! He won't be doling out voice samples any time soon. Get back to the laptop. We'll need to find another way in.
More coppers coming soon. Blonde needs that bag.
Another twelve and we're done.
Look out above, friends! The beast cometh from on high!
Keep low until they've cleared out.
The deal's off!
Check roofs, buildings, car parks - all those kinds of places. That pallet is around there somewhere.
Fucking hell!
Gha, find the breaker and get the juice flowing again!
I gotta admit it's been a while since I broke into a place this loudly. It's gonna be jol!
And...
C'mon friends, grab the donnerse and get out of there!
OK, there's the C4. Help yourself!
I had a guy bribe one of Buluc's old girlfriends. You can apparently find the way to open this door in something he calls his inner sanctum". So
column3: maybe find the entrance to that place first

String: We've seen those symbols before.
Remember guys, you're looking for the head of security. We need his USB stick.
Damn, they have seen us! Action guys!
The game is on, motherfuckers!
Come already...
Keep looking for that computer.
Get into the warehouse.
My man is going to leave the thermal drill you need for the job out back. Good luck.
The escape's all ready! Back to the locomotive, friends!
First thing we need to do is access the server room. We've got intel saying that a worker near the helipad is in possession of the keycard.
SWAT van on the way.
Be careful around that C4 guys.
I don't know what's taking you guys so long, but that coke is NOT waiting around for you.

Our client needs a blood sample from a patient being kept in the isolation ward of Mercy Hostpital. You gotta go in there, take out the surveillance, subdue the civilians and get me into the patient database so I can ID the guy. With the low security in this place, it should be a nice, clean job. I'll get you out via the roof when you're done. This job is a little shady, brokered through a third party- got some serious shadow-company military industrial vibes, but worth the risk. The payday is something we're gonna need in the future, plus a nice cash bonus.
All right, now let the winch do its job.
Come on guys, let some sunset into that garage.
Search the warehouse, the vault is there, you can't miss it.
Wait until you hear my Texas accent! You won't even recognize me.
That was superbly done. Quiet and effective. Excellent work.
Whisky Tango Foxtrot One on the scene. Be there in...
The Mendozas are down there. Cut that fence and get those guns.
The curtain controls are locked tight. This doesn't seem like a security issue. Maybe Reception has the key?
That's every single one of 'em! That's great!
Now, run that sample through a testing machine down in the laboratory. It'll tell us if this batch is pure.
Turn off Garrett's lights, friends.
Ah shit, I've got to move the car!
What about taking the manager's fingerprints off something with a piece of tape, so we can bypass the scanner quietly?
I can't access the network until you hack the computer.
These fuckers are going down!
You come here to fuck our shit up?
Ah! There it is! Now, please, out of the airlock and into the inner complex!
Time to bring in the Beast! Get outside and clear the square!
You really need to find a keycard to get that door open. Come on.
Damn, they rigged the boxes with C4! Defuse them!
Dasvidaniya!
Our plan to get Gabriel's keycard is pretty nasty, but then again, he's a nasty guy. To start, turn off the security lasers outside his command center.
Use the flash drive we stole last night and get going.
Woah, look at this stuff. It can't be real... Can it?
Someone narced on us...

I've traced the truck to a warehouse out by Goose Island. It's a distribution depot, contracted to ship the voting machines to their final destination. With a little technical wizardry, we're going to make those machines a bit more sympathetic to The Elephant's mayoral candidate - that slimy ballbag McKendrick. Get in there, get them hacked, get out - simple. Once again, The Elephant is extending his stealth bonus if you can keep it quiet.
Fuck it, they were waiting for us?
Who are these fuckers?
You gotta get some more gas in that donnerse pump.
You need to get the power back up, friends!
That should do it. He won't be back soon. Thank the culinary spirits for bad chili, yeah?
Ok, I'm in. Give me a second.
That was very innovative. No one suspected a thing and the ballot machines are in play - ready to swing for the fence! Thank you.
Reboot the charge cycle.
Get ready!
Hold em off!
Bastards! I'm gonna fuck you up for this!
OK, the card reader is up and running again, now you need to find the keycard for it.
I don't think of myself so much as a politician - I think of myself as a warrior in a suit.
The Oval Office is right there, so get inside.
Right, this is the place. Get to the traincar and look for your contact. They said they'd meet you there. So far it all looks good. Just trade the paintings and get out fast. Keep it rolling.
Can't do anything without power!
When the pipes are ready, pull the lever on our tank.
I can't decide if I should have him killed, or send him a big fucking cake full of money. Whaddayouthink?
Ha! It's the clowns! It's the fucking clowns from the news!
Another four and we're done.
Have a closer look at that shrine.
You're gonna die, motherfuckers!
That's the last fan. Man, look at that temperature climb. I got a bad feeling about this.
They fucked with the wrong people now...
The code is split onto three laptops.
Another closet. Great. That lock won't give you problems.
Trouble in the air, friends. Coast Guard helicopter. Take it out.
You'll need to hack the door. Place the hacking device!
Come on you chops, signal our contact so we can get that platform going. Remember, use the light by the window.
I think you'll have to hit him to wake him up.
Farewell, momma. Farewell, darling Russia... Urrrrggghh.
Look for a code that starts with two.

Kerels are going to go bossies when they see what we are after, and will be coming after us in droves, so keep your eyes peeled and take them down fast. The longer you can keep them at bay, the more desperate they'll get and give us a bigger load of cash, yeah?
The boxes are rigged with C4! Defuse them quick!
Abducting goats is a federal offence.
Fuck you, go fucking drown in vodka.
Where the fuck are you guys? How the hell did they know we were comin'? I'm comin' to the warehouse... got capped.
For crying out loud, the pilot has hit the deck again. Wake him up!
C'mon guys, get that guy to the roof.
We did it once, we can do it again. Get in there, and boost that art, clowns.
You make more ruckus than a bear that once woke me while I was camping in the jungle.
Alright, I'm coming back soon.
Say your prayers and say 'em fast!
Time to prepare the next component.
Time to juice up that plane. Get the fuel hose connected.
They're keeping the weapon prototypes in these barns. Check around, see what you can find.
Out-goddamn-standing, crew! Get in, fill your bags. Take as much as you can, but remember, we're here for The Dentist's loot.
All mooring ropes must be taken off.
C'mon guys, let's change the change!
Guys, it feels like something's in the air... Money!
Time to get those warehouse doors open and pull Vlad out of there.
I say we work smarter, not harder. Rig those windows with C4, and I'll trash the lab with the push of a button!
Roger that, Broadsword. Approaching for a roof pick-up. Over and out.
Maybe we can't swing the votes - but we can stop them from being cast. We hit the ballot machines at the mall.
Good job! Now drop off the loot into the vent leading into the basement area.
Just fight to the front of the plane, up the stairs and then all the way back. It's the only way to reach those controls.
You're still in the blast zone! Get to the tanker!
The roof? Are you fucking nuts, Sensei? I'm not doing that.
You are one stupid asshole!
That's it! I can't stay any longer!
I see one!
Great, that one's hacked. Get that crate closed, then find another.
Ok, now get the keycard from the auctioneer. Quietly.
Things are heating up... Those are snipers!
Prying that open felt really good. Now check what's underground!
Hack those machines, guys. Each corrupt machine will pile more pressure on Schwartz.
That's the door, and there's the code lock. See if you can override the system.
Whoa, another explosion! Look out!
Holy motherfuckin' shit! That shit fuckin' rocked! Whoooooooooooo!
As you wish.
I'm coming... Three... Yeah three minutes away!
Gonna punch your ticket for ya!
... we'll take what you have.
Halfway there guys, keep going!
Time to go, friends! Get to the boat before this whole place goes up!
Don't forget sneak a peek in the Executive Office.
It's time to go, friends!
The bags will be perfectly safe with me. Send them up, please.
Almir's burgers, what can I get you?
Let's get you to finding that vault, now.

We got a bank here. Not a big branch but I've learned the vault is temporarily holding stacks of cash in transit. Foreign exchange notes. Anyway, you know how to do it - your way. Sneak in silent, or unleash hell. Either way, I got a little idea for how to lift the money out of there. You'll see what I mean. I think you'll like it.
Hold on for a bit and let the thermite work.
You poes need to find a fucking ladder. Fuck me. Come on!
We're done here, there's a van waiting on the other side of the building. Go on through, load the car up, and we're done.
Damn it, gang! You have less than a minute now!
And now we wait for the vault timelock to run down. This is a secured site, you know.
That chute there can transport the loot to the back rooms of...
... Hang in there!
Nice night for a barbacoa. Shame the cartel dwankies know we're crashing it!
I reckon the safe house could do with an extra bob or two, in case you find something nice to bring back.
Start searching for that Murkywater nest egg. It's in the form of weapons.
Find Valentine's desk and computer.
They're pushing us off the road!
Here come the cops!
Come on already! We need more bags!
All gone! Now let's go get our friend out. He should be close by.
You gotta get into the warehouse.
Great. All the safes are in. Now let's see the truck back at the yard, gang - hustle!
Our guy likes Red Dragon scotch. Find it, spike it and serve it.
They're shooting at me!
What the fuck... Cops!
Great, the drills are through.
Don't let the mercenaries stop the scanning process!
Protect the drill from the kerels.
Nice. That's the first batch, but we'll need more. Get after the rest.

OK you chops, time to get some payback for Vlad and make a kakspul of cash doing it. The Black Cat will be in international waters in a few hours and we're going to clean it out. Jiu Feng has an insider working as a barman, and has arranged to help us with gear and intel on shipboard operations. We know that they have put Xun Kang, the piece of kak who tortured Vlad, on the ship because the triad is extra vulnerable and he's one of their best. We also know the casino onboard is being run by a dwankie named Li Deng, who is apparently a bit of a boisterous buffoon and not held in high regard within the Golden Dagger. Both of them likely share security clearance. Once you're on the ship, you will need to conduct a tight operation because the coast guard is patrolling the area and they'll have kerels onboard before you can say Look
I'm here now. I'm here! Get the bags into the boat.
Head to Florida and muscle in on a counterfeiting job.
Shit!
That's half of 'em.
Leave the damn goats alone, clowns!
Cameras will set of the mines, guys! Stay away!
Computer is in sight, and the room seems to be clear.
Head for the elevators, break the doors open, and hook up the ziplines.
Now, rise, my friends!
Get inside the airlock, quickly!
OK guys, time to leave!
You got to move faster than that!
Don't let them run off!
Get the bags to the van to secure them. Don't let the cops run away with your hard earned meth!
The drill has been shut down! Get it working again!
You must have shit for brains, comin' here!
Our escape by helicopter is imminent, but we must cover ourselves. Beyond the door Murkywater has an impressive array of radar equipment.
Back to where it all began. First World Bank.
We're here. Get ready to scare 'em, crew.
...caustic soda?
That's it friends, good work.
This trojan is elegant and simple. It will be deployed to their systems.
The Elephant will be very excited. That's his campaign funding by big oil until 2050 right there. Very professional, folks.
Open the boxes. Our client demands one bag, but your professional honor demands you take as much as you can.
Dompkops! You weren't supposed to kill him!
Don't give the cops a damn thing - just signal Hector's guys with the flood lights in the warehouse and get that coke onto the speedboat. Nothing fancy here.
Come on you chops, get to the casino vault.
I don't feel so good...
That goat is an important witness. Drop it. Now!
Great. Now bring on the waterworks!
If you pull this escape off, you'll be taking the term train heist" to a whole new level."
Back to business. Find those weapons, and be careful this time.
Holy.....nice work! Okay, there's the exposed vault. Get the cutter on there.
What the... intruders! You're going down!
Charge up the cannon again.
OK, bustin' outta here!
Two in the box, ready to go.
Loot secure! Now get out of there so I can detonate the C4.
...bring all the winch parts into the vault room.
Stop this madness and lay down your weapons!
If you believe in a higher power, you tell him we need him!
Look for clues in Garrett's investigation, yeah?
They would probably want easy access to the tunnel, so check around outside.
Army's sending a team to blow up the tracks! If you don't get outta there fast, you ain't going nowhere at all!
We're about to test this ride's air bags!
All right, good find. Now get that gas all over the tires.
This is crazy, the hospital is surrounded. Looks like private military... mercenaries. You gotta go... NOW.
There's no way the Golden Dwankies will recover from this.
It feels bad to leave the gold, but we will get paid. Maybe we can return.
Use the manual to find which cable to cut, yeah?
Get the drill going again.
Come on now...
Who is this? Who the fuck are you?
You really need to take a look at that vault.
A minute.
Sound the alarm! There are rats on the premises!
He only had a week left on his contract.
Put the product in the car...
Find that evidence yet?
You still need to bypass security, so find those two routers!
Have you found the control panel yet?
You're not going to have a look behind the doors?
Great. Now just wait for that time lock to run down. So far this is textbook stuff. Be ready to bag the cash when it opens.
Look in the cells and the interrogation rooms.
Public office. Wow, we are in the wrong line of work gentlemen.
Feeding the fish, eh?
Time to start looking for that stash of Murkywater contraband. It's weapons we're after.
Confirmed! I'm coming in at dock seven!
Making money ain't that hard.
If you need more C4, take a look in the stash outside again, yeah?
The bank has shutters which can be closed from the security office. They should help you keep the police at bay!
Going!
Nicely done! Secure the Neo-2 so we can sell it to Keegan.
Ready guys?
I think the wine cellar is a good place to look for fertilizer.
Make it count guys!
Good, now use the cameras inside to locate which cell Bain is in.
These fuckers are trying to rip us off!
The fuck do you think you're doing!?
Stay clear of the guards.
You'll need a crowbar to get those elevator doors open!
OK, I'm in the area, but the cops got snipers on the roofs all around the building. You need to get rid of those before I can drop the C4.
Sure as shit. He figured out which of the ranch hands was Gemma's insider, messed him up 'til he spilled the beans. You heard Rainey's voicemail. Gabriel wants nothing more than to take y'all on.
Looks like it's working. Will take some time before it's full.
Keep the civilians away from the alarms.
This is Jen at GenSec. Our systems picked up an unscheduled activation of your time lock. I'm just calling to confirm everything is fine.
You need to find Buluc's office.
That's what we heard, yeah.
If there were more crews like you I think the world would need to store its valuables elsewhere.
Prolonged exposure can kill, so you gotta decide if you want to risk going in now or wait it out.
The crane can lift the firetrap container. Look for the controls.
Shit!
Damn. Was kinda banking on you saying yeah.
Watch the entrances, friends!

Bain left me instructions just in case something went wrong. I've double-checked and the warehouse meeting spot still looks quiet, for the time being. Hole up there while I try to find out what's going on.
Okay. Time to head back to the trains and get that EMP in the bag.
You got to fetch some gas and torch those cars.
That's the head of security. He seems to be by the driveway.
All those pretty automobiles...
I choose only reliable associates. One of them will be waiting for you.
Hey, I'm here in the back now. Hurry up and get me any loot you want secured.
Get the gear from the trunk. Fuel the car, and use that jack to hoist it up.
Can't be 100%, but I think that's right.
OK, get into that tunnel. Time for a visit to Mexico.
Look for the cases, break them and bag the jewels.
This is Captain Rogers at Precinct 8. GenSec have raised a concern, regarding some suspicious activity. I'm sending officers over, just as a precaution.
*Cries*
These machines are small fry. We're here for a bigger prize.
You gotta make sure those Murkies don't interfere!
Ooh, friends. Looks like rain is coming. Don't want to ruin those nice Murky uniforms, so get inside.
That's Russia for you, gang! These guys do not mess around!
Our driver is taking heat, guys.
Get ready friends. More will be coming.
For a while there, I was earning more per hour than the Benevolent Bank.
Now, get that wall open! The explosion will trash the voting machines.
Time to go get Vlad's money.
They didn't even see us coming. Great work! See you at the safe house.
There's got to be a cylinder with some kind of gas around there you can use.
Door is unlocked.
The truck driver's in position. Go pack up the guns.
Maybe check the walls?
Okay, now wait for the pilot.
There's a zip-line to the crane here. Hope you're not scared of heights.
You have the code, now we need the hand print.
That looks about right. Grab it!
We're gonna make your rest of your life real short!
Don't forget to hide the body.
Friends, you got to tell me what all the fuss is with those fish tacos. Sounds pretty awful if you ask me. Maybe if it were shark fins...
I'm sending Bile your way!
Crap! Just plant the C4 at the other spot. It's a sure thing now.
Hello, what's this...?
Good! But it will be a long minute!
Tricky business. GenSec started mandating everyone wear 'em.
Gotta get a look at that security camera feed, yeah?
Come on! Get ziplining!
Um... John... Smith. Keep an eye out, gang. Company is coming.
All the shooting make you deaf. Skipping class!
Crap, the cops must have recieved a call.
Xun Kang, status?
Waste 'em!
We screw 'em over, snatch both Taxman and the server. With those, we'll make a $25,000,000 hack. Alex, crane ready?
Aw, for sure?
SWAT responders, coming in hard. Dig in.
Ach, dwankie amateurs, keeping secure codes on USB sticks! Told you, didn't I? Have a look around and see if you can find it.
No standing around. Find the plane, quickly.
Head for the roof right away!
No need to be quiet now.
This is the McKendrick Museum, how can I help you?
You're so dead!
I've got someone waiting for you ouside in the sewers. You'll need some thermite to get through.
I'm sorry, I don't think providing a loan, to buy guns, to rob a bank, is very sensible.
Fuuuuuuuuuck!
Have you found that keycard yet? Maybe see if it's in the office.
We're almost there, gang. It's filling up nicely! Just keep things going a little more. Once it's full, we rig it and enjoy the show!
The gun is ready to go, mash the fire button and enjoy the show.
Secure as much gold as you can, yeah?
Quicky, restart the hacking routine.
This is the deal, right here:
Take the cable and attach it to the vault.
30 seconds guys!
You guys are fucking with the wrong people!
If you move across the roof into the next building, I can meet you there.
Enter the code, friends. Have you forgotten it or something?
The escape will be there in nine minutes.
Well, if you want your merchandise back you will not interfere with the operation. Old Locke doesn't need any backseat pilots!
The system's firewall caught up with us. Get to a computer, shut it down.
This oil will work fine!
Over here!
Good, that did it! Now get to the vault!
You have to go into the office.
I'm eavesdropping now, letting you know what they say.
What are you waiting for? That switch isn't gonna pull itself.
Gang, we need to do this right; both the Taxman and the server is needed, otherwise it all goes to shit. Make sure he has the server on him.
What the fuck are you doing? Answer the pager.
There in....
The van will be there in about two minutes.
Having trouble picking a direction?
The kerels fought hard, but we fought harder. We always do.
Ouch! Careful with that crane, guys. This is a gem of a building.
Kill all the rats on that bus. Hector wants no one to step off at the next station.
Achhh! The paw-paw courier forgot the winch! I'll have to get one to you by train. Keep looking up, yeah?
OK, now you gotta get into the control room.
Yes?
And yes I know. Out of the frying pan, into the fire...
The message has been delivered. Ernesto Sosa is dead. Your work here is done.
We'll settle for this right here.
Gang, you need to locate that turret.
Blerrie chops are getting desperate!
Wait!
They probably keep the evidence files in the chief's computer. Try the upper floor.
Help me get the goats into the barn.
Let's get those plates today, yeah?
Aight check it, this is waht the deal is:
They used a bus to smash right through there!
Get to the wine cellar, chop chop!
Murkywater are trying to sneak a shipment of gold out of their warehouse. You guys up for an ambush?
Over there!
Two ways to go about this, gentlemen. Go loud - you know how to do that. But if you're hoping to raise your game, look for two keycards and unlock the vault. Car trunks are a good place to look.
Get into the house and see if you can find Hector's cooks.
Remember guys, we need three bags to escape.
ETA is three minutes.
Grab all the research documents on the Neo-2!
Grab the artifact, make sure that the kerels don't get their hands on it.
You're all dead men!
Pretty loud, yeah?
I need access to their systems. I've marked out a computer for you.
Another camera here.
Get a drill going on that vault door, yeah? What we need is somewhere inside.
You did good. Better than I thought you would, to be honest. We got what we came for, and I bet we can get a good payday from that gold you stole. Should be more than enough to get you started again.
I need you guys to distribute the violence, yeah? My uniform should let me blend in with them, keep out of the fight.
It's got to be here somewhere! Keep looking!
Great job - it's got all the info on where the money's hidden.
What the hell! It's the cops!
My, that door is a beast. See if the armory has something that can help you break it.
I like the way you're thinking.
You... chop! You gotta listen when Locke warns you!
The key is not going to work any longer, you gotta use a drill, friends.
Shit! Shit! Shit! Shit!
Stop them following. Set off the trap!
Standard response is to get a strong line of armor in there, so expect bulldozers up ahead. Get ready!
The Murkies are headed towards you. Lock and load.
Should be easy to find. It's in the warehouse.
Head up to the apartment, my associate has the info and the cash to pay for the extra meth.
On my way, boss!
So what? You thought it was a good idea to just leave them there? Alright gang, go get 'em.
Keep looking, keep looking...
Cops are at the arena. Stay frosty, gang.
You've defeated the eighth wave of cops!
...caustic soda, friends?
Radio's going crazy. Cops all around!
Yo, Listen here:
Right guys, if you make your way out by the Big John's Burger Joint, the cops will hopefully follow you so that Blonde can get the car out of there.
What the fuck did you guys steal!?
What are you waiting for!?
Up!
No! Stop that!
Damn SWAT van is blocking the route! Move it!
Good, now it's time to leave. Get onboard that dinges, quickly!
Control yourselves! You'll end up chewing through metal until next week!
I confess I was a little worried there. Thank you.
Remember that movie where one person in the lift goes bossies and just eviscerates everyone?
That's it! I'm off now!
Come on, get that gate open. You've seen the type before, surely.
That's all of 'em! Nice!
R.G. here.
Tiaras, nuclear warheads, and safes. Just another job for Vlad.
You need to set off some fireworks to signal Jiu Feng!
Move the gold! Let the crane get it on to the truck.
Good, OK, the reaction seems fine, keep going.
Use that crane to lower the transfer hose.
Chavez won't have any use for that coke anymore, so take it if you want.
One of you should keep an eye out for those snipers at all times!
Could be those safe deposit boxes have some extra valuables we can use, yeah? Maybe you can get into them while you wait for the vault to open?
OK, we can leave now, but try and take it all if you can.
Keegan's insider left some gear to help you cut the command center's airflow. Should be easy enough to find.
Pilot is down! Get him back on his feet.
As with all things, this too must end. I will see you again, my friends. Very soon.
I have a little . . . surprise interview set up with a greedy IRS employee in Washington D.C.
I'm pretty sure there's something suitable around there.
My friends, what are you doing working for that Russian. Let me go. I will make it worth your while.
The info they have will be in a briefcase or something like that. Make the trade and have them hand over the info to you. These guys are scum so keep your eyes open.
Keep emptying that vault!
They store blowtorches in the warehouse.
Your first priority is finding your ride out of there. Maybe check the hangars, yeah?

Locke has asked for help guarding a weapons transaction in Alaska. Says he's not expecting trouble, but want some reliable security just in case. Looks like it might be an easy payday if you can put up with the cold.
Three minutes.
Reboot the hack, and keep those blerrie kerels out of here!
Half the fucking police force is on our ass!
Some good old-fashioned explosives should open up the entryway in the wall behind that shrine, yeah?
Motherfuckers!
Damn! You've got to raise the balloon again.
That was easy! Now go find our friend!
The gate, friends.
So, next step is...
I got snipers incoming. Stay indoors guys!
You need fresh power cells.
All right. now throw that switch. Let's see what BFD can do!
Excellent sabotaging, friends! We're all done here. Let's head home!
You've got a security door blocking you though.

Bear with me on this. They shut down the turntable, but the on-site cargo crane is still up and running. I'm...seventy percent sure it can lift our locomotive to an open track. Get to the controls, and let's find out!
Blimp is over the city and headed for you. Give it a moment.
That was your fault, child!
There. Now just give me a minute.
Now we're talking! That sample's perfect. Beyond perfect.
If you shoot me, who's gonna feed my fish?
You need to crack open those crates.
Now let's finish this. Into the manhole, guys! Time for a sewer escape.
Bring up the shipping manifest on that computer. We need to know which brand is a front for the Army.
Doors are open for you, we are leaving!
Smack daddy in the middle. Alex dropped good.
What's taking so long?
Come one friends, throw the cocktail on the door.
Come on! Fill the barrels!
Find the Jaegerheister and spike it. Green bottle.
Not much time people! Get those bags secured before the cops take 'em. The boat pick-up is coming.
You can use pretty much any laptop to access the USB stick.
The chopper's here! Watch out for snipers when you're moving the loot!
Move the bookshelves back after checking them, or the guards will notice.
Die motherfuckers!
I'm heading off to unload these - but I'm coming back, hold on.
Muerto!
Bile is waiting for the signal, friends.
Might want to pick up the pace gang. The keycard and code are all you need.
That's it, gang. Only the fourth floor left.
You need that keycard, friends.
The cannon is ready, hit that nice shiny button and let's see what it can do!
Hurry, friends. Murky are going to swamp you if you don't get moving.
They messed with the testing machine! Fix it!
Watch out, guys! The cops are surrounding you!
Don't forget: we're looking for voting machines. My money is on them being in shipping crates scattered about.
I'll tell you what. We were never gonna deal with you guys! We'll take it all!
Don't forget to restart the hacking!
Gonna punch your ticket for ya!
The weapon will not fire until you replace the empty power cells.
Who has the second thermite can? More thermite means a hotter burn. Basic chemistry.
If they're going by the book they'll have snipers set up ahead. These cocks always go by the book.
Hurry up, guys. You know which crate we're looking for!
Get to the weapons lab. It connects to a storage room where they're keeping one of the boxes.
Arriving in two!
Someone got to the computer. Restart the hacking routine!
Got it. Doors should be open.
You clever bastards, you'll get around them using those tunnels.
Good, now hurry up and turn the lights back on or people will go bossies and sound the alarm.
Server room, yeah? Maybe if you find the person in charge of it, you can get him to bypass the lock.
Crap! Alright, forget about using the zip-line. Our guy had to run when the cops showed up.
Ah, fuck!
... I'm coming back real quick, don't worry...
The next people they send will probably be more dangerous.
Snip snip. Put that bolt cutter to the chains.
The thermite's done - about time! Now enter the vault!
Alright clowns, you got what you wanted. The money has been released and we have confirmed asset recovery.
Hey, can you report in? Hello?
I'm on the line to my accountant. We need to uh, do some laundry. Nice work.
We got regular cops and SWATs on the scene.
Here goes the next one. Hope that wasn't the one.
Out by the parking lot. Won't crack open without a saw though, but there's one of those around here somewhere.
I'm gonna kill you twice gringo!
You still have to stop the code from changing.
13 to go.
Another keycard, eh? It must open a second gold stash. Couldn't harm grabbing it too.
Come on! Fuck 'em up!
You see the chimney there? That's where Vlad needs those presents"."
... you sure are some thorough sons of bitches!
The chopper touches ground in 30 seconds. Get ready to move!
Ten seconds now!
Blerrie! Murkywater operatives are trying to block off the area, keep away from them, yeah?
One more hack should reset the lockdown.
Something wrong with hose.
Can't wait around out here - get into that building as fast as you can. Try the roof.
The keks are using tear gas! Stay out!
...my courier hid it in a dumpster on the parking lot outside.
You should now be able to see the code. Get it and go open the vault.
Inspect the walls, too!
I could give two shits about your college tuition. Well, if you paid me $50k per shit.
Blerrie, they know something is up and are scanning the building for trespassers!
Bile? I got an airlift job for you. A grab and drop, you could say.
Christ, LA's wrecked. Rubble everywhere.
You're just gonna leave the presents sitting there! Come on! Don't be that guy!
I'm sending Bile in to boost that cash out of there.
By method of elimination it has to be muriatic acid.
Get the winch hooked to BFD, gang.
Is the pickup coming? This is getting pretty hot!
Get the keys!
Let's go!
The Commissar is apparently all if I can't have it
column3: neither can anyone else". He's cornered
column4: so he has his men flush a mountain of coke down the toilets! Hurry up and stop them

String: The plane needs juice to fly.
Wow, hey! How am I supposed to do my thing like this? Take care of 'em!
One of you needs to grab the lance.
You have delivered as promised. You proposed a plan, and you executed it. Enjoy your payday. You will hear from me again.
Alarm's tripped, everyone knows what to do!
Don't worry about it. The Manager was stepping his new assistant through the process. No problem here. Least not with the lock.
You gotta get that code.
Do we really have time for this?
Guys, don't forget to get that terminal back on.
Don't get cold feet on me now! Set up those ziplines.
You made a bad mistake!
Friends, I know you still don't trust me, but we'll talk more once you're away from the cops, yeah?
Well, that usually comes with the territory for my guys, yeah?
This is it. Soon as you active the drill, return to the boat as fast as you can.
I know I'm sounding like a broken record, but don't kill him. You won't be able to trick the Control-Guy again if you try answering the pager.
Come on, let's see what you got.
We've got to stop the trains from leaving! It looks like the Army parked some humvees around the railyard. See if they're carrying explosives.
Get inside those train cars.
It's a nice piece of kit, yeah?
You need to get a blowtorch or something.
No need to catspaw about now. Get inside!
Nicely done, friends. Now follow Bain up to the roof!
Oh man, sounds like a hell of a gig in there.
Coulda put the money in real estate. Instead, I'm putting it in real asstate!
Find the cell block!
Hitting critical hits is critical!
I still require one of you poes to swipe the card.
Barbecue time! Now defend that fire!
Don't let yourself get pinned down! Move!
Wait, STOP! It's electrified!
Great. Now we need some more on the fifth floor and then some on the roof.
I'm coming in!
How is it going with the car keys?
We can't escape if our train's facing the wrong way!
The senior family of the Mendoza has sworn death upon all of you... A good sign you have now made a important impact on our cartel's future in the USA. Muchas gracias por todo, muchachos...
Four

One downtown skyway, five pounds of strategically placed C-4 and impeccable timing should give us a stranded convoy of GenSec trucks. Hit them hard while they're still disoriented. Break into the trucks and the strongboxes, and return the goodies to the escape driver.
The Captain is trapped behind door, you can break with saw.
You must find that lever and pull it.
There, now get out and crack that thing open!
Where's the stuff, man!?
The Money Thrower is so OP.
Damn, he hung up. Somewhere in the city. Keep breaking.
Find the server room. We'll try to override the security lock.
C4 is in the bins, crew. Blast the door with it.
There it is. Neatly stacked. Well, you're robbers, ain't you? Get robbing!
Alright, we're moving again. Make sure the kerels don't screw anything up.
Blerrie, you chops had to go make a ruckus, yeah? Ok, time to start shooting.
Oh no - more snipers!
You cutting though yet?
You hear that everybody? You got three minutes until he gets here. Hold them back!
You've got to hack the console! We need to get inside the display cabinet!
Activate the charge cycle on that gun.
Blerrie! What are the odds?
The first floor of the main building has a server room where you can access the camera feed to find Vlad.
What's... Hey! Don't fuck with me!
Booth team. You better be on goddamn point. I'll give the word, you'll hit the button. Comprende amigo?
That's it. Get it to the vault. Let's to this the hard way.
I need 17 more!
Bah, surveillance didn't show that. Well, you gotta get through it.
Did you press the right floor? Press the right floor!
I don't think this trash can has been emptied since Bush was in power. Bush senior!
Break into the admin office!
How much did you win? Can we all retire?
What if I come back? And bring salsa!
Kerels stopped the device. Get back and rearm it!
These are some determined fucking law enforcers!
We almost had it!
C'mon friends, get to those lights.
There is a jewelry store downtown that just recieved a shipment. You up for a smash and grab?
That was it, nicely done. The vault should be unprotected so you can resume the hack.
We know the vault is controlled by Yufu Wang's two top men. Li Deng has the code, and you need Xun Kang's handprint as well.
...Now start up the winch. And keep the coppers away from it!
That's the first one, guys. Keep working.
Some shitbag ratted on me. Dunno who, but I am sure.
Look, people! Get your shit together and get those bags secured before the cops do. The pick-up boat is on the way.
We got the address - problem is we did not get any intel. This means we are coming in hard and with no info on what to expect. Time is ticking - let's get up the mountains and steal this engine.
That's six!
Last thing we need to do is rotate that turntable. Find the controls, and keep an eye out for any workers in the vicinity. If the system needs an access card, they'll have one.
All projects run here are temporary, so a lot has changed.
Guys, we need to get that safe open.
Good, we got what we need. Murkywater and the Dentist will be in big trouble once this hits home.
Don't stay around longer than you have to... just take it and get out, yeah?
Hands off dicks, hands on button. Now!
What the fuck!? Police!
I don't know! We're just sitting here waiting. I was just making conversation.
What, he knows my brother-in-law?
I'm off in 30!
How are you coming along with that drill, friends?
Neighbors must've heard gunshots. Police signals just went nuts.
The SWAT-team is here! Dallas, you need to take 'em out!
Some insider friends have left the tools we need in a van. Go get them and head for the elevator shaft.
Gas, watch out! Wait for it to dissipate!
The gas should be gone in a minute.
Hurry up and get that statue out of there!
First thing we need to do is access the server room. We've got intel saying that an office worker has the keycard.
Nice! Comm frequencies for the Moretta. This will be useful later on, but stay focused.
Blerrie phone! If we don't want anyone checking in, we should answer it.
Shit, I missed. I'll come around and make another attempt. Hold out for another minute or so!
The wine cellar door - open it with the code, yeah?
Guys! Get to the boat!
...that's my very best guess.
Under fire! UNDER FIRE!
According to Rust, these biker keks keep lots of breaching charges around.
Ready whenever you are. I'm at the gates.
Guys, Vlad is not looking too stable, just hang in there until Jiu Feng arrives.
You gotta blow that door.
Who let them in, eh? What the fuck!?
They have tactical units here.
Hurry, friends!
Oh....Uh, yeah. Well, I guess that would be...prudent.
That Piggy Bank is ready to blow!
It's done. Now hit the button, and lower the bollards.
...for sure. Or, most likely.
Uh....that's great. Yeah, I might do a bit like that too.
Wish I were at a burger joint with my girl right now.
Get the bags to the van to secure them. Don't let the cops run away with your hard earned meth!
Get the water hose laid out all the way down to the safe.
Activate the charge cycle, yeah?
He's got some serious condition... and we need his blood.
Sit tight, it's gonna get rough!
The shells are tucked away. Nice work, I'm sending your getaway.
Something interrupted the charge cycle. You have to restart it.
I got one!
Security here is tight. We might be able to do this heist silently. But if things go loud, don't worry. I've always got a Plan B.
Your extraction is ready. Get out of here as soon as you've finished up.
Think it's almost there... Hang on... Wait... fuck! It crashed again. Get it rebooted.
First router has been hacked.
We're here for the cash, you chop. There's no time for cutting off any noses.
Vault keycard. It gets half the job done. Swipe it in the reader, and then track down the second card.
Still too much blocking the square, get it cleared!
More coppers are going to arrive unless you shut that alarm off.
The manager might have a key too. I'd wish you luck, but you don't need it, right?
We need to find a way over to the workshop.
Bile to the rescue!
What are you waiting for? The vault is open.
Good work. Just need to find one more keycard.
The saw's been tampered with!
Check the other areas and see if there's something you can use.
They're using C4 to blast those doors. Guess they don't know about all the live ammo that train is carrying.
Who's ready to do a bank job? I know I am.
They got me. But it's ok, just a minor flesh wound.
This heist will go down in legend. I'm already writing the wiki entry. It starts with 'Holy crap!'
I'm almost afraid to ask...
What the hell! It's the cops!
Don't stop looking, you kaks. I tell you the pallet is there somewhere.
Damn! Incoming security guard outside! Deal with him before he sees the broken camera and triggers the alarm!
Get those shoes!
Alright, I'm at the spot!
Cut through there with that nice blowtorch you found.
You're dead!
Can't hang around here, gang. Get the money in the box.
Gang, we need that firetrap by our escape. Use the crane controls.
Either secure the bags in the motorboat, or chuck them in the sea. We can pick them up as we leave.
My caaaar!!
Surely there has to be a way to open the crates. A crowbar or something.
Ey man, over here!
It should be acid.
All of them? Hector loves detail-oriented motherfuckers.
The gate's locked with an RFID tag. If we want to pass through, we'll need to get a look at the wiring in that box.
See if you can find Buluc's secret meeting room. The solution for getting into his office should be there.
We're gonna sail around the world, you see the boat over there? You know...put out a mill for it and, uh, I dunno... Maybe we'll put it to sea this year. Huh, we'll see.
Things are looking very good for now.
OK, chopper's coming in, get the prototype ready.
They're making a run for it! Don't let those trains escape!
You'll stand a good chance if some guys provide cover, while others work on those boxes.
Is it true what they are saying about the contractor? The Croat sniper?
My accomplice will assist you. He's waiting.
Their computer systems will be vulnerable to this.
C'mon guys, get that liquid nitrogen.
Okay, I'm trying to hack the security system now...
Turn on the engine! No point hanging around!
Look right outside the Glitter Room for one of the PCs.
Get into the house.
Damn, the door must be locked from the outside. Maybe there's another way out.
Light the flare, gang. Pilot is blind without it.
You gotta clear the area of cops or Bile won't be able to get close!
I'm dry, and I'm outta here.
This is reception. Remember where it is.
Well done. All the machines are reconfigured. The Elephant is going to get an uncharacteristically strong showing in this district.
Deng should be feeling the effects of the barman's drug by now. Unless you feel like drilling, get the key off him.
Throw the loot into the tree!
You got a blerrie death wish?! Back to the boat!
Okay, package is on the floor.
Shit this is top science stuff - use those brains - any color code, chemicals or such can be a clue.
'Course I brought it. Cabots don't hire morons.
Well, no turning back now! That was a hell of a bang! Get into that truck and do your part of the job!

On the 22nd floor of the Garnet Group Building, owned by Nathan Garnet, there's a safe with millions worth of diamonds. The building has high-tech security and trigger-happy guards but luckily for us there's a birthday party going on to keep them distracted.
OK, the chopper's coming over the convoy now, we're on a bridge - well done Alex... For once... Hit 'em and finish it. The money's ours no matter what. Get it done.
Fuck ME!
Great, now get back and get through that door, yeah?
I feel like I know you from somewhere. Post office? Come in.
Crew, you copy that? Pilot is inbound. Protect the goats.
Put all the loot you find somewhere close, so you can collect it later, yeah?
Haha, it worked! The guards in security are sleeping like babies. Don't worry about cameras now.
Hey man, I just follow orders! I don't know nothin'!
Drive through the hole on the street!
I've had it with these guys man!
They have cameras, take 'em out.
We can access the rig from the emergency dock!
Go pick up the drill and thermite. It's hidden inside the copy machine.
Caustic chloride. Says it is some solid form... Wait a... Should be that hydrogen, right?
Just one more and you're done, yeah?
An alarm got tripped! Shut it down!
A keycard, but no damn good right now. Alarm's been sounded. Stay focused on the task.
Our inside man has hidden gasoline and the gear we need in the trunk. Fuel her up and jack up the back wheels.
Ach, the pump again. Donnerse thing needs more gas.
Friends? Friends? Do you read? Blerrie, what was that? Nevermind...
Now burn some rubber!
This is interesting. Military blueprints in a GenSec transport. I'll look into it.
You can't touch me! I got protection!
Excellent! Now, connect me to the laptop. I can pull the intel Gemma needs, no problem.
It's just down here.
You need to help him get through the door.
I like the sweet sound of that! Now, leave it be for a few seconds and we should be in the clear.
Get that saw off there, friends.
This will effectively reduce the number of guards on duty.
That's a blerrie strong door, too tough for the drill. Better check the armory for something to open it with.
Now, get to the lab and test the sample's purity.
That's bag number ten!
All right. Damn. Look, just pick up the phone. Let's wing this.
Ok, the flare is lit. Great job guys, now just wait for Bile.
Gang, the cops have the city locked down. Fighting through is the only option, so we need you on the ground. That means the truck is going to stay with you.
Try to find something highly flammable to light this up with!
Kang is usually overlooking the casino from a meeting room. See if he's there.
Power's back. Now let's try this once more.
I need 17 more!
Oh. You're sure? 'Cos I kind of spent the money already.
This will cause the surveillance system to become a lot less effective.
OK, three left.
Why aren't you drilling that door yet?
The deal's off!
Gracias.
Hey now! Looks like Rainey used company funds to bribe folks at the EPA. Bet the FBI would find this email from her accountant very interesting.
Come on guys. The Butcher wants this guy dead, but don't forget, the house is full of riches too.
...Find the wall-boxes that control the blast doors, yeah?
Fuck you, the deal's off!!!
Wow, you stink of the BO, man. Been working hard recently huh?
Crack that server door!
Close, but no cigar, assholes!
These coppers ain't worth a yak's baff.
What's going on over there?
What are you waiting for? Go into the Oval Office!
Drop the goat, lawbreaker!
Chopper is on its way. Stay put.
The cannon still needs batteries.
I don't know about you guys, but I'm dying of thirst. Would any of you be a sweetheart and grab me a coke from the vending machine?
Time for a close heisting circle, yeah?
What about fucking their shit up a little?
Keep throwing them bags.
The missing server is probably lying on the desk of some IT monkey. Get down there and find it.
I guess I should be surprised to see a GenSec truck out there... But those guys seem to be spreading.
There has to be a way to destroy the evidence here in the station!
Get that container open. Hurry, friends!
Keep looking for that code, friends.
It would give me a lot of pleasure to assist you.
... when it's done, we'll give you what you want.
Now, see those lights? That's your path across. Stay on the path! Step on the wrong tile, and this gets messy fast.
Hello, First World Bank. No sir, I appreciate the offer but I think you'll find, in the small print, that we screw you. Hard!
Damn, more coke flushed. Thousands of dollars swirling away with the turds. Hurry!
Bloody dwankies found you already! Mr. Blonde, take that Porky in the back and the gang will take care of the other krels.
We have SWAT on the adjacent roofs. Dig them out.
Get to the ocean!
The power has been cut! You have to get the juice flowing again, then restart the crane.
Come on friends, get inside the building.
Ok, here comes the eighth wave!
OK I got one!
Two more minutes and I need to go!
Okay, I'm here. Just watch my back while I work!
There's the escape! Ride through the gate and you'll be safe!
We need the square cleared, chop chop!
Seems like a solid, straight fellow...
About two minutes.
If you want, grab some sapphires on the way out.
We've got your money right here. The info is in the safe. I'll open it. No funny shit or you die.
Holy shit! It can actually hold the damn thing! Ain't that a trip...
Keep looking around the place, gang. Somewhere there's something that can help nail the Commissars exact location.
Ah, blerrie. They've got those new ultra-fine detectors installed. Got to take a different approach.
Empty! Move on.
Good, now take hose to fuel pump.
Get that C4 on the pumps at the station. Then stand back. Way back.
A radio earpiece? Sweet!
Head towards the opposite side of the building.
Blerrie! The auctioneer has run off so you gotta use a drill instead. Get one on the door right away.
It landed right out in the open. Zalupa!
You need to get to hacking. Find the server room!
The Extraction Room is the best place to collect oil samples.
Couldn't be helped my friends. Just business, you understand yeah?
There's gotta be something on one of those laptops.
Hurry up and open those bars, friends!
Hahaa, cavalry's here!
I arranged a guy on standby in case you want to take the opportunity to send up some loot with a zipline.
Keep an eye on those sprinklers!
I remember the old days, when heists didn't need computers. Back then, you knew who to trust.
You will likely find Xun Kang in the casino.
Hector got the footage. I'm told he laughed long and hard. And now the FBI looks impossibly incompetent, which takes a lot of heat off of us. Great work.
You're messing with the wrong man. Mr Garnet will make you regret this.
No more stealthing it, crew. But finish the job. Get that cash out of the vault.
You now have all parts of the code.
Have you got the handprint yet?
