He really does a good kerel impersonation. Just keep following him.
Kill 'em all!
Put these sons of bitches down!
I'm fed up waiting for that meat.
You still got a long way to go!
You know I love safe deposit jobs. And this one sounds sweet...
All right, now start stashing that money in the vent!
Goddamn! Y'all are out of your minds. I love it!
Find the elves in the toyshop. You need to shout at them to get them making toys again.
Charon? What's up, you ok?
Get into the elevator with the box. Twitch is waiting for you in the basement.
Come on, crew. Get in there, grab that loot.
I got one!
What the fuck is this!?
Remember we're after the voting machines. We need to hack them to turn the favor towards McKendrick. Look for them in shipping crates.
If you find any locked cabinets, my money says the USB is in there.
You need to restart the detonator.
They locked down the office? Nothing you can't handle.
There must be a used cup around there somewhere.
A sniper team is moving in!
Yo! What the fuck! I can't work if I have these cops right in my fucking face!
Looks like we've got a jewelry store that could use a little lightening. Call me.
You need to set up fake sentry guns.
There's a keycard to open that door, somewhere. You'll need to locate it.
You cleaned it out. Time to leave.
You let the kerels get to the saw!
The turntable short circuited! Think you can fix it?
These guys got balls to be hitting us. But we'll make them pay!
Beautiful work, friends. You made less noise than my cat on that one. Now let's see what we can do with that artifact, yeah? Duke will get to looking at it as soon as you get back to the safe house.
Don't forget. Look for the ladder, dear friends.
Pick that bag up, it's some cash to start you off, get it to the living room.
Are they cops? Are they fucking COPS!?
Playing it cool. They haven't made you yet.
Keep protecting the drill.
Stay sharp, friends! They've activated a defence turret!
Traffic is backed all the way along the southbound I45. If you were planning on getting through that area, forget it.
Vlad wants a word...
Get that hack running again, yeah?
Feng is waiting to pick you up in his boat. Climb down a rope ladder from the balcony stairs.
Plant the C4 and enjoy the moment.
My eyes in the railyard say that gate's electrified. So unless you wanna get crispy, don't touch it 'til you turn off the juice.
Where's the stuff, man!?
And there's the last closet. Deal with the lock.
Alright, I got it! The storage room is now unlocked. Go get the car keys.

I hear the cops got some cool gifts this year! Wanna steal them? Of course you fucking do! Knock the presents out of the Christmas tree, and be careful when you do. The cops are gonna be extra cranky.
I'm at the security checkin by the gates. Come see me.
Empty? Blerrie, Garrett must not have gotten it from Evidence yet.

OK you chops, let's do this. There's a camera feed in the server room that you can use to locate which container Vlad is in. To find it in the compound, look in the control room for a shipping manifest that matches up.
Bet you'll find some good dirt in Rainey's Executive Office.
You gotta saw those trucks open to find the target!
Don't worry, Keegan. I'm sure we'll be back around. If there's money to be made, we'll be there to steal it!
You can use a shape charge if you have one. It's faster than the drill, someone might hear it though.
Guys! I'm waiting on the bags!
They're going to hit you with snipers!
Watch the sprinkler system!
Not sure exactly how many cameras there are.
I'm coming in two...
Crack open the back door with a saw and go through there, yeah?
Those pictures might help us later.
Not even a block away!
You know, there may be a better way in than going through the gate.
Gang, don't forget to crack those containers. Drill 'em!
This area has several vaults, which can be opened from a control room. We want what's in the vaults so necessity demands we get to the control room.
Soviet era machinery. Slow. So slow.
Any sign of that office?
Come on, you kaks! Strap the money to the chopper so I can take it away!
This better be the right one! Don't have much time now.
The keys should be nearby. See if you can find them.
All you'll have to say is Open Sesame.
Gentlemen - an opportunity to change the world awaits. Your effort will count!
They got a lock on the curtain controls? Blerrie excessive! Check the Reception desk for a key.
Keep searching for components.
Blerrie! There goes the alarm!
We still need more C4 on the fourth floor, gang.
Kang is in the meeting room. Smash it open.
Overkill, man.
Blerrie! Gas in the vault! Use the ventilation system to clear it.
Alright, I'm here!
Maybe have a look upstairs.
It might be a good idea to look around before you go loud, maybe you'll find a better approach.
Can't do much until you get inside.
Truck's fucked. I'll secure a ride out.
OK, maybe tiara is somewhere nearby. Gotta be in the building.
How about that security, friends?
That evidence won't burn without some lighting fluid!
Ok, donut boy. I'm gonna take this off and you're gonna talk, capisci? Who set us up?
Now start it up. And keep the kerels away!
Is the Commissar up to something? Get those fires out!

The Golden Grin Casino is the largest casino in Vegas. Their hard currency securities rival that of small nations - and they keep it all on-site. Gangster founders had a healthy suspicion of banks. This will require a plan. Study your options, use your intel and carry out your plan with stringency.
The drill needs some love and attention.
That's the last one! Perfect!
An active ECM jammer will probably make it hard to open the server room security door. Keep that in mind.
You can't get the code without any juice. Get the power turned on again!
Have you looked in the entire sanctum? There's a library, a lounge and even a meeting room. Buluc has thought of everything, yeah?
Ah yeah! Grabbed that motherfucker!
Ten more secs!
Get the cash bagged!
If the van is blocking, move it!
Keep those kerels from interfering.
The container belongs to the Ln Tiyng freight company. Get inside their warehouse and free our Ukrainian.
Take care of the cops in the convoy, and let's open the trucks up!
You're spotted! Fix this.
They wanna mess with me, I'll mess with them!
We know the FBI and our rival cartel, the Mendozas, are hitting our cocaine supply in DC. We need you men to ride with this transport and secure it. Make sure it reaches our boat in the harbor.
Gonna give you a faceful of lead!
Empty the safe!
Where are those blueprints, gang? Scan 'em, send 'em. You can do it in IT.
Those krels put us in the dark! Turn the power back on so we can keep decrypting!
If he's not in a cell, he might be in an interrogation room.
What are you waiting for, you chops? Get to the Oval Office!
There, that's it.

Now, if you will turn to page one, thirty-two in your Manual of Investigative Operations and Guidelines, you will see the chapter listing has been changed from the previous version. This is quite intentional, as previous versions of the text were deemed to be inappropriately convoluted, and as such made the localization of certain passages unnecessarily difficult. As we proceed deeper into analyzing the particulars of the manual, and corresponding regulations, you will no doubt note the abundance of changes that have been made.
I'm going for a drink. Let me know when you've got the box, yeah?
Come on! Fuck 'em up!
Brilliant.
Woah! That flamethrower packs a wallop! Wang means business!
Job done, guys. Now sneak back to the van and we can consider this one closed.
There, all done! Enter the vault and let's get those pardons.
Add muriatic acid, to continue the process!
Kak! The crane's got some electrical problem. Sort it out, quick! We don't want to press our luck!
I think the box is behind that vault door, so get a drill on it, yeah?
Turn off the valves at the bottom of the server rack.
Get ready for the fifth wave!
That's what we're looking for! Gotta admit I'm a bit underwhelmed by how they look, but grab them, yeah?
Yeah, there was a mix-up with a major account holder. Arrived a day early. Time zones, you know.
OK team this is it. The trucks look like they're getting ready to leave - so hurry and find the one carrying the container. GPS is ready to go. Move out.

Ok, now we don't know exactly where in the prison Bain is being held or what condition he is in, and there are Murky keks everywhere. This one is going to go loud pretty fast, yeah? You're going in through the sewer system that empties into the ocean.
There's one!
Hey! Answer the Intercom!
What the hell! It's the cops!
The cops took one of the bags!
Put the delivery in the car!
The crane isn't moving. Damn Murky has stopped it. Go and get it running again, yeah?
All things considered, I'd rather be going back to Vegas.
OK, get into that tunnel. Time for a visit to Mexico.
We are going to need ingredients, so scout the place and see what you can find.
OK, now head back to the library. There's a way into the PEOC there, and the keycard will likely come in handy.
Looks like they switched off the power, friends. You need to restart it.
Before we can do anything else, I need access to the rig's central network. Our intel says the guy with the server room keycard is working near the helipad.
You must have triggered a failsafe. Use a drill to get out again!
Flames?
Get to the West Wing, the gate should be open.
You made a mighty big mistake coming here!
OK, make sure he gets to the server room.
It's hacked. Good. Find another.
My gut feeling told me that wasn't the right ingredient... should have listened!
The pilot is refueling the chopper - he will be back soon I promise.
Get out of there. You're blocking the sun...
There's probably a laptop at the contruction site.
I'll fuck you up!
Time to take these scum out.
I got another idea: Finders keepers, assholes!
Open! Time to release the jailbird!
You're almost done, friends. Move that ramp!
Remember guys, the payoff on this one is important.
Wrong code, the alarm has gone off!
Good. Fifth floor is done.
That's how we rolled.
Good, now watch it cook!
The alarm. All right. Time for Plan B. No mercy, crew.
There's a present! Thank you, nice tree!
And....got it! Guys, I got it! Sometimes I amaze even myself.
Soda. Caustic soda. I don't think you're supposed to drink it.
I'm working on it. Almost in.
You want a loan to.....invade Jamaica...and rule it as Great Emperor. *long sigh* I don't think so.
Mitchell can we go shopping again?
Use the crane to lift the gold container onto the truck.
Hook up the hacking device to the security box.
I'm going to need some time to do this, yeah?
They stalled the crane! You have to fix the controls!
Maybe killing the lights will do it. Have a look around for a circuit box.
The weapons will need fresh batteries.
All right, it's time to leave. If you think we have enough, you can go. But it never hurts to take it all.
Get a move on. This oil rig's not going to blow itself to smithereens!
Refueling is done, so take that hose off.
Just running a red light and I'm there!
All set. Light the fuse by turning on the drill, then get the hell out of there.
That's all of them! No more bodies to scan. Now we need to get the server or we did it all for nothin'.
You hear the rumours about the sniper?
Get everyone in as soon as you are ready!
These are some determined fucking law enforcers!
Remind me again why we're doing this?
Hello, First World Bank. Of course! The current stock value is why don't you call back in an hour?
Get the generator running so we can call the elevator to the top. We'll use it to break those doors open.
Go get those blowtorches from the warehouse.
He should be running out of oxygen soon.
Press the symbols in the correct order.
Don't mind him, he's just hitchin' a ride.
Not going to get in that way, friends. Go outside and find a back door to crack open with a saw.
You need to patch me in so I can open those doors.
A blowtorch would do the trick if you can find one lying around somewhere. Seems like something the triads would have just lying around!
Pick yourself up for a change!
There's something wrong with the drill. You gotta repair it.
Keep collecting things for Vlad!
The van will be there in 30 seconds - get ready!
That's the warehouse where the voting machines are kept. Time for a little political engineering.
Blind here til you get that terminal back on, guys.
What are you waiting for? Grab all the pardons!
Keep your heads down! Don't get fucking shot!
Clever.
There's the bag, get it to Mr Blonde, yeah?
You have to replace the batteries with fresh ones.
Search well and eyes peeled for guards.
Blerrie, looks like there are heavy locks on those containers. If the one holding Vlad is sealed like that, you'll have to find a blowtorch or something to cut it open with.
I'm there in two!
In the field, if you trip an alarm, the cops come buzzing. DC's got a lot of them.
You're inside? Good job.
You got metal security doors blocking the storage room. I can unlock them remotely if you hack their control boxes.
You gotta decide if you want to burn the rest or take it.
Water tanks are empty. Refill them in the bathrooms. Hey, I never promised you glamour.
Come on, Dentist's loot is right there.
You can tell them yourself, domkop.
Get to a life boat and lower it so that you can escape!
The dwankie chop knows enough, for sure.
Ha! Now you're just showing off!
Ok, that's it! You fucking did it!
Escape vehicle is leaving in ten minutes.
... Going, I'm going.
You're wasting time! Repair BFD, get her working and let's finish this caper.

The arena has a huge security floor run by GenSec. Part exhibition for corporate VIP's, but still a working vault. Tonight, we hit it. We got an Inside Man on this one. He stashed some C4 around the Arena. Gather it, blow the vault from beneath and get that sweet dirty money out. We're going to have some unexpected help on this one. You guys hear of a DJ called Alesso? Tonight's the last night of his East Coast tour, and he's promised to lift the roof. What better cover could you want?
Get that key to the car!
You shouldn't have made me mad!
All right, friends. Send the drive down the dumbwaiter. Shayu's guys will take care of it.
Hurry up and enter the White House!
Come on! Fuck 'em up!
Keep your eyes on the Murkies and don't get too close. Even with those uniforms, you might get spotted.
Let's get that gate open.
We do NOT have a deal!
Find something around there to move the container with.
We need to turn the pressure valves in a specific order, so listen carefully.
Get up there and stop them, for crying out loud! This is a tragedy!
When you go to your cabin, a new phone and number cards will be waiting.
Take the boxes from the conveyor, friends.
Shit, gas, gas!!! Get out! Move it!
Near the door!
I don't think the triad domkops are going to invite you for tea, so you might as well get out, yeah?
Don't fuck with me now...
Ooh! Those Piggy Bucks are shiny!
OK, the data is scrambled! It'll seem like just a normal data failure.
Houston, come here. Shh, keep quiet.
Boxes of ammo in the room near the helipad if you need them!
According to Rust, the OVERKILL MC have the tech in one of the cars in the front. Get over there as fast as you can and don't stop. We don't have much time.
There's the house. Get inside!
Yeah, about that. It's out here. In my car.
You're looking for two points of access.
Now, clear the blast area!
Guys, they're throwing everything they have at you. Better make it out, fast!
You're good taking either direction, here. Up to you, friends.
Good work, but these guys are clever. The doors are linked so no one can enter the shelter unless the other one is in on it. You need to override Wilson's system too.
You cutting though yet?
Keep a close eye on those buzzsaws, they're been more prone to jamming than usual, lately.
Just heard that Murkywater are going to try and shift some cash by plane. Gives me an idea.
Yeah! Thats the sweet sound of success. Get yourselves in the basement and check what's in there.
Well, no need to be quiet now. They know something is going on!
Our guy is waiting to shut down the gig. Just answer that intercom when you're ready. Make sure all the loot you wanna take is secured.
One of these trucks is the one we want. When you've finished searching for clues, get the tag on the truck you think is our target. You get one chance, so make sure you're certain.
If your guy Locke doesn't come through, Cabot will sort it out.
Plan A is out the window, we're gonna have to gamble that the server is there!
Find something to take that cell block door down!
Everyone listen up, the pick-up's here now. You're going to need to cross over the walkway, he's on that side.
By the way, your new burner phone and calling cards are in your cabin.
Find a good formula yet, friends?
How is it going?
Comrads get over here, soldiers everywhere. Time to leave!
We know the Mendozas are on the run - seems they are making a last hit on us to retaliate. Our meth lab is under attack - save the meth and save the cooks. You know how to treat the enemy. Do so.
It will be fine.
What'n the hell was that?!
Well, that did it. Not quite his usual self, but not too far removed. Our inside man is waiting outside with a skid loader. Get Vlad into the scoop.
I bet you'll find the key to those curtain controls at the reception desk. Doesn't seem like something Security would bother with.
We're not going in by the main entrance. You see that fence? That's our way in.
It will be in position. Look for it.
Great! Now we can get out of here. Get to the escape. Follow the blue containers!
Do you have the master keycard?
No one is going to miss this message. The FBI's going to search high and low for you but don't worry... I'll take care of it. Great work.
Gang, don't forget - you need to light a flare before Locke will come in.
The roof of that diner can be accessed by a service ladder, but you're going to need a keycard to get to it. Surely there's one around somewhere.
Check all the cases, maybe it's there.
There could be more equipment in the drop outside, friends.
Chopper's just about here!
... but get more if you can!
You should find evidence related to Hoxton's case in the Evidence Room. Get searching.
Blerrie fingerprint scanner. OK, who's got some tape? Does anyone have any tape? You can use it to lift the manager's fingerprints off an object and open that dinges without making a lot of noise.
You need to find Chloe's computer.
Gang what's going on? We are not leaving without the briefcase.
That door has an alarm. Find a way to turn it off.
Gonna feed you to the pigs!
We can unlock the laptop with a fingerprint scan. Look for something you can use to copy Esteban's prints.
OK, we can't shoot through that glass. Try breaking it with the chandelier. Use some thermite on one of the cables holding it, yeah?
The kerels messed up the pump generator!
...Time to pull that door off, yeah? Start the winch and keep the kerels from getting to it!
Go go, find the prison transports.
All these apartments have sprinkler systems. Just look for the valve.
OK the truck is rolling out, and the GPS is working. Good work. Time for us to change history our way.
Wrong key!
That's Buluc! Take him out. No need to dally.
Blues are trying to pull the plug on us, make sure they fail!
Quit wasting our time, this is less than we agreed on!
The alarm! Stealth is out of the window, gang. But the ship is moving, and she ain't gonna stop now.
The shoes should be in the storage cage. Open it!
All right. Now you can keep cooking, or signal the chopper and end this caper.
Late addition, Mr. Santiago. Should be on the updated calendar.
You're going to need two keycards to get in there.
Can't stay right now.
Make sure the police don't interfere.
Did the rat jump off...? No. Can't be.
Gotcha, moving!
Now hop onboard and get out of there, you chops!
Hmm... Yup, there's no way around it. I'm gonna need to get into the garage and take apart one of the bikes there. Only way to get the stuff I need. Take me there and cover my ass while I work.
These Harvest & Trustee branch banks are easy pickings for guys like you. Case the bank so you can find out its weakness.
Looks like we've got a card reader. There's got to be a keycard around here somewhere.
OK, it's in!
Hey, Twitch. What do you need?
Hey! They're trying to fuck with us!
Hurry friends, you need to get into that computer.
There's a thermal drill nearby. Go get it.
Careful now. Another guard is patrolling the area. He's most likely looking for his partners. We can't afford to kill this guy. I repeat: do not kill him.
...And don't forget to get the boxes off the conveyor!
And I don't wanna see no bills written up for this.
Ensure all of the straps are secure. Don't give Locke an excuse to accidentally drop the money.
Sons of bitches!
It's all gone, gang. No point in hanging around!
Shit!
Wait for the helicopter.
Mu... Muriatic acid - we need some more in there.
Something happened to one of the RFID wires! Go restart the bypass!
Drop 'em!
So much value in such a small space.
Robbery is vigilance, folks.
I've got Bile coming with the drill, you need to get outside and wait for it.
I hope this hunk o' metal has air bags!
Connect me to a telephone, friends
That is all, good.
We need to lower those bollards. Find the control room. Gotta be one of these doors.
It'll take years to rebuild this. Just one minute, be ready.
Next, you'll need to find a security box. There are three of them. Plug in the hacking device, and I'll brute force the system. Just make sure nobody interrupts the hack.
In politics, you have to be the change to make the change.
The cops are deploying more snipers!
Slow day... should be good for us.
That sounds great. I am going to pay off my credit cards, put a little into a savings account.
More cops are arriving!
Wipe 'em out!
Before anything else, preparation is the key to success.
Cops are closing in on the arena. Stay on your toes, this will get hairy.
OK! OK, it's empty. Just keep looking!
What are you doing? Help Vlad out of those restraints!
Very good work, folks.
The whiteboard guys, find it, yeah?
Siphoning the oil now. Make sure the kerels don't interfere!
First number. Get the other two.
Now, give me a few moments, friends.
Yeah-yeah-yeah... Run the plan!
Guys, the timer stopped!
You made us come for nothing?
Wait for Santa to get into the tree!
I'm a sitting duck here with those snipers. Can you do something?
Get over here!
Acid. Muriatic acid.
Seven bags!
Alright you got it, now put it in the tree.
Two minutes. Get off the road, old cunt!
Maybe he put it somewhere really obvious, yeah?
Open the gate so you have a clear path to take off.
Friends, how about helping me with a weapons deal, yeah?
Keep pushing forward, gang!
Once you're all done here, I'll have everything I need to patent the Neo-2 as a Keegan Oil invention. Gonna put me light years ahead of the pack.
Well done! When you're good to go, leave by the window cleaning platform. It's time to celebrate!
He's heavier than I thought! Now, let's go!
Chopper's on the scene. Get him there. Just pray he doesn't reach for the controls.
FBI files... I could stay here all night... Alright I'm on this.
Find the code. Did you check the whole room?
Turn the power on, then restart the terminal override.
Cannon still isn't charging. Start it up!
That's it! Now plant the C4 in the underground garage. Our Inside Man has marked the ceiling beneath the vault. That's where the C4 goes.
Eight
Just a minute. I have to open the gate!
Is it inappropriate of me to think this might be kind of fun?
Where are you on shutting down that firewall?
See if you can find something we can use to hack the vault system.
Body is bagged. Question is, where do I hide it?
Kak! The bloody cops shut down the access point. Fix it!
Well, there goes plan A. Glad the crowd didn't hear any of that.
Come on! Get the time lock going again!
Great work! A classic takedown of a classic heist. It was a pleasure to watch!
Right, now just let it fill up.
Have you taken care of the food yet?
OK...
Rust told me the bikers have one of the cars in the front where they guard the stuff we're after. Make your way there and don't let anything stop you.
Cut the power to those security lasers.
Good work, now watch 'em overheat. You'll get that system reboot.
I think Buluc's office is upstairs. Get up there and confirm, yeah?
No more party people, they're all heading out.
Sensors off! Now, let's get to the printing plates. The wagons will be marked with that company you found on the shipping manifest.
With the Army on the roads and that pipeline on the tracks, I don't know how you're getting out of this. Really hope you've got a plan.
Something's fishy here - I think there might be snipers in those windows.
I'm sure we don't have long before the law shows, either, which is in keeping with this spectacular run of bad luck we've been having.
OK crew. You know how it goes, it's a bank hit. Ditch your phones, get your mind condition one and snap on the gloves. We're going to hit this branch bank. They're all over this town.
SWAT helicopter incoming. Get ready to face some heavy firepower.
And another one bites the dust! Nice!
I liked that guy. We'll send his wife a ham. Yeah, for sure.
Did you find the lever?
The first Piggy Bucks dropped!
Hey what's going on? Answer.
*Whimper*
So when you have your fill, I need you to drop the bags into this vent here. We'll pick 'em up later.
Don't throw anymore, it's full. Wait for me to unload these first.
O kaek, I wasn't counting on that. Never can it be easy.
See if you can find a cup with prints.
If I know them, and I know them, trust me on that, they'll have bulldozers up ahead. So get ready for those shits, yeah.
Christmas tree! Oh, Christmas tree! Where are youuuu?
I got another idea: Finders keepers, assholes!
Get to the harbor office and have a look around. We know the triad keeps records there. Maybe there's something we can take and use against them.
We've been expecting you fuckers!
Get that gate open.
Okay, coming back around. There in 60 seconds.
Kiff! Now go and have a look inside, yeah?
Ah, come on! Take him out already. You're not getting paid by the hour.
I don't envy you friends. Gotta be a lot of spiders in that house. Awful things, crawly beasties.
Over-delivering! The boss likes that kinda' shit!
Get to the generator on the roof and shut it down.
Assault wave is incoming, yeah?
You got enough. I'll get our man on the way.
This will facilitate the success of your plan.
Come on! Get him to the tower!
There he is! Wake him up and take him to a safe place. There's a lumber yard nearby.
That's it, guys, we're doing it. Give me a sec. Hey
column4: it's time for the C4. How fast can you be here?""

String: And... In! Great. Now keep the connection secure. Going as fast as can.
The party's waiting for you jokers to fix your shit, all right.
Just burn it right here on the floor! No fuss!
Right, the statue we're after should be in one of those crates, but I reckon you'll need a crowbar to get them open. Be careful, Jiu Feng said they are often booby-trapped!
OK, three!
Right. He got called in to a meeting with a big account. He's doing a great job.
Alright, friends. This must be the shop we were told about. So far, the triad has been able to keep the kerels from discovering its true purpose.
You'll never get me! You fucking clowns are DONE!
Ok, but one more of these and I'll fucking sound the alarm.
Time to get what we came here for, yeah?
Welcome back! See, you didn't even have to answer the phone, I'm keeping my eyes on you as usual!
Over there!
The spirit of Christmas is giving! So let's give some presents to ourselves! Woohoo!
Exit is just ahead. You guys need to get out of that gear pronto. The cops will be able to track that stench.
Pilot dropped the supplies. Get them into the house.
Hot damn!
You'll probably find the tunnel if you look around outside.
There you go, now open it.
Something happened, I lost the connection. Power problem. Get me running again, yeah?
The evidence storage is on the second floor. Go!
Wow. That was...Just...WOW.
Let's do this faster, guys, please!
That's it, the drill is offline. Start it again!
That Piggy was massive!
He missed! That asshole missed the cable. Hold the cops off, he's coming about to try again.
Make sure the cooks gets finished. Give them nothing.
It's hydrogen chloride.
Enter the Oval Office so you can get the keycard!
Our C4 has been stashed in supply closets marked with a red X. Find them.

Ok, it's time to break this guy Kazuo out of prison so we can get the information he has on Kento. I engineered some ah... trouble... to get him transferred to another facility by convoy. We'll ambush that convoy and break the prisoner out. This isn't gonna be a quiet one, guys, we'll need to take extreme measures to stop the prison trucks. And, yeah, Kazuo doesn't know we're breaking him out, so boy is he in for a surprise!
Make sure you find the target quickly. You don't know what they'll do to him.
Finish this once and for all!
Excellent, you found a keycard. Now, head back to the train and open that sucker.
Movement in the alleys. Stay sharp!
No need to let it all end here...
Here...We...Go!
This place will have cameras. Be careful.
I'm under fire! Help!
Have you found the office yet?
The code begins with a four, according to my source.
That was intense! All right, head back to the vault and let's finish the job.
The vault's open. Time to see what's inside.
Damn! All right, that wasn't the vault. C4 the other spot!
Zipline up to the platform, and don't let the security team catch you off guard.
Gang, ignite the trap!
You heard the man! You can either steal more things or you get on that bike and ride! Ride like the wind!
Hot damn! You're on a hot streak!
What the fuck? We didn't even get close!
Get those bags with the cage pieces, and get them on the roof of the bank.
Sure. Thanks for keeping us safe. Bye! Phew, looks like we dodged that one.
Keep looking for a manual or something.
Crew! Don't lose focus. We're here for cash, and it's there for you.
That vault is tough. The drill bit broke. Get a spare part, quick!
The code has been blocked, so forget about it. Going to need another solution.
Alright. The cage is put together. But it's empty. Get it filled!
Gonna cut you into pieces!
She has been notably tight-lipped about what went on, for sure. Something about a triad from Macao?
Wrong guy, keep looking!
Go ahead and grab what you can, then leave when you are ready!
They're shifting long range teams into position.
Good, now set up the connection.
Ok, you're at the top now, right? Have him buckle up in the chair, then release the balloon. The plane will be there any minute now.
Come on friends, make your way out!
Hey, what's going on here...
Get ready for the tenth wave!
Oh, blerrie...
Blowing the walling will wreck the ballot machines. Accident, right? We're just doing an honest bank heist.
Smash and grab on a Murkywater convoy laden with gold.
That's gonna be useful, for sure. Now get back and burn it open.
You're looking for the panic room. Should be easy to find. Search for a reinforced door.
Sorry. Procedure. What was your name again?
That's the CSO's day planner. We can track his movements, now.
There it is, get the phone.
You dwankies! We needed Garrett alive!
Now we need those passwords.
Start hacking, friends.
You're using that truck to open the gate! Why didn't I think of that?
That's it! Doing a background check now. Hold on.
You still have 16 left.
Alright, let's trade!
You better hurry guys, clocks tickin', over.
Mendoza's people are on the scene doing the cook - get them clear and reclaim Hector's meth. You can leave right here when you have the stuff. Go for it.
From what we know, Buluc keeps to himself a lot, when not holding court, so you'll probably find him in his office. See if you can find it.
Alright you chops, time to act nice and casual. Take off your masks and walk calmly out of there.
There's an emergency dock at the base of the platform. Head that way.
Well done, friends!
Almost there!
What are you doing overe there!
The owner is nuts about security. Escape van will be near the dropoff.
Outstanding, guys, we're in! Help yourselves, give nothing back. Remember, our goal is the Dentist's loot.
... you guys are professionals, no doubt.
Don't mess around...
You're almost there, everyone get your guns ready.
You guys are kicking ass and taking names!
Outstanding work! These sweet motors will be in the hands of Arabian sheikhs within the week. Good job!
If you turn the ventilation system to full, you should be able to clear out that gas.
Nice. That cuts their options. Exploit that.
Come on friends. Andal or whatever they say down there.
Like an oiled machine, gentlemen - onwards.
Put thermite on the gate!
Crap guys, the backwater radio chatter is heating up like a mother. Someone is VERY interested in what we're doing. Be ready for major trouble.
Stay alert.
You need to find the code to the vault. Maybe there's something around there that can help. The workstations perhaps? Have a look around but stay quiet.
Shoot 'em dead!
Yes! This batch is worth a kakspul!
OK, gentlemen! Another bag and Hector's end is covered and we can get into the real moneymaking.
You are looking for evidence related to the Hoxton's case. Take a look around. It will be stored throughout the room. Could be marked out.
You can either find more loot or get on the chopper!
I'm pretty sure there was some code-like writing on a whiteboard you went by. Go back and see if it's useful.
I know the vault is here. Not sure the exact position though.
Ah, that's what we came for. Nice and shiny. Send it out on a zipline, yeah?
Vault's open! Bag the cash!
Found those laptops yet?
There's the briefcase! But you can't drill that gate. See if you can find some thermite.
The kerel boss will have the files on his computer.
We need to connect these pipes to the tank that matches our oil sample. When they're ready, pull the lever on the tank. I'll make sure the ship's in position.
I'm sorry. We're not able to offer unguided tours of the premises, and especially not the room where all the money's kept"."
The power room should have a 'High Voltage' sign outside.
What the fu... hey! Are you here to rescue me?!
This is R.G. here.
You think this is bad? This isn't bad.
Ah! Been some good gigs here. And Alesso's is the biggest one yet.
And don't get too close to the Murkies. You may be wearing their uniforms, but these guys are their top agents and know their own.
Better go across the deck of that ship to get past those containers. Should make for good cover.
Hahaha! He's all lit up now!
That's the cash. Remember, unless you want the cops there, get a bag over the yellow wall. Don't worry - that blackmailing asswipe will get what's coming to him.
Aw, bone me in the ear!
Donnerse! That's what we came for? Grab it and get out of there, yeah?
Now go open the door. No time to waste.
Come on. Just stick the thermal paste on the grate and burn through. It's not hard.
14 left!
Right, now open it.
So what's it like in DC? All those scumbag politicians on the payroll keep the cops off your asses?
Don't forget to get that winch running again!
We're here for the cash, you chop. There's no time for cutting off any noses.
Fuck these guys!
You think I'm asshole? Well, in Russia, asshole fucks you!
Careful, I see movement outside the house.
It worked, Bain. All of Crime.net's records have been deleted.
Another eight and I'm off!
The water isn't pumping, gang!
Waste 'em!
Bliksem! Operatives from Murky are in the area. Watch out for them, friends!
Shoot these fuckers!
I lost the damn chopper... ...I thought.
Damn! They have set up an additional security door...
Alright, fuck it...
Good find. But you'll need more C4. Keep searching.
House is beyond those trees, see? Sneak right up.
No, there's something wrong with this one, heading back to pick up another one...
No time to waste, civvies could find you soon. Hurry!
OK, three left.
Move the gold onto the truck! The crane can do it.
Shit! Po-po's here!
Heads up, they got electricity running through that gate. Don't go trying to cut through 'fore you turn off the power.
I need some help with a weapons deal in Alaska.
Find the main breaker and cut the electricity. That should prompt him to come have a look, so you can get to him.
Good job, gang, now we need the explosives from Bile. Give me a moment. Bile
column3: it's time. How soon can you drop off the C4?""

String: Ok, that's all. Get out of there as soon as you are ready.
Hello, friends. You're almost at the drop point I have selected, so, if you would emerge and, as you say, get the party started.
Argh, they pulled the power for the scanner!
Ok, now you gotta get inside the office and get the code. Move over there fast, yeah?
Come on, get that fire going!
Great, you've disabled all cameras in the front and upstairs. Just a few in the vault area.
Roberts Bank. Everything's under control. How can I help you?
Let's settle for this right here.
Opportunity is a haughty goddess who wastes no time with those who are unprepared.
You need to restart the power, friends.
Remember guys, we need nine bags to escape.
That's the bus, take them all out.
We will make you pay for this!
Use the keycard to get inside the server room. It's on the second floor.
Time to fly, friends.
There you go, that's the location. Now get out to the control room and pull it out of storage with the crane.
You need to leave, friends!
Gentlemen - oil is the blood of our world, without it we die. Time to make sure it keeps flowing.
Burn that trap before you leave! Hurry!
You know what to do. Set the C4 up and let it take care of the rest.
Clear out the gas.
These are the guest rooms.
OK, now open that door!
The walls are thick concrete, but I can still hear that concert. Nothing stops the music, huh.
Get the missiles close to the radar and activate them. Things are about to go BOOM.
That's one in, great! We need at least three more.
If you got any more loot, secure it in the tree now! Or it'll be left behind!
Put all the wares in the car!
That's it, gang, just the roof left now.
Master code? I'm sorry, no idea.
Expect me back in a little while.
OK, that looks... right? At least it didn't blow up. Time to mix the next ingredient.
The lifeboats are lowered with a pulley system.
Get the loot bags before we leave.

OK, it looks like one of the artifacts is being stored in the warehouse archive. There's no way you'll be able to search that area on foot, but there's a retrieval system with a crane in the central hub you can use. You just gotta find the right shelf first.
Are you still looking for something to cut with? Look harder, you chops!
Kill 'em!
OK, we've got what we need. Time to get out of there.
30 secs, guys!
Are you having second thoughts or what?
It doesn't look good, guys... It doesn't look good!
Cops responding. Here we go!
Deal's off, so fuck off!
To be honest, the smell of oil always made me nauseous.
Gate won't open with you standing on it, genius. Clear the area!
Yeah, there's a charge on my credit card the wife can't see. I was in Mexico and...
Fuck her! And fuck them! Let them come, I say. They are just easy money for me.
Why you still there? Come on, into the car and floor it!
Okay, let's move it.
There's gotta be something behind these shelves.
Right there on the feed... that's the vault.
Now, get up on deck and use a lifeboat to make your escape.
Connect the magnet to the vault.
Drill the door to the storage room.
OK, I'm in position!
Going to cut you to pieces!
You are lucky I am a kind man...
I'm going in exactly 30 seconds!
Good. That ate right through. Now get inside!
Crap, you just lost a vial.
Everybody, get down into the sewers!
Make your escape, friends! No need to go down with the ranch!
Got it! I'm off!
There has got to be some cleaner around there.
Our inside man will have left you some equipment in a storage space on the crew deck.
Who are THESE fuckers?
You gotta get back to the skylight.
I'm on my way guys, give me a few minutes.
There's the toyshop" right ahead."
Doubt any of these books have much value. To us, at least.
Our rivals, the Mendozas, are fleeing like rats off a ship. They are still dangerous as any cornered animal. Protect our meth lab at all costs.
Hose looks secure. Start the pump.
The two keycards will be around here somewhere.
The mechanic told you to go to the bunker and get the seat for him.
The Piggy won't let you give up that easy!
Security chief's code. His ass is in trouble for leaving this around.
Guys, this is the boat.
You've defeated the fourth wave of cops!
Under fire! UNDER FIRE!
I can only take four at a time, fill it up, and I'll come back for more!
I can make sure a contact of mine places medical supplies where you request them to be placed.
The blowtorch should cut through the gate easily enough. Get to it.
Remember to protect the hacking device!
Huh... everyone must be at the beach.
Now that you're done, get to the helipad and signal your ride out.
Time to leave, friends! Get into the chopper.
Ah! Those fucking shit-eating poes are stealing my money. Our money...sorry. Stop them!
Be ready!
There were spare drill bits in the piggy bank.
Is that Jiu Feng's boat? Good, get onboard, chop-chop!
I still need someone to attach the magnet to the panic room.
Ok, have a breather and I'll do rest, yeah?
Great! Add a few more, we want a proper blaze.
... I'll be back in a moment!
This spot is getting deadly!
Ha! Who wants the quiet life, eh?
Put the wares in the car...
Great. There's no shortage of buyers for these military rounds.
Grassy ass.
You have to swap out those batteries.
You can use the keycard you found.
That shipping brand is a cover for the Army. You find those wagons, you'll find the printing plates.
I know there's lots of fun stuff in here friends, but you need to aim that cannon!
... put the product in the car...
Go by the construction site. They must have a laptop there.
This type of situation is often fluid - you reacted well. Decisively. Enjoy this payday. You will hear from me in due course.
Good, now hurry back to the gate and open it up, yeah?
Bag the diamonds and bring them to the garden for zipline extraction.
Good, the EMP is charging again.
Find a centrifuge.
I want him dead. I want bullets in his kneecaps, then I want him cut open and fed to the fish.
No need to stay any longer, friends. If you're ready, go for extraction.
Blerrie! He's back in his office. Need to get him out again.
Keep looking for those cells.
I got it! Oh, wait... No, you said time lock code? For the vault? One second...
There's the alarm. Cops are en route. Keep hacking those machines. I'll think of a new plan.
Got the ramp sorted yet?
Let me see if I can get into their system from here and point you to the right workstation.
Damn. No match. Keep looking!
It's getting dangerous out here!
You'll probably find a PC in the PR office.
That's how we do it, yeah?
It'll take something big to open that gate to the workshop.
OK, throw me the paintings, and you'll get your money!
They're on to us like a bumper sticker!
... put the product in the car!
Don't forget to check the interrogation rooms.
My friends! We are approaching the location I have selected for the drop point. So, without further ado...
Very nice! A door breaker!
We need more, I already told you.
No worries, I'm on it.
You come here to fuck our shit up?
Do I look like a store clerk? Leave 'em.
Security's tight, friends. We won't get far unless you hook me into the server.
Hack into that computer, friends.
I gotta keep moving!
You have done phenomenally well.
You're not supposed to get captured, you chops! We gotta give this one up.
Refueling is done, so take that hose off.
Search the office space for emails, voicemails, and anything else that will show Alice Rainey's true colors.
Any second now!
Get me the bags!
If you happen to drop one of the guards, you should be able to hide the body under the train so it doesn't get detected.
We do not have a deal!
I'm almost done here. There's gonna be a lot of information to dig through back at the safe house, but we're gonna find that fucking informant, and nail the twat before he rats you all out.
For the sake of a good fuck! You've done this already. Just put paste on the grate!
Crap. You guys seeing this? Something went up there. Pyro team - fix it!
Die! DIE!
They're breaching with a bus!
Give me 30 seconds and I will drop that EMP.
Have a look at the card reader by the security bars. Get it open, yeah?
Forest - cops coming through.
Chop, chop! Turn on the light in the window, so our contact knows to take control of that platform.
We got our first bag of Piggy Bucks!
Why did I offer to fix the bike...
There you go friends, now hurry back in!
Can't unlock the doors until you patch in properly.
Sealed up, donnerse! OK, there's a scaffolding outside, use it to get up to the second floor. Find a door to crack open with a saw, to get into the vault room.
From what we know, Li Deng spends most of his time in the spa, while Xun Kang watches over the casino.
I will personally offer you a reward for all the evidence you bring out. This is about the safety of Crime.net.
OK, that one is on me.
I will meet you on the edge of town, but I don't want you bringing the whole fucking cop army. Get in the sewers. I've organized transport.
You gotta restart the electricity!
... I'm coming back in no-time!
You think you can take me down eh! Think again!
Those are the jewels we are after. Get it to the van.
Come on guys, eenie, meenie, miney, moe... you know the drill.
I bet you thought we didn't expect you guys!
You can drill the safe and cause a minor ruckus, or get the key from Li Deng.
Look in all the sanctum rooms if you haven't found everything you need.
The winch will be there in one minute, friends.
Yeah! Got our seven bucks back. Suck it, parking meter!
Eleven bags, let's go!
It'll be hard to wreck the lab with all these scientists about. If you connect to the PA system in the admin building, I can lure them outside.
There's a safe in Deng's private massage chamber. That's where he keeps the vault code.
Do you want to find a way to open that door?
So that's the fake shipping company. Locate the wagons with that brand. They'll have the printing plates inside.
You gotta wonder, if the nukes were dropping, would you really want to have to go this far to get to the PEOC?
Before we can do anything else, I need access to the rig's central network. One of the office workers should have the server room keycard.
Shit we got bad cops moving in - real bad cops. Keep your heads down!
We're moving the escape car. Hang on.
Come on, gang - get the water pumping again!
This is the police! Release the hostage and we will try to meet your demand!
Second transport is open - check inside!
This is First World Bank. Yes, ma'am, you can deposit that here. Yes, we have a very secure vault. Yes, ma'am, even *those* kind of people bank here.
Use the store computer to take the security system offline.
Ach! The Murkies have gone bossies!
It is done.
This plan is coming together.
Now, breach the elevator and zipline up to the penthouse.
Connect hose to ship, now.
We got what we needed. Let's move out.
Telling the pilot to return with the C4 to bust you through there. Just hang in there.
Alright! The chopper's going to the docks, folks - out of the frying pan.
This is not all of what we agreed on.
Don't break his jaw!
That's one hell of a shooter! He got 'em good! Now, let's do our part. Let's get our loot!
The stones in cases are top priority, but grab whatever else you can.
You're done - get together everyone!
OK, start the next hack.
Ah, the C4 is behind a gate. See if you can find a blowtorch or something to cut it open with.
Start the Beast!
Hurry up you chops, smash that door open!
... Kill these guys and bury 'em!
I sent along a new drill for you. It's based on an older model, but this one will not jam.
Have you got that drill set up yet?
Right, now the vault itself is behind a security gate and you'll need to get past it.
Just keep running!
Where's the shit!?
Good, now get the statue to the van!
Oh, ese, you're over-delivering! Very nice!
We siphoned the best. Time to burn the rest. Head to the Drilling Tower.
*loudly sings Ride of the Valkyries by Wagner*
The server room must be around there.
I hope so. I really fucking hope so. No one puts Vlad through that shit and lives. The world has to know! Vlad has a reputaion to uphold, you know.
What the ...? Get the cops off the access point!
The blueprints indicate the vault is behind those doors.
Follow Bain to the roof!
Yet another successful collaboration! You have my thanks, my admiration and, most importantly, your share of the money.
Come on, you can find a way in.
A good move.
Police about 40 seconds out.
The EMP is heavy and my fuel is limited. I need to drop it soon!
I'm gonna make you bleed!
Who the hell are you!?
They're trying to flank you at the parking lot.
This isn't good. I'm gonna raise suspicion here for sure...
I'm here, I'm here!
Right, follow me and we'll get you out. Hope you got what you wanted.
I can arrange for this keycard to be left where you indicate.
What are you doing? Move!
Still don't know you're there. Look for the keycard.
We managed to get a zip-line set up here. It'll carry you right to the crane.
Head up to the apartment, my associate has the info and the cash to pay for the extra meth.
That's the Neo-2 on stage. Won't be able to sneak it out of here while that blerrie curtain's up.
20 seconds. Cops closing in.

... Put the idiots out of their misery man!
... We'll take what you have.
Where is it?
Now, if I understand you, you don't want to give me some money to provide capital for an operation running smokes out of Mexico?
Don't say a word. I'm well aware you're not only here to save my ass. Rust still wants his bike back, right? Well, to do that I'm gonna need all the parts, and they're spread all over the place.
Hey! Don't leave me!
Oh, shit!
Oh, yeah. Wait. You're gonna need this blowtorch to get inside.
Fuck, this is gonna be tricky... Yeah, you can't do it yourselves. Take me to the garage where I can take a bike apart to collect some special shit for this babe.
I'll get blasted if I go alone, so you need to take me to the garage. I don't know about y'all, but I want to get this shit done and over with.
Come on, where's that coke? I'm thirsty!
Done! Get me the next piece!
You wanna know how I make my money? Hard work. Right through the night.
I kinda like what I do, you know? And when I'm creative, I feel like I'm top of the world really because, you know, how many guys can do what I do?
We rolled the year back. It was like '69 on the Strip. Caddy was low-ridin' 'cos of all the ass in the back.
You guys're dressed pretty sharply for pool repair men. Guess you got your overalls in those bags.
Bodhi's pool repair, should've known.
Uh, come on!
Hey, it's Mitchell, over at Keel Street. The pipes, you know? The ones you fixed"? Yeah
So, I just heard from the boss. He's on his way here to get us but he's pretty pissed, so you guys might wanna bail before he gets here.
The boss just called and he's pissed. Got a guy comin' to get us but you should probably bail. I'll make sure you get your cut.
Cabot's gonna go nuts when he hears about this.
Hey, crooks don't slide on hoods. Only cops.
On the fifth day of Christmas...
Seven sins to carry away.
Ten is our magic number, guys, unless you want to keep going.
That's our minimum, unless you want to try and get more.
Still more? Almost feels greedy.
Hurry up Goddamnit!
They're right on top of me people, can't fucking hold out much longer!
If we get outta this one I might just leave this fuckin' town.
Best of luck with your boss and all guys.
How the fuck did they know we were gonna be here!?
Say hello to our new LMG Dozers...
The asset has been retrieved. That's a win for the boys in blue, over.
I'm smoking anywhere I want!
Let's go! Let's go! We can all fit in the elevator.
Hey Bain, great briefing... I heard jack-shit! Let's just aah, play it by ear.
You're breaking up... Can you hear me ok?
Right!
This is private property, get out of here!
This is Captain Rogers of the MPDC. We got a call from GenSec. Seems they got some concerns about what's happening there. I'm dispatching some uniformed officers to make sure everything's OK.
If you can get through this quietly, you should be able to just melt away with the crowd.
Nice work. The C4 will alert the crowd unless we time it with Alesso's pyrotechnics. Head upstairs and patch me into the tech booth.
Bile's on his way with the chopper!
That's the last door!
More C4. Not quite enough. Find the last batch. Keep searching.
The garage is right below that Investment vault. It's where you need to plant the explosives.
Head to the pyro booth. Top floor. Hurry!
The crowd is heaving tonight. Let's give them a great show.
Console on the right!
Right!
Right! And...left!
That's the cutter done. Let the money rain down!
That chute there can transport the loot to the lobby. Might speed things up.
Okay, ping our Inside Guy when you're ready to de-mask and get out of there. He'll move the loot, so be sure you secure in the vent what you want to take.
When you're ready to get out of here, answer the intercom. Our guy will get the loot out, so make sure you've secured what you wanna take.
Got our seven bucks back, gang. Stretch goals are good.
It was loud and got attention. Excellent work. Tough for GenSec though. Their new design is a joke.
You did it, you got a ton of money and got a lot of attention. And GenSec deserve to suffer publicly.
Jesus, it looked bad on the news, but...
Now, get those trucks opened. Let's get inside them.
You can bet they're important if Vlad sent us to this hellhole for them.
Get the safes out, gang. Yeah, I know it's over a hundred degrees, but get to it.
A little C4 will deal with that. I'm sending some now. Hold on.
Take the C4, crew. That will deal with the construction yard wall.
All right. Now slap the C4 on there. We're busting our way out.
Get inside the truck! The chopper is going to airlift the whole damn thing out!
Guys, the wreckage is incredible. Rubble blocking everything.
This would be easier if the city wasn't a ruin. Just hold on.
Got it! Construction yard, with a truck. Looks like the best way out of here, but you'll need C4 to bust that wall. Sending it now. Mind the safes!

Hey, you guys see the news?! Big quake just hit the West Coast! LA is completely messed up. And that's where you're headed. Seems Vlad has set up some big deal to move some freight from Seattle to DC. The shippers he contracted were in LA when the quake hit - I guess they were going to ship out of Long Beach. Vlad wants his freight secured safely. No time for planning on this one. LA is wrecked, and the roads are messed up so we're going to drop you in by chopper.

GenSec are a big security company on the East Coast. Got a great reputation with the banks and politicians, but today we're going to see what we can do about that. Got a tip-off about a convoy coming into the city. We're going after it.
The underpass is a vulnerable spot for the convoy. Hit it hard.
Haha! You did it! This jewelry should be worth a few bucks don't you think?
Sweet, sweet gold! Great job everyone!
Get it to the van!
Use those roofs to your advantage!
Check the stores if you want some extra money.
Alright! The van should be coming in soon!
Bullseye! You guys OK? That was one hell of a collision! Get to work on those transports!
Holy crap! We knocked all three trucks off the road. Make it count!
Firewalls are tripped. We're going to need a local port - one of the staff terminals. Check them out.
Accessing now...
This one's a wash-out. Another one. Quick!
One of the staff terminals is holding a code. Find it, and start hacking.
OK. Now let's restart the time lock and see if this worked.
Great. Now keep the cops away from it.
Now while the time lock counts down, you can get ahead of the action. There's a zip-line on the roof that will need setting up.
Operate the crane, guys. Get that piggy into position.
This place has a formidable vault. Thankfully, I found just the tool for it. Get that bag to the vault.
What a drill. Let's see if it works as good as it looks. Fire it up.
The van's outside. Get stowing that loot!
I got the van in the garage, but you need to go through the elevator shaft.
The bus is all set up to... Well, you worry about sending the signal. Then you'll see.
Who said the buses in this town can't keep to a schedule! Get moving that loot.
Almost there. Final protocol - the managers code. Check his computer.
Time to light it up, guys.
This will forever be a Red Letter day for the criminal community. The day the Payday Gang broke the Benevolent.
Looks like some codes, that'll come in handy.
They're coming from the east, by the forest.
Alright, do you see the house? Get inside and find the server room. We need to hack into the security system to get to the lab.
This one seems to be malfunctioning, I'll be back to pick up another one.
Well, no fusion, but at least we get to drive gas-guzzling cars a lot longer this way. I love my Firebird as much as the next man.
Good work people. That was a hell of a thing to move, but it's the right engine and it's locked up tight. Maybe one day we'll go freelancing and take it back, huh?
OK, that's the clubhouse. Bikers' got the address we need. Sneak in.
OK guys, search the place. They have a safe somewhere, it's probably in there.
OK, no time to lose, get all that intel.
Don't let them destroy any intel. Get it all!
That might be useful.
They're coming from the east, by the forest.
You guys OK? Bikers sure act like it is war - go get 'em!
Damn it, they're burning it!
The prototypes should be in the lab. To gain access to it we need to hack the main server. Find the server room.
Remember you're looking for the server room.
Server room - find it.
Find the server room.
Make sure the guards don't spot us now.
Great job, I'm connected.
It's done! Open the lab door!
Ah OK... So, seems to be a bit too many of them here. Fusion engines that is. Find the correct one.
Check his papers, notes and computers. Anything for a hint on what is correct here.
Alright, the chopper is on its way.
Helicopters landing. Load up the engine and hope it is the one.
Sorry guys, he says this ain't the one. The chopper will be back in a few so you can get another one over here, hopefully the right one.
Dr Fantastic! You guys sure are smart. We got the right engine and you are rich. Now make it out of there! Chopper is incoming.
Mr Dr Fantastic Sir! You nailed it. Thats some science - well done team. Get your big brains out of there! Use the plane.
Finally, the chopper pilot is heading back to get you guys. Sorry for the hold up.
Damn it! The alarm! The whole house knows we are coming now!
Dentist, you asshole, I'm going to drill out those glowing eyes of yours...
Kento, you got trouble coming...
Dentist... Elephant... Sputnik... gotta warn...
A little cash goes a long way. The local Harvest & Trustee branch bank needs to be lightened of its load. Let's do this bank hit, get their vault open, and fill our pockets a little.
We got a cash situation in this bank. They have missed their delivery to the HQ this week. Don't everyone sigh all at once...
Got a deposit box opportunity in this bank. I have inside info.
Happy birthday. Vault full of freshly loaded safe deposit boxes. Who's in?
Crew this is hot off the wire. I have a gold deposit waiting for us.
Then get the gold out. It's heavy, so bring strong people. Get the loot to the escape van - at least as much as you think you can. Good luck!
There's a bank vault we need to hit...
People, you've probably done this a dozen times. Hitting the Harvest & Trustee Bank over on 5th. No idea what's in there but we know it's gonna be sweet. Get that vault open and away we go. You in?
You're going to need to get into the vault using a thermal drill, get whatever's in there bagged up and moved back to the escape car. Use your judgment and don't be greedy... Good luck, folks.
Everyone, you know how it's done. My guy dropped the thermal drill in the parking lot, so grab that before you make your move inside. Some surveillance would be smart.
OK folks, my inside man stashed the thermal lance you're gonna need for the vault around the back. Recon the spot to find it.
It's a straight cash hit. You know how this goes.
Alright, bring it to the van, it's right around the corner.
Vault's cracked, let's see what we got!
Cash time. Bag it!
Jackpot... Look at all the cash... Get it out now!
More cops on the way.
Don't forget about those safe deposit boxes folks, can be good stuff in there.
Street's clear for now!
OK! you've got enough... Or you can stay for more.
They're in the bank!
We're looking good... Looking good.
It's open! Search through the deposit boxes!
It's open! Let's see what we got!
Alright, bring it to the van, it's right across the street.
OK people, there's the bank, I don't know what's in there but it's gonna be good...
Loot bags in place and money ready to get divided. You guys never disappoint. Love it!
I don't say superb often, but I'm saying it now. Good work.
...This is the setup.
That was too damn close. Now, we don't have time to stand around, gang. Get him off that chair so we can get this over with.
The bikers are apparently storing stuff in an old bunker. The mechanic said you would find a seat for the bike in there.
Perfect, now deliver the part to the mechanic so he can work!
You got what he asked for, now you need to bring it to him.
That's the part he asked for. One step closer gang.
Excellent, that's a part in the bag. Bring it back to the mechanic.
We're taking some of these nice weapons with us. But how, that's the question...
Just keep driving straight!
You're in civilian mode. No guns, no masks - invisible to security. When you're ready, find your gear. Micho the janitor left it in a guitar case somewhere.
We've got cops on the way, so don't dawdle. Find the C4! Check the guard room.
OK, let's blow this place. C4's in the limo. Take it!
There's The Dentist's whatever. Haul it out of there and we are done with him.
We can now redeem the Dentist's contract. You can bounce, or treat Vegas to a Payday Gang party and loot the place.
And... great! There's the top of the vault!
Great. Now turn her back on.
Don't let BFD overheat. Refill that tank with water!
Whatever it is, we got it! Get it to the limo.
Great. Now toss it up onto BFD.
Zero!
Five!
Reception. Okay, we may need it later - note where it is.
This is the Security Center.
Get the blueprints in the archives. They're somewhere in the employee only areas..
Let me check. Room...
I think they saw that from the ISS!
What the hell...
I don't... know...
So good to talk to you, sir.
Nice. Now go get that guest list from reception.
Perhaps sir has a sweet tooth? How would you like enough cake to choke a camel?
Don't forget we have enough sugary desserts to give you diabetes.
You can get a side of cornbread with that. Yummy!
All yours for the price of... say... 18 bucks.
All You Can Eat, remember. Just 18 bucks.
Fix up BFD and let's finish this. Come on, crew, we're so close.
Remember to screw that winch down good.
We need a code to open the armory. Three digits. Colour coded. They're somewhere in the Grin. Get searching!
Find the blue bottle and spike it.
That's it, buddy. Drink up.
Opening the vault needs a three digit code. Each digit is held by a manager, and each is in a computer briefcase. We need that code. Find them.
That's the alarm. OK, gang. Plan B. Force our way through.
That's all the numbers needed for the armory. Go enter that code.
Now load up on C4. You'll need it.
Now plant the C4 in the main hall. The vault is right below. Two possible spots to blow. Hope lady luck is with us!
Nice! Next, we're going to signal the blimp, and for something like that we need a big signal. A fireworks display! Find them!
The drill can't be dropped through that skylight barrier. Gotta open it from the security center.
The cops pulled the hack. Get there and reboot it.
All right. Now this is why we brought the winch. Hook it to BFD, and it'll get the position right.
Power's down. Get BFD reconnected, gang!
She's all done! Quickly, down into the vault!
We're here! Find The Dentist's loot, and let's get it out of here.
You can bounce now, or you can stay and give the Golden Grin a thorough cleaning.
Over there. Your gear's in that guitar case.
Don't forget to send me the list. Head to IT. Plug it in.
That's him. Got his name, SSN, last time he took a dump... Check the screen in IT. Find him. Says here he loves the slots, so maybe that will be where he is.
That's the first number. Keep looking. Two to go.
Second digit for the code. Now, just get the last number and we're set.
Outstanding! That's the vault code. Once we're in the Security Center, we can open the vault with it.
We got the pit boss' code. Nice.
Arriving in style!
Don't forget to find the elves. Shout at them to make them work.
Escape is ready. Van is in place, engine running.
Remember, we need to keep these cars in pristine condition. No scratches, and definitely no bullet holes. Which means no cops. So keep it quiet.
The market for these cars demands they are in perfect condition. Keep it quiet, and you'll keep the cops away. Which means no bullet holes.
Damn. It's locked. Hmmm. Alright. The manager's still there. Take him as hostage. See if he has any information about the lock.
And... it's locked. Damn! OK. Stay quiet. The manager must be around there somewhere. Take him hostage. He should be able to get us in.
I've accessed the manager's file. He'll be wearing a suit.
I can also see that he's balding. You copy that? Look for the old, balding guy.
Manager's got a black suit, thinning hair. Find him, tie him - that might make him more helpful.
Gang, the C4 is in the van. Get it, and plant it.
OK, I'll set these off remotely. Now get back to the storage room. It's open!
Now jump into the car. Oh, and keep your head down - it's time to *blow* the joint.
OK, now drive. Go, go, go!
Ah hell. Wrong pc. Alarms are tripped. Cops are en-route. Not much time now.
Now drive!
Now bail out of there!
Nice, I'll detonate these. You just be ready with the cars.

The Teuer dealership is one of the few East Coast showrooms that sells Falcogini cars. They just got the hot new model in - the La Troienne. I got some people overseas who are willing to pay big for this little beauty. Get in there, get to the wheels and get them out. Simple, right?
Pull over here. Alright gang. Let's do this.
The front of the train, gang!
Make your way to the front, guys. Come on!
The car we're after is in the front, gang!
Use the blowtorch to create a way through that car.
Holy...! They rigged the boxes with C4! Defuse them!
Jackpot! Rust's info was correct. Now, get through the gate and grab the BCI headset and the software.
The tech is in our hands! Time to head back to the helicopter! Don't keep Bile waiting.
What are you waiting for? Run back to the helicopter and secure the loot!
Damn! The cops have blocked the tracks up ahead, which means you need to be gone before you reach that point. Get the BCI tech and run back to the chopper!
The train is rapidly approaching the cop barricade. I give you a maximum of two minutes to secure the loot and get out.
With the speed this train is going, you'll have about two minutes before you reach the barricade. That means two minutes to secure everything and leave!
Damn it! Those oil barrels are in the way. See if you can release the straps, and do it quickly.
You'll have to use the blowtorch to get through this gate. Make it quick.
No broken legs? Good. Head into the forest and find that plane. My guess is the pilot will be nearby. Get him someplace safe and we'll evac him by air. Move out!
Jesus, he's wasted. Stay with him. He's in no shape to defend himself.
Good. I'm sending a chopper to collect him. Keep him safe. He's so wasted I doubt he'd feel the bullets.
Chopper will come back for you, so while we're waiting, why not get looking for Vlad's packages. Could be a nice little bonus.
Sounds like a present fell outta the tree, gang. Might be more of Vlad's coke. Find it.
The night's not so silent. Think I heard another present hit the ground. Find it!
Oh man, the pilot just went down again. Wake that old wino up!
Flare is lit. Alright, he sees it. Chopper is in-bound.

We need you there fast, but it's really out in the sticks, so you're going in like the paras. Find the pilot - he's probably near the wreck - and then we'll send in a chopper to extract him. Stay with him til he's safely out. Also, Vlad says that plane was loaded with product. Search the forest and get as much out as you can. Can always use a little extra cash at Christmas.
Docks are right there. Head in. And watch for guards.
A keycard for the gate. Gonna need another, though.
That's the left panel. Now search for the other keycard. Get the other panel activated.
Guard is down. That's the cameras out of action.
You took care of both guards. Don't have to worry about the cameras anymore.
And that's the guards dealt with. Cameras are no longer a problem.
This is the Storage Room. Check for a keycard. Might be a radio here too.
Ship's there. Get on it! Maybe deploy the zip-line - might speed things up.
You've found the bomb. No need to keep checking the bomb cases!
You already found the bomb. You can leave the containers alone!
The Moretta - That's our girl. But we can't get on board here. You have to see her moved to dock 3B.
You need to find keycards. My guess is that the buildings are your best chance.
Find keycards, gang. Check the buildings.
We need the Moretta's comm frequency. It'll be on one of those terminals. Get checking.
Alright, she's berthed! Get up on deck and start searching the containers.
Moretta is in position. Get on deck and look for the explosives. Move!
No alarm was triggered, so you can simply walk into the containers. Outstanding!
He's en route now with C4. Just hang in there, gang.
Now plant it on the dock gate.
Boom!
Just like St Nazaire!
We can scratch the Captain moving his ship for us now. Nevermind. We can move the ship without him. Hack into the ship control terminal. And don't let the cops interfere with it.
Alright. Let's try this again.
Moretta is powering up. Let it move to its berth. Weapons free.
Drill baby, drill!
And... Jackpot! Moretta specs including comm frequencies. Great work! Now look for the nearest radio, and let's talk to the Captain.
You can use the crowbar to open up shipping crates.
A crowbar. Good find. Always useful.
Gonna need to call the Moretta, and for that we need the comm frequencies. Search for it.
And here's the second control room for the gate.
These wagons might have something valuable in them. Maybe check them out?
Well, it's a keycard, and pretty damn useless now. Maybe if you'd found it earlier...
Great. Now the second card in the other panel, and the Moretta will be free.
The ship is almost there, gang. Be ready.
Nothing in here. Keep looking!
There's a boat ready for you. Head there.
Come on, get to the boat.
Boat's standing by to get you out, guys.
No-one's seen you. Keep it that way. Now, the gate.
They've no clue you're there. Now get to that radio.
Still silent. Nice. Find the radio.
Still no alarms. Now get on the ship.
Damn! It's the alarm. Well, this just got more straightforward. Forget keycards. We're blowing our way through. Light a flare and drop it. Bile will drop you some C4.
The C4 is for blowing the gate. Get it placed.
Get the power back on.
Gang, I can't stress how important electricity is to computers!
Just a few... More... Seconds.
That manifest you picked up will point us to the right containers.
Your escape driver's parked up. Get back there - now!
Chopper's waiting for you. Hurry!
Guys! The chopper!
The boat won't escape the cops' attention forever. Get there, now!
Great! Extra loot... Love it!

The Moretta is sitting in a sealed dock, awaiting customs clearance. This is where you come in. Once you're in the dockyard, you're going to get it moved to a berth from where you can get aboard. From 2B to 3B. Open the dock gates, and let the Captain know he can move. Once the Moretta is berthed in 3B, you can get aboard and boost the explosives. Simple?$NL;$NL;Well, maybe not so simple. Security's too tight for a ship loaded with Balkan farm produce. Starting to guess a lot of shady stuff comes through that route. So be careful.
Pick up that thermite, trust me, you're going to need it.
The ladder and thermite are right there. Don't forget them.
You're gonna need the thermite to pop the wagon open. Get back and grab it.
You can only melt through that wagon with the thermite, so you better head back and fetch it.
Look around for a ladder. You need it to search the wagons. Maybe it's still attached to one of them.
The hose has come loose. Reconnect it!
Search the other wagons for C4! It should be inside one of the crates.
There's gotta be explosives in one of the wagons. Search for them!
That zip-line is your way out - get there!
Bile's on his way to you, but he can't land with those trees in the way. Find a saw, and clear a way for him, then mark it with flares.
Find that saw! It has to be around here somewhere. Try looking around timber logs.
Chopper's right on top of you. Can you see it?
Briefcase with high-temperature thermite paste will be waiting for you here.
Get the C4 in there, and get ready!
That's the pump done. Great work!.
You can try finding vault keycards, two of them, if you want to sneak this place. Maybe in the trunks. Or go loud - it's your choice.
You got one of the keycards, now find the other one.
Alright, thats both keycards. Let's open that vault up.
Beautiful stacks of unmarked Benjamins. Just reward for an honest heister.
Don't make plans for that cash just yet. Remember we need to get it to the blackmailing asshole first. Don't worry, we'll find him.
A great haul, gang. Another top job.
Just hold them off a little longer, gang. I'm finding you a way out.
Keep the people down. Keep them quiet.
Protect the cage. These cops have no respect for your honest work and can take the bags.
Ah! The cage was empty. Did you let the cops snag it back? Nevermind. You guys are just gonna have to mule it out the old-fashioned way.
Grab those bags, guys.
You got one minute til that Captain raises the alarm.
The vault is protected by a laser gate, but no matter. You know what to do. Watch its sequence and time your run through.
We will make actioning that our top priority. Thank you.
Roberts Bank.
Now let it do it's thing, and remember to keep the cops off it.
OK, we're in. Get in that vault, start moving the loot out!
Getting the money is fine, but your priority has to be assembling the skyhook. Look for the pieces of the cage and get it built.
Remember, if you dont get that cage assembled we can't move the cash. Get it done!
The roof is the target for the plane, so the cage needs to be built there.
Find the bags for the cage, and get them to the parking lot.
The plane will collect the cage from the parking lot, so get these bags there and get building.
OK, gang, good. Now hold on.
Dammit! The plane missed the cable. Alright. Still time for another pass. Stand by.
Bullseye! That was some flying! Now get out of there.
No worse than being locked in a van with Wolf's ass on semi-automatic. Find the exit.
That's the alarm. No more tip-toeing, gang. It's all about speed and violence now.
Well, so much for stealth. But the job's half done. Just get that money out of there.
That's the alarm, but we got enough out of there.
Plane is coming in hot. He'll collect from the roof. Make sure everything is ready.
Gang. GenSec need the time lock codes. I'll stall them as long as I can. Can you see them?
Can any of you see the time lock codes. I can't stall them for long.
Today's code is 559732. Sorry it took so long.
Almost there, gang. Any second now.
You're going to have DC's finest crawling up your ass. Cops on the scene.
Crap. That's GenSec. Get ready to deal with them.
Gang, that's a heavy SWAT van that just rocked up. Be ready.
Good job assembling the cage. Can you do as good filling it?
Don't stand around. Start working on those deposit boxes.
Watch your heads, guys. Ass bombs aren't the only thing dropping into here.
It's about to get hot down there, gang. They're dropping grenades.
That red ladder will let you get onto the roof.
An access ladder, with the hatch unlocked. These sloppy assholes deserve to be robbed.
Eight bags. Out-fucking-standing.
Let's strike a counter or two. Bag up a bank.
Crap hit the fan - well, crap hit everything, judging by the stink off you. I'll call in a cleaner crew for the evidence left behind.
The drill is down - cops all over it.
Get the people on the floor. Keep 'em down.
Remember, stay low, stay dark. And stay quiet. Here we go.
Walls and router boxes. They go together like trouble and badges.
There's a router box right near you.
Great, now you just need to find the second one.
That's one box down, one to go.
I'll have the system down in a bit.
Shouldn't be too much longer.
Bag those stones and get them to the garden. Get them out with ziplines.
Use ziplines to get the bags out via the garden.
Set up a zipline to speed things up.
You can do it faster if you set up a zipline.
Guys, I have to pull the chopper out until things cool down.
Ok, guys. Chopper is back so get to loading again!
Almost there!
You're all done. Get to the roof and signal the chopper if you're ready to leave!
What're you still doing there? Get on the helicopter.
OK, that computer had a piece of code to the vault on it, but to be able to use it, you need the other parts as well. They're probably around there somewhere.
Don't loose that keycard, you're gonna need it later.
Hey, Ralph is still there. Be ready to grab him.
The CFO is still there. Keep your eyes open.
Third one found.
You'll probably find a computer in Administration.
Have a look in the Admin Office, there's bound to be a PC there.
Go check the Velvet Room for a laptop. Just don't stick to the walls.
See if someone in Management forgot their computer.
Sales-people always have laptops.
If you get the code order wrong, all hell will break loose.
The vault isn't going anywhere. It's waiting for tha keycard and code.
How far along are you on the vault? Use the card first, then enter the code.
Get to the platorm with the bags!
That's probably worth a small fortune.
