An inside contact has rigged up spy cameras and surveillance drones. You can access them from the gadget on the roof.
An FBI connection of mine has rigged the place with spy cameras and has set up surveillance drones outside. You can control them from the gadget on the roof.
Damn! The timelock has jammed. Your ECM jammers must be interfering with it! Wait for it to resume.
What?!! You let the FBI boss slip away? He's left the scene! Well, he's not coming back. Gotta switch to plan B.
Damn! The Alarm timer ran out. It's not rocket science, people!
The alarm has been activated and it's ticking down. Take care of it before it reaches 0!

OK. If we're going to do this quietly, we need to disable some of these alarm systems. Look around. Search the museum. Find the circuit boxes that power security. If we can hack them, we can shut the place down without setting off the alarms.

Next step... Two time locks. You need keycards to get past each. Guards won't have 'em - but the civvie researchers probably will. Find and, y'know, persuade them. They'll give up their keycards soon enough.
Damn! The time locks are locked down. Keycard's aren't worth crap now. Time to brute force the security panels!
Ah crap! There's the time lock. Forget the keycards. Force through those panels.
Rat! Time locks have kicked in. Alright. Forget keycards. We're going to force this.
Damn! Cops are sending everyone they got. Time to make this a blood diamond. Find security!
Hey, where's the Diamond? They've lowered it into the floor! Wasn't expecting that. Calls for brutal method - break through with a drill!
Keep the cops off the circuit box. Don't let them shut it down.
Protect that circuit box. The cops'll try to shut it down. Don't let 'em!
That's gas! Get out of there!
The gas will clear away. Give it a moment.
OK, the gas is gone. Get back in there!
Surveillance is blind. Cameras are out of action. Should make things easier.
Get a keycard and swipe it through the time locks. Check civvies for cards.
Always thought being a night-guard at a museum would be a great job. But, you know, the whole stealing thing...
The Mongol's were great warriors. Would love to see them in action.
Supposedly, it was Genghis that found the Diamond. He did pretty well out of it.
This place gives me the heebie-jeebies.
Some nice loot in these displays. But some cheap counterfeit crap too. Look for alarms. That'll mark the good stuff.
Looks like every cop is headed your way! You're not driving out. Light a flare, and we'll get you an air extraction.
That was the wrong tile!
Keep it quiet, gang.
They don't suspect a thing. This is great.
Look up - police chopper in the sky!
Police are flying in - heads up!
Heads up our chopper is incoming!
We got a chopper landing on the roof.
Chopper is bound for the roof.
Damn, what is this place?
Let's find a way into the prison.
I think we need to get into the prison.
I don't think we have a choice. We have to spin that wheel!
I don't like the look of the prizes on that wheel, but I think we have to spin it anyway.
It landed on sniper again. Get ready guys.
The wheel has decided, looks like we have some more snipers incoming.
Ok the wheel landed on flames again, watch out!
Smoke incoming guys!
Drills? Not sure what that is...
The wheel stopped on drills. Do you guys know what that means?
Watch out! It stopped on drills again!
The timer is standing still. Get it going again!
Now let's enter the prison. Use the keycard to open the door.
Time to see what the prison has in store for us.
There should be another wheel around here somewhere.
Let's see... Place the keycard in the panel and activate that switch. Hope we're not in for a big suprise...
Place that keycard.
If you wanna leave, there's an escape panel on the top floor. Check it out if you wanna call it quits.
Same procedure as last time - grab the loot or leave this prison on the top floor.
See that timer over there? Hurry up if you wanna secure the loot!
There's no turning back - get out of this goddamn place!
We're taking the train - grab the zipline up to the bridge!
What's that, extra loot? You sure you wanna do that?
Busting up this motel is our first step to getting Hoxton free. Head in there.
Boom! That's the first.
The Commissars' guys've got some hot wheels. How about we make them a little hotter? Look around the gas station, there's gotta be something to burn.
A meth factory! Burn that place up. Or, if you can find a formula, get cooking. Can always move a little extra product.
Keep going, keep trashing!
Like a bull in a china shop!
Shame to see such fine wheels go up in smoke. But if it gets the Commissar's attention...
Get in there, and just mess the place up. Trash the rooms, light up the cars - whatever you can do. Go crazy. The Commissar is bound to give us a call.
And... Got it! Well, looks like our Russian friend is somewhere in, hold on...
Got him! Foggy Bottom!
Look for something connected to that place.
That's a second hatch, guys. The Commissar must have something sweet.
Hey, maybe that hatch hides something that can help us locate the Commissar. I got an idea how we can crack it. Bile is bringing you something.
That's the hatch! I've got an idea for it. Bile is going to be Santa, and since you're such good boys and girls...
Is it working? Nice. But damn, that hatch is strong.
Only one minute to go!
Make sure the cops don't do that again. Keep it running!
Good job, clowns. Keep the wheels burning.
We know he is in West End somewhere. Look around for anything related to it. Files, maps. Remember: West End.
The trace indicates West End. So look for a clue for that - West End.
We know the call originated in West End. Look for something to give us a precise address. West End.
The Commissar is bunkered down somewhere around Foggy Bottom. Find a clue for that place.
Our Russian friend is somewhere in Shaw, so find a clue for that. Remember, he's in Shaw.
No no no, that can't be correct. Get another barcode.
What's that? Russian loot? Get it to the DeLorean. Hurry!
Russians got a bit of loot stashed around the place. Not going to make us rich, but every little helps.
Think the drill is finished, guys. Time to get into that basement.
Now get the cable on both the pick-up and the hatch.
Chopper on the scene, but it ain't the feds!
Chopper's back on the scene! Watch out.
Is this D.C. or Grozny?
Get to cover!
It's firing! Get outta the way... Now!
Remember - track down the mobsters. Track them down, and put them down.
Another mobster taken care of. Keep at it.
What the hell was that? Did they just blow up another entrance?
Guys, I think the cops just shape charged another entrance!
Remember: you're looking for a clue about Downtown Washington. A file, hint - anything. See where he is at.
Now just connect it to the hatch.
Think the Commissar got this thing from Vlad. Slow Russian junk...
Alright, we got the address for where the Commissar's at. It's an old apartment complex. Place is a run-down dump. Hard to say what security you can expect. Suit up, and let's finish this.
The Commissar is dug in tight as a tick. This is one of his operations. Wreak havoc. If you can smash this dump up enough, he should give us a call. Then I can trace him.
We need to put the Commissar in a wooden box. Not stay in one ourselves. Move!
This is the penthouse level. Commissar has to be here.
That crafty bastard! He's using his vault as a panic room. Let me drop you a thermal drill.
A vault! The Commissar is pulling every string to keep his ass alive. I'm sending over a thermal drill.
Your drill is there. Get it started on that vault.
Commissar has called in the big guns. The very big guns. Stay away from that chopper!
Fires are out. Nicely handled.
That's it. The Commissar is dead. We're one step closer to getting Hoxton back. I'm sending in a helicopter, so stay put. Good work up there.
He's dead. Good riddance. Chopper's on the way, guys. Dentist sent a few bottles of champagne with it. Sure Hoxton will be grateful too. Good work.

The good news: Commissar has a HUGE stash of coke up in his penthouse. The bad news: he's flushing it as fast as he can. That's a lot of money swirling down the crapper - the faster you get there, the bigger the bonus!
I can't believe that Russian asshole is destroying that product. Get at it before it's all gone!
They're flushing that coke away. Gang, get up there before it's all gone!
They're wasting cocaine like Hollywood producers with fresh checks in there! Step on it!
Powder's flying like it's a goddamn bakery in there - if you want in, you'd better book it!
Keep pushing forward! This is a time limited offer if there ever was one!
Throw in another gear, will ya? That pile of coke is getting smaller at an alarming pace!
If you get up there fast enough, we'll make a fortune. Come on! Make an effort!
Don't get caught up, get to the coke! They're not fooling around! Oh, my poor heart...
That's another bag of coke. And another one... And... Should I keep going? It's heartbreaking.
Will you hurry up! All this coke going to waste, it's breaking my heart!
Alright, anyway... Let's find the Commissar in his penthouse and kill him. That bastard's gonna pay.
Hm... That's sad, but we have not time to lose! Focus on the Commissar now - track him and whack him!
Uh... Not exactly Wonderland, is it.
Looks like they haven't had time to get the wiring behind the wall. Find the switch.
Staircase's blocked. Gotta be another way up.
Not going up this way. Look around. Has to be another path.
Clock's ticking, people!
I've got a line on a jewelry store that's just begging to be hit. Call me back.
Nice job snatching all those gems guys. I'll called ahead to my diplomatic contacts - they are hungry for this. Let's feed 'em.
DC now has a jewelry shortage - this is where we come in. Well done team!
Hey guys, remember to find the crates Locke has left. They got a strobe on.
Locke sounds a bit...mad. We'd better do what he says.
Locke wants us to sabotage the radars. Better get to it.
Nicely done, guys. Locke transferred our cut. I don't know about this guy, yet, but let's see how things pan out with him.
Hurry, guys! Into the hold!
Light that flare for Locke, crew.
Hope you're okay up there, crew. Here's Locke.
All right, guys. Here's Locke... Be careful up there.
We want at least two bags of jewels from this store. Understand?
Greed is your guide. If you want it, go get it.
Get those bags to the car.
That's enough for Vlad, but get more if you feel brave.
Plenty for Vlad - is it enough for us? Your call.
Amp it up guys - more!
That's 30 seconds till the van leaves.
It has to be there, the tiara is there somewhere.
OK, that's it. Get it to the escape van... Vlad will be pleased.
The getaway just left without you.
Guys we're looking for a tiara, might be in a safe, gotta be inside though.
Guys remember why you're there, we're looking for a tiara.
Guess the vault is gonna be in a Murky shipping container. Get opening them.
The vault will be packed for transport, so check those Murky shipping containers.
Remember, check the Murkywater shipping containers for the vault.
Guys, the vault - find it! Check the Murkywater containers.
Patching in Vlad...
These vaults have one weakness. A failsafe will open the door if the temperature inside gets too high. Look around for crowbars in the warehouse, and jam them into the rear fans.
Remember: you need to find crowbars and jam them into the vault's fans. They are most likely inside the warehouse.
Look around for crowbars in the warehouse. Stick them into the vault's fans, and wait for thermodynamics to do the rest.
Last fan disabled. Temperature is off the hook. The contents must be scorching!
Vlad, are you crazy! Nukes!?
We're done. Now bail! Leave Vlad with his nukes.
Feels like old times, huh?
Keep an eye out for anything you can hustle out of there. The Murkywater containers are your best bet - get them open.
You're in the lair of the beast now, gang. Better loot, but bigger risk.
A nice stash of used dinars. Good find.
Damn, this gold was likely boosted from Saddam's palace!
That was last seen in the Iraqi National Gallery. These guys are shameless.
Who knows what's on that server. Blueprints, records - maybe the password for Area 51.
People will pay fortunes for this ancient Babylonian shit.
Saddam had his enemies heads served on that platter.
Alright, that'll keep Gage sweet. You guys can cash this out now, or stay for more.
That'll do for Gage, but you can stay for more.
The main gate. Direct route, but might be watched. Maybe there're other ways in.
The van will leave in one minute. Make sure you're in it.
You're nearly done. Only one bag to go.
Gage has arranged for one of the dumpsters to be used to stash some loot.
Gage's guy is in a nearby parking lot. Throw the loot over the wall to him.
Hustle! The murkies will notice that open vault!
Almost there, gang. Get those clown masks on.
It's quiet out there tonight. Keep it that way.
If you find a laptop at the computer station, I could use it to help you.
Damn, they interrupted the hacking. Get it started again!
I bet you there are some explosives laying around here. See if you can find any.
Place the C4.
Take cover!
Perfect! They won't be able to use that anymore.
Damn, the EMP crashed right through the roof of the lumber mill.
God dammit, Bile... The EMP fell through the roof and is now inside the lumber mill instead of outside.
Nice drop, Bile! Gang, the EMP is in the yard outside the lumber mill.
The mercenaries interrupted the EMP charge! Every time that happens, the EMP is slowly discharged!
Shit, the mercenaries stopped the EMP charge! It's beginning to discharge!
The EMP is almost done, so listen up! This baby is powerful so don't be surprised if it breaks our communication among other things.
The EMP took care of the magnetic lock, so you have free passage to the laboratory. Let's go!
Man, the EMP took out the whole factory it seems... Use your flashlights and find the X-ray device.
We're going to need an X-ray device to get the data the Elephant needs.
Good job, guys. That should get rid of the gas in the scanning room.
Gang, you need to find the lead scientist.
The lead scientist is dead? Shit. Without him we aren't getting past security... Well, I guess technically we don't need HIM, but rather HIS hand...
Yes, it worked. It doesn't seem to matter that the scientist was dead. Technology is cruel. Well, get started with the scanner.
Alright, gang. You need to look for the test-subjects and get them to the scanner. They are supposed to look pretty much the same.
Okay, scanning is under way. Now make sure it gets to finish without getting interrupted.
Protect the X-ray device! Don't let the mercenaries get to it!
Okay, the data is being transferred to the server in the other room. You can either go and get it or stay and scan more bodies. I'm sure Jimmy can find use for it and that means more cash for us.
That's right! I almost forgot: there is a briefcase in the laboratory. I'm gonna need you to get it, guys. It's important.
Haha, you read my mind, guys. I do want that briefcase.
Great, the server has been secured. Now Jimmy can shut up about it. We did our part.
Guys, search the spot where you landed. Bile has dropped some explosives for you.
Excellent, you got the explosives. Now, plant them on the radar.
We need to take that radar out of action. The missiles from the anti-air gun should do the work. See if you can use it.
Bring those missiles over to the radar!
Hell yeah. Those missiles are perfect. Take them to the radar.
Excellent, gang. With the anti-air defenses gone, Bile can now drop the EMP close to the lumber mill.
We can not leave without that briefcase!
How convenient, he won't run away now. Cut off his hand and bring it to the scanner.
Yep. You heard him right. Vlad is serious. We go into the mall, we destroy as much as we can.
Mall destruction: check. Pissed off police: check. Let's go get paid from old Vlad.
OK we beat on this sorry mall enough for one day. Well done. Vlad has proven his point and I think we need to lay low for a bit after this.
OK, that's around 5000 dollars.
Two-Five-Zero-Zero-Zero, half way! Keep going!
35 thousand dollars.
That's 40 thousand, only ten more to go!
45 thousand.
Almost there guys, forty-five thousand.
50 grand, woah, is there anything left?
You can stay and trash if you want, but the escape's coming soon!
He'll be there soon!
The limo has arrived. Taxman is here.
There he is; the one in the white shirt is the Taxman.
Attention gang, the corporation representative is close.
The customer is getting close, standby.
I'll eavesdrop and tell you what's being said.
I count four guys.
I see four guys.
Okay, Taxman goes for the server - I think...
That is the server, gang! 25 million dollars can be ours! Now we need to act.
Perfect, I knew you could be trusted, Alex.
Excellent, Alex, knew you were the right man for the job.
Guys! That's too early, what if the server isn't there?
Put him down in the chair and get the codes out of him.
They're climbing up on the balcony straight from the front.
Check the vents, guys!
Watch it guys, it's crumbling!
Careful! The roof is about to collapse!
Damn, it's stuck. Try shooting at the wires.
No time to waste, shoot the wires and let it drop.
Guys it fell short. It's on the balcony. Let's go!
The limo is on fire! Get him out!
You could argue we are the good guys in this scenario, right?
Ok last step, let's open her up.
We need a crowbar, look around.
Great it's open! Get Taxman outta there.
We need the server, don't forget it!
The server's not on him.
Hit him!
Okay, take it back a little, we don't want to kill him.
Watch the neck!
You knocked him out? Really?
Is he dead... guys?
That won't do, everything is encrypted. We need more codes!
Nope, that's not enough. Get him talking again!
That's the password, Starbreezer
Get to the circuit breaker and get the power back on.
OK, start up the computer again and let's pick up where we got interrupted.
Nice job, contact resumed.
Great! We got contact again.
Alright, we're past the ASIM. They won't know what hit em.
OK guys, the authentication is almost complete. Keep an eye on that timer.
Guys, I got a callback from the accounting name, When that timer hits zero - we are clear for the transaction.
Done! We're through with loading up. Gimme, gimme, gimme, gimme...
That's it! Time to cash in, baby!
Fantastic! I confirmed the transaction of 25 million.
We're done, let's move and get out!
Keep going guys!
Let's go, let's go!
Chop, chop, people!
All those pretty automobiles...
That's them! They were here just like Wick said. Tie them up and leave them by the van. Wick will take care of the scum when we get back.
No! Dammit, gang... Wick wanted to take care of them himself. He really had it in for these bastards. I guess he will have to be content with the idea of them dead.

Dammit! Why did you do that? You were supposed to bring them to Wick, not kill them yourselves... I'm not sure how he'll react to this. This is the only thing he's been talking about since he saw that disgusting video...
Good. Let the bastards squirm in fear while we take care of the bank.
They're getting away from the van. Wick will be pissed if you don't bring them back to the safe house!
Give Santa a good thrashing! Wake him up!
Get that box!
Get the Jewelry box!
You have to steal Tin Boy!
Search in the piles and find Tin Boy!
Get that shoe box people!
Check the computer. Got to find the shoes!
Check the shoe store's stock in the computer.
Come on, we have to get the shoes with the cocaine!
Look in the boxes, gang!
He hid the coke with a VR headset. Find it, it should be in the electronics store.
Open the door to the back office!
Get that back office door open!
Make sure you find the right wine!
Find the right wine now!
Helicopter will be here in one minute.
To get that tree out, you need to blow the glass roof off the mall. Just light a flare and then wait for Bile, he'll be bringing in some C4.
Vlad wants the Christmas tree. Bile is on his way now!
Plant the C4 and blow the roof off.
Attach the frame to the tree!
You need to get Santa up the tree so he can fly out with it!
Ok, it's time to go!
Time to escape!
Cook meth. Same as always.
Momma always said it was a big world out there, but this...
Okay, I have ingredients on their way. Stand by.
Stand by, crew. I got a batch of ingredients on their way.
Okay. That's good. Now get more in there.
Good spot. Now we wait.
That's it. Now wait for the pilot to signal in.
Bubble, bubble, toil and trouble. Mostly toil and trouble. Especially trouble.
Not a single bag?! This is a nightmare!
You didn't get anything out?
The job wasn't a total bust. Still, fewer stuffed bags than under Leatherface's stairs!
It's a bare bones haul, but it'll do. Better luck next year, crew.
Hot damn! You guys did great! Enjoy your payday - you deserve it.
We came, we saw, we kicked their ass!
I want to hear a cry of fear from those cops!
It's cooking. What music it makes!
Halloween treat, guys. Headed back to the cabin in the woods.
Here to cook a little meth. Just like we did last summer.
Vlad says the club profits are all in a safe somewhere in the office.
Look for the office, guys - it's on the second floor.
Escape is here in a minute!
The ammo bag can be found in the storage room.
OK, we're going to pay a visit to the Tasteful club and uh, liberate their cash reserve. Nothing special. Find the manager's office, contain the crowd, make sure we leave in one piece.
Cops bloodied our nose on that one - somehow I think Vlad was holding back information... As usual. But you did well... Let's see what old Vlad tells us.
Not a cop in the world saw this one coming. Russians will be furious and Vlad will OD on vodka. Let's get paid.
I don't want you hanging around that club for too long. I don't trust this to be as easy as Vlad says. Hit the manager's safe and get the hell out. If you get any phone numbers, I don't want to know.
Vlad is probably right about the police being quick on the draw here. Get in and get out fast after you empty that manager's safe. And Wolf, stay off the dance floor.
You'll have about seven seconds to take out the cameras before the alarm goes off.
You're looking for three cameras.
I count twelve cameras to deal with.
Bring the cooler!
Get out of that burning steel coffin, gang!
Sorry guys, Bile had to leave you for dead...
Wow. That was a helluva thing. You all right? No missing limbs?
Two.
Ok, that takes care of the cameras.
Now you just gotta make sure no one gets away and alerts the guards in the ICU.
Don't let any hostage run off and trigger the alarm!
There goes the alarm. Guess we gotta do this the hard way.
Don't kill any hostages! We want to do this low-key.
No killing hostages, guys! You'll attract too much attention.
Don't let it keep ringing, someone's gonna get suspicious!
Uhm... didn't we solve this already?
There's a repair man coming to check the cameras.
You gotta find the patient file, guys.
Keep searching.
It might've been misplaced- check everywhere!
You're taking forever guys...
You need to look faster gang. Time is running out.
I know you don't like it guys, but it's a huge payday, and that extra bonus item I need to get my hands on. It's worth not asking too many questions.
OK, gotta find a way to make sure none of the hostages does anything stupid. Set up the fake sentry guns.
There's a locker room by the reception. Get there and get into some scrubs.
Come on gang, scrub up!
Don't forget- stay in character.
Stop screwing around, guys! Now you gotta grind through metal doors for ages.
Do them one by one, and keep the cops away.
OK, it's done. Go have a look at the patient.
Get to a centrifuge and test that sample.
Still not enough, you need to take another sample.
You need two samples. Go get 'em.
You afraid of needles or something? Stick him!
Hit the elevator button.
Maybe... two minutes. IF I don't get interrupted.
Guys, I'm getting a bad feeling here. Military-industrial com channels are going like crazy. Looks like we caught some nasty attention.
They cut the power, get it back up! Fast! The elevator won't move otherwise.
Crap, they're fast. Get the power back on!
Bastards cut the power. You gotta get it back.
Elevator aint' going nowhere until you get the power back on.
Power is back, great. Now don't stop.
Put two vials in the cooler so you can leave.
We can leave one you've got two samples in the cooler.
Hop in the elevator guys, then get your asses to the roof!
That's strange... merc units are pulling out.
What the hell... you're not gonna ... other air units in the area.
Guys!... Guys! You still there?! Get... -out!
We're here for the plates. They've been printing fortunes over the last months, spending wildly. Blood's in the water and we're the sharks!
Keep things cool. Don't give the nosey neighbours something to talk about.
The cops have sent an patrol to investigate. They'll be here soon.
Alright, there's the door and there's the first lock. Get the codebreakers working.
OK, no time to lose. Start the codebreaker!
Dammit, the cops disabled the hacking device! You need to reboot it!
Don't let the cops reach the hacking device! Now you're gonna have to reboot it.
Keep going guys - no one's seen you yet.
Pick up the phone or they'll know something is off.
They have called in another car. Take care of it.
All right, the cops are inside. Quiet takedowns!
Who fired? You guys are made now. Go to plan B!
That noise... Ahh some suspicious neighbours called the cops!
I can see one of the civilians making a run for it!
One of the civilians is making a run for it!
Damn! That's it for stealth - time for action. Get ready for company!
Wow, the police are calling for heavy reinforcement. They'll be here any moment!
Get into the shelter!
Into the shelter! Move it!
Gang, get to the shelter - hustle!
Ok guys, get the gates open. Find a crowbar or something.
Through this door we should get to the money plates.
Man, these boys got themselves a Franz-Jaeger safe. Wasn't expecting that! Okay....well, with what we got there's only one way we're cracking that - water!
So, here's the plan. Get a hose down the hole from up top, and blow a pack of C4 inside the water filled safe. After that, grab the loot and get out of there.
Alright, here's what you do. Get a drill onto the safe. Make a hole in it. Then, we need to fill it with water. Drag the garden hose down.
Get a drill onto the safe, gang.
Ok the drill is up and running!
Fill her up good, guys!
Get the water hose and connect it to the safe!
Time to put the water hose to use, turn it on!
Now let the water flow!
Now turn on the water!
Get the valve open again, crew!
Turn the water back on!
Police will burst into the house.
These Florida cops don't mess around. They smashed right through Wilson's wall!
SWATs are coming in from the north, on Keel Street.
SWATs coming in from the east!
The place is booby trapped!
It's a trap! Either you defuse these C4s or you get the hell outta there!
Quick! Grab the loot.
Oh, my god!
That was not a bomb shelter either, just concrete and plaster walls, C4 I must say was a bit.. overkill.
Check out those money stacks, must be a good print. Worth a fortune on the streets.
At least we got the cash before it blew!
Ha! At least you grabbed the money before the bang!
Our money's still burning. That's sad sad sad...
Can't let them all away...
We blew the money.
Yes! Great work. Now stick the C4 into the hole in the safe
Now that's hydropool euphoria. Get the loot!
All that printing press needs is paper and ink. Cha-ching! Instant cash!
Dammit, the ink seems to have run out! Replace it!
Turn on the power again!
Get the power back on!
Grab the counterfeit and do another load or take what we have and scram.
That's a sweet pile of counterfeit cash. Beautiful. Grab it. And if you fancy a little more...
Glad you asked how we get the counterfeit money out of there. I'm dispatching our pilot.
Through the tunnels and get to the beach, gentlemen!
We're not going to be stopped by a gate now. Get it open!
Crash a pool party. Get paid. Not bad at all.
Fuck yeah.
20 until police arrive.
20 and counting - cops imminent.
Police are closing in. They are here in 30 seconds.
30 seconds until the police arrive.
Police arriving at your location in 40 seconds.
T minus 40 seconds. Cops soon to be there!
About 60 seconds until police arrives. They are scrambling!
Community radio says cops in 60 seconds. Bless them for the heads up!
Police are incoming - keep your guns up.
Police en route - coming in fast!
Front entrance. Consider it a way in only.
Access to the roof is here. Emergency ladder.
Manager office can be accessed via roof. Good place for keycards. Computer could be important.
This is where the zip-line to access the crane will be.

Time's up, I'm leaving!
I'm getting the hell outta dodge!
They're on me! I'm naked as a jaybird!
... get 'em off of me!
Careful! Careful!
Guys, I'm on my way back in!
Okay, here's it, clowns. Get that money over here.
Not exactly incon-fucking-spicuous over here. Hurry!
Nice. Come on, keep throwing it in.
Crap, heavy reinforcements moving in. You guys better jump in with the loot if you wanna get out of here.
Oh man. Oh man! I see cops to the horizon. Forget fighting your way out. Jump into the container - we fly out!
Authorities are trying to boost my bird. But injured civs don't pay so well. I'll be with you in 2.
Dust is thick. Hard to see shit. I'm one minute out.
All right, there's the flare. Beginning descent.
Gentlemen, I see an opening for me to come in a short period of time. If you have any loot to secure, now is the time. I'll be at the back of the train.
I'm here. Bring me the loot pronto, because I can't stay too long.
All right cowboys, I'm dropping you off here, and I'll circle around until you call me back to pick up the goods.
This feels like something out from a cowboy movie and Bile likes it, gentlemen! Anyhow, here's where I drop you off. I'll be on standby until you give me the signal to come back and pick up the loot.
All right, I'm close now, but there's snipers spread around the drop zone. I'll need you to take care of those before I can drop the C4.
Hey! I'm getting peppered over here! As long as the snipers are breathing, I can't get close enough to make the drop!
I apologize, gentlemen. I accidently dropped the C4 on the balcony... Sorry.
Okay, I'm back, but I can't do shit with that many cops everywhere. You'll need to clear the roof.
I'm here, guys, but I can't come closer as long as the roof is filled with cops.
The winch is where it needs to be, but I need your help attaching the magnet.
Going in.
This place is getting too hot. I'll come back when the coast is clear!
I dropped some C4 in a rush, look around for them.
I see that you have disabled the guns! Hold on, I'm coming with the EMP.
Huh, well it's on the outside. Should work anyway right?
Shit! These bastards have anti-air defenses set up! I will turn the plane around! Comrads, use the parachutes and get out! We'll figure something out!
Guys, break the windows so I can send down the ladder, over.
About 60 seconds. AKA a minute.
All right, I see you. Dropping the cage by the silo.
Got a nice clear run at the bridge. That's where the cage'll be.
Okay, lining up on the road. Gonna drop the cage there.
The skyhook cage is on the ground!
Copy that, In holding pattern til you give clearance.
And....got it. I got it! I can't believe I got it.
Okay. Here we go again. This is for the money, baby!
Copy that. Returning for another drop. I need half a minute!
Going to leave this one at the silo!
I'm going to drop it on the road. Stand by.
Cage delivered!
Okay, got eyes on the cage. Here I come!
Fuck, to much damage, I have to leave, coming back!
Ok guys... the buildings here make it hard to get close. You need to move to a higher position so I can pick you up.
Can you move up to a higher point? It's hard to get in close where you are now.
It's very hairy here. I'll move to a safer spot, guys. Follow me.
I'll try another spot where it's less hot. Follow me.
Ok, I'm here and ready to get the hell out.
Alright, get on board so we can get the hell out of here.
I can't pick you up with all these cops around here. You need to clear the area.
You need to clear the pickup zone guys! Or I won't be able to get you out.
Clear skies. I'm coming in.
I'll deploy over here where it's less hairy.
Get him into the chopper. I can't hang around here forever.
Hang tight boys.
Alright, I'm ready, get everyone in the chopper!
Let's get the fuck out of here.
We're leaving.
I don't want to die.
Stay still and put your hands in the air.
Stop and give up, your escape is blocked.
Mr Sturr. Comply or we will be forced to take you down.
An agent will now detain you.
Mr Sturr. Don't give them anything.
Mr Sturr, we will get you outta' there.
Mr Sturr we will get you out.
Up top, move people, let's secure alpha one!
You ready for it? I'm dropping the hose.
That's all I got. I'm outta here!
Can't do it, Broadsword. Got a lot of wind shear on that vector. Over.
Almost there. Target in sight. Over.
Broadsword, the package is safe. Repeat: package is safe. Over and out.
I don't even wanna know what you guys are up to this time. Just give me the coordinates.
Be there in a few minutes. Stand by.
Ok guys, I'm here. So we need to wreck these cars, right? Let's drop this sucker in the water. Attach the magnet!
Ok guys. Busting cars I hear. Attach the magnet - this one's going for a swim!
And... off we go!
Got it! I always liked to play with cars as a kid...
There she blows!
Hey guys - did you see the splash it made?
Ok guys, attach the next one.
Here we go, this should do it.
Roof. Got it, Sensei. Five by five.
Understood, Sensei. I can do this. I can do this!
On my way. Four minutes, tops.
I got it! Ya hear me, I scooped up ya package!
Help... help me!
They've got guns!
This is the last show of the greatest tour on Earth. Don't screw the pooch now.
I heard you guys up in the booth were good. Don't let me down, y'hear?
Hey! Asswipe! Stop scratching ya crack and get on the Intercom!
Answer the Intercom. Don't make me come over there, son.
Don't make me whip you like a government mule. Get on the Intercom.
All right, booth team. When I give you the nod, you hit it - you got that?
Listen up, we're gonna put these folks into goddamn ecstacy. When I say, you hit the button. All right!
Yeah! Yeah! Awwwww fuck yeah! Crowd's fuckin' losing it!
Hey, can I get a hell yeah for the booth team.
Man, that was beautiful. Just beautiful. Like my dear old momma. (sniffs)
Hit it!
Hit it!
Do it!
You fucked it, son.
You're makin' a disaster here! Straighten your shit, motherfuckers!
(drolly) Good job, fuckface. Great fucking job.
Out-goddamn-standing! You guys are world class (sniffling) World class, ya hear!
Welcome to the greatest night of my fucking life. Great job everyone!
Best goddamn crew in the history of music! Can I get a hell yeah.
Woah, we just lost of whole bucket of lights. Fix the hardware up there.
Fire warning just lit up. Sheeeeeeeeeit. Get it out, now!
I can see the fire and smoke from here. Grab an extinguisher and get it out!
Keep the pyro for the show, guys. Get the fire dealt with, lickety-spit!
Hey hey hey, shithead! Answer the fucking Intercom!
Answer the Intercom, son!
Any idea why this Esteban chop has it out for you?
Locke, you're payin' the fuckin' laundry bill this month.
Whoever gets to Kento first, pays for the drinks.
Whose idea was it to go in from here?
Keep an eye out for things that glow green.

Henry's Rock. Every crackball conspiracy theory you've ever heard about classified scientific experiments and corporate occult rascality, gathered in one facility. Locke says that Murkywater's top men are up to some rather nefarious skullduggery there. Security footage we hacked shows they have two more gilded cases like the one Commissioner Garrett had in FBI lockup. One of them may even be the very same piece we recovered for the Dentist in Vegas. It isn't clear yet how they connect to Bain's search, but they're obviously important enough to the Murkies that we should probably take them off their hands, and maybe serve them a little comeuppance while we're at it.
More like we're heisting an HP Lovecraft novel...
Oh, look. I did it. Do I get a treat now?
Jesus, Bain. Like I would have forgotten how to get past a fucking fence? Anyhow, I'm through now.
I see a guard up ahead. He's not moving, so I don't think I can sneak by him.
I bagged the body, now I just need a place where I can hide it.
Man, aren't we feisty today?
Jeez, don't lose your head, Bain.
Well excuse me for not noticing it while I took down the guard.
Ah shit!
Jesus Christ... that was a little too close...
Okay, I got it. Are we done with this shit?
Okay, Bain. Let's get this shit over with.
Let's finish this, Bain.
Ok, I can see the door but I also see a camera.
That's the door, but it's guarded by a camera.
Well, this was harder than I remembered it to be.
Suck it!
Heavy motherfucker.
Damn, he's heavy...
I'm outside the security room but I need a keycard.
Okay, I got the keycard.
I got the keycard.
I found the keycard.
Okay... more guards in the lobby.
Hey! I think I see it. Yeah, that should be the computer we're after. And I think it's close by.
Well, hello there gorgeous... Bain, I found the laptop. It should be close by.
There's another guard here.
I see the computer, and no guards. Lucky day.
Okay. I'm outside. We're good to go, right?
All right, I made it outside in one piece.
Bain, I'm outside now.
Rock and roll, baby.
Fuck yeah. This is mine.
Fuck me, Bain. We still usin' these shitty ass-drills that keep jamming?
It's all part of the job, isn't it?
Okay, let's do this then!
Come on, you really thought I couldn't get this shit done?
You better make it happen, Bain. I'm not losing one of my guys over this rookie-ass mission.
You better make the deal go through, Bain. I'll not fucking lose one of my friends over this little test of yours.
How's it going? I swear to God, Bain, you better make a deal happen. I'll not see one of my friends behind bars because you wanted to see if I still got what it takes.
Of course I still got it. You better give us something with a bigger payday next time.
Right, wankers. We do this one for the boss.
I hope that piece-of-shit traitor Kento is up there. I really do.
All of this has happened before. Fuck me.
Fucking hell. Me ears are bolloxed. Was that C4 or a demolition charge?
Fuck me, talk about making an entrance.
Yes! Yes! Now it's time to see helmets flying!
Dunno what Bain was thinking, but we're making a detour. Got something in mind.
I know I was betrayed. I'll find who fuckin' did it.
I'll miss the slags I left behind. Mickey the Squib. Dirty Alan. Fish Fingers. Good lads.
Feels good to be outside. The fresh air, the birds... The bullets, and explosions, and all that shit.
At least in the nick I didn't have Bain yapping in my ear, like a little needy dog. Get the drill, my arse.
Dallas, I thought we were pals. Does a pal leave his BFF in jail? Wanker.
Wolf, you've been barking up the wrong tree for years! And now you find me!
Wolf, what you did with that Bulldozer back there was a bit... I think you need help, mate.
Well fuck me sideways, if it isn't John Wick. I thought you got out? How's the family? What, did I say something bad?
I said it's fucking payday motherfuckers!
Move! Last one in's a nonce!
Operations is our first stop. From there, we should be able to find what we need.
Here! I'm getting to that server. Kill every last fucker ya see!
Shite! Small problem - server's heavily encrypted. The encryption keys are kept in the Security Office. You need to grab them and bring them back here!
You're in. Ha! His password was: iheartrainbows44. The requests are on the way. Approve them!
Keep yer knickers on, lads. Need to find all the files for ya to sign off.
Hold on, fellas. Just finding the files for ya.
Alright, just approve that request. Fuck me, he's got an easy job.
Another request for you to sign off on.
Ah, come on! We're missing a server. According to the log, it was taken to IT. Get over there, and grab it.
OK, I've copied all the information I found to this server. Grab the server and let's get out of here.
That's as much as we can do here. I saved all the intel on this server. Grab it and let's get out and see if we can make sense of this.
Got power again, fellas. Need a sec to reboot this.
Got my file. Let's see what they have on me.
This isn't an average case. Lots of information restricted. I'm not this important, am I?
This case is special. Why am I special? Who's leaking this stuff?
Man, this case goes a lot further than just me. There's references to all you guys in here. No names though. Guess our rat is sitting on those.
Alright, I'm wrapping up in here, almost done. There'll be lots of info to sort through. But we're going to find that arsehole. Silence him before he squeals.
I'll keep schtum in here til you're back.
Back to work, keep me covered.
I'll get to work. Cover me!

Well, lads, thanks for breakin' me out. But I shouldn't have been there to begin with. Someone set me up. I'm sure of it. The Feds had too much on me. Way more than those mingebag wankers could dig up. Someone ratted. Someone fucked me. And I'm gonna find out who.$NL;$NL;Now, it ain't gonna be easy. No fannying about around the edges, right? No shadowy deals or contacts, or that bollocks. We're going to the source. The biggest FBI nest. Gonna find out who screwed me.

Thanks guys, I'm glad to be back. We've got a shitload of intel that I need to go through. Hopefully it's enough so we can find whoever ratted me out, that backstabbing cunt.$NL;$NL;Isn't there something like a thieves code or some bollocks? I'll tell you guys as soon as I find anything worth sharing. We'll find this wanker, and when we do, he'll be sorry he fucked with the Payday Gang.
Fuckin' nice one.
No, I'm too rich to die!
You want the card? Just take it!
The card? Take it! I don't give a fuck about the damn thing!
Don't hurt me It's my birthday.
Are they cops? Are they fucking cops!?
Who is this? Who the fuck are you!?
Oh, shit!
Fuck ME!
The fuck do you think you're doing!?
Son of a BITCH!
I'm gonna fuck you up!
Kill all those pieces of shit!
Prepare to get fucked up!
Come on! Fuck 'em up!
I'm gonna kill you!
You're fucking DEAD!
You must have shit for brains, comin' here!
Gonna send you to the lake!
Game is on, motherfuckers!
You come here to disrespect us?
Ha! You better enjoy your life while you got any left!
Going to spill your blood everywhere!
We'll make you pay for this!
Forget him. We should unpack the crates.
Hey, you see the state of the guys from the motel?
Doesn't matter who they are. Boss is paying big for their heads. I plan to collect.
Boris, you're asshole.
I heard he's working for the clowns.
The clowns have him on their payroll.
We're leaving!
Thanks and good bye, my friends!
What the fuck!? Police!
You trying to pull a fast one on us, huh?
Hell no, don't try no games, sucker!
Over there!
I see one of 'em!
There's one!
I'll tell you what. We were never gonna deal with you guys! We'll take it all!
Shoot these fools! Do it now!
I've had it with these guys!
Fuck these guys!
It's fine, we'll settle for this.
Bring the shit!
You don't think our time's important!?
What are you waiting for?
Hey, we don't have all day!
... put the delivery in the car!
... put all the wares in the car!
... then you get what you came here for.
... then, we'll trade.
Thank you.
These assholes need to die!
I'm gonna kill you!
Prepare to get fucked up!
You just headbutted the motherfucking hornets' nest!
You made a bad mistake!
This won't end well for you, suckers!
Gonna feed you to the pigs!
Gonna send you to the lake!
Put holes in 'em!
Gonna spill your blood everywhere!
Gonna punch your ticket for ya!
You're getting whacked!
I promise you will pay for this!
It's the clowns! It's the fucking clowns from the news!
Yeah. Something about a hit on the motel. Hope Yuri survived.
Ah. Leave them for now. I am drowning my sorrows. Yuri.
They were in bad shape. Who has firepower like that?
Careful what you wish for, my friend. Mother told me so.
She's tipping fast?
She is shipping a pass? What does that mean?
Did you say she is tripping gnats?
We're leaving.
Thanks and good bye, my friends.
We need more.
You have no more? This is not enough.
More bags gentlemen.
It's a goddamn police ambush!
What's... Hey! Don't fuck with me!
Over here!
There's one of 'em!
There's one of 'em!
Here!
Hey, over here!
Kill these guys and bury 'em!
Put these suckers in the ground!
Shoot these fools! Do it now!
Put the idiots out of their misery!
These guys are fucking jokes.
The deal's off!
No deal, assholes!
Deal's off! So FUCK off!
You guys are lucky, I'm feeling generous.
I'm like goddamn Santa Claus here.
We'll take what you have.
This is fine, we'll take it.
It's fine, we'll settle for this.
Where's the stuff, man!
Where is it!
Don't mess around...
What are you waiting for?
Hey, what's the holdup?
... put the delivery in the car!
... put all the wares in the car!
... are you having second thoughts or what?
Here's what I want you to do:
Put the product in the car...
Put the wares in the car...
... when it's done, we'll give you what you want.
... and then we'll give you what you're after.
Yes? No man, nothing going on here. It's dead.
Hey Pablo! Yeah this is Jos. Listen, keep both eyes open, ok? I have a bad feeling tonight.
Yeah, baby. No, I'm working. I'll see you tomorrow, ok?
Hey listen, remember you get the merchandise in early, or the boss won't be happy.
No no, it ain't like that. Yeah, he's downtown. Ok, make sure he gets it.
Yeah boss, all is quiet down here.
Do you have any idea what time it is, Fallere?
I know, I'm sorry. I wouldn't have bothered you if it wasn't...Um...But how are you? How's the bank?
How's the bank?" Jesus
column3: is this you trying to do small talk?"

String: I was just, you know, we haven't talked in awhile. Just catching up.
Most of our clients are terminating their contracts. Even Metro PD's pulling out. We've lost our foothold.
But that doesn't make sense! A crime wave should increase the demand for security!
Bullshit! GenSec is top of the line!
Those stats are fucked, and they know it! This isn't some ambiguous crime wave. This is the fault of one group! One! That fucking Payday Gang!
We've been fighting a PR nightmare ever since they hit GenSec Arena.
That DJ tweeted some nasty memes about our vault...
There've been a million one-in-a-millions. The damage is done. D.C. is dropping us, and the GenSec stocks are going to take a hit. A very, very big hit.
Ms. Sharke? Are you still there?
...Someone's going to fucking pay for this.
Fuck! Jeeze, man! Didn't see you up there.
None of your business.
Who you roll with?
Overkill MC.
Oh yeah, I heard of them. Biker gang, right?
Yup.
Wait...If you're in here, you got picked up in D.C.
Wasn't just any bike
They didn't mop shit! They got the jump on us. We'd have crushed them in a fair fight.
Fuck the train! Those clowns are bush league! And I'll tell you what: their time's running out.
Nah, man.
How come?
Hay intrusos en el edificio!
Llamando a todas las unidades! Estamos bajo ataque!
Atencin todos! Nos estn atacando!
Atencin! Delincuentes armados dentro!
Fuego en la segunda planta!
Todos a la segunda planta!
Estn atacando la armera!
Todas las unidades a las celdas!
Apliquen mxima fuerza!
OK, the airport is just down the hill. Cut through the fence and find the hangar where the truck holding the cases is. The FBI is of course, on scene. Get Vlad's guns and bring em here.
Go in through the fence, find the guns and bring them back here. Prepare to fight and fight hard. Let's do this.
The FBI is holding the trucks and the guns. Find the warehouse they keep the truck in. Hit the FBI hard and make it back here with the guns. Best of luck, sorry about the mess.
OK we're good to go. I'll get you guys clear to the safe house. We have the guns to keep Vlad happy. And I'm sure it'll go over great with him. The FBI... Are another matter.
Well executed. Guns secured and Vlad is preparing the money for us. Let's cash in.
You guys never disappoint. Full house gentlemen. Vlad will be proud of this work. We are in business for real.
More guns, more money. Great work. Vlad will be dancing like a Russian bear, or something.
This is still DC though, not Baltimore... So expect that you're going to get heat if you go guns blazing.
Let's do this.
I don't what kind of loot we're talking about so be ready for anything. Use the van to make your escape.
Turns out the bank manager here should have kept his mouth shut - one of our guys overheard him bragging about how great the security is there, unblemished record, blah blah blah.
Let's go in there and take all the little square packages we can find. It will be a lot of money I'm sure.
Robbery time. Keep the civilians in check, don't let 'em use phones, watch for cameras. See you at the van.
OK crew, that's the target. Get those people on the floor, hit those cameras, get your drill going. See you at the spot.
Roll in there like the tide, they won't know what hit 'em. Get that drill up fast, they'll start calling you an EVIL team...
Now this is no First World bank, small and compact, you should be able to do this thing in ten minutes. Just keep cool and we all win.
We've done this before. Go in there, get that vault lanced and bring home the loot.
Payday is upon us soon. Masks on, guns up - and follow the plan. Hit it!
...Damn it to hell they're onto us, they're onto us! You gotta escape with the loot!
...They tailed us from the scene, switch car failed, everyone batten down the hatches!
...Lose 'em... Lose 'em... Dammit... Dammit! You gotta stand and fight!
No-no-no-no-no! Ambush coming! Hang onto your loot people!
Oh... Dammit to hell. We're busted. We're busted! Fighting time!
Your wheelman didn't lose the tail! Goddammit!
...We got a tail! Can't shake 'em! Take it to the streets!
We picked up a tail... Shaking him's no good... You know what comes next... Good luck!
I'm about a minute out.
I'm about thirty seconds out, keep cool.
This is Hawkeye, OK I can see you, what a fuckin' mess, here I come.
Four bags - Hector's happy now, everything else is gravy.
Seven.
Eight.
That's all of 'em, you guys are hardcore.
Find a way into the warehouse, we need to signal the loot boat from there with the dock floodlights.
Guys we need to get into the warehouse and use the floodlights to signal the loot boat.
You guys aren't exactly subtle. I'm comin'!
OK find a way to get into that building, stay low.
Your call.
There's one there.
See if there's anything there that looks like it might work.
If it's not cutting it probably needs a new blade, there have to be some more nearby, it's a goddamn warehouse.
Gonna get a little difficult from here.
Thats one, seven left.
That's 2.
That's 4, half way there.
That's all of them, let's get out of here.
There should be more weapon caches somewhere, see if you can find them.
Don't lose sight of the plan... Those caches still need to get destroyed!
Don't forget about the caches!
You can use the higher-ups" keycard to open up the doors."
We're good, escape's clear!
Whoa... Wait, that fence is electrified.
Find the weapons and destroy them. Easy.
Great, law enforcement - probably tailing the gangsters. Better and better.
Great, SWAT - following the gangsters probably!
You found a stash! Bag it up and destroy them.
Might be a little something in the safes...
There's probably some in the safes.
The chiefs are fleeing.
Both the chiefs got away.
The office will be highly guarded, so keep your eyes open for guards and cameras.
We need to locate the position of the server room, sneak inside and disable the alarm for the door, so that we can get in unnoticed.
So what we need to do is, locate the server room, sneak in, then disable the door alarm. After that, we roll in like the tide.
Government offices... Never good.
Biting my nails up here folks, but so far so good.
OK good. Let's find that server room.
Beautiful, they're still in the dark.
Get the damn door open, no need to be careful.
I'm in... Good work. Gimme a second here.
Get that last door open then go get the server.
OK...OK... Just need to get the server out of its housing and walk it to the van.
Just get the server clear of its housing and take it to the van...
You guys are so close. Don't get sloppy now.
There goes the alarm, kick it into plan B people.
Shit! Was really hoping we wouldn't need to go to plan B here!
Watch the server room door... If someone comes near you might need to take care of them.
Bring it home fellas. So goddam close I can taste it.
This is going to be a good one.
Move that server! Move it! Come on!
Go on and find... What...
Could be the cartel...
This is not the plan...
OK listen up. You will do the cook for Hector. He will be grateful, trust me.
You need to find the materials.
Now I don't want to worry you. But if you mess up... It would be bad.
Thing is they have to be added in the right order...
OK, add muriatic acid to keep the reaction going.
Muriatic acid will be in a greenish gas can looking thing...
Search around for the caustic soda.
These idiots must have had it here somewhere.
The hydrogen chloride should be in a metal tank...
Search around for it, it has to be there...
Search around for the hydrogen chloride.
They're inside!
They're breaching the house!
Ambush! Feds are moving in for the bust!
Be on your toes.
Keep your eyes open.
Well those look like FBI heavy units. Watch yourself.
You might as well take that cash. My guess is they probably left a present.
How lucky are you feeling? There's still that money in the bus...
Yeah, I guess we got their attention, we have law enforcement on the way...
Bag it up so we can continue cooking, and get the bag to the van.
OK folks, the trucks are about to go. Find out which one has the ballot machines and get the GPS on it. Gotta be a clue around there.
Any luck? Keep your eyes open for anything, a sign... Something.
Obvious, but keep a low profile. We don't need the heat.
Lot of guards. Heads up.
OK well you still need to figure out which one it is and get that tracker on the bottom of the truck... Or get out.
OK that's it. Let's sneak out of here and see what's what.
Ah... Well that's going to get everyones attention...
Guns out on this one fellas.
Yep, this is it. Get it open.
They're still in the dark, great.
Drill or saw... Maybe you have a more exotic way to get in here I dunno.
This should look like a regular robbery... As regular as this can look. Keep them away from the hacking device.
Keep 'em away from the truck we're hacking to be safe.
OK here we go.
I wish we had some goddamn equipment that worked... Start it again.
Go get the gas can from the truck and burn the truck. Make it look like an accident or something. What a mess.
Truck's burning. If you haven't already, you can clean out the other trucks and then make your escape. Hurry it up.
OK, the truck's open, get our goods out.
Come on, get that vault open.
Open sesame. Now let's see what we have there.
That'll keep them from seeing our business. Good.
There are bandit barriers in the bank - you can close 'em from the security office. Will help keep cops out of your area of operation.
So far so good people.
I love your focus... They haven't made you yet.
They're going to be expecting us. These are not good people.
Watch yourself.
We just need to get this before they do. We don't want them burning information we can use.
Must be there somewhere...
The safe's gotta be there somewhere, these clowns aren't smart enough to put it in storage.
Have you found the safe yet? The address got to be in there.
You found it. Now get it open and get that address.
They're trying to... They just torched a piece of intel. We could have used that.
Right on time...
Was hoping we'd do this without police for once.
